SUMMARY: V1 was traveling northeast, on a median divided roadway, with two lanes in the same direction trailing a non-contact vehicle in lane one. In an attempt to pass the non-contact vehicle, V1 entered lane two and continued forward going off the edge of the roadway on the left side into a non-paved median. V1 continued forward crossing over a paved cut through in the median. V1 began to rotate in a clockwise direction and proceeded to enter into a left leading roll striking a light pole with its top plane. V1 rolled six quarter turns coming to final rest on its roof off of the roadway.

V1 was traveling west bound in lane 1 of a 2 lane, two-way, not physically divided roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right while continuing to travel forward. V1 front right wheel struck a concrete driveway culvert. V1 continued path of travel forward off the roadway across the driveway hitting another culvert before contacting the ground with the front plane. V1 continued traveling and came to final rest in the roadway.
V1 was traveling south bound behind V2 in lane 1 of a 2 lane, two-way, not physically divided roadway approaching an intersection.  V1 front plane contacted V2 rear plane.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V2 was legally parked on the right side of the same roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right and the front of V1 contacted the back of V2. V1 rolled to the left four-quarter turns, and came to final rest on the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling northbound in the first lane, exit ramp, of an eight lane positively divided roadway. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway to the left and entered the gore area, crossing thru the gore and crossing the entrance ramp on the opposite side of the gore. V1 impacted a concrete traffic barrier off of the ramp with its frontal plane. Vehicle 1 caught fire coming to rest on the paved shoulder.

V1, V2, and V3 were all traveling westbound in the same lane of a two-lane divided expressway. Lane 1 was closed due to a bike race.  V3 was the lead vehicle and stopped in lane 2. V2 was the middle vehicle and decelerating when it was struck in back end by the front of V1. Subsequently, the front of V2 struck the back V3. All three vehicles came to final rest near the point of impact.

V1 was traveling north, towards an intersection, on a not physically divided trafficway (with two-way left turn lane), and was in lane 1 (of three lanes). V2 was traveling south to west (making a right turn) through the same intersection V1 was approaching, from a not physically divided trafficway (with two-way left turn lane), and was in lane 1 (of three lanes). V3 was legally parked along the curbline, facing west on a two way, not physically divided trafficway, west of this same intersection. Prior to the intersection, V1 departed its lane and the road on the left, where its left front wheel/tire contacted a curb (Event 1). V1 continued in a northwesterly direction, and just west of the intersection, its front end contacted the left side of V2 (Event 2), and then its right side contacted the the left side of V2 (Event 3). Next, V1's front end contacted the back end of V3 (Event 4). V1's left front wheel and tire then contacted a curb (Event 5) and its front end contacted an embankment (Event 6). V2's left

V1 was traveling east in lane two of a three lane undivided one-way traffic roadway, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north in lane one of a wo lane divided (no positive barrier), approaching the same intersection. V3 was stopped at a gas station in the northeast corner of the intersection. Within the intersection, the front of V2 impacted the right side of V1. V1 rotated counter clockwise, and V2 rotated clockwise before both vehicles impacted each other in a side slap impact. V2 came to rest in the intersection, facing northeast. V1 departed the intersection to the northeast and impacted a raised curb with its right front wheel. V1 drove onto the business lot of the gas station and impacted the right side of V3 with its front. V3 rotated clockwise and impacted a gas pump. V2 came to rest on the gas station business lot, facing north. V3 came to rest at the gas pump, facing east.

V1 was traveling southbound in the second lane of a two lane, one-way divided roadway. V2 was traveling southbound, behind of V1, in the second lane of a two lane, one-way divided roadway. V1 departed the roadway on the left. The frontal plane of V1 then impacted the guardrail end. The left front tire of V1 became detached from the vehicle. V1 re-entered the second lane from the left. The detached tire of V1 impacted the left side plane of V2 twice, as V2 was continuing traveling southbound. V1 departed the roadway on the left again and impacted it's left side plane with the guardrail face. V2 came to final rest in the roadway facing south in the second lane. V1 was at final rest off the roadway, on the left, facing south.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a single lane with westbound only traffic, approaching an intersection.V2 was traveling northbound in the first lane of a two lane, two-way roadway, approaching the same intersection as V1. V1 and V2 both entered the intersection at the same time. The frontal plane of V1 impacted the left side plane of V2. V1 and V2 were at final rest in the roadway with V1 facing east and V2 facing north.

V1 was traveling north in lane 2 on a four-lane, two-way roadway approaching a four-way intersection. V2 was traveling west in lane 1 on a two-lane divided roadway approaching the same intersection. As V1 entered the intersection, its front plane contacted a pedestrian. V1 continued forward as V2 entered the intersection and the front of V1 contacted the right side of V2. V1 rotated clockwise as V2 rotated counter-clockwise and the left side of V1 contacted the right side of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in the intersection facing north.

Vehicle #1 was traveling west on a three-lane, two-way road in lane 2, approaching an intersection. Vehicle #2 was traveling east on the same road in lane 2, approaching the same intersection. V1 entered the intersection and turned left. The front plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2. Both vehicles came to rest on the road.

V1, V2, V3 and V4 were traveling east on a two lane undivided roadway in lane one.  The front of V1 contacted the rear of V2 was decelerating in road.  This pushed V2 forward.  The front of V2 contacted the rear plane of V3 that was stopped in traffic.  V3 was pushed forward into the rear of V4 that was also stopped in traffic.  V1 and V2 came to final rest in the eastbound lane facing east.  V3 and V4 pulled off the roadway to the right to final rest.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a two-lane, one-way, undivided roadway in lane No. 2 position. Vehicle 2 was traveling west on the same roadway in the lane No. 1 position. Vehicle 1 attempted to change lanes to the right. The right side of Vehicle 1 contacted the front of Vehicle 2. Vehicle 1 then rotated coming to rest facing east in the westbound lane. V2 came to rest, still facing west.

V1 was traveling north in lane 2 on a 3-lane divided roadway. V2 was traveling south in lane 1 on a 3-lane divided roadway. V1 departed its left road edge onto the dirt/grass median and the front of V1 impacted a metal utility marker. V1 continued across the median into the southbound lanes, and began to travel north in lane two of the southbound lanes. V1 then crossed over to lane one of the southbound lanes towards the paved shoulder and the front of V1 impacted the front of V2. After the impact V1 rolled left, one quarter turn and came to rest on its driver side, on the dirt shoulder facing a northwest direction. After the impact V2 continued off the roadway and the front of V2, impacted a barbed wire fence, then V2 rolled left one quarter turn, coming to rest on its driver side, in a ditch, facing a northerly direction.

Vehicle #1 was traveling north on a two-lane, two-way road. V1 departed the road to the right, and the front plane of V1 contacted a sign post, then a chain-link fence. V1 continued off-road, and the front plane of V1 contacted a wooden fence, then a utility pole. V1 rotated clockwise. The front plane of V1 contacted a utility box. V1 came to rest partially off road to the east.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a two lane, two-way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1 position approaching a 4 way intersection. V2 was traveling south on a two lane, two-way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1 position also approaching the same 4 way intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection. The front of V1 contacted the left rear side of V2. V1 came to rest in the west side of the intersection facing south west. V2 departed roadway right side at the south west corner of the intersection. V1 struck the curb with its right front wheel. V1's front then struck a residential chain link fence and traveled a couple feet through the fence before coming to rest.

V1 was passing through an intersection while traveling south on a two-lane, two-way road. V2 was passing through the same intersection while traveling west on a two-lane, two-way road. The front of V1 impacted the left side of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in the intersection.

Vehicle 1 was exiting a one way, two lane driveway southbound to turn left.  Vehicle 2 was westbound on a two way, five lane roadway.  The front plane of vehicle 2 struck the left plane of vehicle 1.  Vehicle 2 front plane struck vehicle 1's left plane a second time.  Vehicle 1 came to rest facing south in the roadway.  Vehicle 2 came to rest facing westbound in the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west in lane one of two on an unprotected roadway approaching a four-legged intersection..Vehicle 2 was traveling north in lane one of two approaching the same intersection protected by a stop sign. Both vehicles entered the intersection going straight. The front of Vehicle 1 contacted the right plane of Vehicle 2. Vehicle 1 came to final rest on the right side of the roadway. Vehicle 2 overturned and came to final rest off the right side of the roadway of the north leg of the intersection.

Vehicle #1 was traveling south in lane one of a two-lane undivided roadway, approaching a T-intersection.  V1 departed the end of the T-intersection and the front of V1 contacted a ditch (event 1).  V1 came down in the ditch and the undercarriage of V1 contacted the ditch (event 2).  V1 continued south and came to rest off the road facing south.

Vehicle #1 (V1) was traveling east in lane 2 of a two-lane, divided roadway without a positive barrier.  Vehicle #2 (V2) was traveling west in lane 2 of a two-lane, divided roadway without a positive barrier.  V2 departed the roadway to the left and began to rotate clockwise.  V2 entered V1's roadway and the front of V1 contacted the left of V2.  V2 rotated counterclockwise and the left of V1 contacted the front of V2. V2 re-entered the median and came to rest facing south.  V1 rolled over and came to rest on it's right side, partially on the roadway and partially in the median.

V1 was negotiating a left turn while traveling west on a two-lane, two-way road. V1 departed the right side of the road where it impacted several trash cans, an embankment and a mailbox with its front plane. The embankment caused V1 to become airborne. V1 continued to travel off of the right side of the road and its front plane impacted a utility pole, causing it to rotate clockwise. The front of V1 struck several more trash cans and another mailbox before reentering the road and coming to rest back in its original lane of travel.

V1 was traveling north on a two-lane, two-way road passing through an intersection. V2 was traveling east on a two-lane, two-way road passing through the same intersection. The front of V2 impacted the left side of V1. V1 came to rest in the intersection. V2 departed the left side of the road where its left wheel impacted the curb and its front plane impacted a guardrail. V2 came to rest in the west bound lane.

Vehicle 1, 2, and 3 were eastbound on a two way, two lane roadway.  Vehicle 1 front plane struck the back plane of vehicle 2.  Vehicle 2 front plane struck the back plane of vehicle 3.  Vehicle 1, 2, and 3 came to rest facing east in the roadway.
Vehicle 1 and 2 were eastbound on a two way, five lane roadway .  Vehicle 1's front plane struck vehicle 2's back plane.  Vehicle 1 and 2 came to rest facing east in the roadway.

V1 and V2 were traveling west in the #3 lane of a 3 lane divided roadway. Both vehicles were approaching an intersection. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2. V1 and V2 came to rest facing west in the #3 lane.

V1 was eastbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway approaching a four leg intersection. V2 was stopped at the same intersection facing east waiting to make a left turn. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2 causing damage. V1 came to final rest in the intersection facing east. V2 came to final rest facing east.

V1 was traveling north in lane 4 of a 7 lane,of a physically divided roadway with a left turn lane approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south in lane 1 of a 7 lane,  physically divided roadway with a left turn lane approaching the same intersection  V1 made a left turn in the intersection heading west. V2 entered the intersection at the same time as V1. V1 right plane was contacted by V2 front plane.
V1 was traveling WB in lane 1 of a 2 lane, two-way, not physically divided roadway. D1 lost control of the vehicle departing the roadway to the left striking a pole with the front plane.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a two lane, two-way undivided roadway approaching a four-legged intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling east on the same roadway, stopped at the intersection. Vehicle 3 was traveling north on a two lane, two way undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. In the intersection the left side of Vehicle 1 contacted the front of Vehicle 3. Vehicle 1 rotated counterclockwise and the back plane of Vehicle 1 contacted the front of Vehicle 2. Vehicle 1 then departed the roadway to the northwest corner of the intersection and the front of Vehicle 1 contacted a ditch. Vehicle 1 came to final rest off of the roadway. Vehicle 2 and Vehicle 3 came to final rest on the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling northwest on a five lane undivided roadway in the second travel lane entering the intersection with a three lane one way roadway. Vehicle 2 was traveling eastbound on the one way roadway in the first travel lane and entered the intersection. Vehicle 1 was contacted on the right side by vehicle 2's front. Vehicle 1 then traveled west and into the oncoming traffic lanes. The front of V1 then contacted the left side of V3. Vehicle 3 was stationary in the second southeast travel lane of the same roadway as vehicle 1. All vehicles came to rest on the roadway.

Vehicles 1, 2, and 3 were traveling in the eastbound lanes of a six lane divided roadway at the intersection with a two lane undivided roadway. Vehicle 1 was towing a trailer and occupying the first travel lane. V1 made a left turn from this travel lane in the intersection. Vehicle 3 was traveling in the third travel lane and contacted its frontal plane with the left side plane of the trailer. After contact vehicle 3 came to rest in the intersection. Vehicle 2 was in the fourth lane, a left turn travel lane, and contacted the frontal plane on the left side of vehicle 1's trailer. Both vehicles 1 and 2 came to rest within the intersection.

V1 was southbound on a 3 lane roadway, in lane 2 and approaching an intersection. V2 was westbound on a 3 lane roadway, in lane 2 and approaching the same intersection. V1 turned left at intersection. Within the intersection the right side of V1 was contacted by the front of V2. V1 came to rest partly on the south shoulder. V2 came to rest in the intersection.

V1 was traveling northbound on a five lane, two-way roadway in lane three, Attempting to make a left turn. V2 was traveling southbound on a five lane, two-way roadway in lane one approaching a four-way intersection. V3 was traveling eastbound, on a two-lane, two-way roadway stopped waiting for the traffic light. V1's front plane contacted V2's front plane, after initial impact with V2, V1 continued west. V1's front plane contacted V3's front plane. V1 came to final rest facing westbound. V2 came to final rest at point of impact at intersection.  V3 came to final rest at point of impact.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two-way roadway negotiating a left curve. V1 departed the curb edge, rotated counter-clockwise the tripped and rolled 3-quarter turns coming to rest on its left side in the intersecting roadway facing west. During the rollover sequence, the right side of V1 contacted a low brick wall.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a two lane undivided two way roadway in lane one approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling southbound on a 3 lane undivided roadway two way traffic with a two way turn lane in lane one approaching the same intersection. At the intersection V1 attempted to turn left at the intersection and the left side of V1 was impacted by the front of V2. V1 rotated counter clockwise and departed the roadway to the left and impacted a light pole with it's right side. V2 also contacted a guy wire with it's left side mirror and came to rest between the pole and guy wire facing northwest. V2 came to rest in lane one facing south.

V1 was traveling southbound on a two lane positively divided highway in lane two. V1 hydroplaned and lost control then departed the roadway to the left. The front of V1 then impacted a cable barrier and came to rest in the grassy median facing south.

V1 was traveling north east on a three lane two way positively divided roadway, and merging. V2 was traveling north east on the same roadway. V1 departed their initial lane of travel to the left, and the left side of V1 contacted the right side of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling north on a two-lane rural roadway negotiating a curve. An unidentified vehicle was traveling in the opposite direction on the same road. The unidentified vehicle entered the northbound lane. In doing so, V1 departed the roadway to the right side (east) of the road and its front plane contacted a directional sign. V1 came to final rest on the grass roadside facing north.

V1 was traveling south in lane one on a two lane, two way, non divided roadway negotiating a left curve. V1 departed the roadway on the right, traveled down a grass embankment and across a stone culvert wall, contacting it with its undercarriage. After contacting the wall, V1 continued forward and contacted a ditch embankment with its right side where it tripped and rolled right 2-quarter turns and came to rest in a private driveway on its top facing southeast.

V1 was traveling northbound on a two way, two lane undivided roadway, approaching an intersection with a stop sign. V2 was traveling eastbound, on a two way, two lane undivided roadway, negotiating a slight left hand curve and approaching the same intersection as V1. Both vehicles entered the intersection proceeding straight. The front of V1 contacted the right side of V2. V2 continued forward and north and departed the north road edge where the front of V2 contacted a curb. V2 came to rest facing northeast off the north road edge in a private yard.  V1 came to a final rest on the roadway facing northeast near the point of impact.

V1 was traveling south in lane 1, on a median divided roadway, with three lanes in the same direction, approaching a traffic signal controlled intersection. V2 was traveling west on a two-way, two lane undivided roadway, approaching the same intersection as V1. Both vehicles entered the intersection. The frontal plane of V1 contacted the right side plane of V2. V2 continued forward and the right side plane made contact a second time with the front plane of V1. Both vehicles came to a final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling north in lane 3 on a 4-lane, two-way, divided  roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling west in lane 2 on a 3-lane, one-way roadway with both a left and right turn lane approaching the same intersection. Both V1 and V2 entered the intersection simultaneously and the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in the intersection.

V1 was traveling NB on lane 2 of a 4 lane, two-way, divided without positive barrier roadway with a left turn lane approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling WB in lane 1 of a 3 lane, one-way roadway approaching the same intersection. V1 and V2 enter the intersection simultaneously. V1’s front plane contacted V2’s left plane. V2 rotated clockwise contacting a curb with both its right side rims. V2 then contacted a sign with the right plane before coming to final rest.

V1 was traveling EB in lane 1 of a 4 lane, two-way, not physically divided roadway with a left turn lane approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling SB in lane 1 of a 3 lane, two-way, not physically divided roadway with a left turn lane approaching the same intersection. V1 and V2 enter the intersection simultaneously. V1 front plane contacted V2 right plane. V2 rotated clockwise and tripped over 2 quarter turns contacting the ground with the left plane and coming to final rest on the roof.

V1 was traveling WB in lane 3 of a 5 lane, two-way, not physically divided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling EB in lane 1 of a 4 lane, two-way, not physically divided roadway approaching the same intersection. V1 attempting to make a left turn in the intersection. V1 right plane contacted V2 front plane.
V1 was traveling south on a two lane two way grass median divided roadway. The front of V1 contacted a Deer in the roadway. V1 came to final rest on the roadway.
V1 and V2 were traveling west on a five lane two way undivided roadway in lane one. The front of V1 contacted the back of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 and V2 were both traveling southbound on a 2 lane undivided two way road in lane 1. V2 was traveling ahead of V1. V2 slowed down to turn into a private drive, the front of V1 impacted the back of V2. V1 came to rest partially in lane 2 and the east shoulder of the road facing south. V2 departed the road the west and came to rest in a grassy area north of the private drive facing south.

V1 was traveling south in lane one of a two lane undivided (two-way traffic) roadway. V1 departed the road to the right. The front of V1 impacted a wooden utility pole. V1 came to rest at the pole, facing southwest.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane, two way street. V2 was parked on the side of the southbound lane headed south. The frontal plane of V1 struck the rear plane of V2. Both vehicles came to rest headed south near the point of impact.

V1 was traveling southwest on a three lane, two way, roadway with a center turn lane, passing through a four leg intersection. V2 was traveling east on a two lane, two way roadway, making a left turn at the same four leg intersection. The right plane of V1 struck the frontal plane of V2. V1 came to rest heading south, just south of the intersection. V2 came to rest near the point of impact.

V1 was traveling south bound on a two lane, non divided,bidirectional roadway. V2 was traveling north bound on the same roadway. A deer entered the roadway causing V1 to depart its lane to the left, where its frontal plane impacted the left plane of V2. V1 came to final rest on the when west side of the roadway. V2 came to final rest on the east side of the roadway.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane, non divided roadway that curved to the left. V1 departed the roadway to the right, where V1 impacted a utility pole with its frontal plane. V1 rotated clockwise, and came to final rest partially off the roadway.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane, two-way roadway approaching an intersection.  V2 was traveling south on a two lane, two-way roadway approaching the same intersection as v1.  Upon entering the intersection, the front plane of V2 made contact with the right plane of V1.   V2 continued moving forward and the right plane of V1 made contact with the right plane of V2    V2 came to final rest on the roadway facing south west, while V1 came to final rest off the roadway, facing south.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane two way undivided roadway approaching a three way intersection. On the north side of the intersection, V1 departed the roadway to the left side. V1 rolled to the left six quarter turns and came to final rest off the roadway.

V1 was northbound on two lane, two way, undivided roadway negotiating a right hand curve. V1 departed its initial travel lane to the left then departed the left side of the roadway in a clockwise yaw. V1 impacted a mailbox with the left plane causing damage. V1 then rolled left side leading eight quarter turns coming to final rest on its wheels facing south.  V1 contacted a utility box with an unknown plane during the rollover.

V1 was backing up to leave a parked position. V2 was parked behind V1. The back of V1 connected with the front of V2 (event 1). V1 then pulled forward to head west. V3 was heading east on the left side. The front of V1 connected with the front of V3 (event 2). All three vehicles came to rest at point of impact.

Vehicle #1 was traveling south, negotiating a right curve, in lane one of a two-lane undivided roadway.  Vehicle #2 was traveling north, negotiating a left curve, in lane one of the same roadway.  V2 departed the road to the right, re-entered and departed its lane to the left.  The left of V1 contacted the front of V2.    V1 began to rotate counterclockwise and departed the road to the right.  The right of V1 impacted two small trees and a ditch before coming to rest off the road to the right, facing southeast.  After the initial impact, V2 began to rotate counter-clockwise as well.  V2 came to rest still on the roadway, near impact, facing south.

V1 was traveling south on a four lane non-physically divided roadway in lane two. V2 was traveling north on a five lane non-physically divided roadway in lane two. V3 was parked along the southbound curb. V1 crossed over into the northbound lanes and the front left of V1 impacted the front left of V2. V1 continued back over the southbound lanes and the front of V1 impacted the rear of V3. V1 came to rest facing in lane one of the southbound lanes facing north west. V2 came to rest in between lanes one and two in the northbound lanes facing east. V3 came to rest along the southbound curb facing southwest.

V1 was traveling westbound in the number 1 lane of a 5 lane divided roadway. V2, V3, and V4 were traveling westbound in the number 2 lane of a 5 lane divided roadway. V3 and V4 were at a stop. V1 departed the lane to the left where the front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. Both vehicles stayed engaged and started to move northerly. V1 disengaged from V2 and the left side of V1 impacted the right side of V2. Both vehicles disengaged and the left side of V2 impacted the right of V4. V2 came to rest facing westerly in the number 2 lane. V4 came to rest facing northerly in the number 2 lane. V1, after disengaging from V2, traveled off the edge of the road on the right where the front of V1 impacted a temporary concrete barrier. V1 entered the roadway where the front of V1 impacted the rear of V3. V3 came to rest facing westerly in the number 2 lane. V1 came to rest facing westerly behind V3.

V1 and V2 were traveling westbound, on a 2 lane roadway. V1 was traveling behind V2. V1 crossed the lane line to the left and the right side of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V1 then began to yaw and driver re entered the original lane of travel, this time in front of V2. V1 left the roadway to the right and then front of V1 contacted a tree. V1 continued forward and the front of V1 then contacted an embankment. V1 rolled backwards too a final rest, still off of the roadway, where it caught fire. V2 came to rest on the shoulder just past V1's final rest.

Vehicles #1 and #2 were traveling east in lane one of a two-lane, undivided roadway. V2 began to turn left at an intersection. At the same time, V1 began to pass V2 on the left. The front plane of V1 contacted the left plane of V2. V1 departed the road to the left and came to rest off road, facing northeast. V2 came to rest near impact, facing east.

V1 was traveling in a northwesterly direction, through the right hand curve of the roadway, on a designated north/south, two-way, not physically divided trafficway, and was in lane 1 (of two lanes). V1 departed its lane on the left, and was then steered sharply to the right. Control over V1 was lost. V1 skidded laterally in a clockwise rotation and departed the road on the left, where it then overturned (5 quarter turns, leading left). V1 came to rest on its left side, facing a northeasterly direction on the roadside.

V1 was traveling southeast in lane one on a two lane, non-divided, two way, roadway and was turning left at an intersection onto another two lane roadway. V2 was traveling northeast in lane 1 on a two lane, non-divided, two way, roadway and was passing through an intersection. At the intersection, V1's front plane contacted V2's left side plane. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway, in the intersection.

V1 was traveling north east on a two lane, non divided, bidirectional roadway. A deer entered the roadway from the left, where V1's frontal plane impacted the animal. V1 came to final rest on the right side of the roadway.

V1, V2, and V3 were all westbound in the same lane, on the same roadway approaching a three-leg intersection. V2 and V3 were stopped ahead at the intersection. The frontal plane of V1 struck the rear plane of V2. Subsequently, V2’s front end struck the back of V3. V1, V2, and V3 came to final rest in the westbound lane facing west.

V1 was eastbound on a three lane, two way, undivided roadway with a left turn lane. V2 was westbound on the same roadway. V1 attempted to turn left from the center turn lane. The front of V2 struck the front of V1 causing damage. V2 came to final rest near the point of impact facing west. Upon impact V1 rotated counter clockwise traveling southwest into another intersection coming to final rest facing south.

Vehicle 1,2,3,4 and were all traveling north on a 4 lane physically divided roadway in lane number 1. Vehicle 1's front end made contact with vehicle 2's rear end. After contact, vehicle 2's front end was pushed into vehicle 3's rear end. Vehicle 3's front end was pushed into vehicle 4's rear end. All vehicle's came to rest forward of impact still facing north.

V1 was traveling southbound in the second lane of a two lane, one-way positive divided roadway. A deer entered the roadway from the right into V1's lane of travel. The front of V1 impacted the deer. The right plane of V1 then impacted the deer for a second time. V1 departed right from the second lane into the first lane and then departed the roadway on the right. V1 was at final rest off of the roadway facing south.

V1 and V2 were traveling north in lane two of a four lane divided roadway with V2 ahead of V1. V2 was stopped in the roadway. V1's front plane contacted the rear plane of V2. V1 came to rest near impact and V2 came to rest a short distance forward of impact.

V1 was traveling south in lane two of a four-lane divided roadway, negotiating a right curve. V2 was traveling northeast in lane two of the same four-lane divided roadway, negotiating a left curve. V1 departed the roadway to a concrete median, where it's left front wheel contacted a curb. V1 then entered opposing lanes of traffic while beginning to rotate clockwise. The front plane of V1 then contacted the front plane of V2. V1 continued to rotate clockwise and came to final rest in the roadway facing northwest. V2 was pushed backwards by the impact and came to final rest facing northeast in lane one of the roadway.

V1 was traveling east in lane one of a two lane roadway approaching a sign controlled intersection attempting a left turn. V2 was traveling south in lane one of a five lane roadway approaching the same intersection. In the intersection V1's left plane contacted V2's front plane. Both vehicles came to rest near impact.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a two lane two-way roadway approaching a four leg intersection controlled by a stop sign. Vehicle 2 was traveling south on a two lane two-way roadway approaching the same intersection with no traffic controls. Within the intersection the front plane of vehicle 2 contacted the right plane of vehicle 1. Upon impact vehicle 1 rotated counterclockwise departed the roadway to the southwest and the front plane of vehicle 1 contacted a utility marker before coming to final rest off the roadway facing southwest. Vehicle 1 then rotated slightly clockwise coming to final rest at impact with a barbed wire fence.  The light pole was sheared off and fell on the roof of Vehicle 1.  Vehicle 1 came to final rest at the south exit of the round-a-bout.

V1 was traveling northwest on a two lane, two way, rural roadway. V2 was traveling southwest on the same roadway. The left side plane of V1 struck the frontal plane of V2. V1 came to rest heading northwest in its original travel lane. V2 came to rest heading southwest in its original travel lane.

V2 was leading V1 on a two-lane, two-way road with a negative grade while approaching a T-intersection. V2 stopped at the intersection and the front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. Both vehicles came to rest at the point of impact.

V2 slid north on the median while on its left side and rotated clockwise. The rear of V2 impacted a light pole located on the median. V2 came to rest on the median. lying on its left side, facing south.

V1 was traveling west in lane one of a three lane divided (with positive barrier) straight roadway. V2 and V3 were traveling in the same lane ahead of V1. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. After the impact with V3, V2 rotated counter clockwise, crossed all lanes and departed the roadway to the south. The front of V2 impacted a concrete traffic barrier. V2 bounced off the barrier, kept rotating counter clockwise and impacted the barrier with its right side. V2 came to rest on the shoulder, facing east. V1 and V2 were both northbound in lane one of a two-lane divided highway. V1 was ahead of V2 when the frontal plane of V2 impacted the rear plane of V1. Both V1 and V2 came to final rest in the first lane of the roadway facing north.

V1 was traveling westbound in the second lane of a two lane, one-way, positive divided roadway.V2 was traveling ahead of V1, in the same second lane of the two lane, one-way, positive divided roadway. V2 braked and stopped in the roadway. The frontal plane of V1 impacted the rear plane of V2. Both V1 and V2 came to final rest in the roadway facing west.

V1 was traveling east in lane 1 on a 3-lane divided roadway. V1 crossed all lanes to the left then departed the left road edge into the dirt median where it began to rotate counter-clockwise. V1 crossed the westbound lanes of the trafficway as it rotated counter-clockwise then departed the left road edge where its right plane contacted an embankment. V1 then flipped onto its back top then back onto its wheels and came to rest on the roadside facing south.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west negotiating a curve on a two lane undivided roadway in lane one. Vehicle 1 drove off the left side of the roadway and the front of Vehicle 1 contacted a tree. Vehicle 1 came to final rest off the roadway, facing northwest.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north in lane one of a two-way, undivided roadway. Vehicle 2 was traveling in front of Vehicle1 on the same roadway going the same direction. The front of Vehicle 1 contacted the back of Vehicle 2. Vehicle 2 continued forward and departed the roadway on the right side before coming to final rest on a private drive facing northeast. Vehicle 1 came to final rest on the roadway facing north.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north on a two lane two way roadway. The front plane contacted a deer crossing the road from the left side. Vehicle 1 continued forward and came to final rest on the roadway facing north.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south in lane two of a two lane divided highway approaching a four leg intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling east on a two lane road approaching the same intersection. Vehicle 3 was traveling west on a two lane road approaching the same intersection. The intersection was controlled by traffic signals. All three vehicles entered the intersection and the front of V3 struck the left of V1 (event 1). V1 departed the road and came to final rest in the grass median south of the intersection. V2 came to final rest in the southeast quadrant of the intersection. V3 came to final rest in the southwest quadrant of the intersection.

V1 was traveling southwest on a median divided roadway, with three lanes in the same direction. V1 attempting to avoid a NCV that entered V1’s travel lane, steered left and departed the left hand side of the roadway. V1 continued forward crossing through the median and entered the northbound side of the roadway. Crossing both lanes of the roadway V1 departed the left (east) side of the roadway contacting a utility pole with its frontal plane. V1 continued forward rotating in a clockwise direction making contact with the utility pole’s guy-wire with its frontal plane. As V1 continued forward in a clockwise direction its right rear undercarriage made contact with the steep embankment of the roadway. V1 continued forward coming to final rest off of the roadway.

V1 and V2 were both traveling east, in lane two, on a two lane, non-positively divided roadway. V1's front plane contacted V2's rear plane. As a result of the contact, V1 crossed over lane one and departed the roadway to the right, contacting an embankment with its front plane. V1 then rotated clockwise and the rear of V1 contacted the embankment. V1 came to final rest facing east along the south shoulder. V2 departed the roadway to the left coming to final rest facing east behind a guardrail.

V1 was traveling east in lane four on a five lane, non positively divided, roadway. V1 was turning left at an intersection to travel north onto another roadway. V1 was traveling eastbound on a two lane, undivided roadway two way traffic in lane one approaching an intersection. V1 rotated counter clockwise and departed the roadway north of the intersection to the right. The front of V1 then impacted a tree, V1 rotated counter clockwise and came to rest against the tree facing northwest. V2 rotated clockwise and came to rest in the intersection facing northeast.

V1 was traveling westbound on a two lane undivided two way traffic roadway in lane one approaching a small bridge. V1 departed the roadway to the right and impacted a raised concrete bridge barrier with it's right rear tire. V1 then rotated clockwise and departed the roadway to the right and came to rest north of the roadway facing east.

Vehicle 1 was traveling southeast on a two lane undivided roadway. Vehicle 1 swerved right to avoid an animal in the roadway and the frontal plane contacted the back of vehicle 2, which was legally parked against the right side curb facing southeast on the same roadway. Vehicle 2, post impact, came to rest off the roadway to the right, and vehicle 1 came to rest on the roadway facing southeast.

V1 was traveling southeast on a 4 lane undivided roadway in lane two. V2 was travel southeast on the same roadway adjacent to V1 in lane one. The right plane of V1 contacted the left plane of V2. Both vehicles veered right off the road contacting the curb. V1 then struck a tree with the front plane and came to final rest facing north off the roadway. V2 struck 2 wooden sign posts and a tree. V2 came to final rest off the roadway facing northeast.

V1 was traveling westbound at a four way intersection on a four lane, two-way roadway. Attempting to make a left turn to head south. V2 was traveling eastbound approaching the above mention intersection, on a four lane, two-way intersection in lane one. The front plane of V1 contacted V2's front plane. V1 came to final rest facing south on roadway. V2's front plane struck decorative rocks with its front plane before coming to final rest off roadway.

V1, V2, V3 and V4 were traveling south in lane 2 on a left curved divided three lane roadway. The front of V1 contacted the rear plane of V2 that stopped in traffic.  V2 was pushed forward into the rear plane of V3 that was also stopped in traffic.  The front of V4 then contacted the rear plane of V1.  All vehicles remained on the roadway facing south at final rest.

Vehicle 1 was traveling in the northbound lane of a two lane undivided roadway. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway to the right contacting a curb, vehicle 1 continued traveling off the roadway contacting a fire hydrant and a tree with its frontal plane. After this contact vehicle 1 continued traveling and contacted a stairway of a residence with its frontal plane, coming to rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two-way roadway, that curves to the left.  V1 departed the roadway to the right and the front of V1 made contact with a utility pole. V1 continued traveling off road and the front of V1 made contact with decorative rocks. Next V1 made contact with a sign post.   V1 continued off road and the front of V1 struck a second pole.   V1 began to roll to the right.  V1 came to final rest off of the roadway (after having reentered and departed a different roadway) on its wheels, facing west having, completed four 1/4 turns.

V1 was traveling north in the first lane of a two lane, one way roadway (on-ramp). A deer entered the roadway from the left  into V1's lane of travel. The frontal plane of V1 impacted the deer. V1 came to final rest in the roadway facing north.

V1 was traveling southbound in the first lane of a two lane, two-way roadway. V1 departed left into the second lane and then made a left roadway departure. V1 was at final rest off of the roadway facing southeast.

V1 was traveling south west in the #1 lane of a 2 lane undivided roadway. The roadway started to curve left. V1 traveled off the road to the right. The front of V1 impacted a curb. V1 continued forward where the front of V1 impacted a tree. V1 rotated counter clockwise and came to rest facing south next to the tree.

V1 was traveling east in lane two, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north towards the same intersection in lane two, waiting to turn left. As V2 entered the intersection for a left turn, the left side of V2 was impacted by the front of V1. V1 then continued towards the center median, where the front of V1 impacted a sign. and then the wheels and undercarriage impacted the median curb. V1 came to rest partially in the intersection and on the median curb, facing a easterly direction. V2 began to spin clockwise and came to rest within the intersection facing a southerly direction.

V1 was traveling north on a non-physically divided four lane road in lane one, behind V2. As V2 decelerated and began to turn right into a driveway access, the rear of V2 was impacted by the front of V1. V2 then spun in a clock-wise motion and the left side of V2 impacted a raised curb divider island. V2 continued to yaw left side leading and the left of V2 contacted a sidewalk curb. V2 came to rest on its wheels straddling the sidewalk and mulch landscaping, facing a southerly direction. V1 continued forward and came to rest on the shoulder of the road, facing a northerly direction.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a three lane, one way roadway in the center lane.  V2 was traveling eastbound in the third lane of the same roadway adjacent to V1.  V2 struck V1 in the center lane with the right side.  V1 sustained impact damage to the left side from the impact.  V1 continued in a southeast direction exiting the roadway right and struck a fence with the front plane and came to final rest there.  V2 came to final rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a single lane, one-way roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling northbound on a two lane, two-way roadway approaching the same intersection as V1. Both vehicles entered the intersection at the same time. The right side plane of V1 was impacted by the frontal plane of V2. Both V1 and V2 both came to final rest in the roadway facing northeast.

V1 was traveling north on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway. V2 was traveling south on the same roadway as V1 negotiating a slight right hand curve in the roadway. V1 continued off the the left (west) side of the roadway where it came to final rest off of the roadway. V2 departed the right hand (west) side of the roadway where it also came to final rest off of the roadway.

V1 was traveling southeast on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a right hand curve in the roadway. A deer entered the roadway from the northern edge of the pavement, and the frontal plane of V1 contacted the deer in the roadway. V1 came to final rest on the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling eastbound on a two lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position. Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a 5 lane two-way  physically divided roadway in lane number 1. V1 and V2 were traveling southbound in the number 1 lane of a 2 lane divided roadway. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. V1 was traveling south west exiting a parking lot attempting to turn left. V2 was traveling north west in the #2 lane of a 5 lane undivided roadway. V1 was pushed north west into the two way left turn lane and came to rest facing south west. V2 traveled into the two way left turn lane and came to rest facing north west.
V1 and V2 were traveling southbound in the number 1 lane of a 2 lane divided roadway. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. Both vehicles came to rest facing south in the number 1 lane.

Vehicle 1 was traveling eastbound on a 5 lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 3 position indicating a left turn.  Vehicle 2 was traveling northbound on a 2 lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position.  After stopping at the intersection Vehicle 2 entered the intersection making a left hand turn. Vehicle 2 was pushed into a clockwise rotation with its left plane coming in contact with V1's right plane. coming to rest in the middle of the intersection facing east.  Vehicle 1 passed through the intersection coming to rest facing east.

V1 was traveling westbound on a 4 lane non divided roadway, in lane 1. V1 departed the roadway to the right. V1's front contacted a tree. V1 then struck a fence with an unknown plane before catching on fire. V1 remained off the roadway at final rest.

V1 was traveling south in lane 1 on a 4-lane divided roadway. V2 was traveling north in lane 4 on the 4-lane opposing roadway. V2 continued in a northeasterly direction until it departed the road on the left, and its front end contacted the concrete traffic barrier in the median strip, where it then came to rest, on its wheels, facing a northeasterly direction.

V1 was traveling west on an undivided, two-way roadway, in the third of five lanes approaching an intersection to make a left turn. V2 was traveling east on a two lane, two-way roadway divided by a median. V2 approached from the west passing through the intersection. As both vehicles entered the intersection, the front plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2, pushing both vehicles to the southeast corner of the intersection. V1 rotated counterclockwise departing the road striking the face of the corner guardrail with its front where it came to final rest. After the initial impact V2 rotated clockwise departing the road also impacting the guardrail with its front plane where it came to final rest.

V1 was traveling west on a four lane, two way, physically divided trafficway, taking a right exit ramp. V1 departed the left side of the exit ramp striking a reflector pole with its frontal plane (event 1). V1 continued off the left side of the road striking another reflector pole with its frontal plane (event 2). V1 then crossed over the road and traveled off the right side of the road striking a reflector pole with its left side plane (event 3). V1 then rolled four quarter turns, left side leading, crossing over a two lane, two way, undivided roadway before coming to rest on its wheels, heading east in a parking lot.

V1 was traveling north on a two way, two lane road, that is divided by a painted median, passing through a four leg intersection.
