V1 came to rest heading northeast, near the point of impact.

V1 was traveling north on a 2-lane roadway while negotiating a curve to the left. The front of V1 contacted a deer in the road. V1 then departed the right road edge where its front plane contacted a wire fence and a tree. V1 rotated clockwise and came to rest near the tree facing northeast.

V1 was traveling southeast in lane three, a two way left turn lane, of a five lane, undivided roadway. V2 was traveling northwest in lane one on the same roadway. V1 turned left to enter a parking lot when it's right side plane was contacted by V2's front plane. V1 came to final rest in lane one and V2 came to final rest in lane 2. Both were a short distance from the point of impact.

V1 was traveling northwest in lane one on a two lane, two way, gravel roadway. As V1 was negotiating a right curve in the roadway, the vehicle departed the roadway on the left side and began traveling down a steep embankment where it's front plane contacted a tree. After this contact, V1 began a left side leading rollover and rolled down the embankment. The vehicle completed four quarter turns and came to final rest over a creek, on it's wheels, next to a tree. V1's final rest position was approximately 21 meters from the point of roadway departure.

V1 was traveling south on a four lane, undivided, roadway, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north on a four lane, undivided, roadway, approaching the same intersection. In the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the front of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 and V2 were traveling southeast in lane one of a two lane roadway. V2 was ahead of V1 and stopped in the roadway and unoccupied. V1 departed its travel lane to the left attempted to pass V2 to the left and its right plane contacted the rear of V2. V1 then departed the left road edge and its front plane contacted a fence. V1 then contacted a pole with the front plane and rode up the pole and flipped and rolled right one quater turn. V1 came to rest on its right plane.

V1 was traveling southwest in lane two of a two way, four-lane, undivided roadway, attempting a left turn at an intersection. V2 was traveling northeast in lane one of a two way, two-lane, undivided roadway, passing through the same intersection. The front plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest near impact on the roadway.

V1, V2, and V3, were all traveling southeast, in lane two of a four lane divided roadway. V3, was ahead of V2, and V2 was ahead of V1. V1's front plane, contacted V2's rear plane, and V2's front plane contacted V3's rear plane. All vehicles came to rest near impact.

V1 was traveling northbound in the second lane of a three lane, two-way roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling southbound in the first lane of a three lane, two-way roadway approaching the same intersection as V1. V1 attempted to turn left at the intersection, to continue traveling westbound. The frontal plane of V1 impacted the frontal plane of V2, as they both entered the intersection at the same time. V1 rotated slightly counterclockwise from impact. Both V1 and V2 came to final rest in the roadway: V1 facing west and V2 facing south.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane divided roadway in lane two behind V2. V2 was traveling south on a two lane divided roadway in lane two and due to traffic ahead, came to a stop behind V3. V3 was traveling south on a two lane divided roadway in lane two and due to traffic ahead, came to a stop behind V4. V4 was traveling south on a two lane divided roadway in lane two and due to traffic ahead, came to a stop. V1 was unable to stop in time and the front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. The front of V2 then impacted the rear of V3 which caused the front of V3 to impact the rear of V4. All vehicles came to rest in lane two facing south.

V1 was traveling north in lane No. one (1) of a five-lane undivided roadway and was approaching a four-leg intersection.  V1 drove off of the right road edge at the northeast intersection quadrant, where the front of V1 impacted a pole (Event 1). The front left tire/wheel impacted a curb (Event 2) and another pole with its frontal plane (Event 3). V1 then began to rotate counter-clockwise where the right side of V1 impacted a building (Event 4). V1 then rebounded off of the building and initiated a clockwise rotation while at the same time rolling right one quarter turn (Event 5). V1 came to rest on the east sidewalk on its right side facing east.

V1 was traveling north on a  two way road, passing through a round about intersection. V2 was legally  parked on the same two way road, on the right shoulder facing north. V1 traveled over the lane line on the right side and the front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. V1 came to rest within lane one facing a northeast. V2 came to rest, parked on the shoulder facing a northerly direction.

V1 was traveling East on a non-physically divided six lane road in lane three approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south on a non-physically divided seven lane road in lane three, entering an intersection. As V1 entered the intersection, the left of V1 impacted the front of V2. The momentum spun V2 counter-clockwise and the right side of V2 to impact the left rear side of V1. V1 then rolled left one quarter turn, where it came to rest on it's left side, on the south side of the intersection facing a southerly direction. V2 also came to rest on the south side of the intersection facing a southerly direction.

V1 and V2 were traveling eastbound on a four-lane, two-way roadway; V1 in lane two and V2 in lane one. V3 was traveling westbound in lane one. V2 changed lanes to the left where the front plane of V1 contacted the left plane of V2. V2 continued into the westbound lanes after impact with V1, and the front plane of V2 contacted the left plane of V3.  V3 then continues westbound rotating counterclockwise. V3 departs the roadway where the right plane contacts a sign pole. V3 then overturns one quarter turn and came to final rest off the roadway facing southwest. V1 came to final rest in the roadway facing northeast, V2 came to final rest in the westbound lanes facing north.

V1 was traveling north in lane one of a four lane (one-way traffic) left curved connection ramp of an interchange area, negotiating a left curve. V2 was parked and not in transport on the right shoulder. V1 departed the roadway to the right and drove on the shoulder. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. V1 came to rest on the shoulder, facing north. V2 was pushed forward and came to rest on the shoulder, facing north.

V1 was traveling west in lane one of a three lane divided (with positive barrier) highway, approaching the merger with an entry lane to the highway. V2 was traveling on the entry ramp / lane to the highway. At the point where both lanes merge, V2 steered to the right in order to avoid a collision with V1. It is not clear if both vehicles made contact or at what plane, but V2 departed the road onto a paved shoulder. V1 did not stop and continued to drive west until it left the highway via an exit ramp. V2 re-entered the lanes of travel, crossed all westbound lanes of travel and started to rotate counter clockwise. V2 departed the road to the south. The front of V2 impacted a concrete traffic barrier. V2 bounced off the barrier and continued to rotate. The back right of V2 impacted the concrete traffic barrier. V2 came to rest at the barrier, facing east.

V1 was traveling southbound on a two-way undivided roadway approaching a four-way intersection, in lane one.  V2 was traveling eastbound on a divided two-way roadway, attempting to make a right turn at the intersection to travel south. The front of V1 contacted the rear plane of V2.  Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway facing south.
V1 was traveling east on a two-lane, two-way road that curved to the left. A deer entered the road from the south and the front of V1 impacted the deer. V1 came to rest in the east bound lane.

V1 and V2 were traveling northeast on a three-lane, two-way road with a center turn lane. V1 stopped to let another vehicle turn in front of it and the front of V2 impacted the rear of V1. Both vehicles came to rest on the roadway, at the point of impact.

V1 was traveling northbound on a two lane, undivided roadway in lane one approaching an T intersection. V1 continued northbound and departed the roadway. V1 continued north on private property and the left side of V1 impacted a utility pole. V1 continued north and the front of V1 impacted a tree. V1 rotated counter clockwise and came to rest facing west bound.

V1 was traveling northeast on a three lane undivided roadway approaching a four way intersection controlled by traffic signals. V2 was traveling southwest on a four lane roadway approaching the same intersection.  As V1 turned left at the intersection and V2 traveled straight through the intersection, the front plane of V2 contacted the right plane of V1.  V1 rotated counterclockwise to final rest in the roadway facing west. V2 rotated clockwise to final rest facing southwest.

V1 was traveling south on a four lane, undivided roadway, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north on a four lane, undivided roadway, approaching the same intersection. In the intersection, V1 made a left turn and the right side of V1 contacted the front of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling northwest in lane one of a two-lane divided highway when it departed the left side of the road and its front end struck a jersey barrier. V1 continued northbound, crossed both lanes, and departed the right side of the road. The left side of V1 struck an LED message board as it came to final rest on the east roadside.

V1 and V2 were both eastbound in the same lane of a two-lane divided roadway. V1 was stopped ahead of V2. The front of V2 struck the back of V1. Both vehicles came to final rest near the impact in the roadway.

Vehicles 1 and 2 were both traveling west on a 3 lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position. Vehicle 1 was behind V2. Vehicle 2 began to make a right hand turn. The front plane of Vehicle 1 made contact with the rear plane of Vehicle 2. Vehicle 1 came to final rest facing west in the center turn lane shortly after impact. Vehicle 2 spun clockwise coming to final rest in private drive facing northeast.

Vehicle 1 was traveling southbound on a two lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position approaching a 3 way intersection. V1 attempted to turn right but departed roadway right side traveling on the side walk. V1 then re-entered the roadway after making right turn. The right plane of V1 sideswiped the left plane of V2 which was legally parked. Vehicle 1 came to final rest shortly after impact facing west.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north on a two lane, two-way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1 position approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling west on a two lane, two way. non-physically divided roadway in lane 1 position approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection. The front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. After impact V1 departed roadway left side striking a curb with its right front wheel. V1 continued off the roadway and came to final rest on the sidewalk facing north/west. V2 after impact rotated clockwise coming to rest facing north on the north/west corner of the intersection.

V1 was traveling east on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a left hand curve in the roadway and approaching a dead end. V2 was parked off of the roadway on the far eastern end of the dead end roadway. V1 continued traveling east departing the east end of the dead end roadway before contacting a fence with its frontal plane. V1 then continued forward a short distance before contacting two trees with its right side plane. V1 then began to rotate clockwise and rolled one quarter turn with its left side leading before contacting V2 with its top plane. V1 came to final rest off of the roadway, and V2 remained parked coming to final rest off of the roadway.

V1 and V2 were traveling westbound on a five-lane, two-way roadway with a two-way left turn lane with V1 traveling behind V2. V1 was slowing and attempting a left turn in the two-way turn lane when the front plane of V1 contacted the back plane of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest further east from point of impact facing west.

V1 was traveling southbound on a two lane, two-way roadway in lane one. V2 was overturned and partially in the southbound lane due to a previous crash. V1's front plane struck V2's left plane. V2 was overturned and unoccupied at the time of the crash. V1 came to final rest on roadway after impact. V2 remained at point of impact overturned on roadway.

V1 and V2 were traveling on a four-lane, two-way roadway with a rumble strip dividing east and west bound traffic. V1 was traveling westbound in lane two and V2 traveling eastbound in lane two. V1 departed its lane on the left side where the front plane contacted the front plane of V2. After impact V1 came to final rest in the westbound planes facing north, V2 came to final rest in the westbound lanes facing south.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a three-lane, two-way roadway approaching an intersection controlled by a traffic light intending to turn left. V2 was traveling eastbound on a non-physically divided roadway with one lane traveling west. In the middle of the intersection the front plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest at point of impact facing in their initial travel directions.

V1 was traveling eastbound in the number 3 lane of a 3 lane divided roadway, negotiating a curve to the right. V1 began to fishtail and departed the roadway to the left where the front of V1 impacted a concrete barrier. V1 traveled along the wall and entered the roadway, coming to rest partially blocking the number 3 lane facing east.

Vehicles 1, 2, 3 and 4 were all traveling west on a two way, undivided roadway in lane one of a three lane road. Vehicles 2, 3, and 4 were stopped ahead of V1. The front of Vehicle 1 contacted the back of Vehicle 2. Subsequently, the front of Vehicle 2 contacted the back of Vehicle 3. Finally, the front of Vehicle 3 contacted the back of Vehicle 4. All vehicles came to final rest facing west on the roadway.

Vehicle #1 was traveling north bound in lane one of a two lane, two way roadway approaching an intersection. Vehicle #2 was traveling west bound in lane one of a two lane, two way roadway approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection and the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V1 came to rest in the roadway facing north bound. V2 came to rest in the roadway facing westbound.

V1 was traveling northbound on a 2 lane non divided roadway while negotiating a curve to the right. V2 was entering the roadway, westbound, and making  U-turn to head southbound on the same roadway. V1's front contacted the left side of V2. Both vehicles came to rest on the roadway.

V1 and V2 were traveling in the northbound proper lanes, in lane 3 of a 3 lane physically divided highway. V2 was at a stop in the roadway. V1's front contact the back of V2. Both vehicles came to rest within the roadway.

V1 was traveling southeast on a two-way, two lane road. V2 was traveling northwest on the same two-way, two lane roadway. V1 departed its original travel lane to the left. The front of V1 impacted the left side of V2. The impact caused V2 to rotate clockwise. While rotating, the left side of V1 impacted the back of V2. V2 came to final rest on an intersecting roadway, facing southwest. After impact, continuing forward, V1 departed the roadway on the left. The front of V1 impacted an unknown unfixed object before coming to final rest off of the roadway, facing southeast.

V1 was traveling south following a two way, two lane roadway with a curve to the left. As V1 was negotiating the curve, it departed the roadway to the right. The front of V1 impacted a tree and then a metal pole before coming to final rest off the roadway facing south.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two way undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was following V4 and V4 was following V3, traveling south on the same roadway approaching the same intersection. V3 made a left hand turn crossing paths with V1. The frontal plane of V1 contacted the frontal plane of V3. V3 came to final rest on the roadway. V1 continued on and the frontal plane of V1 contacted the frontal plane of V4. V4 rolled backwards and the rear plane of V4 contacted the frontal plane of V2. V1, V2, and V3 all came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling in a northwesterly direction on a designated north/south divided trafficway (median strip without positive barrier) in lane 3 (of three lanes) and was approaching V2, which was traveling in the same direction, on the same roadway, ahead in lane 3. In lane 3, the front end of V1 contacted the back end of V2. V1 then departed the road on the right, where its front end contacted a fence. V1 came to rest on its wheels, facing a northeasterly direction on the roadside. V2 came to rest on its wheels facing a northwesterly direction in lane 3.

Vehicle 1 was facing north at a 2 lane, two way, private drive roadway in lane 1 position attempting to turn in an unknown direction in the intersection. V2 was traveling east on a 3 lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1 position approaching the intersection with the private drive. Both vehicles entered the intersection at the same time. The left plane of V1 contacted the front of V2. V1 came to rest on the north part of the intersection facing north east. V2 also came to rest facing north/east in the west bound turn lane.

V1 was traveling southeast on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a slight right curve in the roadway behind V2. V2 was traveling southeast on the same roadway as V1 stopped in the road and attempting to make a left hand turn into a private driveway. The frontal plane of V1 contacted the rear plane of V2. V1 and V2 both came to final rest on the roadway.
V1 was traveling north on a two way, three lane, undivided roadway. A deer entered the roadway from the western shoulder and contacted the frontal plane of V1. V1 came to final rest on the roadway.

V2 was traveling in an eastern direction on a two lane, on divided, bidirectional roadway. V2 was approaching an intersection with a south bound road, and driveway on the north side of the intersection. V1 was pulling out of the private drive attempting to turn east bound on to the same road as V2 was traveling. V1 attempted to avoid an impact with V2 by changing direction of travel to cross the roadway. V1's right plane impacted the frontal plane of V2. V1's right plane impacted V2 a second time. Coming to final rest in the intersection. V2 continued forward, traveling off the south east side of the intersection, and impacted a traffic delineator and a cement culvert with its frontal plane before coming to final rest in the culvert.

V1 was traveling in a south western direction on a two lane non divided roadway. V1 departed the road to the right. V1 then returned to the roadway, crossed both lanes of travel and exited the left side of the roadway, where it impacted a large rock with its front. V1 continued forward, crossing over a small parking lot, and impacted a tree with its frontal plane. V1 rolled backwards after this impact to final rest.

V1, V2, and V3 were eastbound in lane two on a four lane, two way, trafficway with a grass median and cable barrier guardrail. The frontal plane of V1 struck the rear plane of V2, then the frontal plane of V2 struck the rear plane of V3. V1 came to rest in the median headed southwest. V2 came to rest in its original travel lane headed northeast. V3 pulled forward onto the left shoulder and made a controlled stop.
V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 struck a deer with its frontal plane and then drove off the right side of the roadway coming to rest heading north.
Vehicle #1 was traveling southeast in lane one of a two-lane undivided roadway.  The front of V1 contacted an animal.  V1 came to rest on the right shoulder facing southeast.

Vehicle #1 was traveling southeast in lane one of a three-lane divided trafficway.  Vehicle #2 was traveling southeast in lane two the same three-lane, divided trafficway with a positive barrier.  Lane one began to end and V1 merged left into lane two.  The left of V1 contacted the right of V2.  V1 began to rotate counterclockwise and departed the road to the left.  V1 came to rest in the grassy median, facing west.  V2 came to rest on the right shoulder, facing southeast.

V1 was traveling eastbound in the number 3 lane of a 4 lane divided roadway, approaching an intersection. V2 and V3 were stopped facing west in the number 4 lane of a 4 lane divided roadway, preparing to turn left. V3 was stopped behind V2. V1 and V2 entered the intersection. The front of V1 impacted the right of V2. The force of the impact pushed V2 counter clockwise in an easterly direction. V2 continued to rotate and drive forward where the front of V2 impacted a sign on the center median. V2 continued forward where the front of V2 impacted the left side of V3. V1, after colliding with V2, moved in a southeasterly direction and came to rest facing southeast in the number 1 eastbound lane. V2 came to rest facing northerly in the number 4 westbound lane. V3 came to rest facing westerly in the number 4 westbound lane.

V1 was traveling west on a two-way, not physically divided traffic, in lane 2 (of four lanes) and was approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south to east (making a left turn) while exiting a driveway, west of the intersection, in lane 1 (of two lanes). V1 departed its lane to the left to overtake a tractor trailer. As V1 was returning to its lane, the front end of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V1 came to rest on its wheels facing a westerly direction in the intersection, east of V2. V2 came to rest on its wheels facing a northwesterly direction in the intersection, west of V1.

V1 was traveling in a southwesterly direction on a designated north/south divided trafficway (median strip with positive barrier) in lane 4 (of four lanes) and was approaching V2, which was traveling in the same direction, on the same roadway, and in the same lane, at a lower steady speed.  In lane 4, the front end of V1 came in contact with the back end of V2.  V2 rotated counter-clockwise, and its front end came in contact with the concrete traffic barrier in the median strip.  The left side of V1 then came in contact with the left side of V2.  V1 came to rest on its wheels, facing a southwesterly direction, on the median shoulder, ahead of V2.  V2 came to rest on its wheels, facing a northeasterly direction, partially in lane 4 and on the median shoulder.

V1 was traveling south on a rural gravel roadway. V1 departed the left side of the roadway, returned to the roadway, and rolled left side leading four quarter turns. V1 came to rest on its wheels headed west.

V1 was traveling northbound on a three lane positively divided highway in lane three. V2 was traveling northbound on the same highway traveling in lane one an entrance ramp to the highway. V2 attempted to pass a slower vehicle that was in the on ramp lane. V2 changed lanes to lane three. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in lane three facing northbound.

V1 was traveling northbound on a two lane undivided roadway in lane one negotiating a right curve. V2 was traveling southbound on the same two lane undivided roadway in lane 1 negotiating a left curve. V1 departed its lane to the left and the front of V1 impacted the front of V2. V2 rotated clockwise and came to rest facing northbound partially in lane one and lane 2. V1 departed the roadway to the right and the front of V1 impacted a barbed wire fence. V1 came to rest facing northbound west of the roadway against the fence.

V1 was traveling east and following a non-involved vehicle, in lane two of a four lane, two way trafficway, divided by a cable barrier guardrail. V1 was traveling faster than the non-involved vehicle and swerved left to avoid the non-involved vehicle. V1 departed the left side of the road and struck the cable barrier guardrail with its frontal plane. V1 continued traveling forward through the cable barrier guardrail and came to rest heading north.

V1 was traveling west on an undivided two lane, two way roadway, with a left hand curve. V1 departed the right side of the roadway, then returned to the roadway crossing over the left lane line. V1 then began yawing in clockwise direction before returning to its original travel lane. V1 then departed the right side of the roadway while sliding backward, still in a clockwise yaw. After departing the roadway V1 rolled, left side leading, three quarter turns coming to rest on its right side, heading north.

V1 was traveling east in lane three of a four lane divided (positive barrier) right curved highway. V2 was traveling on the same highway in lane two. V3 was traveling on the same highway in lane four. V1 changed lanes to the right. The right side of V1 impacted the the left side of V2. V2 started to rotate counter clockwise and crossed all lanes to its left, traveling into lane four. The front of V3 impacted the left side of V2. V2 was pushed east and impacted the concrete traffic median with its front. V2 came to rest in lane four, pointing northeast. V3 came to rest in lane four, facing east. After the impact with V2, V1 changed back into lane two. The unit jack knifed and came to rest partially in lane two and three, facing east.

V1 was traveling west in lane two of a four lane divided (with positive barrier) straight highway. V2 was traveling on the same highway in the same direction in lane three. V1 changed into lane three. V2 changed to its left into lane four to avoid a collision. V2 kept changing lanes and drove into lane four ahead of V2. The front of V2 impacted the rear of V1. V1 rotated clockwise and came to rest partially in lane three and partially in lane four facing northwest. V2 came to rest in lane four facing west.

V1 was northbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway approaching a four leg intersection. V1 made a right turn and departed the northeastern section of the intersection impacting a utility pole guidewire with the frontal plane causing damage. V1 came to final rest at the point of impact facing northeast.

V1 was traveling north exiting a driveway intending to make a left turn. V1 departed the right side of the road and impacted a guardrail with its front plane. V1 came to rest on the right side of the road against the guardrail.

V1 was traveling east on a four-lane, divided road with two lanes going east and two lanes going west approaching a T-intersection. V1 crossed over the left lane line and returned to its original travel lane. V1 then made an end departure with its front left wheel impacting a curb. The front of V1 then impacted an embankment and continued up a hill where it impacted a tree with its front plane. V1 came to rest against the tree.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a 3 lane, one way, non-physically divided one way roadway in lane 3 position. V2 was legally parked on the left side of the roadway legally facing east. V1 departed roadway. The Left of V1 contacted the right side of V2. V1 came to rest after impact in the roadway still facing east. V2's final rest is at impact.

Vehicle #1 was traveling south in lane one of a two-lane undivided roadway. V1 departed the road to the right and the front of V1 contacted a mailbox (event 1). V1 continued south and passed over a driveway. The front of V1 contacted a tree (event 2). V1 began to rotate clockwise and rolled over two quarter-turns to the left (event 3). During the rollover, the left of V1 contacted a tree (event 4). V1 came to rest off the road to the the right, facing northwest, on its top. After coming to rest, V1 caught fire (event 5).

V1 was traveling southbound in the first lane of a two lane, two-way roadway. V2 was parked legally, facing south. V1 departed the roadway on the right. The frontal plane of V1 impacted the back plane of V2. V2 was at final rest facing south. V1 then re-entered the roadway on the left, where it came to final rest, facing south.

V1 was traveling southbound in the first lane of a two lane, two-way roadway. V2 was a legally parked, not in transport vehicle, facing south. V3 was a parked vehicle on the sidewalk/driveway entrance facing west.  V1 departed the roadway on the right. The frontal plane of V1 impacted the rear plane of V2. V2 traveled forward,departing the roadway on the right, with its frontal plane contacting the right side plane of V3. V1 was at final rest off of the roadway facing southeast. V2 was at final rest off of the roadway facing southwest. V3 was at final rest off of the roadway facing west.

Vehicles 1, 2 and 3 were all traveling westbound on a 4 lane, non-physically divided roadway, in the lane 2 position. Vehicle 1 was behind V2 and V2 was behind V3. Vehicles 2 and 3 were stopped just east of the intersection. The front plane of Vehicle 1 made contact with the rear plane of Vehicle 2. Vehicle 2 then traveled forward contacting the rear plane of Vehicle 3 with its front plane. Vehicles 2 and 3 came to rest after contact east of the intersection facing west. After Vehicle 1 made contact with Vehicle 2 it started to travel backwards coming to rest on the north shoulder of the roadway facing southwest.

V1 was traveling east in lane two on a two lane, positively divided roadway. V1 then began to hydroplane, departed it's lane on the right side, crossed over lane one, and departing the roadway on the right side. V1's front plane then contacted a guardrail face, and the vehicle began to rotate in a counter clockwise direction. The vehicle then contacted the guardrail face a second time with it's right side plane, and then crossed back over both lanes of the roadway to the left. V1 then departed the roadway on the left side, and contacted another guardrail face with its front plane. V1 came to final rest a short distance past the second guardrail contact, and approximately ? cm from the initial roadway departure.

V1 was traveling northwest in lane two on a five lane, two way, roadway, and was turning left into a parking lot. V2 was traveling southeast in lane one on the same roadway, when V1's right side plane contacted V2's front plane. Both vehicles continued forward after impact and V1's right side plane contacted V2's front plane a second time. Both vehicles came to final rest in lane one, a short distance from the initial contact.

Vehicle 1 was traveling southwest on a four lane undivided roadway, turning left into a driveway entrance from the second travel lane. Vehicle 2 was traveling northeast on the same roadway going straight in the second travel lane. Vehicle 2 contacted its frontal plane with the right side plane of vehicle 1. Vehicle 1 rotated clockwise and came to rest on the roadway. Vehicle 2 came to rest in on the roadway within its travel lane.

Vehicle 1 was traveling southeast on a two lane undivided roadway. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway to the right. Vehicle 1 reentered the roadway then steered right and began to rotate clockwise. V1 departed the right road edge as it rotated clockwise where it tripped and rolled left 4-quarter turns. The left side and top of V1 contacted a concrete well during the rollover sequence. V1 came to rest on the roadside on its wheels facing west.

V1 was traveling northwest on a two-lane, on a two-way divided traffic way with a positive barrier. V1 departed the roadway on the right side, where it rotated counter clockwise and impacted a sign with its right plane. V1 continued further west and entered a parking lot where V2 was parked. V1 front plane impacted back of V2. V1 continued further west where its right plane impacted a building before coming to final rest.

V1 was traveling northbound on a two lane, two-way roadway passing through a four-way intersection. V2 was traveling on a two lane, two-way unmarked roadway approaching the mentioned four way intersection. V1 front plane contacted V2's left plane. After initial impact with V2, V1's right plane contacted V2's left plane. V1 came to final rest further north on roadway, V2 came to final rest at intersection on roadway.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a five-lane, non-physically divided roadway with a two-way left turn lane, in lane one. V2 was traveling northbound on a two-lane, two-way roadway approaching a T-shaped intersection attempting a left turn. In the eastbound lanes, the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V1 came to final rest in the roadway facing east, V2 came to final rest facing northeast.

V1 was traveling north on a 2-lane roadway negotiating a left curve. V2 was traveling south on the same roadway negotiating the right curve. V2 departed its lane line to the left and the front of V1 contacted the front of V2. V1 came to rest in the northbound lane facing north. V2 rotated clockwise and came to rest partially in the northbound lane facing southwest.

V1 was traveling on a three-lane, two-way roadway approaching an intersection controlled by a traffic light. V1 was traveling northbound in the southbound lane two. V2 was traveling westbound on a three-lane, physically divided roadway approaching the mentioned intersection. Within the intersection at the northwest quadrant, the front plane of V2 impacted the right side of V1 (Event 1) which then resulted in a side slap (Event 2) with the right plane of V1 and left plane of V2. After impact one and two, V1 departed the roadway on the northwest corner where the front plane of V1 struck the face of a guardrail (Event 3) and its left front tire/wheel impacted the curb (Event 4). V1 came to final rest against the guardrail off the roadway facing northwest. V2 came to final rest on the roadway facing northwest.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a six lane, two way, concrete median divided roadway approaching a four legged intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling north approaching the same intersection on a five lane, two way, undivided roadway in lane three. Vehicle 2 attempted to turn left onto an intersecting roadway and the front of Vehicle 1 contacted the right side of Vehicle 2. Both Vehicles came to final rest within the intersection..

Vehicle 1 was traveling south, in lane four, on a seven lane, two way trafficway physically divided by a concrete barrier. Vehicle 2 was traveling south, ahead of vehicle 1, in lane three on the same trafficway. Vehicle 3 was traveling south, in front of vehicle 1, in lane four on the same trafficway. Vehicle 4 was traveling south, in front of vehicle 3, in lane four on the same trafficway. Vehicle 1 departed its original lane of travel on the right side and the right plane contacted the left plane of Vehicle 2. Vehicle 1 continued forward, departed the lane three on the left side and the left plane contacted the right plane of Vehicle 3. Vehicle 1 continued forward and the front plane contacted the back plane of Vehicle 4. All vehicles came to final rest on the roadway facing south.

V1 was traveling northeast on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway. V1 stopped before an intersection and began to accelerate in the roadway. V1 then departed the left hand side of their initial travel lane and then departed the left hand side of the roadway. V1 struck shrubbery and then a tree with an unknown plane. V1 the proceeded to come to rest in a swamp off of the roadway.

V1 was traveling south on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a right hand curve in the roadway and approaching a T-intersection. V1 entered the intersection and departed the roadway at the southern side of the intersection. V1 continued forward off of the roadway where its right side contacted a rock pillar, then a concrete porch, then the rock pillar a 2nd time. V1 continued forward and its front contacted an unknown object and came to rest facing south.

V1 was traveling west in lane two on a two lane, physically divided roadway. V1 departed the roadway on the left side, returned to the roadway, crossed both travel lanes, and departed the roadway on the right side. V1 then contacted a guardrail face with its front plane and its left side plane, continued forward, and struck a concrete culvert with its undercarriage. V1 continued forward and struck a tree with its front plane before coming to final rest.

V1 was traveling north bound in lane one of a two lane, two-way, not physically divided roadway approaching a T intersection. V2 was traveling north bound behind V1 on the same two lane, two-way roadway. V1 rear plane was contacted by V2 front plane.

V1 was traveling southbound on a two lane positively divided highway in lane one negotiating a curve. A deer attempted to cross the roadway and entered V1's travel lane. The front of V1 impacted the deer. V1 came to rest on the shoulder of the roadway facing southbound.

V1 was traveling westbound on a two lane undivided two way traffic roadway in lane one. A deer ran out into the road. V1 steered to the left to avoid contact with the deer and departed it's lane and the roadway to the left. The front of V1 impacted a fire hydrant and then a fence. V1 came to rest against the fence facing westbound.

V1 was traveling south on a three lane divided road approaching a four-way intersection. V2 was traveling east on a five lane divided roadway approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered intersection and the front of V1 contacted the right side of V2. Subsequently, the left side of V1 contacted the right side of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 and V2 were traveling west on a four lane, two way, undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was stopped ahead of V1 when the front of V1 contacted the back of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling south on an undivided, two-way road. V2 was parked on the east curb facing north. V1 departed the road on the right side, contacted the curb and lost directional control of the vehicle. V1 returned to the roadway, crossed left across both lanes and the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V1 departed the east side of the road and came to rest off the road.

V1 was traveling east in the fourth of five lanes on a divided, two-way roadway entering a light controlled, three-legged intersection attempting to turn left. V2 was traveling west in the fourth of four lanes on the same roadway entering the same intersection as V1. Within the intersection, the right side of V1 contacted the front of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling south in the first of two lanes, on a two-way roadway divided by a median. A non-contact vehicle also heading south swerved into the first lane and V1 swerved right to avoid contact. The right front tire, and right rear tire, struck the right curb, and then V1 lost control until the vehicle stopped, facing east.

V1 was exiting a parking lot attempting to turn northbound on to a two way four lane roadway, V2 was southbound in lane two on the same roadway approaching the parking lot exit. The left side of V1 contacted the front of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling southwest following a two way, two lane road, approaching a four way intersection. V2 was traveling northeast on a two way, two lane road, approaching the same four way intersection. V1 attempted to turn left in the middle of the intersection. The right side of V1 impacted the front of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway; V1 facing southeast, V2 facing east.

Both Vehicles 1 and 2 were traveling northbound on a two lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position. V1 is behind V2. Vehicle 2 was in the process of slowing for a non contact bus ahead. The front plane of Vehicle 1 made contact with the rear plane of Vehicle 2. Both vehicles came to final rest facing north shortly after impact.

V1 was traveling south in lane 2 on a 3-lane divided, two-way roadway entering a three-legged intersection. V2 was traveling north in lane 3 on a 3-lane divided roadway approaching the same intersection to turn left. Both vehicles entered the intersection and the front of V1 contacted the right side of V2. V2 rotated clockwise and departed the roadway on the southwest corner where its left rear wheel contacted a curb then its left side contacted a stop sign post. The stop sign then broke free and contacted the top of V2. V2 came to rest on the eastbound sidewalk facing west. V1 rotated clockwise as it continued forward and came to rest in the roadway facing south.

V1 was southbound in lane No. 3 of a three-lane physically divided roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the left and the front of V1 contacted a guardrail (Event 1). Then the left rear contacted the guardrail (Event 2). V1 the re-entered the roadway and rolled six-quarter turns crossing all travel lanes coming to rest on its top in the roadway.

V1 was traveling east six lane, divided roadway, turning left at an intersection. V2 was traveling west on a six lane, divided roadway, approaching the same intersection. In the intersection, the frontal plane of V1 contacted the front of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling northeast in lane four of a seven-lane divided roadway, turning left. V2 was traveling southwest in lane two of the same roadway going straight and V3 was in lane three of the same roadway, stopped. The right plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2. The impact pushed V1 and it's left plane contacted the back plane of V3. All vehicle came to rest close to impact.

V1 and V2 were traveling west in lane one of a two lane divided roadway with V2 ahead of V1. V2 slowed in the roadway and V1's front plane contacted V2's rear plane. V1 came to final rest near impact. V2 traveled a short distance and departed the right road edge where it came to rest.

V1 was traveling north exiting a private parking lot making a right turn onto a roadway with three eastbound lanes and six westbound lanes divided by a non-positive median. V2 was traveling east in lane two on the same roadway. As V1 made a right turn the front of V2 contacted the left plane of V1. V1 rotated clockwise to final rest on the roadway facing southwest in lane two. V2 rotated counterclockwise after impact and crossed the median. V2 came to final rest on the roadway facing north across lanes five and six of the westbound lanes.

Vehicle 1 was traveling northbound in the first lane, exit ramp, of an four lane positively divided roadway. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway to the left and entered the gore area, crossing through the gore and impacted a concrete traffic barrier with its frontal plane. Vehicle 1 came to rest on the paved shoulder.

V1 was traveling in a northwesterly direction on a designated north/south roadway in lane 1 (of five lanes) and was approaching V2, which was stopped facing the same direction, on the same roadway, ahead in lane 1. In lane 1, the front end of V1 contacted the back end of V2. V2 then departed the roadway on the right where its front end and then right side contacted a concrete traffic barrier. V2 returned to lane 1, where the front end of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V1 was driven to the right shoulder and parked. V2 came to rest on its wheels facing a northwesterly direction on the right shoulder.

V1 was traveling north on a two-lane undivided roadway in lane one. V2 was on the southbound shoulder of the same roadway facing south preparing to make a U-turn into the northbound lane. V2 was unable to make a full U-turn and was stopped in the northbound lane facing east when the front of V1 impacted the right side of V2. V1 came to rest in the northbound lane on its right side facing northeast. V2 came to rest in the northbound lane facing east.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane physically divided roadway in lane two negotiating a curve with lane one closed due to construction. V1 departed the left road edge where the front impacted a safety drum. V1 continued off the roadway where the front of V1 impacted a jersey barrier. V1 started a counterclockwise yaw when it tripped and began to rollover right side leading. V1 rolled 6 quarter turns before coming to rest on its roof facing south.

V1 was traveling east on a non-physically divided five lane road in lane three, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north on a three non-physically divided three lane road, in lane two, stopped at the light. As V2 entered the intersection to make a left turn, the front of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V2 spun in a counter-clockwise manner and came to rest within the intersection facing a northwest direction. V1 came to rest within the intersection facing a easterly direction.

V1 was traveling south on a non-physically divided seven lane road in lane two. For an unknown reason V1 veered to the right and departed the road edge; where the right side of V1 impacted a tree. V1 then impacted the curb and continued traveling south within the sidewalk, and the front of V1 impacted another tree. V1 came to rest partially in lane one and the sidewalk facing a southerly direction.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a westbound freeway in lane 4 of 5. V2 was traveling westbound in lane 4 of the same roadway. The front of V1 contacted the front of V2. After impact, both vehicles rotated counter-clockwise. V1 then contacted a guardrail face located in the gore of the interchange area with its right side and came to rest on the roadway facing west. The back of V2 contacted a concrete barrier and V2 came to rest on the roadway facing south.

All Vehicles were northbound on a 4 lane physically divided roadway. V1 and V3 were in the 2nd lane V2 was in the 1st lane. V1 departed its lane to the right and the front of V1 contacted the rear of V2. V1 then spun in front of V2 and the right side of V1 contacted the front of V2. As V3 approached, a wheel/tire from V1 was laying in the roadway in lane 2 and the front of V3 contacted the wheel/tire of V1. V1 came to rest on the right hand shoulder V2 and V3 came to rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling east in the first of five lanes on a positively divided, two-way roadway. V1 departed the road on the right side. The right side of V1 contacted a guardrail face at the end of a guardrail section. V1 began to rotate clockwise and the front of V1 contacted a pole. V1 continued rotating until it came to rest off the road.

V1 was traveling east in the second of four lanes on a divided, two-way roadway entering a light controlled, four-legged intersection. V2 was traveling north in the third of four lanes on a one-way roadway entering the same intersection. Within the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V2 rotated counterclockwise and rolled left one-quarter turn and came to rest on its left side in the roadway facing east. V1 rotated counter-clockwise and came to rest in the intersection facing northeast.

V1 was heading northeast on a four lane undivided roadway. V2 was heading southwest on the same roadway. V1 departed its initial travel lane to the left. The front of V1 contacted the front of V2. V1 was then redirected to the right. V1 came to final rest facing generally west in the northeast-bound lanes. V2 was redirected to the right. V2 departed the roadway and the left of V2 contacted a tree. V2 came to final rest off-road facing generally east.

V1 and V2 were traveling south west on a four lane undivided roadway. V2 stopped to make a left turn. The front of V1 contacted he back of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest near the point of impact.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a four-lane, two-way roadway in lane one attempting to crossover an intersection. V2 was stopped westbound on the same roadway in lane two attempting to left turn to head south at the same intersection. A non-contact bus was stopped southbound in lane 2 waiting to turn left, possibly obstructing views. Within the intersection, the front plane of V2 contacted the left plane of V1. V1 then departed the roadway right where the right rear wheel of contacted a curb on the southeast corner and came to final rest in the roadway facing west. V2 came to final rest in the roadway facing south.

V1 was traveling south on a two-way, five lane roadway in lane two approaching a light controlled 4-legged intersection. V2 was traveling east on a three lane, one-way roadway in lane three approaching the same intersection. In the intersection the right side of V1 contacted the front of V2. After the initial impact V1 departed the roadway and contacted a light pole with its left side, V1 then contacted a power utility box with its right side. V1 continued on before contacting a power pole with its front plane and coming to rest. V2 also departed the roadway and contacted a light pole with its front bumper before coming to rest.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south in lane two of a two lane, non-divided, one-way roadway.  Vehicle 1 left its travel lane to the left, departed the roadway to the left, and then struck a ditch with its front.  The vehicle came to rest off the roadway at the ditch, facing south.

Vehicle 1 was traveling northbound on a three lane divided roadway. Vehicle 1 was in the first of three travel lanes and departed the initial travel lane and the roadway to the left side. V1 contacted a tree in the grass median with its frontal plane. Vehicle 1 continued travelling and contacted another tree with its frontal plane. Vehicle 1 rotated counterclockwise and contacted a third tree with its right plane. V1 entered into the southbound lanes of travel coming to rest on the roadway.

V1 was eastbound on a 2 lane roadway V2 was westbound on the same roadway. V1 departed its lane to the left and V2 departed the roadway to the right (to avoid V1). The front of V1 contacted the front of V2. V1 came to rest on the southern shoulder. V2 crossed all lanes departed the roadway to the left and came to rest on the southern shoulder.

V1 and V2 were both on a 2 lane, physically divided roadway (the right hand lane was coned off and closed due to construction). V1 began to slow because of traffic conditions. The front of V1 contacted the back of V2. After impact V1 pulled into the closed right-hand lane and V2 came to rest on the left hand shoulder.

V1, V2, V3 and V4 were all traveling in lane two of a two-lane divided highway.  V4 was the lead vehicle with V3, V2 and V1 following sequentially. As traffic began to slow, the front of V1 impacted the back of V2 (event 1) causing the front of V2 to strike the back of V3 (event 2). Finally, the front of V3 struck the back of V4 (event 3). All of the vehicles came to final rest on the roadway facing south.

V2 was traveling south on a non-physically divided two lane roadway in lane one approaching an intersection. V1 was traveling west on a two lane non-physically divided roadway in lane one approaching an intersection. As V2 entered the intersection the front right of V1 impacted the front of V2. V1 then impacted a curb and continued off of the southwest road edge where the front impacted a boulder. V1 came to rest off of the roadway on top of a boulder facing southwest. V2 came to rest in the southbound lane in the intersection facing north.

V1 was eastbound and approaching an intersection in Lane 2 of a 5 lane roadway with 2 way left turn lane. V2 was Northbound on a 2 lane physically divided roadway and approaching the same intersection. Within the intersection, V2 turned left and V1 continued straight. V1's front plane contacted V2's front plane. V1 came to rest partially on the northeast side of the intersection. V2 came to rest in the south east portion of the intersection.

V1 was traveling north in the #5 lane of a 5 lane divided roadway. V2 was traveling south in the #3 lane of a 3 lane divided roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the left and entered the #3 lane of the southbound roadway. The front of V1 impacted the front of V2. V1 came to rest partially on the center median facing north. V2 came to rest facing south between the #3 lane and the #2 lane.

V1 was traveling east in lane one of a four lane divided (no positive barrier) roadway, approaching an intersection. V2 and V3 were traveling on the same road in lane two. V2 moved further east and V3 impacted the left side of V1 with its right side. V1 came to rest in lane one, partially in lane two, facing east. V2 and V3 came to rest in lane two, facing east.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north on a two lane, one-way roadway, in lane number one. Vehicle 1 left the roadway to the right and its front end made contact with a pole. After initial contact, vehicle 1 rotated clock-wise and came to rest facing southwest across the roadway.

V1 was traveling in a northeasterly direction, on a designated north/south divided trafficway (median strip with positive barrier), in lane 1 (of two lanes), when it departed the roadway on the right and its front end contacted a guardrail. V1 was returned to the roadway from the right and control over V1 was lost. V1 skidded laterally in a counter-clockwise rotation and departed the road on the left, where it then overturned (6 quarter turns, leading right). During the rollover, Occupant 1 was totally ejected. V1 came to rest on its roof, facing a southwesterly direction in the median strip.

Vehicles #1, #2 and #3 were traveling west in lane one of a four-lane roadway with a two-way left turn lane.  V2 and V3 slowed due to traffic congestion.  The front of V1 contacted the back of V2.  This pushed V2 forward the front of V2 contacted the back of V3.  All three vehicles came to rest facing west, near impact.

Vehicle #1 was traveling south, negotiating a left curve.  V1 departed the road to the right and passed over an intersecting roadway.  The front of V1 contacted the ground.  V1 came to rest near the impact, off the road to the right, facing south.

V1 was traveling west down an incline on a two-lane, two-way road, approaching a T-intersection. V2 was traveling north on a two-lane, two-way road, passing through the same intersection. V1 tried to make a left turn when its front plane impacted the right side of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in the intersection.

V1 was traveling north on a two-lane, two-way trafficway with a painted median, negotiating a left curve. V1 departed the left side of the road when its front undercarriage and right front wheel impacted a curb. V1 came to rest off of the left side of the road.

Vehicle #1 was traveling east in lane one of a two-lane, undivided roadway.  Vehicle #2 was parked facing east along the south curb of the same roadway.  V1 departed the roadway to the right and the front of V1 contacted the back of V2.  Both vehicles came to rest near impact.

Vehicle #1 was traveling east in lane one of a two-lane, undivided roadway.  Vehicle #2 was traveling north in lane 2 of an intersecting three-lane, undivided roadway.  Both vehicles entered the intersection and the right of V1 contacted the front of V2.  The vehicles rotated and the right of V1 contacted the left of V2.  V1 departed the road to the left and the front of V1 contacted a sign post.  V1 came to rest near this impact.  V2 came to rest just north of the intersection.

V1 was traveling south on a one way off ramp, in lane one. After the impact, V1 rolled left four quarter turns and came to rest on its wheels facing a northwesterly direction.

V1 was traveling east on five lane undivided roadway in lane two. V2 was heading west on the same roadway in lane two. The left front tire of V1 became detached. V1 traveling west out of parking lot to continue straight into an adjacent parking lot by crossing all lanes of travel. V2 was traveling south in lane one of a three-lane roadway with a two-way left turn lane. The right of V1 was contacted by the front of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest near the point of impact.

V1 was traveling northbound in the number 2 lane of a 5 lane undivided roadway. V2 was traveling northbound in the number 1 lane of a 5 lane undivided roadway. V1 was east bound on a two lane bidirectional local roadway, negotiating a curve to the left. V1 departed the roadway to the right, where it impacted the side of a culvert with its front plane, and impacted the end of the culvert with its frontal plane east of the initial impact. V1 came to final rest in the culvert facing east.

V1 was traveling west in lane one of a two lane undivided (two-way traffic) roadway, approaching an intersection. V1 was traveling west in lane one of a three lane divided (no positive barrier) roadway, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north in lane two of a three lane divided (no positive barrier) roadway, approaching the same intersection. Within the intersection, V1 impacted the left side of V2 with its front. V2 rotated counter clockwise and came to rest within the intersection, facing northwest. After the impact with V1, V1 continued to move west and departed the roadway to the north. V1 was traveling north in lane 3, of a 5 lane roadway with two way turn lane. V2 was traveling south, in lane 2, of the same roadway. V1 turned left within intersection. V1 was traveling on a 2 lane roadway, in lane 1 and approaching intersection. V2 was in lane 3 of a 4 lane roadway, with a 2 way left turn lane. V1 attempted to make a left turn. V1's front contacted V2's right side. Both vehicles came to rest within the roadway.

V1 was heading south on a two lane undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was heading east on a two lane undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. The right of V1 connected with the front of V2. Both vehicles were redirected to the west of the intersection where V2 went off road and made contact with the ground before coming to final rest.

V1 was traveling south in lane 1 of a 2 lane, two-way, not physically divided roadway approaching an intersection. V1 left plane contacted V2 front plane. Both vehicles came to final rest off the roadway in an open grass median.

V1 was traveling southeast in the U-turn lane of a highway interchange entering the northbound road of the west service road of the highway. V1 was traveling eastbound on a two lane roadway and negotiating a curve to the left. V1 departed the roadway to the right. V1's front contacted a pole. V1's right side then contacted the same pole while V1's left side contacted a curb. V1 continued forward and came to final rest in a stream.

V1 was traveling northwest in lane one of a five-lane roadway. V2 was traveling northwest, also in lane one, ahead of V1. V2 was attempting a right turn. V1 traveled across a ditch and its front undercarriage plane contacted the ground. V1's front plane then contacted a chain link fence and came to final rest again the fence.

V1 was traveling south negotiating a right curve in lane three of a five lane roadway attempting to make a right turn. V1's right plane was contacted by V2's front plane V1 rotated counter-clockwise and came to final rest in the southbound lanes facing east. V2 departed the right road edge and its front plane contacted a utility pole where it came to final rest facing southwest.

V1 was traveling northwest on a four lane undivided roadway approaching a four-way intersection controlled by traffic signals.  V2 was traveling southwest on a five lane one-way roadway approaching the same intersection. Vehicle 1 was traveling in the northbound lanes and entered onto the one way exit ramp. Vehicle 1 departed the travel lane to the left and contacted a guardrail with its frontal plane and came to rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling eastbound in lane two, on a three-lane, physically divided roadway, approaching an intersection controlled by a traffic light. V2 was in lane two stopped in traffic also facing eastbound. The front of V1 contacted the rear of V2. V1 continued eastbound through the intersection and departed the roadway on the southeast corner. The front plane of V1 contacted a light pole and came to final rest facing east. V2 came to final rest in the area of impact also facing east.

V1 was traveling east on a two-lane, one-way roadway approaching a four-way intersection controlled by a traffic light in all directions. V2 was traveling north on a three-lane, two-way roadway approaching the mentioned intersection.  In the middle of the intersection, the front plane of V1 contacted the left plane of V2. After this impact V2 continued northeast and departed the roadway where the front plane struck a fire hydrant and came to final rest partially of the roadway. V1 came to final rest in the roadway facing northeast.

V1 was traveling southwest in an unknown lane on a two-lane divided roadway. V1 departed the right curb edge and traveled a distance on the grass roadside where its 2 front tires contacted unknown debris on the ground. V1 came to rest facing west on the roadside.

V1 was traveling west on a three lane, two way, undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling east on a three lane, two way, undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. In the intersection, V1 attempted a left turn, and the right side of V1 contacted the front of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling west on a three lane divided roadway approaching a four-way intersection. V2 was traveling east on a four lane divided roadway approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection and the front of V1 contacted the front of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.
V1 was traveling southwest in lane one of a five lane roadway. V1 departed the right road edge and it front plane contacted a tree. V1 came to rest against the tree.

V1 was traveling northeast in lane two of a five-lane undivided roadway, negotiating a left curve, approaching an intersection. V2 was stopped in lane one of a two-lane undivided roadway at the same intersection, traveling southwest. V1 executed a right turn and traveled over it's left lane line. The front plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2. V1 then backed up and fled the scene. V2 came to final rest at impact.

V1 was traveling southeast in lane two of a five lane undivided roadway negotiating a left curve. V2 was traveling northeast in lane one of a private drive attempting a left turn. V1's front plane contacted V2's front plane both vehicles came to rest near impact.

V1 was traveling southeast in lane three of a five lane roadway approaching an intersection, turning left. V2 was traveling northwest in lane one of the same five lane roadway, approaching the same intersection. The right plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2. V2 came to final rest on the roadway near impact. After the initial impact, V1 departed the roadway, impacting a curb with it's left front wheel. V1 then traveled off the roadway before contacting a store sign with it's front plane and coming to final rest against the sign.

V1 was traveling south following a two-way, two lane road with a slight curve to the left. As V1 was negotiating the curve, it departed the roadway to the right. After the fourth turn, when V1 was back on its wheels, the right side impacted a large tree. V1 came to final rest off the roadway, against the tree, facing east.

V1 was traveling south behind V2 on a two way, three lane, undivided roadway negotiating a slight right hand curve in the roadway. V2, a school bus, was traveling south on the same roadway in front of V1. V2 stopped in the roadway, and the front plane of V1 contacted the rear plane of V2. V1 and V2 both came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling south in lane one of a two-lane undivided (two-way traffic) roadway, negotiating a left curve while approaching an intersection. V1 rotated clockwise and came to rest within the intersection, facing southwest. V2 rotated counter clockwise and came to rest within the intersection, facing southwest.

V1 was traveling east in lane three of a four lane divided (with positive barrier) highway. V2 was traveling in the lane to the right of V1. V1 attempted to change into V2's lane. The right side of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V1 moved back into its lane of travel where it came to rest facing east. V2 stayed in its lane of travel where it came to rest facing east.

V1 was traveling westbound on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway, in lane one approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling southbound on a two way, three lane, undivided roadway, in lane one. At the intersection V1 attempted to turn left and V2 continued straight. The front of V1 impacted the left side of V2. The right side of V1 then impacted the left side of V2 in a side slap manner. V1 came to rest facing south partially in lane one. V2 came to rest facing south in lane one.

Vehicle #1 was traveling south in lane one of a two-lane, undivided roadway.  V1 began to rotate clockwise and departed the road to the right.  V1 tripped over four quarter-turns to the left.  V1 came to rest on its wheels, facing north, off the road to the right.

Vehicle #1 was traveling south on a one-way, one-lane road. Vehicle #2 was parked facing south on the right side of the same road. V1 steered right to avoid an animal in the road, and the front plane of V1 contacted the left plane of V2. V1 immediately rolled two quarter turns to the left. Both vehicles came to rest on the road.

V1 and V2 were both traveling, in opposite directions, on the same 3 lane roadway with 2 way turn lane. V1 was traveling in lane 2, northeast bound. V2 was traveling in Lane 1, southwest bound. V1 turned left. V1's front contacted V2's front. Both vehicles came to rest within the roadway.

V1 was traveling northwest bound on a 2 lane roadway while negotiating a curve to the left. V2 was traveling southeast bound on the same roadway while negotiating a curve to the right. V1 crossed the lane line to the left with the curve. V1's front contacted V2's front. Both vehicles came to final rest within the roadway.

V1 was traveling south on a two-lane undivided roadway in lane one approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling west on a 5 lane undivided roadway in lane three approaching an intersection preparing to make a left turn. As both vehicles entered the intersection, the front of V2 impacted the left side of V1. V1 came to rest facing west in lane one of the eastbound lanes, west of the intersection. V2 came to rest facing south in lane one of the southbound lanes, south of the intersection.

V1 was traveling south on a two-lane, two-way road. The front of V1 impacted a horse that was standing in the road. The horse rolled up and over V1, impacting its top. V1 came to rest on the right side of the road. The horse came to rest on the roadway.

V1 and V2 were traveling westbound in the number 3 lane of a 6 lane divided roadway. V3 was traveling westbound in the number 4 lane of the same 6 lane divided roadway. V1 was approaching the rear of V2 and the front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. V1 then moved southwesterly where the front of V1 impacted the right side of V3. V2, after the impact with V1, rotated clockwise and came to rest facing southwesterly in the number 3 lane. V1 came to rest facing westerly in the number 4 lane, west of V2. V3 came to rest facing westerly in the number 5 lane, east of V1.

V1 was traveling west in lane one on a two lane, two way, non-divided roadway and was negotiating a right curve. V2 was traveling east in lane one on the same two lane, two way, non-divided roadway and was negotiating a left curve. V1 then departed its lane on the left side and its front plane contacted V2's front plane. After impact, V2 departed the roadway on the right side and came to final rest off of the roadway. V1 rotated in a counter-clockwise direction and came to final rest in lane two.

V1 was traveling west in lane one on a two lane, positively divided roadway. A deer then entered the roadway from the median, hurdled a passing vehicle in lane 2, and landed in front of V1. V1's front plane then contacted the deer. V1 came to final rest on the right shoulder of the roadway, a short distance from impact.

V1, towing a trailer, was traveling east on a 2-lane roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling directly in front of V1 and making a right turn at the intersection. V1 departed the southeast corner of the intersection and the front of the towed trailer contacted the back of V1. V1 came to rest facing southeast. V2 came to rest on the roadway facing east.

V1 was traveling northeast bound on a 2 lane roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south east bound on a 3 lane, non-physically divided roadway in lane 3 approaching the same intersection. 1 turned right at the intersection. The front of V1 contacted the right side of V2. V1 came to rest in the roadway. After the initial impact V2 went off the roadway to the left. V2's LF wheel contacted a curb. V2 came to final rest, mostly on the roadway.

V1 was traveling northeast on a two-way, two  lane undivided portion of the roadway.  As the roadway becomes divided the front of V1 contacted a pedestrian in the road.  V1 came to final rest in the road facing northeast.

V1 was traveling north in the third of four lanes on a left curved, divided, two-way roadway. V2 was traveling north on the same road in the second lane. V1 attempted to change lanes and crossed over the right lane line. The right side of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V1 lost directional control and departed the roadway on the right side. V1 twice contacted a concrete traffic barrier with its front and then right side. Both vehicles came to rest on the road.

V1 was traveling south in the first of seven lanes on a undivided, two-way roadway entering a light controlled, four-legged intersection. V2 was traveling east in the second of five lanes on a divided, two-way roadway entering the same intersection as V1. Within the intersection, the right side of V1 contacted the front of V2. The vehicles came to rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling west on a two-way road, divided by a median.  V1 departed the roadway to the left and the front of V1 contacted a light pole. After impact an unknown object fell from the light pole and contacted the front windshield. V1 came to rest in the median against the pole.

V1 was traveling west on a 4 lane undivided roadway in lane 2 approaching a 4 way intersection, V3 was eastbound on the same roadway in lane 2 approaching the same intersection. V2 was southbound on a 2 lane undivided roadway in lane 1 approaching the same intersection. Within the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. All vehicles came to rest in the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a 5 lane, two-way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 2 position approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north on a 3 lane, two-way, non-physically divided roadway in lane one position approaching the same intersection attempting to turn right. V3 and V4 were both stopped in the roadway traveling west on a 5 lane, two-way, non-physically divided roadway with V3 in lane 3 and V4 in lane 2. Both vehicles rotated away from each other causing a "side slap" where the right side of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V1 then was traveling north east and departed the roadway left side. An unknown plane of V1 contacted a utility box. V1 then came to rest in a private parking lot north east of the utility box. After the Side slap with V1, V2 traveled east into the westbound lanes making contact with an unknown plane of V3 and V4 before coming to rest facing east.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a two lane, two way drive way attempting to exiting a business access to make a left hand turn. Vehicle 2 was traveling northbound on a five lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position. The left plane of Vehicle 1 made contact with the front plane of Vehicle 2. Vehicle 1 came to final rest shortly after impact facing southwest in the left hand turn lane. Vehicle 2 rotated counter clockwise following impact coming to final rest facing northwest.

V1 was traveling south in lane one of a two-lane undivided roadway, negotiating a left curve. V1 departed the roadway to the right and continued traveling off the roadway. The right plane of V1 contacted a tree branch then a tree V1 continued forward and the front plane contacted a stump and then another tree. V1 came to final rest against the second tree facing east.

V1 was traveling southeast negotiating a left curve in lane one of a two lane roadway. V1 departed the right road edge and the right plane contacted a tree. V1 rotated clockwise and the front plane contacted another tree. V1 contacted a mail box before coming final rest off the right road edge.

V1 was traveling north on a four lane, two way median divided roadway. V2 was traveling south on the same roadway. V1 attempted a U-turn and the front of V2 contacted the right side of V1. V1 and V2 then departed the roadway to the west. The front of V1 then contacted a ditch. The front of V2 then contacted a ditch. Both vehicles came to final rest off of the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west in lane one on a three lane, two way roadway, approaching a four-leg intersection with a traffic control signal. Vehicle 2 was traveling north in lane one on a five lane, two way roadway, divided by a grass median, approaching the same intersection with a traffic control signal. Within the intersection the front plane of vehicle 2 contacted the left plane of vehicle 1. Upon impact vehicle 1 rotated clockwise and the front plane contacted a curb before coming to final rest on the roadway facing north. Vehicle 2 continued forward and came to final rest on the roadway facing northwest.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a five lane two way roadway. Vehicle 2 was in front of vehicle 1 stopped in traffic traveling south on the same roadway. The front plane of vehicle 1 contacted the back plane of vehicle 2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway facing south.

Vehicle 1 was traveling northeast in lane one on a three lane, two way roadway that is physically divided by a cable barrier. Vehicle 2 was traveling northeast on the same roadway in lane two. Vehicle 1 departed the original lane of travel over the left lane line. The front of Vehicle 2 contacted the back of Vehicle 1. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway on the left side and the front plane of Vehicle 1 contacted the cable barrier before coming to final rest facing northeast. Vehicle 2 pulled over and came to final rest on the right shoulder facing northeast.

V1 was traveling west in lane two on a two lane divided roadway negotiating a left curve. V1 departed the roadway on the left side into a grass median. V1 steered right and re-entered the roadway where it tripped and rolled left 4-quarter turns and came to rest in the roadway on its wheels facing north. The driver was ejected during the rollover sequence.

V1 and V2 were both traveling east in lane one on a three lane, two way, roadway. V2 had stopped at a traffic signal when V1's front plane contacted V2's rear plane. Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling west on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway, approaching an intersection with a stop sign. V2 was traveling south, on a two way, two lane undivided roadway negotiating a right hand curve in the roadway, approaching the same intersection as V1. Both vehicles entered the intersection and the frontal plane of V1 contacted the left side plane of V2. V2 rotated in a clockwise direction and departed the right side of the roadway contacting a tree with its left side plane. V2 continued forward contacting V3 that was parked off the roadway with its left side plane. V2 continued forward making contact with the ground with its undercarriage. V2 came to final rest off of the roadway. V1 continued forward and came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling west in lane 2 on a five lane, two-way roadway. V2 was stopped ahead of V1 in lane 2 on the same roadway.  The front plane of V1 made contact with the rear plane of V2. V1 came to rest in the roadway facing west, while V2 came to rest on the roadway facing east.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a 4 lane median divided roadway in lane 4. Vehicle 2 was exiting a private drive attempting to go straight. The front of V1 made contact with the left of V2. V1 came to rest in it's original lane facing west. V2 came to rest in it's original lane facing south.

V1 was traveling north in lane two of a two-lane,  two-way, divided roadway.  V1 departed its lane to the right and its frontal plane impacted the rear plane of a legally parked vehicle.  V1 came to final rest on the roadway facing north. V2 came to rest near the point-of-impact and facing north.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a four-lane, two-way roadway approaching a four-way intersection controlled by a traffic light. V2 was traveling northbound on a three-lane, one-way roadway approaching the mentioned intersection. In the middle of the intersection the front plane of V2 contacted the right plane of V1.  After impact V1 entered a clockwise yaw and departed the roadway on the northwest corner. The front plane of V1 contacted a utility pole and rotated off the pole where the left rear wheel impacted a curb and the left plane impacted a light pole.  V2 came to final rest in the intersection facing northeast; V1 came to final rest partially off the roadway facing southeast.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a two lane, grass median divided roadway, in lane one.  A deer entered the roadway and the front of Vehicle 1 impacted the deer.  Vehicle 1 came to rest forward of impact, facing south, still in lane one.

V1 was heading west on a five lane undivided roadway. V2 was heading south on a five lane undivided roadway way. Both vehicles entered the intersection intending to pass through it. The front of V1 connected with the left of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest near the point of impact.

V1 and V2 were heading east on parallel roadways, V1 was in lane two. V2 was in lane two of its own roadway. V1 began to merge and make a U-turn in an attempt to head west. The left of V1 connected with the front of V2.  V1 came to final rest straddling the center line facing southwest. V2 came to final rest straddling lanes 3 and 4 facing northeast.

V1 was traveling east in the second of three lanes on a positively divided, two-way roadway. V2 was traveling east in the third lane of the same roadway. V1 changed lanes to the left to avoid debris in the roadway and the left side of V1 contacted the right side of V2. The impact caused V2 to depart the roadway on the left side and the left side of V2 contacted the concrete barrier. Both vehicles came to rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling north in the first of two lanes on an undivided, two-way road approaching a three-legged intersection attempting to turn left. V2 was traveling east in the second of three lanes on a divided, two-way road approaching the same intersection. Within the intersection, the left side of V1 contacted the front of V2. Both vehicles came to rest within the intersection.
