V1 was traveling east in lane 2 on a 4 lane non-divided roadway approaching a traffic circle when V1 departed the roadway to the left and the left front tire contacted a curb. V1 continued to travel forward and the left front then left rear tires contacted another curb. V1 continued forward and entered the roadway where its front plane then undercarriage contacted the ground. As V1 departed the roadway again, its right front, left front then right rear tires contacted another curb. V1 traveled down an embankment and its front plane contacted a large mound of dirt. V1 then flipped onto its left side and came to rest facing northeast. A minor fire then occurred in the engine compartment.

V1 was traveling northeast on a one lane highway exit ramp curved to the right. As V1 was negotiating the curve, the left front tire experienced a tire failure. V1 lost control and departed the roadway to the left impacting a guardrail face with its frontal plane. V1 came to final rest on the shoulder facing northeast.

V1 was traveling southwest on a two way, two lane road, approaching a controlled four way intersection. V2 was traveling northeast on a two way, two lane road, approaching the same four way intersection. At the mentioned intersection, V1 attempted to turn left, in front of V2. The right side of V1 impacted the front of V2. V1 rotated clockwise, coming to rest in the roadway facing west. V2 came to final rest in the roadway, facing east.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 crossed over the left lane line then re-entered the original travel lane. V1 continued off the southern road edge. An unknown plane of V1 contacted the a ditch. V1 came to final rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway negotiating a right hand curve. V1 swerved left to avoid an animal in the road and crossed the left lane line. V1 then departed the left roads edge. The frontal plane of V1 contacted two trees with its front bumper, before rotating counterclockwise and rolling onto its right plane. V1 contacted a pole with its windshield while on its right side before coming to rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling north bound on a two lane, non-divided, bidirectional roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right, were the right side of the vehicle impacted a utility pole. Unit 1 then traveled down and embankment into a creek, where the vehicle rolled one quarter turn coming to final rest on its driver side in the creek.

V1 was traveling in a southern direction on a two lane, non-divided bidirectional roadway, with a negative grade. Road conditions at the time were snow covered and slippery. V1 lost control as it approached a curve to the left. V1 traveled off the roadway, where its frontal plane impacted a traffic delineator. V1 began to go down a steep embankment into a creek, in doing so, V1's front impacted an embankment. V1 rolled one quarter turn before impacting a small tree. V1 came to final rest on its passenger side in the creek.

V1 was traveling south through a four leg intersection. V2 was traveling west through the same four leg intersection. The frontal plane of V2 struck the left side plane of V1. Following the initial impact V1 rotated counterclockwise striking the left side plane of V2 with it's left side plane. V1 came to final rest off the southwest corner of the intersection heading northeast. V2 came to rest on the shoulder of the westbound lane heading north.

All vehicles were traveling south on a straight four lane divided (with positive barrier) highway. V1 and V2 were traveling in lane three. V3 was traveling in lane one and V4 was traveling in lane four. V2 was stopped in lane three due to backed up traffic. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. V1 crossed over the two lanes to its right and impacted V3's left side with its right side in a side swipe type impact. V1 came to rest in lane two facing south. V3 came to rest in lane one facing south. After the impact with V1, V2 rotated counter clockwise and partially entered lane four. The front of V2 impacted the right side of V4. V2 came to rest partially in lane three and partially in lane four, facing southeast. V4 came to rest in lane four, facing south.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 departed its lane to the left and then departed the left side of the roadway. V1 struck an embankment with its lower front, went airborne and began to rollover left side leading, four quarter turns. During the roll sequence V1 contacted a tree branch with the right side. V1 came to rest on its wheels facing north along the east road edge.

V1 was traveling north, in lane 1 of a 2 lane not physically divided roadway attempting to crossover an intersection. V2 was traveling west following a two-way, two lane road, approaching the same four way intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection at the same time. The front of V1 impacted the left side of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway, facing north.

V1 was exiting an interchange and pulling into lane 1 of southbound lanes. V2 and V3 were both traveling southbound in lane 1 of same roadway. V2's front contacted V1's back plane. V2 then came to a stop partially within the roadway. V3 left the roadway to the right. V3's left side contacted V2's right side. V1 and V2 came to rest within the roadway. V3 came to final rest off of the roadway.

Vehicle 2 was traveling south on a 5 lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 3 position  approaching an intersection. V1 was traveling east on a 3 lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 2 position approaching the same intersection attempting to turn left. V1 entered the intersection to turn left the front plane of V1 contacted the front of V2. V2 came to rest still facing south in original lane and V1 came to rest facing north/east just north of the intersection.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north in lane 1 on a two lane, one way roadway approaching an intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling west in lane 4 on a 4 lane, one way roadway approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection and the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V1 continued driving straight without stopping. V2 rotated counter-clockwise and came to rest in the roadway facing southwest.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a 3 lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1 position. V1 departed roadway right side. The front of V1 contacted a bush, and then a utility pole. V1 came to rest on the sidewalk facing south east.

V1 was traveling south down a two lane, two way, undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V1 departed the right road edge contacting the ground with its frontal plane. V1 came to final rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V2 was traveling south on the same roadway. V1 departed its lane to the left. The frontal plane of V1 came into contact with the frontal plane of V2. V1 and V2 came to final rest on the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south in lane one on a two lane, two-way roadway. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway on the right side and the right plane contacted a guardrail face. Vehicle 1 continued forward, returned to the roadway and came to final rest on the roadway facing south.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north on a two lane, two-way undivided roadway in lane one. Vehicle 1 traveled off the left side of the roadway where its left plane contacted a property marker. Vehicle 1 overturned and the right plane of Vehicle 1 contacted a tree. Vehicle 1 came to final rest on its roof, facing northeast.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south, in lane two on a six-lane two-way trafficway physically divided by a grass median and cable barrier. The front of Vehicle 1 contacted a deer in the roadway. Vehicle 1 came to final rest on the right shoulder facing south.

V1 was traveling southwest in lane two on a three lane, two way roadway and was making a left turn at an intersection to travel southeast. V2 was traveling southeast in lane two on a four lane divided roadway, and was passing through the same intersection. V3 was traveling northwest in lane four of a four lane, divided roadway, and was stopped in the left turn lane at the same intersection. Within the intersection, V1's front plane contacted V2's left side plane. This impact caused V2 to rotate counter clockwise and  V2's front plane contacted V1's rear plane. This impact caused V1 to cross over the median and contact V3's left side plane with its front plane. V1 came to final rest across the median perpendicular to the northbound travel lanes facing east. V2 came to final rest across the southbound travel lanes facing north, and V3 came to final rest in lane four in the northbound turn lane facing northwest.

V1 was traveling east on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a right hand curve in the roadway. V1 began to lose control and exited the right hand (southern) side of the roadway. V1 contacted an embankment with its frontal plane, began to rotate in a clockwise direction and then overturned left side leading. V1 rolled 3 quarter turns before coming to final rest off of the roadway.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane divided roadway in lane two. V1 departed the left road edge and the left side of V1 impacted a guardrail. V1 then continued back across both lanes and departed the right road edge where the front of V1 impacted a tree. V1  then rolled down an embankment right side leading two quarter turns. V1 came to rest on its roof facing west.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south in the number 2 lane on a two-way non-physically divided roadway. Vehicle 2 was traveling north on a two-way non-physically divided roadway in the number 2 lane. Vehicle 3 was traveling north on a two-way non-physically divided roadway in the number 1 lane. Vehicle 1's front end and  Vehicle 2's front end made contact with each other. Vehicle 1 continued forward and pushed  Vehicle 2 into Vehicle 3's left side. Vehicle 1 came to rest in the number 1 lane facing southeast.   Vehicle 2 came to rest in lane number 2 facing northeast. Vehicle 3 came to rest in lane number 1 facing northeast.

V1 was west bound on a two lane, non divided, bidirectional roadway, negotiating a curve to the left, passing through an intersection. V1 departed the roadway to the right, where its frontal plane impacted a utility pole. V1 rotated clockwise and came to final rest on the right side of the roadway.

V1 was east on a two lane, two way, undivided, rural roadway. V1 departed its initial travel lane to the left then departed the left side of the roadway. V1 impacted a ditch with the frontal plane causing damage. V1 then traveled down the length of the ditch before overturning left side leading four quarter turns. V1 came to final rest off the road on its wheels facing south east.
V1 and V2 were both in Lane 1 of a 2 lane roadway and heading southwest. V2 was behind V1. V2's front contacted V1's back of cargo area. Both vehicles came to rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling south on a one way, two lane highway. V1 lost control due to snow on the road and departed the left highway edge. V1 contacted a tree with an unknown plane. V1 came to final rest off the road way.

V1 was traveling northeast in lane one on a two lane, two way roadway. V2 was traveling southwest in lane one on the same roadway. V1 departed the lane to the left and the front of V1 contacted the front of V2. V1 continued to travel north and fled the scene. V2 came to final rest on the roadway facing south..

V1 was traveling east in lane two of a four lane undivided (one-way traffic) road. V2 was traveling in lane one of the same road into the same direction. V1 attempted to change its lane to the right, partially in front of V2. V2 steered to the left and impacted the back of V1 with its front. V1 rotated clockwise and came to rest in lane one, facing southeast. V2 rotated clockwise and came to rest partially in lane one and partially in lane two, facing east.

V1 was traveling south from a parking lot and was attempting to turn left. V2 was traveling east on a five lane undivided roadway in lane one. The front of V1 connected with the left of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest near the point of impact.

V1 was traveling north following a two-way, two-lane road. V2 was stopped in traffic on the same two-way, two-lane road, in front of V1. V3 was stopped in traffic, in front of V2 on the same two-way, two-lane road. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2 causing the front of V2 to impact the back of V3. All vehicles came to final rest at impact, on the roadway, facing north.

V1 was traveling south east in the #1 lane of a 2 lane divided roadway. V2 was traveling north east in the #1 lane of a 3 lane undivided roadway. Both vehicles entered an intersection. The right side of V1 impacted the front of V2. V1 rotated clockwise and traveled onto the center median. The left side of V1 impacted a bush. V1 continued sideways and the left side of V1 impacted another bush. V1 continued sideways where the left side of V1 impacted a pole. V1 came to rest facing south partially on the center median and partially in the #2 lane. V2 after impact with V1 rotated clockwise and came to rest facing east in the #2 lane of the south east bound roadway.

V1 was traveling south in the first of three lanes, on a divided, two-way roadway, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling east in the second of five lanes, on a divided, two-way roadway, approaching the same intersection. Within the intersection, the right side of V1 was contacted by the front of V2. V1 departed the southwest corner of the roadway and the front of V1 contacted a dense, tall weed patch, then its right side contacted a wood post. V1 came to rest in the field of weeds facing southwest. V2 rotated clockwise and came to rest in the intersection facing southeast.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a 4 lane median divided intersection in lane number 3. Vehicle 2 was traveling east on a 3 lane median divided traffic way approaching the same intersection in lane number 2. Vehicle 3 was stopped at the intersection  in lane number 1, facing north. V1 and V2 entered the intersection and the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V2 rotated counter-clockwise and departed the southeast corner where it rolled left 1-quarter turn. The top of V2 contacted a metal utility pole and V2 came to rest on its left side facing west. V1 rotated counter-clockwise as it moved forward and came to rest in the intersection facing southeast. During the crash events, the left rear tire of V2 was torn from the vehicle and the tire contacted the top of V3.

V1 was traveling south in lane one of a two-lane undivided roadway, turning left at an intersection. V2 was traveling west in lane one of a two-lane undivided roadway, turning right at the same intersection. The front plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway close to impact.

V1 was traveling west in lane one of a two lane roadway negotiating a right curve. V2 was traveling east on the same roadway approaching V1. V1 departed its travel lane to the left. The driver steered right overcorrecting and reenter it travel lane in a clockwise yaw. V1 tripped on the roadway and rolled left nine quarter turns departing the right road edge and contacting a fence and a tree before coming to rest against the tree. V2's driver steered right, avoided V1, departed the right road edge, and contacted a ditch before coming to rest off the right road edge.

Vehicle 1 was making a left turn from westbound travel lanes in lane 3 of a three lane roadway. Vehicle 2 was traveling through the intersection on the same roadway in the opposite direction in lane 2 of 3. Vehicle 1 contacted the left side plane of vehicle 2 with its frontal plane. Both vehicles came to rest in the roadway.

Vehicle 2 was stopped in the southbound travel lane of a two lane undivided roadway. Vehicle 1 was traveling in the same lane of the roadway and contacted its' frontal plane with the back plane of vehicle 2. Both vehicles came to rest on the roadway.

V1 was heading west on a five lane undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south on a two lane undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. V2 entered into the intersection to make a left turn. V1 also entered into the intersection to continued on its initial path of travel. The front of V1 connected with the left of V2. Both vehicles were redirected into the eastbound lanes where they came to final rest.

V1 was traveling north on a four lane undivided roadway in lane two. V2 was also traveling north on the same roadway in lane one. V1 departed its travel lane to the right. The front of V1 contacted the left of V2. V2 rotated counter-clockwise and the right side of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V2 came to rest in the roadway facing north. V1 departed the curb edge to the left where its left front and left rear tires contacted the curb. V1 continued forward off of the road and its front plane contacted a tree. V1 came to rest off of the road facing west.

V1 was traveling north on a two way, two lane road. V2 was traveling on the same two way, two lane roadway, in front of V1 at a slower speed. V3, V4, V5, V6, V7, and V8 were all legally parked on the right side of the roadway facing north. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2, pushing the right side of V2 into the left side of V3. Continuing forward, the front of V2 impacted the left side of V4. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2 again. The front of V2 then impacted the left side of V5. The back of V2 was impacted by the front of V1 again, before coming to final rest. V2 came to final rest in the roadway facing east. V1 continued forward, impacting the left side of V6 with its' frontal plane. The right side of V1 then impacted the left side of V7. Finally, the front of V1 impacted the left side of V8 before coming to final rest in the roadway facing north. V3, V4, V5, V6, V7, and V8 all came to final rest at impact, on the right side of the road, facing north.

V1 was traveling west on a two-way, three lane road in the first lane of travel. V2 was traveling west on the same two-way, three lane road, in front of V1. V3 was traveling on the same two-way, three lane road, in front of V2. V3 was slowing in traffic. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2 causing the front of V2 to impact the back of V3. All three vehicles came to final rest in the roadway near impact, all facing west.

V1 was eastbound, stopped at a four leg intersection. V2 was southbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway approaching the same 4 way stop intersection. In the intersection, V1's front contacted V2's right side. V1 and V2 both came to final rest in the middle on the intersection. V1 facing east V2 facing south.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway negotiating a left curve while approaching a three leg intersection, attempting to make a left hand turn. V2 was traveling west on the same roadway negotiating a right curve approaching the same intersection. The front of V1 contacted the front of V2. V1 rotated counter-clockwise as V2 rotated clockwise and continued forward where the left side of V1 was contacted by the front of V2. V1 came to rest in the northwest corner of the intersection facing south. V2 continued forward where it departed the right curb edge and contacted the curb with its left front tire. V2 continued forward and came to rest partially on the roadside and partially in the westbound lane facing west.

V1 was traveling northeast in lane one on a two lane, two way, roadway and was negotiating a curve to the left. V1 then departed the roadway to the right and traveled approximately 35 meters before it's front plane contacted a tree. V1 came to final rest at the tree.

V1 was traveling east in lane one of a three-lane divided roadway. As V1 entered and negotiated a right curved exit ramp, the vehicle departed the roadway to the left. The vehicle then crossed over a grass median, traveled through another off-ramp lane, and departed the roadway to the left a second time. After departing the roadway the second time, V1 contacted a guardrail face with its front plane. V1 then began a left leading roll, rotated two quarter turns, and came to final rest on its top in a southbound entrance ramp lane.

Vehicle 1 was southbound on a five-lane roadway approaching an intersection. Vehicle 2 was westbound on an intersecting five-lane roadway approaching the same intersection. The intersection was controlled by traffic signals. Both vehicles entered the intersection and the front of V2 struck the left side of V1. Subsequently, the left side of Vehicle 1 struck the right side of V2. V1 came to rest on the roadway, northwest of the intersection. Vehicle 2 came to rest west of the intersection on a grass median.

V1 was in traffic in the middle of the road, on the center painted median traveling southeast. V2 was exiting a shopping center facing northwest, entering a four-way intersection attempting to make a left turn. V1's front plane contacted V2's left plane. V1 and V2 came to final rest in the intersection on roadway.

V1 was traveling westbound on a two-lane, non-divided, two-way roadway. V1 departed the roadway on the right side where the front plane struck a pole. V1 came to final rest off the roadway facing south.

V1 was traveling westbound on a two-lane, non-divided roadway approaching a four way intersection with north and south lanes controlled by a stop sign. V2 was traveling northbound approaching the intersection. In the middle of the intersection the front plane of V1 contacted the right side of V2. After impact with V1, V2 continued off the roadway on the northwest corner where the front plane struck a utility pole.  V1 came to final rest partially in the roadway facing west and V2 came to final rest partially off the roadway facing northwest.

V1 was traveling south-east on a three lane undivided roadway approaching an intersection to make a left turn. V2 was traveling north-west on the same roadway approaching the intersection. V1 began its left turn. The front of V1 connected with the front of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest near the point of impact.

V1 was traveling north in lane 3 on a 4-lane divided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north in the same lane in front of V1 stopped at the intersection. The front of V1 contacted the back of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in the area of impact facing north.

V1 was traveling north in the third of seven lanes on an undivided, two-way roadway approaching a light controlled, four-legged intersection. V2 was traveling west in the second of three lanes on an undivided, two-way roadway attempting to turn left at the same intersection. V3 was stopped facing south in the fourth of seven lanes. V4 was stopped in the lane behind V3. V5 was stopped in the lane behind V4. V6 was stopped in the lane behind V5. Within the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. The right side of V1 then contacted the front of V3. V3 was pushed backward and the back of V3 contacted the front of V4. V4 was pushed backward and the back of V4 contacted the front of V5. Debris from the collisions contacted the front of V6. All six vehicles came to rest in the roadway.

V1 was westbound on a 2 lane roadway when V1 departed the roadway to the right and the front of V1 contacted 2 trees and a fence. V1 continued to travel and the undercarriage of V1 contacted a culvert. V1 then crossed a rock/gravel driveway before coming to rest.

Vehicle 1 was traveling eastbound on a 7 lane physically divided trafficway in the lane 4 position approaching an intersection to make a left hand turn.  Vehicle 2 was traveling westbound on a 7 lane physically divided trafficway in the lane 1 position approaching the same intersection to pass through.  As both vehicles entered the intersection, the right plane of Vehicle 1 made contact with the front plane of Vehicle 2.  After contact Vehicle 1 came to final rest facing north near the north side of the intersection.  Vehicle 2 rotated clockwise after impact coming to rest facing north also near the north side of the intersection.

V1 was traveling north on a 8 lane divided roadway in lane 2 approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling east on a 4 lane non-physically divided roadway in lane 2 approaching an intersection. As V1 was passing through the intersection V2 passed through at the same time and the front of V1 impacted the right side of V2. After the impact, V2 began rotating clockwise and rolled over one quarter turn before rolling back over onto its wheels. V1 came to rest in northbound lane 1 in the intersection facing south. V2 came to rest on its wheels in lane 2 of the westbound lanes facing east.

V1 was traveling westbound on a two lane undivided roadway approaching an intersection without traffic controls.  V2 was traveling northbound in lane one of the intersecting undivided four lane roadway. As V1 made a right turn at the intersection the front plane of V2 contacted the left plane of V1.  V1 came to final rest facing north in the intersection.  V2 came to final rest facing northwest in the intersection.

V1 was traveling westbound in the number 1 lane of a 5 lane divided interstate. V1 departed its lane to the right where the front of V1 impacted a guard rail face. V1 continued traveling along the guard rail and rotated counter-clockwise, coming to rest facing westbound on the north shoulder.

Vehicle 1 was westbound on a two way, two lane roadway turning left at a T intersection.  Vehicle 2 was northbound on a two way, two lane roadway traveling through the same intersection.  Vehicle 2 front plane struck the left plane of vehicle 1.  Vehicle 1 came to rest facing west in the roadway.  Vehicle 2 came to rest in the roadway facing north.

V1 was traveling northbound on a two lane undivided roadway.  V2 was legally parked against the right curb facing north. The front of V1 contacted the back plane of V2.  V1 then rotated clockwise, rolling over 2 quarter turns left. During the final quarter turn (onto roof), the top of V1 contacted a curb.  V1 came to rest facing north near curb impact. V2 remained facing north at final rest.

V1 was traveling north on a two-lane, two-way road that curved to the right. V1 departed the right side of the road where its right plane impacted a tree. V1 rotated clockwise and overturned one quarter turn onto its driver side. The top plane of V1 then impacted two trees and came to rest off of the right side of the road on its left plane, heading south.

V1 was traveling eastbound in the first lane of a three lane, one-way divided roadway. V2 was traveling eastbound, ahead of V1,in the same first lane of a three lane, one-way divided roadway. There was traffic slowing in the roadway. The frontal plane of V1 impacted the rear plane of V2. Both V1 and V2 were at final rest in the roadway facing east.

V1 was traveling northwest in the number 1 lane of a 2 lane divided interstate. V1 departed its lane to the left and continued off the roadway to the left. The front of V1 impacted a guard rail face.  V1  rotated counterclockwise and began to roll, right side leading.  V1 rolled over 1 quarter turn and came to rest on the right side, facing north in the roadway.

V1 was traveling east in lane one of a five-lane divided roadway, passing through an intersection. V2 was traveling northwest in lane two of a three-lane undivided roadway, turning left at the same intersection. The front plane of V1 contacted the left plane of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest in the intersection near impact.

Vehicle 1 was traveling southeast in lane 1 on a 5-lane roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling northeast in lane 1 on a 3-lane, one-way roadway approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection at the same time and the right side of V1 was contacted by the front of V2. V1 rotated counter-clockwise as V2 rotated clockwise and the right side of V1 contacted the left side of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in the intersection facing east.

Vehicle 1 was traveling westbound on a two lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position.  Vehicle 2 was traveling southbound on a two lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position.  Both Vehicles 1 and 2 entered the intersection at the same time.  The right plane of Vehicle 1 made contact with the left front corner of Vehicle 2.  The impact caused V1 to rotate counter clockwise slapping the right rear plane with the left rear plane of Vehicle 2.  Vehicle 2 continued through the intersection facing south at the southwest corner of the intersection.  Vehicle 1 continued to rotate counter clockwise coming to rest facing east at the south east corner of the intersection.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane, non-divided, bidirectional roadway negotiating a slight curve to the right. V2 was traveling west on the same roadway approaching V1's location. V1 departed its lane to the left, crossing into V2's path of travel, where V1's frontal plane impacted V2's frontal plane. V1 came to final rest on the north side of the roadway. V2 came to final rest in its lane of travel.

V1 and V2 were traveling westbound on a four lane, divided roadway in lane three approaching an intersection. V2 was stopped at the intersection ahead of V1. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2. Both vehicles came to rest facing westbound in lane three.

V1 was traveling westbound on a two lane, divided roadway in lane one. V1 departed the roadway to the right and the front right tire of V1 impacted a raised curb. The back right tire then impacted the same curb. V1 continued off road and the front of V1 impacted the end of a metal guardrail. V1 rotated clockwise and came to rest facing northwest.

V1 was travelling west bound on lane 1 of a 2 lane, two-way, not physically divided roadway. V2 was traveling east bound on the same 2 lane, two-way, not physically divided roadway. V1 departed lane of travel to the left attempting to enter a parking lot adjacent to the edge of pavement. V1 front plane contacted V2 front plane.

V1 was traveling west bound on lane 1 of a 2 lane, two-way, not physically divided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north bound on lane 1 of a 2 lane, two-way, not physically divided roadway approaching the same intersection. V1 and V2 both enter the intersection  at the same time. V1 left plane contacted V2 front plane.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane, undivided roadway, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling west on a four lane, undivided roadway, approaching the same intersection. V1 turned right at the intersection, and the left side of V1 contacted the front of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane, undivided roadway, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling east on a three lane, undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection. The right of V1 contacted the front of V2. V1 came to final rest on the roadway. V2 proceeded to depart the roadway to the southeast section of the intersection. The left front tire contacted a curb, then the front contacted a pole, and came to final rest.

V1 was traveling east in lane four of a eight lane divided roadway, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling west in lane five of the same roadway, turning left at the same intersection. The front plane of V1 contacted the right plane of V2. V2 rotated clockwise and the right plane of V1 was then contacted by the front plane of V2. V1 came to final rest past the point of impact facing east. V2 came to final rest on the roadway facing northwest.

V1 and V2 were westbound on a two lane freeway interchange roadway approaching a fork in the road. V1 departed its lane to the right and the right side of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V1 continued to travel and did not come to rest. After contact, V2 departed the roadway to the left and the front of V2 contacted a pole. V2 then rotated clockwise and the right side of V2 contacted a concrete barrier before coming to rest off the roadway.

Vehicle1 was traveling west on a 7 lane, two way, median divided roadway in lane 1 position attempting to make a right hand turn at an intersection. Vehicle 1 spun 180 degrees while turning and the left side of V1 contacted a curb edge with the left side. Vehicle 1 was facing south at impact and came to final rest with the rear of V1 on top of the curb and facing south.

V1 was traveling southbound on a 2 lane roadway. V1 left the roadway to the right. V1's front contacted the face of a guard rail. V1 continued forward along the guard rail before rolling to its left back onto the roadway. V1 came to rest on it's left side in the roadway.

V1 was stopped on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway facing north. V2 was traveling north on the same two way, two lane, undivided roadway approaching V1 from behind. The front plane of V2 made contact with the left side plane of V1. V1 came to final rest on the roadway. V2 continued forward crossing the left lane line and came to final rest off the left hand (northwest) side of the roadway

V1 was traveling north on a two lane undivided road negotiating a left curve.  As V1 was negotiating a curve, a bear entered its lane of travel. V1 left the roadway to the left, where it rolled over, coming to final rest on its left side.

V1 was traveling south, negotiating a slight curve to the left, on a two lane, non divided roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right, where it's right side impacted a guardrail face. V1 returned to the roadway, crossing both lanes of travel and departed the left side of the roadway. V1 impacted the guardrail face on the left side of the roadway with its frontal plane. V1 came to final rest partial on the roadway in the north bound lane facing south.

V1 was traveling east on a non-physically divided two lane road in lane one negotiating a curve to the right. V1 drove off the south road edge and rolled right down an embankment four quarter turns.  During the rollover the undercarriage of V1 impacted a wire fence.  V1 came to rest on its wheels at the bottom of the embankment facing east.

V1 was traveling east on a divided trafficway (median strip without positive barrier), in lane 1 (of two lanes), in the rain. V1 hydroplaned on the wet roadway surface, and control over V1 was lost. V1 skidded laterally in a counter-clockwise rotation and departed the road on the left, where it overturned (6 quarter turns, leading right). V1 came to rest on its roof facing a northerly direction in the median strip.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west negotiating a left curve, on a two-way, not physically divided roadway in lane 1. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway to the right and vehicle 1's front made contact with a fire hydrant.  Vehicle 1 came to rest at the fire hydrant, facing south.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north on a two-way in lane number 1 intending to turn left.  Vehicle 2 was traveling south on a  4 lane median divided intersection in lane number 2. Vehicle 1's right side and vehicle 2's  front made contact with each other in the intersection. Vehicle 1 came to rest facing north west in it's original lane. Vehicle 2 came to final rest facing south in it's original lane.

V1 was traveling northeast in lane two of a four lane divided roadway. V2 was traveling northeast in lane one ahead of V1. V1 came beside V2 then attempted a lane change to its right. V1's right plane contacted V2's left plane. V1 departed the roadway to the right to final rest. V2 departed the roadway to the left into the median and came to final rest.
V1 was traveling southeast in lane two of a four-lane divided roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the left and it's front plane contacted a tree. V1 came to final rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling southwest in lane one of a three-lane undivided roadway, passing through an intersection. V2 was traveling northwest in lane one of a four-lane undivided roadway, passing through the same intersection. The front plane of V1 contacted the right plane of V2. The impact caused V2 to rotate clockwise, coming to final rest in the roadway, facing southeast. V1 came to final rest also in the roadway.

V1 was traveling northwest negotiating a left curve. V1 departed the right road edge, the driver steered left and over corrected causing V1 to depart the left road edge. V1 tripped and rolled left four quarter turns coming to final rest on its wheels off the left road edge.

V1 was traveling southeast turning left into a driveway from the left turn lane of a three lane, two way, roadway with a left turn lane. V2 was traveling northwest on the same roadway. V2 was driving on the shoulder passing vehicles that were stopped in the northwest bound lane. The frontal plane of V2 struck the right side plane of V1. V1 came to rest heading north in the driveway. V2 came to rest heading north in the driveway.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V2 was traveling east on the same roadway. V1 attempted to make a left turn into a driveway and crossed paths with V2. The frontal plane of V1 contacted the frontal plane of V2. V1 and V2 came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling northeast on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. A deer entered the southern road edge and crossed paths with V1. the frontal plane of V1 contacted he deer. V1 came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling south on a two-way, three lane road with a two way left turning lane in the middle. V2 was slowing in traffic in front of V1 on the same two-way, three lane road. V3 was stopped on the same roadway in front of V2. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2. The impact caused the front of V2 to impact the back of V3. All the three vehicles came to final rest in the roadway facing south.

V1 was traveling east following a two way, three lane road with a two way left turning lane in the middle. V2 was traveling north on a two way, three lane driveway, in the first lane of travel. V2 was attempting to turn right from the driveway onto the same roadway V1 was traveling on. The front of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V1 rotated clockwise after impact. Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway; V1 facing west and V2 facing southwest.

V1 was traveling west in lane two of a four-lane divided roadway attempting to negotiate a right curve. V1 departed it's travel lane to the left, crossed over both eastbound lanes, and then departed the roadway to the left. V1's front plane contacted a pole, shearing the pole. V1 continued to travel off the roadway in a clockwise yaw. V1's left plane contacted a tree. V1 continued to travel before coming to final rest off the roadway facing northeast.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east in lane four of a seven lane, two way, not physically divided roadway with two way left turn lane, intending to turn left. Vehicle 2 was traveling west on the same roadway, in lane one. The front of Vehicle 2 contacted the right side of Vehicle 1. As the vehicles rotated after impact, the right side of Vehicle 1 contacted the right side of Vehicle 2. After the secondary impact, Vehicle 2 continued forward to final rest, still facing west. Vehicle 1 came to rest facing northeast, just west of impact.

V1 and V2 were heading north on a three lane interstate roadway with a positive barrier. V2 began to slow for traffic ahead. The front of V1 contacted the rear of V2,. Both vehicles came to final rest near the point of impact.

Vehicle #1 was traveling north in lane one of a two-lane, divided roadway without a positive barrier.  The front of V1 contacted an animal. The animal then contacted the right side of the vehicle after the initial impact. V1 came to rest near impact.

Vehicle 1 was traveling northeast, in lane three of a three-lane divided highway. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway on the left side and contacted a cable barrier with its front and left side. Vehicle 1 continued forward, returned to the roadway, crossed all three lane and departed the roadway on the right side. It traveled up an embankment before coming to final rest off the roadway facing east.

V1 was traveling north in the #1 lane of a 3 lane one way road. V2 was traveling north in the #2 lane of a 3 lane one way road. V1 and V2 entered into an intersection. V1 attempted to turn left. The left side of V1 impacted the right side of V2. V2 veered left and departed the roadway to the left. The front of V2 impacted a curb. V1 came to rest facing north west in the middle of the intersection. V2 continued north and came to rest facing north off the roadway.

V1 was traveling southbound on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a left hand curve in the roadway. V1 departed the left hand lane line, returned to their initial travel lane, and then began to rotate in a clockwise direction before departing the right (west) side of the roadway. V1 rolled four quarter turns with its left side leading before contacting a utility pole with its left side plane. V1 came to final rest off of the roadway.

V1 was heading west on a five-lane undivided roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right. The front of V1 contacted a tree. V1 continued on its path of travel. The front of V1 contacted a second tree. V1 reentered the roadway while rotating clockwise. V1 came to final rest facing northeast in the road.

Vehicles 1 was  traveling west on a two-way, 4 lane, physically divided roadway in lane number 4. Vehicle 2,3,4 and 5 were all traveling west on the same roadway stopped in traffic. Vehicle 1's front end made contact with vehicle 2's rear end. V2 was pushed forward and the front of V2 contacted the rear of V3.  Vehicle 4's front end made contact with vehicle 5's rear end. All 5 vehicles came to final rest in their original lanes.

V1, V2, and V3 were traveling south west in the #2 lane of a 4 lane divided highway. V3 and V2 came to a stop due to traffic. V3 started to move forward slowly. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2. V2 was pushed forward and the front of V2 impacted the back of V3. V1 came to rest facing south west in the #2 lane behind V2. V2 came to rest facing south west between V1 and V3 in the #2 lane. V3 came to rest facing south west in the #2 lane in front of V2.

V1 was traveling northwest in lane two on three lane, divided roadway and was approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling west in lane two on a two lane off ramp, and was turning left at an intersection to travel southeast on another roadway. At the intersection, V1's front plane contacted V2's left side plane. Both vehicles came to final rest in the intersection.

V1 & V2 were both traveling south in lane one on a two lane, positively divided roadway, and were approaching a controlled intersection. V2 began to slow for the traffic signal ahead when V1's front plane contacted V2's rear plane. This impact caused V2 to rotate in a clockwise direction and depart the roadway on the right side. V2 then struck an embankment with it's front plane, climbed the embankment, and began a left side leading rollover. V2 rolled over two quarter turns and came to final rest on it's roof, laying perpendicular to the roadway in lane 1. V2's front plane was partially off of the roadway, it's back plane was in the roadway, and it was located approximately 27 meters from the initial impact. After the initial impact with V2, V1 rotated in a clockwise direction and began a left side leading rollover. The vehicle then rolled one quarter turn onto it's left side plane before coming to final rest in lane 2. V1's final rest position was perpendicular to the roadway and was approximately 27 meters

Vehicle 1 was traveling south in lane three of a physically divided roadway. Vehicle 2 was traveling south, in lane one, ahead of vehicle 1 on the same roadway. Vehicle 1 experienced a right front tire failure, departed lanes three and two to its right. The right plane of vehicle 1 then contacted the left plane of vehicle 2. Upon impact vehicle 1 rotated counterclockwise, continued forward and came to final rest on the left shoulder facing south. Vehicle 2 rotated clockwise, continued forward and came to final rest on the right shoulder facing south.

V1 was traveling westbound on a four-lane, two-way roadway approaching an intersection controlled by a traffic light. V2 was traveling northbound on a two-lane, two-way roadway approaching the mentioned intersection. In the intersection the front plane of V1 contacted the right side of V2. After impact V2 rolled over two quarter turns and came to final rest facing east on its roof. V2 came to final rest in the roadway facing west.

Vehicles #1 and #2 were traveling northwest on a three-lane divided road, approaching an intersection. V2 came to a stop at the intersection. The front plane of V1 contacted the back plane of V2. Both vehicles came to rest on the road.

Vehicle 1 was traveling eastbound on a five lane physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position.  Vehicle 1 was negotiating a right curve.  The front plane of the vehicle made contact with a raised curb.  Vehicle 1 traveled across a raised curb median before entering back onto a north directional roadway.  Vehicle 1 continued across this roadway, again, making contact with its front plane to a raised curb.  Vehicle 1 began to travel up an embankment making contact with the embankment to the undercarriage.  Vehicle 1 then glanced off a utility pole.  After traveling across a grassy area, Vehicle 1 came to final rest facing east.

V1 was traveling south in lane 3 on a 4-lane divided roadway approaching an intersection to turn left. V2 was traveling on the same roadway in lane 4 next to V1 intending to turn left. As both vehicles began to turn left, the left side of V1 contacted the right side of V2. V1 continued traveling without stopping. V2 cam to rest in the intersection facing east.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a 4 lane, two way, median divided traffic way in lane 1 position approaching a roundabout intersection. V2 was traveling west on a 4 lane, two way, median divided traffic way in lane 2 position entering the roundabout to travel south. Both vehicles entered the west side of the roundabout's intersection. The unknown plane of V1 contacted the right side of V2 Both vehicles came to rest facing south at the sound end of the roundabout.

V1 was northbound on a two way, 2 lane, undivided roadway approaching a 4 way intersection. V2 was on a two way, 2 lane, undivided roadway, approaching the same intersection. Within the intersection the front of V1 contacted the right side of V2, both vehicles came to rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling north in in lane 2 on a 2- lane divided roadway. V2 was traveling north in the same lane ahead of V1. V3 was traveling north in the same lane ahead of V2. The front of V1 contacted the back of V2. The front of V2 then contacted the back of V3. All three vehicles came to rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling west in the #1 lane of a 2 lane undivided roadway. V2 and V3 were parked on the south shoulder facing east. V1 impacted a center median curb. V1 began to rotate counter clockwise and departed the road to the left. The front of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V1 continued west where the front of V1 impacted the front of V3. V3 was pushed back into another parked vehicle and traveled off the road south. V1 continued rotating counter clockwise and the right side of V1 impacted the back of V3. V1 continued west and the front of V1 impacted a tree. V1 rotated clockwise where the left side of V1 impacted the base of a light pole. V1 came to rest facing south with the front against a tree and the left side against a light pole base. V2 came to rest on the south shoulder facing east. V3 came to rest facing south off the road.

V1 was traveling east in the #1 lane of a 5 lane undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north in the #2 lane of a 3 lane undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection proceeding straight and the front of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V1 continued north east and came to rest facing north in the westbound travel lane. V2 rotated clockwise and came to rest facing south in the #1 lane of the roadway partially on the shoulder.

V1 was traveling northeast in the number 2 lane of a 3 lane divided roadway, in a right turn only lane. V1 was approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling westbound in the number 3 lane of a 5 lane divided roadway, approaching an intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection proceeding straight. The front of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V2 rotated counter-clockwise after the impact and came to rest facing west on the northwest side of the intersection. V1 came to rest facing north in the intersection.

Vehicle #1 was traveling northeast on a two-lane, two-way road. Vehicle #2 was traveling southwest on the same road. V2 began to turn left into a parking lot. V1 departed its lane to the left and the front plane of V1 contacted the right plane of V2.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a three lane, two-way, undivided, left curving roadway.  Vehicle 2 was traveling east on the same roadway.  Vehicle 1 lost control and began a clockwise rotation while crossing the center line.  The front of Vehicle 2 impacted the left side of Vehicle 1.  After impact, Vehicle 1 rolled two quarter turns, landing on its roof at final rest facing northwest in the middle of the roadway.  Vehicle 2 came to rest off the south shoulder, still facing east.

V1 was eastbound on a 4 lane physically divided roadway in lane 1. V1 departed the roadway to the right and the front of V1 contacted a cement traffic barrier then the right side of V1 contacted the same cement traffic barrier. As V1 continued to travel it crossed all 4 travel lanes the the left and the front of V1 contacted a cement traffic barrier and finally the left side of V1 contacted the same cement traffic barrier. V1 came to rest on the roadway.

V2 was traveling northwest in the first of three lanes on an undivided, two-way roadway. V1 was traveling southwest entering the roadway from a driveway attempting to turn left. The left side of V1 contacted the front of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in the roadway

V1 was traveling south on a 1- lane divided roadway approaching an intersection to turn left. V2 was traveling west in lane 1 on a 4-lane roadway approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection and the left side of V1 was contacted by the front of V2. V1 rotated counter-clockwise and came to rest on the eastbound shoulder facing west. V2 continued forward and came to rest on the westbound shoulder facing west.

V1, V2, and V3 were all westbound in the same lane of a 3-lane undivided road. V3 was the lead vehicle, stopped at a four-legged intersection. V2 was the middle vehicle decelerating behind V3. V1 was the trailing vehicle when its front struck the back of V2. Subsequently, the front of V2 struck the back of V3. All three vehicles came to final rest in the same lane facing west.

V1 was traveling in a north western direction on a two lane, non divided, bidirectional roadway, approaching an intersection. V1 traveled through the intersection, where it departed the roadway to the left, where its frontal plane impacted a ditch. V1's left plane then impacted the ground. V1 came to final rest on the left side of the roadway.

V1 was traveling northeast in the number 3 lane of a 4 lane roadway, preparing to turn left at an intersection. V1 began to turn left and departed the roadway to the right where the front of V1 impacted a curb. V1 continued to turn left off the roadway and began traveling northerly  where the front of V1 impacted a pole. V1 came to rest against the pole facing northerly.

V1 was traveling northeast in lane one of a two-lane undivided roadway. V2 was traveling southwest, negotiating a curve, in lane one of the same roadway. V1 departed it's travel lane to the left to avoid a non-contact vehicle that was stopping to turn left. V1's front plane contacted V2's front plane. V1 came to rest partially on the roadway. V2 departed the roadway and it's front plane contacted a ditch before coming to final rest in the ditch.

V1 was traveling southbound on a two lane non divided road (two way traffic) in lane one. V1 departed the roadway to the right and the front of V1 impacted an embankment of a private driveway. After impact the V1 climbed the embankment and rotated counter clockwise and came to rest facing east in the private driveway.

V1 and V2 were both traveling northbound on a 4 lane undivided road with two way turn lane in lane 1 approaching a private drive to the east. V1 was traveling ahead of V2. V1 swung wide to the left to turn right into the private drive. The front of V2 impacted the right side of V1. Both vehicles came to rest in the private drive V1 facing east and V2 facing northeast.

Vehicles 1 and 2 were both traveling south in lane two of a two-lane divided highway. V2 was slowing ahead of V1 as it approached a crossover. The front of V1 struck the back of V2 and both vehicles came to rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling east on an eight lane divided without positive barrier roadway in lane four. To avoid debris in the road the driver steered right and moved into lane three.  The driver lost control of the vehicle and departed the eastbound lanes to the left through the median break in a right rotation.  V1 then crossed all of the westbound lanes and departed the south edge of the road with the right plane striking a guardrail end.  V1 rotated clockwise and traveled down an embankment where the left plane struck a tree coming to final rest off the road.

V1 was traveling northbound on a two lane, two-way roadway in lane one. V1 veered to the right side roadway, V1's front plane contacted V2's back plane. V2 was legally parked facing northbound and unoccupied at time of impact. V1 came to final rest at point of impact.

V1 was traveling in a southeasterly direction on a designated east west not physically divided roadway in lane 1 (of five lanes) and was approaching V2, which was traveling in a northwesterly direction on the same roadway in lane 2 (of five lanes). V1 departed and was returned from the road on the right. Control over V1 was lost and it began to rotate counterclockwise. V1 entered lane 4, in the path of V2, and the front end of V2 contacted the back end of V1. V2 then departed the road on the right where it overturned (3 quarter turns, leading left). V1 came to rest on its wheels facing a northwesterly direction in lane 3. V2 came to rest on its right side facing a westerly direction on the roadside.

V1 was traveling northbound in the third lane of a three lane, one-way roadway, approaching a controlled intersection. V2 was traveling northbound, ahead of V1, in the same lane. V2 stopped for the controlled intersection. The frontal plane of V1 impacted the rear plane of V2. Both V1 and V2 came to final rest in the roadway facing north.

V1 was traveling north while negotiating a left curve on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 departed the right side of the roadway while rotating clockwise and contacted the side of a ditch with its left side. V1 then tripped and rolled left 3-quarter turns and came to rest on its right side facing east in a grass field.

V1 was traveling north in lane one on a two lane, two way, non-divided roadway and was negotiating a right curve. V1 departed the curb edge on the right side where its right front wheel, left front wheel, undercarriage and left rear wheel contacted the curb. The front of V1 then contacted an embankment then a small tree.  V1 traveled down the embankment and came to rest partially on the roadway facing northwest.

V1 and V2 were traveling east on a two way, two lane undivided roadway negotiating a right hand curve in the roadway. V2 was behind V1. V1 began slowing and stopped in the roadway. The frontal plane of V2 made contact with the rear plane of V1. V1 came to final rest on the roadway facing east. V2 came to final rest partially off the roadway facing southeast.

V1 was traveling west bound in lane 1 of a 2 lane, two-way, not physically divided roadway approaching an intersection to make a left turn. V2 was traveling north bound in lane 1 of a 2 lane, two-way, not physically divided roadway approaching the same intersection. V1 and V2 entered the intersection simultaneously. V1 left plane made contact with V2 front plane. The vehicles then sideslapped, with the left side of V1 impacting the right side of V2.  V1 then departed the roadway at the northwest corner and the front of V1 impacted landscape bushes, where it came to rest.  V2 came to rest facing west.

V1 was traveling south on a 2-lane roadway decelerating as it approached an intersection. V2 was traveling east on a 2-lane intersecting roadway. V2 departed its roadway to the left where its front plane contacted a guy wire. V2 continued forward, entered the southbound roadway and its front plane contacted the right side of V1. V1 rotated counter-clockwise as V2 continued forward and the right side of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V1 departed the northeast corner of the intersection and came to rest facing east. V2 departed the northeast corner of the intersection and came to rest facing east.

V1 was traveling east on a four lane divided by a painted median roadway in lane two.  V2 was traveling on the same roadway headed west in the westbound lane two.  The front of V1 contacted the front of V2.  V1 rotated clockwise to final rest facing south in lane two of the westbound side.  V2 rotated counterclockwise to final rest facing south beside V1.

V1 and V2 were traveling north on a two-lane, undivided (two way) roadway in lane one. V2 was traveling ahead of V1. V2 slowed to turn left into a private drive. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2. V2 rotated counter clockwise and came to rest facing northwest. V1 departed the roadway and came to rest facing north.

V1 and V3 were traveling westbound in the number 2 lane of a 4 lane divided roadway. V1 was traveling to the rear of V3. V2 was traveling westbound in the number 3 lane of a 4 lane divided roadway. V1 departed the lane to the left where the left side of V1 impacted the right side of V2. V1 then steered back to the right where the right side of V1 impacted the left side of V3. V1 then rolled over onto its roof and came to rest facing west, blocking the number 2 and number 3 lane. V2 came to rest facing west in the number 3 lane. V3 came to rest facing west in the number 2 lane.

V1 was traveling south west in the #1 lane of a 3 lane divided roadway. V2 was traveling north east in the #3 lane of a 3 lane divided roadway. V1 was traveling straight through an intersection. V2 was turning left in the intersection. The front of V1 impacted the right of V2. V1 rotated clockwise and V2 rotated counter clockwise. The left side of V1 impacted the right side of V2. V1 rotated clockwise slightly and came to rest facing west north of the intersection in the #1 lane of the southbound road. V2 rotated counter clockwise and came to rest facing south west on the north shoulder.

V1 was traveling eastbound in the number 3 lane of a 5 lane divided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling southbound in the number 1 lane of a 4 lane divided roadway approaching an intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection. The left side of V1 impacted the front of V2. V1 continued forward and to the south after the collision and came to rest east of the intersection facing eastbound, partially on the curb. V2 rotated counter-clockwise after impacting V1 and came to rest facing northeast within the intersection.

V1 was traveling north east negotiating a right curve. V2 was traveling south west negotiating a left curve. V1 attempted to turn left at an intersection. V2 traveled through the intersection. The front of V1 impacted the front of V2. V1 was pushed backwards and rotated counter clockwise and came to rest facing north in the middle of the roadway. V2 traveled west off the roadway to the north and came to rest facing west partially on the roadway.

V1 and V2 were both traveling westbound, on a 3 lane roadway, with 2 way turn lane. Both vehicles were in lane 1 and V1 was traveling behind V2. V2 was stopped. V1's front contacted V2's rear. Both vehicles came to rest on the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling northbound on a two lane non-physically divided roadway approaching a four way intersection.  Vehicle 2 was westbound on a two lane non-physically divided roadway approaching the same intersection.  As both vehicles entered the intersection proceeding straight, the front of V2 contacted the right side of V1.  Vehicle 1 came to final rest just north of the intersection facing north.  Vehicle 2 rotated clockwise coming to rest facing north west at the north east corner of the intersection.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway, making a left turn at a four leg intersection. V2 was traveling south on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway, passing through the same four leg intersection. The frontal plane of V2 struck the left side plane of V1. V1 came to rest north of the intersection, heading north, in the northbound lane. V2 came to rest south of the intersection, heading south, in the southbound lane.

V1 was traveling north, negotiating a right curve, and approaching a T intersection . V1 departed its travel lane to the left and then departed the left side of the roadway. Upon departing the roadway V1 impacted an embankment with its frontal plane. V1 continued off the roadway striking another embankment with its frontal plane. V1 continued traveling north, crossed over the east west direction roadway, traveled straight off the north side of the roadway, and came to rest heading north off the roadway.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a four lane, two-way roadway in lane one. V1 departed the roadway on the right side, where it struck a utility pole with it's front plane before come to final rest at point of impact off-roadway.

V1 and V2 were both traveling north on a three-lane, positively divided two-way roadway. V1 was in the second lane and V2 was in the first lane. V1 began to rotate clockwise, departed the lane on the right side and the right side of V1 contacted the left side of V2.  V1 continued to yaw clockwise and departed the roadway to the right.  The left side of V1 impacted a concrete bridge wall.  V1 continued to rotate clockwise and the right side of V1 impacted a guardrail.  V1 came to rest facing north with its right plane against the guardrail.  V2 was redirected off the roadway to the right and the front of V2 impacted a guardrail.  V2 rotated clockwise and came to rest facing southeast with the front plane against the guardrail.

V1 was traveling westbound in the first lane of a two lane, two-way, undivided roadway, behind V2. V2 was traveling westbound, ahead of V1, traveling in the first lane of the same two lane, two-way, undivided roadway, as V1. V2 stopped in the roadway in an attempt to turn right into a parking lane. V1 attempted to go pass V2 on the right side. The frontal plane of V1 sideswiped the right side plane of V2. Both V1 and V2 came to final rest in the roadway: V1 was facing west and V2 was facing northwest.

Vehicle 1 was eastbound on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway, negotiating a curve to the right. Vehicle 1 crossed the center, over correcting right, and then back left.  Vehicle 1 rotated counter clockwise across the roadway.  Vehicle 1 departed the roadway to the left. Vehicle 1 front plane struck the ground.  Vehicle 1 rolled one quarter turn onto its right side.  Vehicle 1 came to rest facing west on the roadside.

V1 was traveling northeast on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 began in a clockwise yaw and departed the roadway on the right side.   An unknown plane of V1 contacted a snowbank and came to final rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling North on a physically divided two lane highway in lane one. V2 was also traveling North on a physically divided two lane highway in lane two, ahead of V1. V1 began to switch lanes into lane two when the left rear contacted the right front of V2. V1 then crossed into the center divider where the front left corner impacted the jersey barrier. V1's momentum caused V1's left rear corner to impact the jersey barrier. V1 then crossed over both northbound lanes while rotating clockwise 180 degrees, where V1 came to rest on the dirt shoulder, facing a southerly direction. V2 came to rest on the left shoulder facing north.

V2 was traveling east in lane two,on a two way, four lane trafficway divided by a median cable guardrail. V1 was traveling east in lane two of the same trafficway, following V2. The frontal plane of V1 struck the rear plane of V2. V2 came to rest on the right shoulder heading east. V1 came to rest in the grass median heading east

V1 was traveling northeast through a four leg intersection on a two way, three lane roadway, with a left turn lane. V2 was traveling northwest through the same four leg intersection on a two way, two lane roadway. The frontal plane of V1 struck the left side plane of V2. V1 right side then contacted V2 left side as the vehicle traveled to final rest.  V1 came to rest on the right shoulder headed northeast. V1 came to rest off the roadway on the northeast side of the intersection.

V1 was west bound on a two lane, non divided, bidirectional roadway, when the left front wheel fell off. When this happened, the left front wheel impacted the left side, and the undercarriage impacted the roadway. V1 came to final rest on the right side of the roadway, partially blocking the west bound lane of travel

Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a 6 lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1 position approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north on a 6 lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway in the lane 4 position approaching the same intersection to make a left turn. Both vehicles entered the intersection. The front of V1 contacted the right side of V2. V1 came to rest still facing south at the south west corner of the intersection. V2 came to rest facing south west just on the west side of the intersection.

V1 was traveling northbound on a two-lane, two-way roadway. V1 departed the roadway on the right side where the front plane contacted the face of a guardrail. V1 rotated clockwise and came to final rest in the roadway facing south.

Vehicle #1 was traveling east in lane one of a two-lane, undivided roadway.  The front of V1 contacted a deer.  The deer rotated clockwise and contacted the right plane of V1.  V1 came to rest near impact, facing east.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west in lane one on a two-lane, undivided roadway.  Vehicle 2 was traveling east in eastbound lane one on the same roadway.  V1 departed its lane to the left and the front of V1 contacted the front of V2.  V1 and V2 both began to rotate counterclockwise.  V1 came to rest still in its lane, facing northwest.  V2 departed the road to the right.  V2 came to rest off the road to the south, facing northwest.

V1 was traveling south in the #3 lane of a 3 lane divided roadway. V2 was traveling north in the #2 lane of a 3 lane divided roadway. V1 departed its roadway to the left where it contacted a raised median with its LF tire. V1 then entered the other roadway where its front impacted the front of V2. V1 rotated counter clockwise and came to rest facing east in the #3 lane. V2 was pushed back and came to rest facing north in the #2 lane.

V1 was traveling westbound in the number 2 lane of a 3 lane undivided roadway, preparing to turn left at an intersection. V2 was traveling eastbound in the number 1 lane of a 3 lane undivided roadway, approaching an intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection. The right side of V1 impacted the front of V2. V1 rotated counter-clockwise and southerly coming to rest facing south in the intersection. V2 rotated clockwise and southerly and came to rest facing southerly in the intersection, west of V1.

V1 was traveling eastbound in the number 1 lane of a 2 lane undivided roadway, behind a non-collision vehicle. V2 was traveling westbound in the number 1 lane of a 2 lane undivided roadway. V1 departed its lane to the left to overtake the non-collision vehicle. The front of V1 impacted the left of V2. V1 continued along the left side of V2 and came to rest facing eastbound in-between the number 1 and 2 lanes, to the east of V2. V2 came to rest facing westerly in the number 1 lane, west of V1.

V1 was traveling west on a two-way, two lane undivided roadway, approaching a traffic signal controlled intersection. V2 was traveling north, on a median divided roadway, with four lanes in the same direction, approaching the same intersection as V1. Both vehicles entered the intersection. The frontal plane of V2 contacted the left side plane of V1. V1 continued forward rotating in a clockwise direction and came to final rest partially off the southbound roadway. V2 continued forward and came to final rest on the roadway.
V1 was traveling north in lane 1 on a two lane, grass median divided roadway. The front of V1 contacted a deer in the road. V1 came to final rest on the road facing north.
V1 was traveling southeast on a two lane, grass median divided roadway. The front of V1 contacted a deer in the road. V1 came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling south in lane one of a five-lane divided roadway, negotiating a curve. V2 and V3 were pulled off the roadway, with V2 (a police vehicle) having emergency response lights activated, with V3 ahead of V2. V1 departed it's travel lane to the right and it's front plane contacted the back plane of V2. V1 continued forward and its front plane contacted V2's left plane. V2 was pushed forward by the impact and it's front plane contacted V3's back plane. V1 and V2 then went down an embankment, where V1's front plane contacted shrubbery and V2's front plane contacted a tree. Both came to final rest down the embankment. V3 came to final rest close to impact with V2.
V1 was traveling northwest in lane one of a two lane roadway. V1 departed the right road edge and the front plane contacted a pole. V1 came to final rest at impact.

V1 was traveling east on a single lane off-ramp, negotiating a right curve. V1 began to skid longitudinally and departed the roadway to the left. V1's left side contacted a guardrail. V1 then returned to the roadway and came to final rest on the opposite shoulder past the point of impact.

V1 was traveling west in lane one of a two lane divided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south in lane one of a two lane roadway approaching the same intersection. V1's right plane contacted V2's front plane. V1 rotated clockwise and departed the left road edge into the median. V1's left plane contacted two signs and a pole. V1 then reentered the travel lane then departed the right road edge and the front plane contacted a pole were it came to rest. V2 rotated clockwise and the LR wheel contacted the curb were it came to rest.

V1 traveling east bound on lane 1 of a 2 lane, two-way, not physically divided roadway approaching a curve. V1 departed the roadway to the left where the left side of V1 impacted a tree and then the front of V1 impacted a post. V1 came to final rest against the tree and post.

V1 and V2 were traveling southeast on a four lane, divided roadway. V1 was entering the same roadway from an on-ramp lane, and V2 was traveling in the third lane. V1 changed lanes to the left and the left side of V1 contacted the right side of V2. V1 and V2 continued on the roadway and the left side of V1 contacted the right side of V2. V1 came to final rest on the roadway. V2 continued off the roadway to the left, and the front of V2 contacted a jersey barrier, and rotated counter-clockwise after impact. Again off the roadway, the back of V2 contacted the jersey barrier, and came to final rest off the roadway.
V1 was traveling south on a two lane, divided roadway. The front of V1 contacted a deer in the roadway. The deer then contacted the right side of V1.  V1 came to final rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling southeast in the number 1 lane of a 2 lane undivided roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right where the front of V1 impacted a fence post. V1 continued forward where the front of V1 impacted a concrete block. V1 continued forward where the front of V1 impacted a pole. The last impact with the pole caused V1 to begin to rotate counter-clockwise and V1 began to roll over onto its right side. V1 continued to roll over and came to rest on its roof facing in a westerly direction.

Vehicle 1 was traveling eastbound on two-lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane one position approaching an intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling northbound on a two-lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection at the same time. The right plane of Vehicle 1 was impacted by the frontal plane of Vehicle 2. Vehicle 1 was deflected off the northeast intersection quadrant. Vehicle 1 made contact with a drainage ditch putting it into a two-quarter turn roll before coming to rest on its top, facing north. Subsequent to the impact, Vehicle 2 also departed the northeast intersection quadrant coming to rest facing southeast

Vehicle 1 was traveling eastbound on a two lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway right side and returned. Vehicle 1 departed roadway left side, making contact with an embankment with the front plane. Vehicle 1 continued downhill making contact to shrubbery with the front plane. Vehicle began to roll counter clockwise 5 quarter turns before coming to final rest on its left side facing east.

V1 was heading north on a four lane undivided roadway in lane two. V2 was heading south on the same roadway in the second lane. V1 departed its initial travel lane to the left. The front of V1 connected with the front of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest near the point of impact.

V1 was heading southeast on a five lane roadway with a left turn lane in lane two. V2 and V3 were heading northwest on the same roadway. V2 was traveling in lane two and V3 was traveling in lane one. V1 departed its initial travel lane to the left. The front of V1 contacted the front of V2 and V3 simultaneously. All vehicles came to final rest near the point of impact.

V1 was traveling southeast on a two way, four lane, median divided roadway. A deer entered the roadway from the southern shoulder, and the frontal plane of V1 struck the animal in the roadway. V1 came to final rest on the roadway.

Vehicle #1 was traveling north in lane one of a two-lane divided roadway without a positive barrier.  The front of V1 contacted an animal.  The animal flew up and contacted the front of V1 again.  V1 came to rest near impact.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east in lane one on a two lane two way roadway approaching a four leg intersection controlled by a stop sign. Vehicle 2 was traveling north in lane one on a two lane two way roadway approaching the same four leg intersection with no traffic controls. Within the intersection the front plane of vehicle 2 contacted the right plane of vehicle 1. Upon impact vehicle 1 rotated counterclockwise and departed the roadway at the northeast corner of the intersection. The front plane of vehicle 1 then contacted a ditch before coming to final rest off the roadway facing north. Upon impact vehicle 2 rotated clockwise, departed the roadway at the northeast corner of the intersection and came to final rest off the roadway facing northeast.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway in lane one approaching a four legged intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling north on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. Within the intersection, the front of Vehicle 1 contacted the right side of Vehicle 2. The left side of Vehicle 1 then contacted the right side of Vehicle 2 in a side slap configuration. Vehicle 1 came to final rest on the north leg of the intersection facing northeast. Vehicle 2 departed the roadway on the northwest corner of the intersection and came to final rest facing southwest.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a two-lane, two-way roadway approaching a four leg intersection controlled by a traffic light. Vehicle 2 was traveling west on a two lane two-way roadway approaching the same intersection controlled by a traffic light. Within the intersection vehicle 1 turned left and the front plane of vehicle 2 contacted the right plane of vehicle 1. Upon impact vehicle 1 rotated clockwise and departed the roadway on the left side and came to final rest off the roadway facing south. Vehicle 2 came to final rest on the roadway facing west.

V1 was turning left(east) from an exit only business driveway onto a two way, two lane, undivided roadway. V2 was west bound on the same two way, two lane, undivided roadway approaching the business driveway that V1 was exiting. The frontal plane of V2 made contact with the left side plane of V1. V1 continued forward rotating in a counter clockwise direction making contact again with V2 on an unknown plane with it’s left side plane. V1 continued forward coming to final rest partially off of the south side of the roadway. V2 continued forward coming to final rest partially off of the north side of the roadway.

V1 was traveling northeast on a median divided roadway, with four lanes in the same direction, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling southwest, on the same a median divided roadway as V1, approaching the same intersection as V1. V1 attempted a left hand turn at the intersection and the frontal plane of V1 made contact with left side plane of V2. Both V1 and V2 came to a final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling North on a non-physically divided two lane highway in lane one, behind V2. V2 was also traveling North on a non-physically divided two lane highway in lane one, behind V3. V3 was on the same highway also in lane one, in front of V2 and behind V4. V4 is also traveling on the same highway in front of V3 and behind V5. V5 also traveling on the same highway in lane one, behind V6. V6 also traveling North, on the same highway, in front of V5 and behind V7. V7 also traveling North on the same highway in lane one, in front of V6. Due to heavy traffic, the front of V1 impacted the back of V2. This caused a chain reaction, and the front of V2 impacted the back of V3, V3's front then impacted the back of V4. V4 pushed forward and the front of V4 impacted the back of V5, then the front of V5 impacted the back of V6, and the front of V6 impacted the back of V7. V1, V2, V3, V4, V5 and V6 all came to rest within lane one facing west. V7 came to rest on the right shoulder also facing a westerly direction.

V1 was traveling east in the second lane of a four lane, two-way unprotected divided roadway. V1 hydroplaned as it traveled through the intersection, with V1 rotating counterclockwise.
