V1 departed left into the third and fourth lanes before departing right from the roadway. The right rear tire of V1 impacted the curb. The right side plane of V1 impacted a utility pole. As V1 continued to rotate, the right side plane of V1 impacted a pedestrian, that was walking on the sidewalk. The right side plane of V1 impacted the rock wall, as V1 continued to rotate counterclockwise. The right side plane of V1 impacted the rock wall for a second time.

V1 was traveling north in the #2 lane of a 4 lane divided roadway. V2 was stopped in the #4 lane of a 4 lane divided roadway facing north waiting to turn left at an intersection. V2 turned right crossed the #3 lane and entered the #2 lane. The front of V1 impacted the right side of V2. V1 continued forward and came to rest facing north in the middle of an intersection. V2 continued east and came to rest in the #1 lane of the east bound roadway facing east.

V1 was traveling northeast in lane one of a five-lane divided roadway, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling northwest, stopped at a stop sign, in lane one of a two lane roadway. A noncontact vehicle passed through the intersection and V1 departed its travel lane to the right. The front plane of V1 contacted the left plane of V1. V1 departed the roadway and came to final rest facing southeast. Following impact 1, V2 departed the roadway to the right and it's back plane contacted a pole. V2 then went down an embankment and came to final rest off the roadway at the bottom of the embankment.

V1 was traveling east in lane one of a two lane roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling southeast in lane two of a five lane roadway approaching the same intersection. V1's left plane was contacted by V2's front plane. V1 rotated 180 degrees and came to final rest in the NW corner of the intersection. V2 came to final rest in the roadway just past impact

V1 was traveling northbound from a two lane, undivided private drive in lane one. V2 was traveling westbound on a four lane, undivided roadway in lane one. V1 was crossing the roadway V2 was traveling on, from a private drive to another private drive. While crossing the roadway the front of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V2 rotated clockwise and came to rest in the entrance of the private drive north of the roadway. V1 rotated counter clockwise and came to rest in the entrance of the private drive north of the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was making a left turn from the westbound travel lane of three lane non-divided roadway onto a five lane median divided roadway. Vehicle 1 was contacted on the left side plane by the frontal plane of vehicle 2, which was traveling in the second northbound lane of a five lane non positively divided roadway. Both vehicles came to rest on the roadway within the intersection.

Vehicle 1 was traveling in the first of three northbound travel lanes of a six lane positively divided roadway. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway to the right, due to falling asleep and contacted a ditch with its frontal plane. Vehicle 1 came to rest off the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a 6 lane, two-way, median divided traffic way in lane 1 position approaching an intersection to turn right. V1 entered the intersection and began a right turn. The left of V1 contacted a guard rail face causing damage down the left side. V1 then came to rest facing west parallel to the guardrail.

V1 was traveling west on a 4 lane, two-way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 2 position. V2 was traveling east on the same 4 lane, two-way, non-physically divided road way in lane 2 position. V1 departed lane of travel left side. The front of V1 contacted the front of V2. V1 then rotated counter-clockwise coming to rest facing south in the east bound lanes. V2 came to rest facing south east in the east bound lane 1.

Vehicle 1 was traveling westbound on a two lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position.  Vehicle 2 was legally parked facing west.  The front plane of Vehicle 1 made contact with the rear plane of Vehicle 2.  Vehicle 2 was pushed slightly forward and came to rest facing west.  Vehicle 1 came to final rest just after impact facing west.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a 5 lane, two-way, non-physically divided roadway approaching an intersection to make a left turn. V2 was traveling east on a 5 lane, two-way, non-physically divided roadway approaching the same intersection attempting to continue east. Both vehicles entered the intersection at the same time. The front of V1 contacted the front of V2. V1 rotated clockwise and V1 rotated counter-clockwise causing the left side of V2 to contact the right side of V1. V1 came to rest facing south east and V2 came to rest facing south.

V1 was traveling east in lane three of a three lane divided (no positive barrier) straight roadway, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling in the same lane ahead of V1, driving slower than V1. Before both vehicles reached the intersection, the front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in their original travel lanes, facing east.

V1 was traveling south on a 2 lane non-divided roadway, when it began to yaw counter clockwise.V1 crossed the lane line to the left. V2 was traveling north on the same roadway. V1's right side contacted V2's front. V1 continued off the roadway, continuing to yaw. V1's rear contacted a fence before coming to final rest. V2 came to rest off the roadway as well.

V1 was traveling south in lane 2, on a 3 lane, two way roadway. While negotiating a right curve in the roadway, V1 departed the roadway to the right, possibly due to a medical problem, and contacted a tree with it's front plane. V1 continued traveling forward off of the roadway and contacted 3 more trees with it's front plane. The vehicle then came to final rest off of the roadway and approximately 4 meters from the 4th tree.

Vehicle 1 was traveling northbound on a two lane, two way undivided roadway and entered into the intersection of another two lane, two way, undivided roadway. Vehicle 1 was contacted on the left side plane with the frontal plane of Vehicle 2, which was traveling eastbound on the intersecting roadway. Both vehicles came to rest on the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway to the right and sideswiped a grouping of bushes along the right side plane. Vehicle continued traveling forward and contacted a tree with its frontal plane. Vehicle 1 came to rest off the roadway facing north.

V1 was south on a 2 lane physically divided roadway in lane two when V1 departed the roadway to the left and contacted a cable guardrail with its front, right side, coming to rest on the shoulder facing south.

V1 was traveling east bound on a two lane, non divided bidirectional roadway, negotiating a curve to the left. V1 departed the roadway to the right, where V1's left plane impacted a tree.  V1's right plane then impacted a tree, where it came to final rest.

V1 and V2 were traveling west, V1 in lane in lane four and V2 in lane 3 of a four lane divided (with positive barrier) left curved highway, negotiating a curve. V2 changed lanes to the left and the left side of V2 impacted the right side of V1.  V1 departed the road to its left and impacted the concrete traffic barrier median with its front corner. V1 came to rest a short distance further at the median, facing west.  V2 left the scene of the crash and was not included on the PAR.

V1 was traveling west in lane one of a two lane undivided (two-way traffic) road, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south in lane one of a two lane divided (no positive barrier) road, approaching the same intersection. Within the intersection, the front of V1 impacted the left side of V2's trailer. V1 was dragged to its left by the trailer and came to rest in the southbound lane one, facing south. V2's trailer rotated counter clockwise and departed the roadway to the southwest corner. The wheels of V2's trailer impacted a raised curb. The right side of the trailer unit impacted a pole. V2 came to rest in lane one of the southbound lanes, facing south.

V1 was eastbound on a two lane, one way, roadway divided by a grass median. V1 departed the right side of the roadway impacting a ditch with the frontal plane. V1 came to final rest near the point of impact facing south.
V1 was northbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. The front of V1 impacted a deer causing damage. V1 came to final rest on the right side of the road facing north.

V1 was traveling south on a two-lane, two-way road while negotiating a turn to the left. V1 departed the road to the right where its front plane impacted ledge rock formation. V1 continued along the right side of the road when its front plane impacted a utility pole. V1 came to rest back in the roadway heading north.

V1 was traveling south on a two-lane, two-way road while attempting to make a left turn onto another road. V1 departed the corner of the intersection on the right side and its right plane impacted a guardrail. The front of V1 then impacted a tree causing it to rotate counterclockwise. This caused the vehicle to overturn, right side leading, three quarter turns, coming to rest on its left side. Bystanders then pushed the car onto its wheels.
Vehicle #1 was traveling west in lane one of a two-lane, undivided roadway, negotiating a left curve.  V1 departed the road to the right and the front of V1 contacted a ditch.

V1 was traveling south on a four lane, two way divided roadway with a flush median in the second southbound lane.  V2 was traveling eastbound on a two lane, two way intersecting roadway in the eastbound lane.  V2 initiated a right turn at the intersection and was struck on the left side plane by V1.  V1 struck V2 with the front plane.  V2 rotated clockwise off of the roadway at the southwest corner and struck a utility pole with the front plane before coming to rest off the roadway at the corner.  V1 came to final rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling south on a two-way, two lane roadway in the southbound lane.  V2 was traveling east on a two-way, two lane intersecting roadway in the eastbound lane.  V2's front plane impacted V1's right plane. V1 and V2 came to final rest on roadway after impact.

V1 was traveling westbound on a two-lane, non-divided roadway, V2 was traveling eastbound on the mentioned roadway. V1 departed its lane on the left side and its front plane struck the front plane of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest at point of impact.

V1 was traveling northeast following a two-way, two lane road. V1 departed its original travel lane to the left. Continuing forward, V1 departed the roadway to the left. V1 began to rotate clockwise, impacting a tree with its left side. Leading with its left side, V1 rolled a total of 6 quarter turns before coming to final rest on its roof on the side of the road facing south. The driver was fully ejected and came to final rest in roadway.

V1 was traveling northeast on a four lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 departed the right roads edge. The frontal plane of V1 contacted a fire hydrant. After contact V1 returned to the roadway and drove to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 crossed the left lane line and departed the eastern road edge. The frontal plane of V1 contacted a tree. V1 came to final rest off the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a two lane, two-way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1 position approaching a 4 way intersection. V2 was traveling east on a two lane, two-way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1 position approaching the same 4 way intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection at the same time. V1 attempted to make a left turn and V2 attempted to pass through the intersection. The front of V1 contacted the left front side of V2. V1 came to rest facing south in the intersection. V2 came to rest facing south east at the corner of the intersection.

Vehicle 1 was traveling eastbound on a two-lane non-physically divided roadway attempting to make a left hand turn at a four-leg intersection. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway at the northeast intersection quadrant impacting a light pole with the front plane (Event 1). Vehicle 1 initiated a counter-clockwise yaw as its rear spare tire impacted the wall of a building (Event 2). The same spare tire impacted an air-conditioning unit (Event 3) as the vehicle tripped and completed two-quarter-turns (Event 4) coming to rest on its roof and facing south.

V1 and V2 were traveling southeast, on a median divided roadway, with two lanes in the same direction. V1 was trailing a non-contact vehicle in lane one and V2 traveling in lane two. In an attempt to pass the non-contact vehicle, V1 entered lane two and the front plane of V2 made contact with the left side plane of V1. V1 continued forward rotating in a counter clockwise direction going off the edge of the roadway on the left side into a non-paved median. V1 continued forward through the median. V1 proceeded to enter into a right leading roll. V1 rolled eight quarter turns breaking into four pieces before the truck cab came to final rest on the northbound roadway. V2 continued forward crossing over into lane one before leaving the southern side of the roadway. V2 continued forward off the roadway and came to final rest partially on the paved shoulder of the roadway. V2 then was consumed by a fire.

V1 was traveling north in the south bound lanes of a median divided roadway, with two lanes in the same direction approaching a hillcrest. V2 was traveling south on the same roadway in the same lane as V1 approaching the same hillcrest. The front plane of V1 made contact with the front plane of V2. V1 continued forward in a counter clockwise direction and departed the left hand side (east) of the south bound roadway. V1 came to final rest off of the roadway in the median between the north and south bound lanes. V2 continued forward in a counter clockwise direction coming to a final rest partially off the right hand side (west) of the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north in lane one on a two lane, two-way roadway. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway on the left side, traveled down a ditch and the left plane contacted a utility pole. Vehicle 1 continued forward, returned to the roadway, then departed the roadway on the right side and traveled down a ditch before coming to final rest off the roadway facing northeast.

Vehicle 1 was negotiating a curve to the right headed northwest in lane one, on a two lane, two way roadway. Vehicle 2 was negotiating a curve to the left traveling southeast in lane one on the same roadway. As the roadway curved vehicle 1 departed its lane to the left and the front plane of vehicle 1 contacted the front plane of vehicle 2. Upon impact vehicle 1 continued forward and came to final rest on the side of the roadway facing north. Vehicle 2 came to final rest on the roadway facing south.

Vehicle 1, Vehicle 2, and Vehicle 3 were traveling northeast on a four lane, physically undivided roadway in lane two. The front of Vehicle 1 contacted the back of Vehicle 2. The front of Vehicle 2 contacted the back of Vehicle 3. All vehicles came to final rest on the roadway facing northeast.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north on a three lane, two-way roadway physically divided by a concrete barrier in lane one. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway on the right, the front plane contacted a fence and rolled over four quarter turns to the left before coming to final rest on a separate, two-way non-physically divided roadway facing northwest.

V1 was traveling east in lane two on a two lane, median divided, roadway and was negotiating a right curve in the roadway . A deer then entered the roadway from the median side of the road, and V1's front plane contacted the deer. V1 came to final rest a short distance from the contact, on the right shoulder of the roadway.

V1 was traveling southwest in lane two, and crossing into lane three, on a five lane, positively divided roadway. . V2, V3, and V4 were all traveling west in lane 3 on the same roadway. V2, V3, and V4 were all slowing due to other traffic ahead. V1's front plane contacted V2's rear plane, which then caused V2's front plane to contact V3's rear plane. V3's front plane then contacted V4's rear plane before all four vehicles came to final rest in lane three.

V1 was driving westbound on a two lane, undivided roadway in lane one approaching an intersection. At the intersection a vehicle turned from the north to the east crossing the path of V1. V1 steered to the right to avoid contact. V1 then departed the roadway to the right. The front of V1 impacted a stone wall. V1 continued through the wall and came to rest in the grass northwest of the intersection facing northwest.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a two lane, undivided roadway in lane one. V2 was legally parked on the side of the road facing eastbound. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2. V1 rotated clockwise and came to rest in lane two facing southeast. V2 was pushed forward and came to rest facing east.

V1 was traveling north on a physically divided trafficway (median strip with positive barrier) in lane 3 (of five lanes) and was approaching V2, which was parked on the west shoulder, facing north. V1 began to rotate counter-clockwise in a northwesterly direction. V1 departed the roadway on the left where its back end contacted the back end of V2. V1 then continued in a southerly direction and its front end and right side contacted a concrete traffic barrier. V1 came to rest on its wheels facing a southeasterly direction partially on the left shoulder and partially in lane 5. V2 came to rest on its wheels facing a northerly direction on the left shoulder.

V1 was traveling northbound in the number 4 lane of a 4 lane divided highway. V1 departed the three lanes to the right and departed the roadway on the right side. V1 began traveling down an embankment. The front of V1 impacted the embankment and  V1 began to roll-over, end-over-end. V1 continued down the embankment and came to rest facing northerly on an unrelated on-ramp.

V1 was traveling south negotiating a curve to the right in the #1 lane of a 1 lane divided highway on ramp. V1 departed the roadway to the right and drove onto an embankment. V1 rolled over down the embankment and rotated clockwise. V1 came to rest on its roof facing north on the right shoulder of the on ramp.

V1 was traveling southbound in the number 3 lane of a 4 lane divided roadway. V2 was traveling southbound in the number 2 lane of a 4 lane divided roadway. V1 changed lanes to the right where the front of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V1 moved back into the number 3 lane and began to spin counter-clockwise towards the center median. The left side of V1 impacted the center median wall. V1 continued to rotate counter-clockwise and to the south where the left side of V1 impacted the wall. V1 came to rest on the east shoulder facing southwest. V2, after the collision with V1, traveled to the right and began rotating clockwise. V2 departed the roadway to the right where the front of V2 impacted a concrete traffic barrier. V2 continued rotating back into the roadway and came to rest facing southeast between the number 1 and number 2 lanes.

V1 was traveling northeast in the #2 lane of a 5 lane undivided roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the left into a center median where the front of V1 impacted a fence. V1 continued forward and the front of V1 impacted a tree. V1 rotated counter clockwise and came to rest partially in the #2 lane against the tree facing north.

V1 was traveling southeast exiting a private drive attempting a left turn. V2 was traveling southwest in lane one of a two lane roadway. V1's left plane was contacted by V2's front plane. V1 came to rest in the roadway near impact. V2 exited the right road edge and came to final rest.
Vehicle 1 was traveling in the southbound lanes of a three lane roadway. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway and contacted a guard rail end with its frontal plane, coming to rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling east on a one-way, left curved, 5 lane roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north on a divided two lane intersecting roadway coming to a stop at a traffic signal. V1 moved from the 2nd lane into the right turn lane and then entered the crossing north bound road but still in an easterly direction. The front wheels for V1 struck the concrete median curb. V1 went airborne and the front struck the left plane of V2. V1 and V2 remained entangled moving off the road to the right. The right wheels of V2 struck the curb. The left rear wheel of V1 struck the curb. The right plane of V1 struck a sign base. The right plane plane of V2 struck a sign. Both vehicles came to rest on the grass island with V1 facing northeast and V2 facing west.

V1 (an unknown vehicle) was south on a 3 lane roadway approaching an intersection V2 was west on a 3 lane roadway approaching the same intersection. After V2 made a successful left hand turn, the front of V1 contacted the rear of V2. Next, the front of V2 contacted a concrete traffic barrier then the right side of V2 contacted the same concrete traffic barrier. Finally, V2 crossed all traffic lanes to the left and the front of V2 contacted a concrete bridge before coming to rest. V1 did not come to rest but continued to travel.

V1 was southbound in lane 4 of 4 on a divided roadway approaching a 4 way intersection. V2 was northbound in lane 3 of 5 on a divided roadway approaching the same intersection. Within the intersection V1 initiated a left turn. The front of V1 contacted the front of V2.  Both Vehicles came to rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling north in the first of two lanes on an undivided, two-way roadway entering a sign controlled, four-legged intersection attempting to turn left. V2 was traveling east in the first of five lanes on an undivided, two-way roadway entering the same intersection as V1. Within the intersection, the left side of V1 contacted the front of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling north in the second of seven lanes on an undivided, two-way roadway. V2 was traveling north in the first lane of the same roadway as V1. V3 was stopped in the second lane ahead of V1. V1 changed lanes to the right and the right side of V1 contacted the front of V2. V1 rotated counterclockwise and the front of V1 contacted the back of V3. All three vehicles came to rest in the roadway.

V2 was traveling east on a divided trafficway (median strip without positive barrier) in lane 4 (of four lanes) and was approaching V1, which was traveling in the same direction, on the same roadway, ahead in lane 3. As V2 was overtaking V1, V1 departed its lane on the left and the left side of V1 contacted the right side of V2. V2 then departed the roadway on the left, where its left side contacted a guardrail. V2 came to rest on its wheels facing a southeasterly direction in lane 4. V1 fled the scene.

V1 was traveling west through an intersection from a two-way, not physically divided trafficway and was in lane 1 (of three lanes). V2 was traveling south through the same intersection from a two-way, not physically divided trafficway and was in lane 1 (of five lanes). In the intersection, the front end of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V1 came to rest on its wheels facing a southwesterly direction in the intersection. V2 came to rest on its wheels facing a southerly direction in lane 1, south of the intersection.

V1 was traveling in a northeasterly direction, through the left hand curve of the roadway, in lane 3 (of three lanes), and was approaching V2, which was traveling in the same direction, on the same roadway, in lane 1.  V1 departed its lane on the right, twice.  The front end of V1 came in contact with the back end of V2's trailer.   V1 skidded laterally in a counterclockwise rotation and departed the road on the left, where its front end, and then its back end, came in contact with the concrete traffic barrier in the median strip.  V1 came to rest on its wheels, facing a southerly direction, on the median shoulder.  V2 was driven to the shoulder and parked.

V1 was traveling in an easterly direction, through the left hand curve of the roadway, on a two-way, not physically divided trafficway, in lane 1 (of two lanes), when it departed the roadway on the right, and was then returned to the roadway from the right.  Control over V1 was lost.  V1 skidded laterally in a counterclockwise rotation, and departed the road on the left, where its right side came in contact with an earthen embankment.  V1 then overturned (6 quarter turns, leading right), and came to rest on its roof, facing a southwesterly direction, on the roadside.

V1 was traveling west on a non-physically divided two lane road in lane two, behind V2. V2 was west on the same non-physically divided two lane road in lane two, in front of V1. Due to heavy traffic, the front of V1 impacted the back of V2. V1 and V2 came to rest in lane two facing west.

V1 was traveling south in lane 1 on a two-lane divided roadway. A pig was crossing the roadway in a westward direction from the dirt median when the front of V1 impacted the pig. V1 came to rest on the shoulder facing south. The pig came to rest on the shoulder.

Vehicle 1 was traveling in the left turn lane of a ten lane median divided trafficway, turning left onto a cross street. Vehicle 2 was traveling in the eastbound lanes of the same roadway and contacted its frontal plane with the right side plane of vehicle 1, in the intersection. After the impact with Vehicle 2, Vehicle 1 entered into a rollover event with the left side leading, 2 quarter turns. Both vehicles came to rest on the roadway.

V1 and V2 were both traveling westbound on a two lane, two-way roadway. V2 was stopped ahead of V1. V1’s front plane contacted V2 back plane. V1 and V2 came to final rest on the roadway near the point of impact.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a 4 lane non divided roadway; in lane 1, pulling a cargo trailer. V2 was behind V1 in lane two of eastbound travel. V1 began to make a U turn. V2's front then contacted the left side of the cargo trailer. As the trailer began to rotate the front of V2 contacted the left side of the trailer a second time. Both vehicles came to rest within the roadway.

V1 was eastbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway negotiating a left turn. V1 departed the right side of the roadway impacting a fence with the frontal plane. V1 continued through the fence impacting another fence with the right side causing damage. V1 came to final rest at the final point of impact facing north east.

V1 was eastbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 departed its initial travel lane to the left departing the left side of the roadway. The front of V1 impacted a ditch.  V1 then rolled over coming to final rest in the ditch.

Vehicle #1 (V1) was traveling northeast in lane one of a two-lane, undivided roadway.  V1 departed the road to the right and impacted the curb with both right side wheels.  V1 continued off road and the front of V1 contacted a tree.   V1 began to rotate clockwise and re-entered the road.  V1 came to rest facing southeast on the road.

V1 was traveling north on a two-lane, two-way road that went down an incline and curved slightly to the right. V1 departed the left side of the road where it struck an embankment and several small trees with its front plane before coming to final rest off of the left side of the road facing north.

V1 was traveling west on a non-physically divided two-way roadway in lane one, negotiating a right curve. V2 was traveling east on the same roadway in lane one, negotiating a left curve, in front of V3. V3 was traveling east behind V2.  V1 traveled over its left lane line and the front of V1 impacted the front left of V2. V1 rotated counter-clockwise and the front of V1 impacted the left front of V3, which had pulled over on the right shoulder and stopped. V1 traveled backwards towards the westbound lanes and came to rest on the westbound shoulder facing a northwest direction. V3 came to rest on the eastbound shoulder facing a easterly direction. After the impact V2 rotated counter-clockwise as it departed the right road edge then rolled right, 2-quarter turns, down an embankment and came to rest on its top facing south.

V1 was traveling south in lane two of a two lane divided (no positive barrier) straight roadway, approaching an intersection. V1 passed through the intersection and departed the roadway to the left. V1 impacted the raised curb with its left wheel that caused damage (Event 1) and then the left rear wheel (Event 2). V1 drove onto the median and continued south on the median. The front of V1 impacted a light pole on the median (Event 3). V1 kept moving south until it impacted a tree with its front (Event 4). V1 came to rest at the tree, facing south.

V1 was traveling north through the right hand curve of the roadway, on a one-way trafficway (Entrance Ramp), in lane 2 (of two lanes). Control over V1 was lost. V1 skidded laterally in a clockwise rotation as it departed the road on the left, where it then overturned (8 quarter turns, leading left). V1 came to rest on its wheels, facing a southeasterly direction on the roadside.

V1 was traveling south in lane 1 on a 2-lane divided roadway. V2 was traveling on the same stopped in lane one in front of V1. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2. After the impact, V1 continued off the right road edge onto an uphill embankment, and came to rest on the embankment facing a southeasterly direction. V2 continued across the number two lane off the left road edge where the left front of V2 impacted a concrete median. V2 then bounced back across the lanes and came to rest on the right shoulder facing an easterly direction.

V1 was traveling east on a non-physically divided six lane road in lane two, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north on a three lane road in lane one, stopped at a red light of the intersection. As V2 entered the intersection, the right side of V1 impacted the front of V2. V2 came to rest within the intersection facing a northerly direction. V1 came to rest within the intersection of the eastbound lane facing a easterly direction.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a one-way, 3 lane exit ramp in lane number 2. . Vehicle 2 and 3 were on the same roadway stopped in the roadway. Vehicle 2 was in lane number 2 and vehicle 3 was in lane number 3. Vehicle 1's front end made contact with vehicle 2's rear end. After initial contact, vehicle 2's front was pushed into vehicle 3's right side. Vehicle 1 came to final rest in there original lane facing east. Vehicle 2 came to final rest against vehicle 3 facing north. Vehicle 3 came to final rest in there original lane.

Vehicle 1 and 2 were traveling west on a 7 lane, physically divided roadway in lane number 3. Vehicle 1's front and vehicle 2's rear end made contact with each other in lane number 3. After initial contact, Vehicle 2 was redirected to the the north side of the roadway, and vehicle 2's front made contact with the concrete barrier, and coming to final rest against it. Vehicle 1 continued forward in lane 3 where it came to final rest and caught on fire.

Vehicle 1 was traveling westbound on a two lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position.  The front plane of vehicle 1 made contact with two live animals in the roadway. After the initial impact, the first animal impacted rotated around the vehicle and impacted the right plane.   Vehicle 1 came to final rest facing west on the side of the road.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane, undivided roadway, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north on a two lane, divided, roadway approaching the same intersection. In the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the right side of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling northbound on a two lane, undivided roadway in lane one negotiating a left curve. V1 departed the roadway to the right and the right front tire and right rear tire impacted a retaining wall. V1 then rolled over 2 quarter turns right side leading and came to rest against a fence on it's top facing west.

V1 was traveling west in lane one of a two-lane undivided roadway. The roadway ended and V1 departed the roadway forward. V1 began to skid longitudinally and contacted an embankment. V1 continued and entered a creek bed/ditch where it came to final rest.

V1 was traveling south in lane one of a two-lane roadway, exiting a private drive, attempting to cross over an intersection. V2 was traveling west in lane three of a four-lane divided roadway, approaching the intersection. The left plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2. The impact caused V1 to rotate counterclockwise, coming to final rest within the median break/crossover location facing northeast. V2 continued west and came to final rest on the left shoulder, past the point of impact.

V1 and V2 were both traveling southeast in lane one of a two lane roadway. V2 was ahead of V1 attempting to turn left onto a private drive. V1's front plane contacted V2's rear plane. V1 came to rest in the roadway near impact. V2 was pushed forward and departed the right road edge where it came to final rest.

V1 was traveling northeast on a median divided trafficway, with three lanes in the same direction, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling southwest, on the same a median divided trafficway  approaching the same intersection as V1. V1 attempted a left hand turn at the intersection and the frontal plane of V2 made contact with right side plane of V1. Both V1 and V2 came to a final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling south, approaching a four leg intersection and made a right turn onto a two lane, two way undivided roadway. V2 was traveling west on the two lane, two way, undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. The front end of V2 struck the rear end of V1 . V1 and V2 both came to final rest off the north side of the road facing west.

V1 was westbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway approaching a three leg intersection. V2 was eastbound on the same roadway. V1 attempted to make a left turn at the intersection and front of V1 struck the front of V2.  Upon impact V1 rotated counter clockwise, departing the roadway to the north, coming to final rest off the roadway facing east. V2 continued off the north side of the roadway impacting a road sign with the frontal plane causing damage. V2 then continued southeast coming to final rest facing east.

V1 was heading north in lane two of the southbound lanes of the divided interstate. V2 was traveling south in lane three of the same interstate. V1 entered lane three and the front of V1 contacted the front V2. V2 was redirected to the left where it cam to final rest facing southeast in lane four. V1 was also redirected left and came to rest facing northwest partially in lane one.

Vehicle #1 was traveling east attempting to turning right from a private driveway. Vehicle #2 was traveling south bound in lane one of a non-divided, three lane trafficway. The front bumper of V2 contacted the left side of V1. V1 rotated counter-clockwise and contacted its left side on the right side of V2. V1 departed the roadway on the right and came to rest off the roadway facing west. V2 came to rest in the roadway facing south.

V1 was traveling east on a two way, two lane road with a curve to the right. As V1 was negotiating the curve, it lost control, departing its original travel lane to the left. Continuing forward, V1 departed the roadway to the left. The left side of V1 impacted a tree. Continuing off road, the front of V1 impacted a tree. The impact caused the tree to uproot and to fall on the left side of V1. The front of V1 impacted three more trees before coming to final rest off the roadway facing northeast.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway negotiating a right had curve. V2 was traveling south on the same roadway. Due to poor road conditions V1 crossed the left lane line crossing paths with V2. V2 steered to the left. The frontal plane of V1 contacted the right plane of V2. V1 and V2 came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 and V2 were traveling on the ramp from the westbound interstate. V1 was in the right lane and V2 was in the left lane. V1 departed its travel lane to the left. The left of V1 contacted the front of V2. V1 rotated clockwise and the left of V1 contacted the front of V2. V1 continued its rotation and the right of V1 contacted the front of V2. During its rotation off of V2, the front and right of V2 contacted the guardrail face just prior to it came to final rest on the shoulder facing southeast. V2 came to final rest near the point of impact.

V1 was traveling northbound, while negotiating a curve to the right, on a 2 lane roadway. V1 crossed the lane line to the left and then departed roadway on the left as well. V1's front contacted a pole. V1 then came to final rest off of the roadway.
V1 was westbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. A deer impacted the front plane of V1 causing damage. V1 came to final rest in westbound lane facing west.

V1 was westbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway negotiating a right curve. V1 departed its travel lane to the left then departed the roadway to the left in a clockwise yaw. V1 continued off the road traveling into a ditch then overturning left side leading four quarter turns. V1 came to final rest on its wheels facing north.

V1 was stopped heading north on a two-lane two, two-way road at a T-intersection. V2 was traveling east in lane two of a four-lane, two-way intersection passing through the T-intersection. V1 attempted to turn left and its front plane impacted the right plane of V2. V1 came to rest in the road at the point of impact. V2 continued to travel across the west bound lanes and departing the left side of the road, coming to final rest off of the left side of the road.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a 4 lane, one way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 2 position approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north on a 2 lane, two-way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1 position approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection at the same time. The left side of V1 contacted the front of V2. V1 lost control, rotating clockwise continuing to travel west. V1 then struck a curb departing roadway left side. The left of V1 contacted a light pole sheering it off, V1 entered a left side roll roll. V1 overturned approximately 5 quarter turns before coming to rest on its left side in a small landscaped area. V2's final rest was facing north west in the intersection.

V1 was traveling southeast on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V1 lost control, crossed an intersection and departed the far right road edge. The frontal plane of V1 contacted three trees and came to final rest off of the roadway.

V1 was traveling southbound in the third lane of a two way not physically divided roadway approaching a four way intersection. V2 was traveling northbound in the second lane of a two way not physically divided roadway approaching the same intersection. As V1 was making a left turn, the right side plane of V1 made contact with the frontal plane of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling south following a two way, two lane road. V2 was facing south, legally parked, on the right side of the same roadway.  V1 departed the road to the right where the right side of V1 impacted the left side of V2.  V2 came to final rest at impact, on the shoulder, facing south. V1 continued forward, coming to final rest off of the roadway facing west.

V1 was traveling south west following a two way, two lane road with a curve to the right. V1 departed its travel lane to the left. Continuing forward, V1 departed the roadway on the left where the front of V1 impacted a guardrail end. Continuing off road, the front of V1 impacted a total of five trees before coming to final rest off the roadway, facing south.

V1 was traveling north following a two way, two lane road approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south on the same two way, two lane road. At the mentioned intersection, V2 attempted to make a U-turn. The front of V1 impacted the right side of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway facing northeast.

V1 was traveling south on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a right hand curve in the roadway. V1 departed their initial travel lane over the left side of the travel lane entering into the northbound lane; V1 then departed the left hand (east) side of the roadway. V1 then struck an embankment with it's frontal plane.  V1 then yawed clockwise and tripped into a left side leading rollover.  The top of V1 impacted a tree.  V1 continued to yaw and due to the slope of the ground, dropped back onto it's wheels, contacting the ground with the undercarriage and causing damage to the vehicle.  V1 came to rest off the east side of the roadway facing north.

V1 was westbound on a two lane, two way, undivided rural roadway. V1 departed its initial travel lane to the left then departed the roadway to the left in a clockwise rotation. V1 impacted the ground with its undercarriage coming to final rest in a field, facing north.

V1 was traveling south in lane three of a three-lane divided roadway, attempting a left turn. V2 was traveling west in lane four of a five-lane divided roadway, passing through the intersection. The traffic signals at the intersection were malfunctioning, with V1's signal flashing red and V2's signal flashing yellow. The left plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2. The left plane of V1 then contacted the right plane of V2. V1 crossed a concrete median and came to final rest partially on the median. V2 came to final rest on the roadway near impact.

V1 was traveling northeast in lane one on a two lane, two way, non-divided, roadway. V1 then departed the roadway to the right and contacted a tree with its front plane. V1 came to final rest against the tree, off of the roadway, and approximately 6 meters from the point of roadway departure.

Vehicle #1 was traveling east on a one-lane, one-way road with legal parking on both sides. Vehicle #2 was parked on the left side of the street, and Vehicle #3 was parked on the right side of the street. V1 entered the left parking lane, and the left plane of V1 contacted the back plane of V2. V2 crossed over the road and entered the right parking lane. The front plane of V1 contacted the back plane of V3. V1 came to rest on the road. V2 came to rest off road to the north. V3 came to rest off road to the south.

V1 and V2 were traveling east on a three lane, non-divided, two-way roadway, in lane one, approaching an intersection.  V1's front impacted the back plane of V2, which was stopped at the intersection.  Both vehicles came to rest in the roadway, just forward of impact, still facing east.

V1 was eastbound on a 4 lane roadway approaching a 3 way intersection. V2 was westbound on a 4 lane roadway approaching the same intersection. Within the intersection the right side of V1 contacted the front of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in the roadway.
V1 was traveling west on a two-lane, two-way road. V1 departed the right side of the road and impacted a landscaping boulder with its front plane, coming to final rest against the boulder.

V1 was stopped on the shoulder of a 2 lane divided roadway facing north. V2 was traveling north in the #2 lane of a 2 lane divided roadway. V1 began turning to travel through a break in the center median and complete a U-turn. The left side of V1 impacted the front of V2. Both vehicles traveled off the roadway to the left into the center median. The right side of V1 impacted a tree. Both vehicles continued traveling west across the southbound lanes. V1 began rotating counter clockwise off the road to the left. The left of V1 impacted the front of V2. V1 came to rest on the sidewalk facing south. V2 came to rest facing west partially on the sidewalk with the front of V2 against the left side of V1.

V1 was traveling north east exiting a driveway. V2 was traveling south east in the #1 lane of a 5 lane undivided roadway with a two way left turn lane. V1 exited the driveway. The front of V1 impacted the right side of V2. V1 came to rest facing north east in the #1 lane. V2 came to rest facing south east in the #2 lane.

V1 was traveling northeast in lane one of a two-lane undivided roadway, negotiating a left curve. V1 departed its travel lane to the left and then departed the roadway to the left. The front plane of V1 contacted an embankment and came to final rest close to impact.

V1 was traveling south in lane one of a two lane divided roadway attempting to pass through an intersection. V2 was traveling north in lane two of a three lane roadway attempting a left turn at the same intersection. V1's front plane contacted V2's right plane. Both vehicles came to rest in the intersection near impact.

V1 was traveling southwest in lane one of a four lane roadway attempting to pass through an intersection. V2 was traveling northwest in lane one of a three lane roadway attempting to pass through the same intersection. V1's left plane contacted V2's front plane. Then V1's left plane contacted V2's front plane. Both vehicles came to rest in the intersection.

Vehicle 1 and Vehicle 2 were both traveling north on a 6 lane, undivided roadway in lane three. Vehicle 2 was stopped on the roadway ahead of Vehicle 1. The front of Vehicle 1 contacted the back of Vehicle 2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway facing the same direction.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a 2-lane roadway when it departed the right road edge and its front plane contacted a ditch. V1 rotated clockwise then tripped and rolled 6-quarter turns and came to rest on its top in a grass field facing west. During the rollover sequence, the top plane of V1 contacted a wire fence and the driver was ejected completely.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north on a two lane two way roadway negotiating a curve to the left. Vehicle 1 traveled off the road on the right side where it contacted a tree, a mailbox, and two additional trees before returning to road on the right side and coming to final rest on the roadway facing north.

V1 was traveling north on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway. V2 was following V1 on the same roadway. V1 stopped in the roadway and began to drive in reverse. The back of V1 contacted the front of V2. V1 and V2 came to final rest on the roadway.
V1 and V2 were traveling west on a three lane roadway.  V2 stopped and the front of V1 contacted the back of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1, V2, and V3 were traveling east on a five lane physically divided roadway. V1 and V2 were slowing for traffic ahead. The front of V3 contacted the rear of V2. V2 then moved forward and the front of V2 contacted the rear of V1. All vehicles came to final rest near point of impact.

V1 was traveling north on a four lane non-physically divided roadway in lane one. V2 was traveling north on a four lane non-physically divided roadway in lane one in front of V1. V2 began to make a right turn when the front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. V1 came to rest on the shoulder facing north. V2 came to rest on the shoulder facing north.

V1 was traveling southbound on a two lane, two way, non-divided roadway, and was turning left at the intersection of a four lane, non-divided roadway. V2 was traveling north on the two lane, two way, non-divided roadway and was traveling through the intersection when V1's front plane contacted V2's front plane. Both vehicles came to final rest in the intersection a short distance from the point of impact.

V1 was traveling north in lane one of a four lane divided right curved roadway approaching slower moving traffic. V1 began to pass vehicles on the right shoulder and its front plane contacted a guardrail face. V1 continued forward and crossed all lanes to the left where its front plane contacted a concrete barrier median. V1 rotated clockwise and its left side contacted a light pole that was attached to the concrete barrier. V1 rotated counter-clockwise and came to rest in the northbound lane four facing southeast.

V2 was traveling east bound on a three lane, non-divided bidirectional roadway. V1 was pulling out of a drive way traveling south bound across the same roadway, attempting to enter a private driveway. V1 entered V2's lane of travel, where its right plane impacted V2's frontal plane. V1 and V2 came to final rest in the roadway at the point of impact.

V1 and V2 were traveling in a north western direction, when V1 attempted to pass V2. V1's frontal plane impacted V2's rear plane. V1 came to final rest on the right side of the roadway, V2 came to final rest on the left side of the roadway.

V1 was traveling northwest on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a left hand curve in the roadway. V2 was traveling southeast on the same roadway as V1 negotiating a right hand curve in the roadway. V1 departed the left hand lane line and the left plane of V1 contacted the left plane of V2. V1 and V2 both came to final rest on the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a two-way non physically divided roadway in lane number 4 attempting to make a left turn into a private drive. Vehicle 2 was traveling west on a two-way non physically divided roadway in lane number 1.  Vehicle 1's front and vehicle 2's front end made contact with each other in the roadway. Both vehicles came to rest in there original travel lanes.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west in lane four of a six lane, not physically divided, two-way roadway, intending to turn left at the intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling east in lane two of the same roadway, passing through the intersection. Within the intersection, the front of vehicle 1 front impacted the front of vehicle 2. Both vehicles came to rest within the intersection. Vehicle 1 came to rest facing southeast, vehicle 2 came to rest facing east.

V1 was traveling south in the second of four lanes on a right curved, undivided, two-way roadway entering a stop sign controlled, four-legged intersection. V2 was traveling east in the second of four lanes on a one-way roadway entering the same intersection as V1. Within the intersection, the right side of V1 contacted the front of V2. Both vehicles came to rest within the intersection.

V1 was traveling east on a four lane undivided roadway (two way traffic) in lane two. V2 was traveling west on the same four lane undivided roadway in lane one. V1 attempted to turn left into a private drive, V2 continued straight. During V1’s left turn, the front of V1 impacted the front of V2. V1 rotated counter clockwise and came to rest partially in both westbound lanes facing northwest. V2 came to rest in lane 1 facing west.

V1 and V2 were traveling northbound on a divided three lane road in lane one approaching an intersection. V1 was traveling behind V2, at the intersection both vehicles turned right onto a two lane undivided (two way traffic) road. V2 then stopped in the road and the front of V1 impacted the back of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in lane 1 facing east.

V1 was traveling west in lane one of a two-lane undivided roadway, negotiating a left curve. V2 was traveling south and turning left from a gravel roadway onto the two-lane undivided roadway. The front plane of V1 contacted the left plane of V2. V1 then departed the roadway to the right. The front of V1 contacted a ditch/culvert and rotated clockwise before coming to final rest off the roadway. V2 came to final rest on the roadway near impact.

V1 was traveling northeast in lane one of a two lane roadway negotiating a left curve. Deer entered the roadway from the left and the driver steered right in an attempt to avoid a collision. V1 departed the right road edge and the undercarriage contacted a ditch. V1 then went airborne and contacted a garbage can before its front plane contacted another ditch where it came to final rest.

V1 was traveling southeast in lane one of a six lane divided trafficway. V2 was traveling in lane two on the same roadway ahead of V1. V1 changed lanes to its left and its front plane contacted V2's rear plane. V1 continued forward and its left plane contacted V2's right plane. Both vehicles came to rest in the roadway near impact.

V1 was traveling south on lane 2 of a 4 lane, two-way, not physically divided roadway with both left and right turn lanes approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling east on lane 1 of a 2 lane, two-way, not physically divided roadway with a left turn lane approaching the same intersection. V1 and V2 enter the intersection simultaneously where V1 front plane contacted V2 left plane. V1 rotated counter-clockwise while V2 rotated clockwise with V1 right plane contacted V2 left plane.
V1 was traveling north bound in lane 1 of a 2 lane, two-way, not physically divided roadway. A deer entered the roadway from the right edge of roadway, contacting V1's front plane.

V1 and V2 were traveling west on a five lane undivided roadway. V1 was in lane 4 and V2 was lane 3 (a designated left turn lane). The driver of V2 initiated a left turn sequence as the front of V1 impacted the left side of V1 (Event 1). V1 initiated a rollover sequence with its right side leading (Event 2). V2 departed the left side of the roadway and initiated a two-quarter rollover sequence (Event 3). V2 impacted a fuel pump (Event 4) and the steel fuel pump guard (Event 5) before coming to rest on its roof, facing south. V1 came to final rest on its top on the eastbound lanes facing south.

V1 was traveling north on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a right hand curve in the roadway. V1 departed the left hand lane line and then departed the left side of the roadway. V1 contacted a utility pole with its frontal plane. V1 then continued forward striking an embankment with its undercarriage and the utility pole a second time with its left plane. V1 came to final rest off of the roadway with the top portion of the utility pole laying on its front right hood.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south in lane two on a six lane, two way roadway approaching a four leg intersection with a traffic control signal. Vehicle 2 was traveling north in the left turn lane on the same roadway approaching the same intersection with a traffic control signal. Within the intersection vehicle 2 turned left and the front plane contacted the front plane of vehicle 1. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway within the intersection facing west.

Vehicle 1 and Vehicle 2 were both traveling north on a two lane unprotected roadway. Vehicle 2 slowed to turn left into a private drive. The front of Vehicle 1 contacted the back of Vehicle 2. Vehicle 1 came to final rest in the roadway facing north, and Vehicle 2 came to final rest on the side of the roadway also facing north.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south in lane one on a two lane two way roadway approaching a three leg intersection controlled by a stop sign. Vehicle 2 was traveling west in lane one on a two lane two way roadway approaching a three leg intersection with no traffic controls. Within the intersection vehicle 1 turned left and the front plane of vehicle 2 contacted the left plane of vehicle 1. Upon impact vehicle 1 rotated clockwise and came to final rest on the roadway facing north. Vehicle 2 rotated counter-clockwise and came to final rest on the roadway facing southeast.

Vehicle 1and Vehicle 3 were traveling south on an undivided roadway approaching a four-legged intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling north on the same roadway approaching the same intersection. Vehicle 1 was turning left, the front of Vehicle 2 contacted the right side of Vehicle 1 within the intersection. Vehicle 2 went left of center and the front of Vehicle 2 contacted the front of Vehicle 3. Vehicle 1 came to final rest in the northeast corner of the intersection facing northwest. Vehicle 2 & Vehicle 3 came to final rest on the northwest corner of the intersection facing west.

V1 was traveling north on a two way, two lane undivided roadway, attempting to crossover an intersection. V2 was traveling west in lane one, on a median divided roadway, with three lanes in the same direction, attempting to crossover the same intersection. Within the intersection, the right plane of V1 contacted the frontal plane of V2. Both vehicle rotated where the right plane of V1 contacted the left plane of V2. V1 continues rotating counterclockwise, roughly 270 degrees, coming to rest off the roadway facing southeast.  V2 continued forward, departing the roadway to the right, traveling down a slope where the front plane contacted a ditch and came to final rest facing northeast.

V1 was traveling westbound in lane four on a divided highway with five lanes of travel. V2 was traveling in front of V1 in the same lane. The frontal plane of V1 made contact with the rear plane of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

Vehicle #1 was traveling east on a four-lane road in lane 2 approaching an intersection. Vehicle #2 was traveling east on the same road in lane 1. V1 turned right at the intersection, and the right plane of V1 contacted the left plane of V2.

V1 was traveling eastbound in the second lane of a four lane service roadway. V2 was traveling in front of V1 in the same lane. The frontal plane of V1 made contact with the rear plane of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling westbound on a two-way, two lane roadway, approaching an intersection.  V2 was traveling southbound on a one-way, one lane, median divided roadway.  As both vehicles entered the intersection, the front plane of V2 made contact with the right plane of V1. After the initial impact, V2 rotated clockwise and the right side of V2 made contact with the left side of V1.  Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway.

V1 (a motorcycle) was a stopped in a private driveway on the westbound side of a non-physically divided two way street. V2 was traveling west on a non-physically divided two way street in lane one. V3 was legally parked on the east bound shoulder facing west. V2 slowed to a stop to attempt a left hand turn into a private driveway. V1 entered the westbound lanes and attempted to overtake V2 when the front of V1 impacted the left side of V2 as V2 attempted a left turn into a private driveway. After the impact, V1 continued towards the eastbound shoulder where the front of V1 impacted the right side of V3. V1 then dropped onto its side on the ground.  V1 came to rest on the eastbound shoulder facing Southwest. V2 came to rest in a private driveway, facing a easterly direction.

V1 was traveling northeast in lane four of a four lane divided (no positive barrier) right curved roadway, approaching a left turn. V2 was traveling southwest in lane three of a three lane divided (no positive barrier) roadway, approaching the intersection with the oncoming left turn lane. At the intersection V1 attempted to turn north on the service road of a highway. Within the intersection the front of V2 impacted the right side of V1. V1 rotated counter clockwise and came to rest within the intersection, facing north. V2 rotated clockwise and came to rest within the intersection, facing west.
V1 was traveling eastbound on a 2 lane roadway. V1 was in Lane 1 and a deer was in the roadway. V1's front contacted the deer. V1 came to rest off of the roadway to the right.

V1 was traveling southwest in the first of three lanes on a positively divided, two-way roadway. V2 was traveling southwest in the second lane of the same roadway. V1 changed lanes to the left and the left side of V1 contacted the front of V2. After the impact, Vehicle 1 departed the location without stopping. Vehicle 2 came to rest in the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was southbound on a two way, two lane roadway.  Vehicle 2 was northbound on the same roadway.  The front plane of Vehicle 1 struck the front plane of vehicle 2. After the initial impact vehicle 2 rolled one quarter turn to the right coming to rest on the northbound shoulder facing west.  Vehicle 1 rotated counter clockwise coming to rest in the middle of the roadway facing east.

V1 was traveling southwest in lane two of a four lane divided interstate roadway. V1 departed the left road edge into the median. V1's front plane contacted a tree then the left plane contacted another tree and the vehicle tripped and rolled left four quarter turns coming to rest upright in the median.
V1 was traveling southwest in lane one of a two lane roadway. V1 departed the right road edge and its front plane contacted a fire hydrant. V1 came to rest off the right road edge.

V1 was traveling west in lane 3 on a 3 lane divided roadway. V1 departed the left road edge, steered right, returned to the roadway and crossed all lanes to the right as it rotated clockwise. V1 departed the right road edge and contacted a guardrail face with its front plane. V1 continued to rotated clockwise as it stayed in constant contact with the guardrail with its left side where it broke through the guardrail and came to rest on the roadside facing east.

V1 was traveling south, in the second lane, on a two-way, non- physically divided roadway with a raised curbed median strip. V1 departed roadway and entered a raised, curbed, grassy median. The front of V1 impacted with a sign (event 1), and continued traveling on the median until impacting the front of vehicle with a tree (event 2). The impact forced V1 to rotate counter clockwise and roll right side leading (event 3). V1 completed four quarter turns, and came to final rest on its wheels on the roadway facing east in lane two of southbound travel.

V1 and V2 were traveling south, in the first lane, on a two-lane, one way exit ramp roadway. As V2 came to a stop, the front of V1 impacted with the rear of V2. V1 and V2 came to final rest in the original lane facing southwest.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a two lane, two-way, undivided roadway.  The roadway initially curves left, straightens, then curves right.  Just before the right curve of the roadway, V1 went off road to the right where it struck a wooden utility pole with its front.  The vehicle came to rest at the pole, facing south.

V1 was traveling south on a two way private driveway attempting a right hand turn. V2 was traveling west on a three lane two way roadway approaching the private driveway. The left side of V1 contacted the front of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was northbound on a 2 lane roadway when a deer ran into travel lanes. V1 swerved to the left and departed the roadway to the left. V1 continued to travel northbound on the shoulder and the front of V1 contacted an embankment. V1 then crossed an east/west roadway while airborne. V1 was traveling south on a two-lane undivided rural roadway negotiating a curve left when it departed the right (west) side of the roadway. V1 continued forward contacting a concrete culvert with its frontal plane (event 1), a sign post with its left side (event 2) and the lower left side against the concrete culvert (event 3). V1 came to final rest off the roadway facing south.

V1 was traveling east on a bridge, on a two lane, undivided roadway. V2 was traveling west on the same two lane, undivided roadway. The front of V1 contacted the front of V2 in the westbound lane The two vehicle sustained contact as V1 rotated rapidly in a counterclockwise fashion. The right side of V1 was in contact with the left side of V2. V2 was deflected on north shoulder where its right side plane impacted a w-beam guardrail and came to rest on the right shoulder facing west. V1 came to rest in the westbound lane heading northwest

V1 was traveling northwest on a two-lane divided roadway in lane one, negotiating a curve. V1 departed the roadway on the right side and traveled off the roadway, striking a pole with its front plane. V1 came to final rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling west negotiating a left curve in lane one of a two lane roadway. V1 departed the right road edge and contacted a fence. V1 then contacted a small tree and then the front plane contacted another larger tree where it came to rest.

V1 was traveling south on a two-way, two-lane road passing through an intersection. V2 was traveling east on a two-lane, two-way road, approaching the same intersection. V2 attempted to make a left hand turn and its left plane was impacted by the front of V1. V1 came to rest east of the intersection. V2 continued to strike a cement pole with its right plane (Event 2), another cement pole with its front plane (Event 3), and a stop sign post with its front plane (Event 4), before coming to rest east of the intersection.  The front of V1 impacted a snow bank at the road edge (Event 5) as V1 came to rest partially off the road facing east.

V1 was traveling north on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway. A deer entered the road from the east crossing paths with V1. The frontal plane of V1 contacted the deer. V1 came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane, one way, undivided highway. V1 lost control and crossed the right lane line and continued of the right road edge. V1 went in a counter-clockwise yaw then rolled four quarter turns. While rolling to final rest an unknown plane of V1 contacted an unknown diameter tree. V1 came to final rest off the east road edge.

V1 was traveling north following a two-way, two lane road with a curve to the right. V1 departed the roadway to the left. The front of V1 impacted a cable wire. Continuing forward, the front of V1 impacted an embankment before coming to final rest off the roadway facing north.

V1 was traveling north following a two way, two lane road with a curve to the left. V1 lost control on the roadway and began to skid clockwise.  V1 departed the roadway to the right. The left side of V1 impacted a pole. The pole split in two as V1 continued forward. The left wheels impacted the a rock causing V1 to roll to the left. V1 rolled a total of 3 quarter turns coming to final rest on its passenger side, off the roadway, facing northwest.

V1 was traveling east in lane four of a left curved five lane divided (with positive barrier) major highway. V2, V3 and V4 were stopped ahead of V1 due to backed up traffic. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. V2 moved forward and impacted the rear of  V3. V3 was pushed forward and impacted the rear of V4 with its front. All vehicles came to final rest in their original lane of travel, facing east.

V1 was southbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway negotiating a left curve. V1 departed the right side of the roadway impacting a sign with its frontal plane. V1 then impacted a utility pole with its right plane and sent V1 into a clockwise rotation. V1 then overturned, left side leading, eight quarter turns.  V1 impacted a utility marker during the roll sequence. V1 came to final rest on its wheels facing north.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V2 was also traveling southbound on the same roadway, ahead of V1. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2 causing damage. V2 continued southbound coming to final rest on the right side of the road facing south. V1 spun counter clockwise coming to final rest in the northbound lane facing north.
V1 was traveling eastbound on a 2 lane roadway. V2 was legally parked next to curb, on the same roadway, facing east. V1's front contacted V2's rear. Both vehicles came to rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling north west in the #1 lane of a 2 lane undivided roadway. The roadway began curving to the right. V1 departed the roadway to the left. The front of V1 impacted a collection of bushes. V1 traveled through the bushes and down an embankment where the front of V1 impacted a tree. V1 came to rest facing north west against the tree.

V1 was traveling southbound in the number 3 lane of a 3 lane divided roadway, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling westbound in the number 2 lane of a 3 lane divided roadway, approaching an intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection. The left of V1 impacted the front of V2. V1 rotated clockwise and came to rest facing southerly. V2 rotated counter-clockwise and came to rest facing southerly.

V1 was traveling west in the #1 lane of a two lane undivided roadway. V1 departed the road to the right. The front of V1 impacted a cement lining for a ditch. V1 continued forward where a broken piece of the cement impacted the right side of V1. V1 continued forward across a driveway and came to rest facing southwest, partially in a ditch.

V1 was traveling northeast in the #1 lane of a 2 lane undivided roadway. The front of V1 impacted a metal object that was located in the #1 lane.
