V1 traveled across the road to the left and departed the road on the left. The front of V1 impacted a tree. V1 continued forward where the front of V1 impacted a second and then a third tree. V1 continued forward into a ditch where the front of V1 impacted an embankment covered in bushes. V1 came to rest facing north east in the ditch with its left side up against the embankment.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane two way roadway approaching a three way intersection. At the intersection was another vehicle stopped attempting to turn left, and V1 lost directional control due to road conditions being ice covered. V1 departed the roadway to the right and rolled one quarter turn to the right. V1 came to final rest off the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a 3 lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling west on a two lane, one way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1, at the intersection stopped in traffic. V3 was directly behind V2 traveling the same direction. V1 entered the intersection to continue to travel east and the front of V1 contacted the front of V2. V2's back plane then made contact with the front of V3. V1 came to rest after impact facing east. V2 and V3 final rest was at impact.

V1 was entering the roadway from a driveway north bound across the eastbound travel lanes. V2 was traveling east on a four lane roadway in lane two. V3 was parked on a dirt shoulder on the north road edge. As V1 entered the roadway, the left side of V1 contacted the front of V2 in lane two.  V1 continued across the westbound lanes and departed the roadway, the right side of V1 contacted the front left of V3. V1 came to rest partially in lane one of the west bound lanes facing north. V2 came to rest in lane one of the west bound lanes facing north. V3 came to rest on the dirt shoulder of the north road edge facing north.

V1 was traveling north through an intersection from a two-way, not physically divided trafficway, and was in lane 2 (of five lanes). V2 was traveling west through the same intersection from a two-way, not physically divided trafficway, and was in lane 1 (of two lanes). In the intersection, the front end of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V1 came to rest on its wheels facing a northwesterly direction in the intersection. V2 came to rest on its wheels facing a northwesterly direction in the intersection.

V1 was descending a snow covered, two-lane, two-way road that curved to the right while headed north. V1 lost control rotating clockwise, and departed the left side of the road. The left side of V1 impacted a tree, causing it to then rotate counter clockwise where it impacted a landscaping rock with its front left tire. V1 came to rest off of the left side of the road.

V1 was traveling in lane 3 of a seven-lane divided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 entered the roadway from a commercial driveway, and was traveling in lane 2 of the same roadway as V1. V3 was in lane 4 (designated left turn lane), decelerating as it approached the intersection. V1 began to change lanes from lane 3 to lane 2 and it's front plane contacted V2's left plane. V1 then rotated clockwise slightly and rolled backwards and it's left plane contacted V3's right plane. All vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.
V1 was northbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. The front of V1 impacted a deer causing damage. V1 came to final rest on the east side of the road facing north.

V1 was traveling westbound on a two way, two lane roadway in lane 1 approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling northbound on a four lane, two way roadway in lane 1 approaching the same intersection. While passing through the intersection the front of V1 made contact with the right side of V2. Both vehicles came to rest on the roadway

V1 was traveling northbound on a two way, two lane roadway in the northbound lane.  V2 was traveling south in the southbound lane of the same roadway.  V1 departed the lane left where the frontal plane of V1 impacted the frontal plane of V2.  Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway.
Vehicle 1 was driving northbound in lane 1 of a two-lane undivided roadway.  The front of V1 contacted an animal.  V1 came to rest near impact, facing north.

V1 was east bound on a two lane, non divided roadway, negotiating a curve to its left. V1 departed the roadway to the right and the front of V1 contacted a guardrail. V1 then returned to the roadway, crossing both lanes of travel, and struck the guard rail face on the left side of the roadway with its frontal plane. V1 came to final rest on roadway in the west bound lane of travel facing north.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 crossed the left lane line and continued off the left side of road side. The frontal plane of V1 contacted a rock and came to final rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling west on a 5 lane non physically divided roadway, with 2 way left turn lane. V1 began in lane 2. V2 was stopped on a 2 lane roadway pointed north. V1 went over all lane lines to the left and exited the original roadway. V1 entered intersecting roadway, to the right of V2. V1's front contacted V2's right side. V2 then spun around clockwise and came to rest on the other side of it's original roadway. V1 continued across the roadway. V1 exited roadway and the front of V1 contacted a pole. V1 continued forward and came to rest off of the roadway.

Both vehicles were traveling south on the three lane exit ramp of a highway, approaching an intersection. V1 was traveling in lane three, V2 was traveling in lane two. At the intersection both vehicles made a left turn. V1 departed its lane of travel and impacted the left side of V2 with its front. V2 rotated clockwise and departed the road to the south. The front of V2 impacted the pole of a traffic signal. After the impact V1 rotated counter clockwise and came to rest in the eastbound lanes, facing southeast. V2 came to rest at the pole, facing southeast.

V1 was traveling east in lane one on a two lane, two-way undivided right curved roadway. V2 and V3 were legally parked on the street, facing east. V2 was on the south side and V3 was on the north side. The right side of V1 impacted the rear of V2. V1 rolled left 2-quarter turns and its right side contacted the back of V3 as it slid to rest on its top in the roadway facing northeast.

V1 was north bound on a four lane physically divided roadway, with two lanes north bound, and two lanes south bound. V1 was in the number one lane of travel, when a deer entered its path. V1's frontal plane impacted the animal. V1 then departed the roadway to the right, where its frontal plane impacted a guard rail face. V1 returned to the roadway, crossed both north bound lanes, and came to final rest in the median.

V1 was traveling east in lane two of a three lane divided (no positive barrier) roadway. V1 departed its lane of travel to the right, crossed another lane of travel and departed the roadway to the south. The right front wheel impacted a raised curb. V1 continued to drive off road and impacted two trees with its front. The second, smaller tree, fell onto the roof of V1, causing damage to the roof as well as the right side. V1 rotated clockwise and impacted a brick wall with its front. V1 bounced off the wall and moved backwards to the north. V1 came to rest partially in lane one of the roadway and partially off road, facing south.

V1 was traveling north in lane one of a two lane undivided (two-way traffic) roadway, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling west in lane two of a four lane divided (no positive barrier) roadway, approaching the same intersection. Within the intersection, the front of V2 impacted the right side of V1. V1 rotated clockwise and came to rest within the intersection, facing northeast. V2 rotated clockwise and came to rest within the intersection, facing northwest.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a 2 lane roadway while negotiating a curve to the left. V2 was traveling on the same roadway, traveling westbound, and negotiating a curve to the right. V2 crossed over the lane line to the left. V1's front contacted V2's front. V1 came to rest off of the roadway to the right. V2 came to rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling west and exiting a private driveway to the right. V2 was traveling north, in lane 2, on a 2 lane and physically divided highway. V1's left side contacted V2's front. Both vehicles came to rest on the roadway.

V1 was northbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 departed the right side (east) of the road traveling down an embankment hitting a tree trunk with the right plane causing damage. V1 came to rest near the point of impact facing northeast.

Vehicle #1 (V1) was traveling west in lane one of a two-lane undivided trafficway.  V1 departed the road to the right.  The front of V1 contacted a mailbox.  V1 began to rotate counter-clockwise and rolled to the right four quarter-turns.  During the rollover, the top of V1 contacted  a sign post. V1 came to rest off the road to the north on its wheels, facing south.

V1 was traveling east on a 2-lane roadway. V2 was legally parking on the eastbound side of roadway. A non-contact vehicle was legally parked on the westbound side of roadway. V1 traveled off the right side of the roadway and its right side contacted the left side of V2. V1 rotated clockwise then rolled 3-quarter turns left the 1 quarter turn right and came to rest on the roadway on its top facing southeast.

V1 was traveling in lane three of a four lane divided highway. V2 was traveling on the same roadway in front of V1. The frontal plane of V1 made contact with the rear plane of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling eastbound in a single lane attempting to exit the parking lot. V2 was traveling southbound in the second lane of a four lane, two-way roadway. A non-contact vehicle in the first lane traveling southbound stopped for V1 to turn left. V1 attempted to turn left to continue travel northbound. The frontal plane of V1 impacted the right side plane of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway: V1 was facing east and V2 was facing south.

V1 was traveling west on a two-way (not physically divided) trafficway in lane 2 (of four lanes) when it departed its lane on the right and then departed the road on the right.  V1's front end came into contact with a pole, and the pole then came into contact with V1's top.  V1 came to rest on its wheels facing a westerly direction atop the sidewalk on the north side of the trafficway.

V1 and V2 were both traveling east, in lane 2, on a two lane, non-positively divided roadway. V2 had come to a stop for a traffic light when V1's front plane contacted V2's rear plane. V2 came to final rest in lane 2, on the roadway, approximately 3.5 meters from the initial contact. V1 fled the scene after impact.

V1 was traveling south west in the #2 lane of a 4 lane divided roadway. V2 was traveling north west in the #2 lane of a 3 lane undivided roadway. V1 was crossing through the intersection. V2 was turning left to head south west. The front of V1 impacted the right of V2. V1 and V2 traveled south west after the initial impact. V2 came to rest facing south west in the #3 lane just through the intersection. V2 continued south west in the #3 lane and the left front wheel impacted the curb median before V1 came to rest in the #3 lane facing south west.

V1 was traveling northbound in the number 2 lane of a 5 lane divided roadway. V2 and V3 were traveling southbound in the number 4 lane of a 5 lane divided roadway, preparing to turn left. V1, V2, and V3 entered the intersection. The front of V1 impacted the front of V2. This impact caused the front of V3 to impact the rear of V2. V1 rotated clockwise and came to rest facing northerly. V2 and V3 came to rest facing westerly.

V1 was traveling east in the #1 lane of a 2 lane undivided roadway. V2 was traveling south in the #1 lane of a 2 lane undivided roadway. V3 was parked facing south on the west shoulder south of the intersection. V1 turned right in the intersection. V2 crossed through the intersection. The left side of V1 impacted the front of V2. V1 rotated clockwise and the left side of V1 contacted the right side of V2. V1 continued forward off the roadway to the right where the front of V1 impacted the back of V3. V1 came to rest on the west shoulder facing south. V2 came to rest in the #1 lane facing south. V3 came to rest off the road facing south.

Vehicle 1 was southbound on a two way, two lane roadway.  Vehicle 1 departed the roadway to the right.  Vehicle 1's front plane struck an embankment.  Vehicle 1 continued south in the ditch with the right plane sideswiping the  embankment.  Vehicle 1 undercarriage struck a rock in the ditch.  Vehicle 1 continued down a slopping embankment with the front left wheel striking rocks.  Vehicle 1 left plane had contacted an unknown object.  vehicle 1 came to rest near the bottom of the embankment facing south.

V1 was eastbound in lane one of a two-lane, non-physically divided roadway.  V2 and V3 were legally parked on the roadway, facing east, against the south curb. The front of V1 impacted the back left corner of V2.  V1 continued forward and its front impacted the rear of V3.  All vehicles came to rest facing east.  V1 against V3 and V2 just forward of impact.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a two lane two-way non physically divided road in lane 1 negotiating a slight left curve. V2 was also traveling west behind V1. V1 pulled off the right side of the road to attempt to make a "U" turn. The left side of V1 contacted the front of V2. V1 came to rest facing south/east in the east bound lane. V2 came to rest still facing west after impact.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a two lane two-way non-physically divided road way in lane 1, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north on a two lane two-way non-physically divided roadway in lane 1, approaching the same intersection.  Both vehicles entered the intersection and the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2.  V1 came to rest in the north/east corner of the intersection. V2  came to rest in the west bound lane on the east side of the intersection.

V1 was traveling south on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling east on a two way, two lane undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. V1 began to turn left as V2 entered the intersection and the front of V2 contacted the right side of V1. V1 rotated counter-clockwise and came to rest in the intersection facing east. V2 came to rest in the southeast corner of the intersection facing southeast.

V1 was traveling north east on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 crossed the right lane line then departed the right roads edge. V1 traveled up the guardrail and began in a counter clockwise yaw. V1 rolled primarily to the right over the guardrail and down an embankment contacting several trees. V1 came to final rest off the roadway.

V1 was heading east on a four lane, one-way roadway. V1 departed its initial travel lane and then the roadway to the left. The front of V1 contacted a utility pole. V1 was redirected back onto the roadway, and crossed two lanes before coming to final rest facing south.

V1 was making a left turn headed southbound on a divided, three lane roadway. V2 was traveling straight northbound in lane one, of a two way, three lane, undivided roadway. As V1 was making the left turn, V1's front plane came into contact with V2's right side plane. Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling eastbound in lane three of a two way divided roadway in the left turning lane. V2 was traveling westbound in lane two of a two way divided roadway. As V1 was making a left turn at the intersection, the right side plane of V1 made contact with the frontal plane of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 and V2 were travelling West on a 4 lane 2 way not physically divided roadway. V1 attempted to pass in the right lane when V2 began to change lanes to the right. V1 Left plane struck V2 right plane causing V1 to tip over onto it's Right plane. V1 came to rest facing North in the entrance to a parking lot.

Vehicle 1 was southbound on a two way, two lane roadway crossing through an intersection.  Vehicle 2 was eastbound on a two way, 5 lane roadway crossing the same intersection.  Vehicle 1's front plane struck the left plane of vehicle 2.  Vehicle 1 came to rest in the roadway facing south.  Vehicle 2 came to rest facing east in the roadway.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane, two way roadway divided by a two-way left center turn lane. V2 was stopped in the same lane on the same roadway. The front plane of V1 contacted the rear plane of V2. V1 rotated clockwise and came to rest on the roadway facing northwest. V2 rotated clockwise and came to rest on the roadway facing northwest.

V1 was traveling southbound in the second lane of a three lane, two-way roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling westbound in the second lane of a four lane, two-way roadway approaching an intersection. V1 was attempting to turn left to continue traveling eastbound. The left side plane of V1 was impacted by the frontal plane of V2 as both vehicles entered the intersection at the same time. As V1 rotated counterclockwise, it's frontal plane impacted the left side plane of V2. V2 departed the second lane on the left and entered into the third and fourth lane, traveling in the wrong direction.V1 came to final rest in the roadway facing west. V2 then departed the roadway on the left impacting a curb with its frontal plane. V2 came to final rest off the roadway facing south.

V1 was traveling northwest in the number 1 lane of a 4 lane divided trafficway. V1 departed the roadway to the right where the front of V1 impacted a wall. There is also an unknown event to the rear. V1 then rotated clockwise and came to rest facing southerly on the east shoulder.

V1 was traveling northwest following a two-way, two lane road. V2 entered the same roadway from a driveway on the right and was traveling at lower speed in front of V1.  The front of V1 impacted the back of V2. V1 came to final rest on the roadway facing northwest. V2 departed the roadway to the right before coming to final rest facing north.

V1 was traveling south in the second of four lanes on a positively divided, two-way road. V2 was traveling south in the third lane of the same roadway. V1 changed lanes to the left and the left side of V1 contacted the right side of V2. V1 departed the location without stopping. V2 came to rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling west on an undivided, two-way roadway in the second of four lanes. V2 was traveling east in the first lane on the same roadway. V1 lost directional control and started to rotate counterclockwise. V1 departed the lane on the left side and traveled into the eastbound lanes of travel. The right side of V1 contacted the front of V2. V1 departed the roadway on the south road edge and came to rest off the roadway. V2 came to rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling in a northerly direction on a 2 lane non-divided roadway. V1 applied brakes and began to skid laterally in a counter clockwise motion. Vehicle left the roadway to the right and rolled over right side leading rolling 1 quarter turn. V1 came to rest on its right side off of the roadway.

V2 was traveling southbound on a 3 lane physically divided highway, in lane 3. V1 was originally traveling northbound and made a U turn to go southbound. V1's left side contacted V2's front. Both vehicles came to rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling northbound on a 3 lane divided roadway in lane 2 approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling eastbound on a 3 lane one way roadway in lane 2 approaching the same intersection. During the intersection the front of V1 impacted the right side of V2. V1 rotated clockwise and V2 rotated counter clockwise. The right side of V2 then contacted the front of V1. Both vehicles came to rest in the intersection facing northeast.

V1 was traveling north in lane one of a two-lane undivided straight roadway. V1 departed its lane of travel to the left, crossed the oncoming lane of traffic and departed the roadway to the left. The front of V1 impacted a Fire Hydrant. The right front wheel impacted a raised curb. V1 slightly rotated counter clockwise and came to rest partially on the side of the road and partially on the street, facing northwest.

V1 was traveling south on a 3 lane divided roadway approaching an intersection for an entrance ramp to a major highway. V2 was traveling north on the same roadway in lane 2. At the intersection V1 attempted to turn left and the front of V2 impacted the right side of V1. V1 rotated counter clockwise and came to rest facing northeast. V2 rotated clockwise and came to rest facing northeast straddling the road edge and lane 1.

V1 was traveling east in lane two of a three-lane roadway. V2 was traveling west on the same roadway. V1 departed its initial travel lane to the left. The front of V1 connected with the front of V2. Both vehicles came to an uncontrolled final rest near the point of impact.

V1 and V2 were traveling east on a two lane divided interstate, V1 was in lane one and V2 was in lane two. V1 completed a U-turn and started traveling west in lane 2. The front of V1 connected with the front of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest near point of impact.

V1 was eastbound in lane one on a four lane, two way, divided roadway. As it began to travel over an elevated bridge, V1 departed its initial travel lane to the left then struck a curb on the left side of the road with the left front wheel, causing damage. V1 then traveled over the curbing and the left side of V1 contacted a concrete traffic barrier. V1 came to final rest in the left lane facing east, east of the impact area.

V1 was negotiating a right curve while traveling west on two-lane, two-way, snow covered gravel road. V1 lost control and departed the left side of the road and down an embankment where its front plane impacted a tree. V1 came to rest off of the left side of the road.

V1 was traveling north on a two-lane, two-way road when a deer entered the roadway. V1 veered right to avoid the deer and departed the right side of the road where its front plane impacted a utility pole. V1 rotated clockwise where it rolled over two quarter turns, coming to rest on its roof in the roadway.

V1 was traveling west on a 2-lane 2-way not physically divided roadway. V2 was traveling east on the same roadway. V1 began to turn left into a parking lot and the front of V1 contacted the front of V2. V1 rotated counter-clockwise and the right side of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V1 came to rest in the westbound lane facing southeast and V2 came to rest in the eastbound lane facing southeast.

V1 was backing out going westbound on a two way roadway with a single lane of travel in each direction. V2 was traveling northbound on a two way roadway with a single lane of travel in each direction. At the intersection, the back right side of the trailer of V1 made contact with the frontal plane of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling northbound in the first lane of a two way roadway with three lanes of travel. V1 departed the roadway on the right side and the frontal plane of V1 made contact with a tree. V1 traveled forward and proceeded to make impact with a garbage can, a bus sign, and another tree with the frontal plane. V1 then came to final rest off the roadway.

V1 was headed westbound on a multi lane roadway making a left turn. V2 was traveling straight southbound. V1's right plane came into contact with V2's front plane. Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling south west in the #1 lane of a 2 lane undivided roadway. V2 was traveling north east in the #1 lane of a 2 lane undivided roadway. V1 began a U-Turn in the middle of the intersection. The right side of V1's Trailer impacted the front of V2. V1 came to rest in the middle of the intersection facing east. V2 continued off the roadway to the left where V2 came to rest facing north east on the north shoulder.

V1 and V2 were traveling south in the number 1 lane of a 2 lane interstate on-ramp, approaching a metering light. V2 came to a stop for the metering light. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. Both vehicles came to rest facing south in the roadway.

V1 was traveling south on a two-lane two-way road.V2 had been traveling on the same roadway in front of V1.  V2 stopped to make a left turn into a private driveway. The front plane of V1 struck the rear plane of V2. Upon impact V2 departed the road on the right side and came to final rest off the roadway. V1 came to final rest on the roadway.

Vehicle 1 and Vehicle 2 were traveling east in lane 1 of a three lane non-physically divided roadway. After both vehicles passed through a four-legged intersection, Vehicle 2 came to a stop. The front of Vehicle 1 contacted the rear of Vehicle 2. Both vehicles came to final rest in the original lane of travel.

V1 was traveling west in lane two of a four lane divided (with positive barrier) major highway. V2 was traveling in lane one of the same highway, ahead of V1. V1 changed lanes to the right. The front of V1 impacted the the rear of V2. V2 started to rotate counter clockwise and crossed all lanes of traffic to its left. The front of V2 impacted the concrete traffic barrier. V2 came to rest in lane four, facing south. V1 came to rest in lane one, facing west.

V1 was traveling east in lane two in the westbound lanes on a 2-lane  physically divided roadway. V2 was traveling west in lane two on the same roadway. The frontal plane of V1 struck the frontal plane of V2. Both vehicles came to rest a short distance east of the point of impact, in their initial travel lane, still in contact with each other's frontal planes. V2 was facing northwest and V1 was facing southeast at final rest.

V1 was traveling north on a four lane, two way roadway with a left and right turn lane, passing through a four leg intersection. V2 was traveling south on a three lane, two way roadway with a left turn lane, turning left at the same four leg intersection. The frontal plane of V1 struck the frontal plane of V2. V1 came to rest heading north, at the northeast corner of the intersection. V2 came to rest heading east, near the point of impact.

V1 was traveling northwest on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway. V1 departed the right hand side (east) of the roadway contacting a cable barrier guardrail with its frontal plane. V1 then proceeded forward reentering their initial travel lane before coming to final rest on the roadway.

Vehicle #1 (V1) was traveling south in lane two of a three-lane undivided roadway.  Vehicle #2 (V2) was stopped facing south, waiting to turn left at an intersection, in the same lane.  The front of V1 contacted the back of V2.  V1 came to rest on the south edge of the intersection still facing south.  V2 came to rest on the east edge of the intersection facing east.

Vehicle #1 was traveling northwest in lane two of a two-lane divided trafficway without a positive barrier.  V1 departed the roadway to the left.  The front of V1 contacted a ditch.  V1 entered another roadway from the right and departed that roadway to the right into the median.  V1 came to rest in the median, facing northeast.

V1 was traveling northbound in the number 1 lane of a 2 lane undivided roadway. V1 was approaching a curve. V1 departed the roadway to the right where the front of V1 impacted a concrete wall. V1 came to rest facing north on the east shoulder.

Vehicle #1 was traveling east in lane one of a two-lane divided trafficway without a positive barrier.  The front of V1 contacted an animal in the roadway.  V1 came to rest in the roadway, facing east.

V1 was traveling southeast in lane one of a two-lane undivided roadway. A deer crossed the roadway from north to south, striking a westbound vehicle and then striking the front plane of V1. The deer then struck the undercarriage of V1. V1 then made a U-turn and came to a controlled stopped off the roadway on the westbound side.

V1 was traveling south following a two-way, three lane road.  A non-contact vehicle was stopped in the roadway in front of V1. V1 steered to the right, onto the shoulder, in an attempt to pass the non-contact vehicle. V2 was traveling north on the same two-way, three lane road in the second lane of travel. V2 was making a left turn into a driveway, across the path of V1. The front of V1 impacted the right of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest off the roadway facing south.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 crossed the left lane line and departed the left road edge. The undercarriage of V1 contacted the ground and came to final rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling west on a four lane roadway approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered into the intersection. The left of V1 contacted the front of V2. Both vehicles came to a final rest near the point of impact.

V1 and V2 were traveling east on a 2 lane divided bidirectional roadway. V2 was towing a medium/heavy disabled truck. V2 stopped on the roadway to make a right turn.V1's frontal plane impacted the rear of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway in their lane of travel.

V1 was traveling south on a two-lane bidirectional roadway negotiating a slight curve to the left. V1 departed the left (east) side of the roadway where its front end impacted a guardrail face two separate times. V1 rotated counterclockwise and its right plane swiped the guardrail face. V1 came to final rest off the east roadside against the guardrail.
V1 was traveling east on a 3 lane divided roadway in lane 3. V1 departed the roadway to the left, into the median and the front of V1 impacted a light pole. V1 came to rest in the median facing east.

V3 was stopped facing west in lane 1, the left turn lane, on a 4-lane roadway. V1 was traveling west directly behind V3. V2 was traveling east in lane 3 on a 4-lane divided roadway and V4 was traveling east in lane 2 on the same roadway as V2. V1 steered left to avoid V3 and entered the intersection as V2 also entered the intersection. The front of V1 contacted the front of V2. As V4 entered the intersection, V2 was pushed back into the front of V4 and the back of V2 contacted the front of V4. V1 rolled backwards and the back of V2 contacted the front of V3 and came to rest. V2 and V4 came to rest in the intersection facing east.

V1 was traveling southwest in lane 2, a right turn lane, on a 7 lane divided roadway. V2 was also traveling southwest, in lane 3, on the same roadway. V2 had stopped at a traffic signal when V1 departed it's lane on the left side. V1's front plane then contacted V2's rear plane. After impact, both vehicles then rotated in a counter clockwise direction, came to final rest close to the point of impact, and were located in lanes 3 and 4 on the roadway.

V1 was traveling north, in lane one, on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. While negotiating a left curve in the roadway, V1 possibly experienced a tire issue and lost control of the vehicle. V1 then departed the roadway on the right side, traveled down an embankment, and contacted a tree with it's front plane. V1 continued traveling down the embankment, contacted a second tree with its right side plane, and then contacted a third tree with its left side plane. V1 came to final rest, off of the roadway, approximately 59 meters from the impact with the first tree.

V1 was traveling south in lane two on a two lane median divided roadway. V2 was also traveling south on the same roadway in lane one in front of V1. Attempting to avoid a collision with a non-contact vehicle merging into lane two V1 departed the left hand side of the roadway. V1 continued forward returning to the roadway and crossing the right lane line into the same lane as V2. The right side plane of V1 impacted the left side plane of V2. V1 continued forward in a counter-clockwise rotation as its full right side plane stayed in contact with V2's right side plane. V1 continued forward, coming to a final rest partially off of the roadway on the left (east) shoulder of the roadway. V2 continued forward and came to a final rest on the right (west) side shoulder of the roadway.

V1 was traveling north on a two-lane, non-divided roadway. V1 departed the lane to the left, departed the roadway to the left, and the left plane impacted a tree. V1 came to rest on the roadway facing northeast..

V1 was traveling west in lane one of a three lane, undivided, icy roadway. V1 was turning right when it departed the right road edge while rotating clockwise.    V1 contacted a metal utility pole with its left side. V1 rotated clockwise and came to rest in the roadway facing northeast. The driver was ejected during the crash.

V1 was traveling northbound in the second lane of a two lane, one-way roadway. V2 was traveling northbound in the first lane of a two lane, one-way roadway. V1 began to rotate clockwise and departed the second lane into the first lane on the right. V1 came to rest facing east. The frontal plane of V1 was impacted by the frontal plane of V2, as V2 was moving forward. Both V1 and V2 came to final rest on the roadway: V1 was facing east and V2 was facing north.

V1 was traveling east on a divided trafficway (median strip with positive barrier) in lane 1 (of four lanes) and was approaching V2, which was stopped/legally parked facing east on the right hand shoulder.  V1 departed the roadway on the right and its front end came into contact with the back end of V2.  V1 reentered the roadway and came to rest on its wheels facing a northeasterly direction in lanes 2 and 3, east of V2.  V2 was pushed into the roadway (rotating clockwise) where it came to rest on its wheels facing a southwesterly direction in lanes 1 and 2.

V1 was traveling north on a two-way (not physically divided) trafficway in lane 1 (of two lanes) and was approaching V2.  V2 was traveling in the same direction, on the same roadway, and in the same lane as V1, and was slowing in response to V3.  V3 had stopped in preparation for a left turn at the intersection, and was facing north on the same roadway and in the same lane as V2.  V2 stopped in lane 1 in response to V3.  In lane 1, the front end of V1 came into contact with the back end of V2.  V2 was propelled forward and its front end came into contact with the back end of V3.  In lane 1, V1 came to rest on its wheels facing a northerly direction to the rear of V2, V2 came to rest on its wheels facing a northerly direction to the rear of V3, and V3 came to rest on its wheels facing a northerly direction.

V1 was traveling east on a divided trafficway (median strip with positive barrier) in lane 1 ( of four lanes) in the rain, with wet roadway conditions. Control over V1 was lost. V1 rotated counter-clockwise and departed the road on the right, where its right rear wheel/tire contacted the curb at the road edge. V1 overturned (6 quarter turns, leading right) as it ascended and then descended the earthen embankment adjacent to the curb. V1 came to rest on its roof, facing a northeasterly direction in lane 2.

V1 was traveling in a southeasterly direction on a designated north/south two-way, not physically divided trafficway in lane 1 (of four lanes). V2 was traveling in the same direction, on the same roadway, and was in lane 2, to the rear of V1. V1 attempted a U-turn and departed its lane to the left. In lane 2, the left side of V1 contacted the right side of V2. V1 came to rest on its wheels facing a southeasterly direction in lane 2. V2 came to rest on its wheels facing a southeasterly direction in lane 2, just ahead of V1.

V1 was traveling south on a four lane, two-way, undivided roadway, in lane one.  V2 was traveling on the intersecting four lane, two-way, painted median divided roadway, in lane two, intending to turn left.  Within the intersection, the front of V1 impacted the left side of V2.  V1 came to rest off the SE corner, facing east, on the sidewalk.  V2 came to rest within the intersection, facing SW.

V1 was northbound in the first lane of a two-lane, non-physically divided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was eastbound in the second lane of a four-lane, non-physically divided roadway approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection and the front of V1 impacted the right side of V2. V2 came to final rest in the intersection, facing east. V1 came to final rest in the intersection, facing north.

V1 was traveling northeast on a four lane, median divided roadway, in lane four, turning left at the intersection. V2 was traveling southwest on the intersecting six lane, undivided, one way roadway, in lane two, passing through the intersection.  Within the intersection, the front of V1 impacted the front of V2. Both vehicles came to rest within the intersection, near the impact location.

V1 was traveling west on a five lane, non-divided roadway. V2 was traveling east on the same five lane non-divided roadway. The frontal plane of V1 impacted the frontal plane of V2.  After the initial impact, V1 rotated counterclockwise and came to rest in the eastbound lanes. V2 came to rest at the point of the initial impact.

V1 was traveling east in lane 1 on a three-lane, two-way roadway approaching a four way intersection. V1 departed the roadway to the left and the left front tire contacted a curb. V1 proceeded east through the intersection departing the roadway to the northeast corner of the intersection. V1 continued off the roadway and the front of V1 contacted a snow bank. V1 rolled to the right four quarter turns and came to final rest off the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling eastbound on a 4 lane, One-way, non-physically divided roadway in the lane 4 position. Vehicle 2 was traveling southbound on a 6 lane, Two-way, non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position. Vehicle 1 and 2 entered the intersection at the same time. The left side plane of Vehicle 1 made contact with the front plane of Vehicle 2. Vehicle 1 came to rest in the intersection facing east. Vehicle 2 came to rest in the intersection facing southeast.

Vehicle 1 was traveling westbound on a 4 lane, one-way, non-physically divided roadway in the lane 2 position. Vehicle 2 was traveling northbound on a 2 lane, one-way, non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position. Both Vehicle 1 and Vehicle 2 entered the intersection at the same time. The left plane of Vehicle 1 made contact with the front plane of Vehicle 2. Vehicle 1 came to final rest facing northwest in the intersection. Vehicle 2 also came to final rest facing northwest in the center of the intersection.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a two lane, two-way, non-physically divided road way attempting to park behind legally parked Vehicle 2 on the right side of the road. V1's front contacted the rear of V2. V1 then crossed over to the south side of the road and the front of V1 contacted the front of V3 which was legally parked facing east. final rest for V1 was after impact with V3. facing west.

V1 was on the west side shoulder facing south. V2 was southbound on a 5 lane with middle turn lane roadway in the number 2 lane. V1 crossed into traffic lanes to make a u-turn when the left side of V1 was contacted by the front of V2. V2 then traveled across all travel lanes and departed the roadway to the left and the front then left side of V2 contacted a barbed wire fence and came to rest facing east. V1 came to rest on the roadway facing south.

V1 traveling northbound in  lane one of a two lane, two-way, undivided roadway. V2 entering the same roadway backing from a residence driveway adjacent to the roadway.  V1 front plane contacted V2 front plane.

V1 was traveling northbound on a 2 lane, non divided roadway, in lane 1. V2 was traveling southbound on the same roadway, in lane 1. V1 turned left. V1's right side contacted V2's front. Both vehicles came to rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling in an eastern direction on a two lane, non-divided, bidirectional dirt road. V1 departed the roadway to the right and continued in a south eastern direction, where its left plane impacted a pole. V1 rotated counter clockwise, where it's right plane impacted a pole, before coming to final rest on the right side of the roadway.

V1 was stopped on the west shoulder of a two lane non-physically divided roadway waiting to make a U-turn onto the northbound lane. V2 was traveling southbound on a two lane non-physically divided roadway in lane one. V1 entered the roadway and the left side of V1 was impacted by the front of V2. After impact, V1 rotated counterclockwise 360 degrees and came to rest in the middle of the northbound and southbound lanes facing east. V2 came to rest on the west shoulder facing south.
V1 and V2 were both traveling south on the same highway ramp. V2 stopped ahead of V1. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the ramp.

V1 was traveling east in lane two of a two lane divided roadway. V2 was traveling west in lane two on the same divided roadway. V1 departed the north road edge and traveled onto the dirt/grass median where the front of V1 impacted a sign (event 1). V1 continued on the median and re-entered the roadway in the westbound lanes where the front of V1 impacted the front of V2 (event 2). V1 came to rest in the middle of the median facing south. V2 came to rest in the middle of the median facing southeast.

Vehicle #1 (V1) was traveling north in lane one of a two-lane divided trafficway without a positive barrier.  The front of V1 contacted an animal.  V1 came to rest on the right shoulder, facing north.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a two-way, non-physically divided six lane roadway in the number 1 attempting to turn right at a 4 legged light controlled intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling west on a two-way median divided roadway in the number 2 lane entering the same intersection. In the intersection vehicle 1's left side and Vehicle 2's front made contact with each other. Both vehicles came to rest facing west in the number 1 lane.

V1 was traveling south on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a left curve. V1 departed the right side of the roadway, traveled forward along the grass roadside then traveled down a steep embankment where its front plane contacted a tree. V1 rotated clockwise and as it was leaning to the right, contacted another tree with its right side. V1 then rolled onto its right side and came to rest at the bottom of the embankment facing south.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a 2 lane undivided road in lane 1 approaching an intersection. V1 attempted to turn right at the intersection. V1 departed the road to the left of the southbound leg of the intersection. V1 then impacted a stop sign pole with it's front. V1 continued and the front of V1 impacted a cable guide wire. V1 then rolled over 1 quarter turn right side leading, and came to rest on it's right side facing south.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a two-lane divided road in lane No. 1. V1 departed the road to the right as the driver attempted to steer back to the road and initiated counter-clockwise rotation. V1 was leading with its right side when it rolled over eight (8) quarter-turns. V1 came to rest on it's wheels facing north in lane 1.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane two way undivided roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right and the front of V1 contacted a grass embankment. V1 rotated clockwise then tripped and rolled left 4-quarter turns. While on its roof during the rollover, the right side of V1 contacted a utility box and a utility pole. V1 came to rest on its wheels on the roadside facing east.
V1 was traveling northeast in lane one of an undivided two-lane road. V1 departed the road to the right and it's front plane contacted a tree. V1 came to final rest off the roadway against the tree.

V1 was traveling north negotiating a right curve on a single lane interstate entrance ramp. V2 and V3 were on the same roadway ahead of V1. V2 was stopped in the roadway and the driver was out of V3 attaching V2 to V3 to be towed. V1's front plane contacted the rear plane of V2.  V2 was displaced forward and the front of V2 impacted the rear of V3.  V1 came to rest near impact off the right road edge. V2 was pushed forward and came to rest against V3 near impact.
V1 was traveling north east on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 caught fire and came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling east in the number 1 lane of a 3 lane undivided roadway, preparing to turn right at an intersection. V2 was traveling south in the number 2 lane of a 3 lane divided roadway, approaching an intersection. V1 and V2 entered the intersection. The left side of V1 impacted the front of V2. After the impact V1 rotated clockwise and came to rest facing northerly in the southbound number 1 lane, south of the intersection. V2 came to rest facing southerly in the southbound number 1 lane, south of V1.

V1 was turning right to exit a private driveway and travel west on a 4 lane, two way, non-divided roadway. V2 was traveling west in lane two of the same roadway. V2 departed the left road edge into the grass median where its front plane contacted a cable barrier. V2 came to rest in the median facing south.

V1 was northbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. The front of V1 impacted a deer. V1 came to final rest on the right side of the road facing north.

Vehicle #1 (V1) was traveling west.  V1 entered a T-intersection and departed the end of the road.  The front of V1 contacted a metal handrail (event 1).  V1 began to rotate counterclockwise and continued west.  The right of V1 contacted a fence (event 2), followed by two trees (events 3 and 4).  The left of V1 contacted another fence (event 5). V1 was traveling south on a two-lane, two-way road that curved to the left.V1 departed the roadway to the right where it impacted a utility pole with its right side two times. V1 continued down the road and came to rest on the right side of the road.

V1 and V2 were travelling North on a 2 lane 2 way not physically divided roadway. V2 was stopped to turn into a parking area. V1 front plane struck V2 rear plane. Both vehicles came to rest facing North.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane divided highway in lane two in front of V2 and behind V3. V2 was traveling south on a two lane divided highway in lane two behind V1. V1 was traveling west on a non-physically divided two lane highway in lane one. V1 departed the right side of the roadway and traveled along the right roadside. V1 was traveling southeast in lane one on a two lane roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling northeast in lane one of a two lane roadway approaching the same intersection. V1 was traveling east in lane one of a two-lane divided roadway, negotiating a right curve. V1 departed it's travel lane to the right, then departed the roadway to the right. V1 was traveling northwest in lane one of a two lane roadway. V1 departed its travel lane to the left then departed the left road edge. V1 contacted a culvert rotated counter clockwise and tripped and rolled two quarter turns coming to rest on the top plane off of the left road edge.

V1 was westbound in the first of three lanes on a divided, two-way roadway approaching a four legged intersection. V1 was traveling west in the third of five lanes on a divided, two-way roadway. V2 was disabled facing west in the same lane ahead of V1. The front of V1 contacted the back of V2. V1 was traveling north on a two-lane, two-way road and stopped to make a left turn. V2 was directly behind V1, traveling in the same direction when the front of V2 impacted the rear of V1. Both vehicles came to rest in the road.

V1 was traveling south on a two-lane, two-way road, passing through a T-intersection. V2 was traveling east on a two-lane, two-way road approaching the same T-intersection. The front of V2 impacted the front of V1 and both vehicles came to rest south of the intersection.

V1 was traveling westbound on a two lane undivided two roadway in lane 1. V1 was negotiating a right curve that turned the roadway north. V1 departed the roadway to the left and the front of V1 impacted a tree. V1 rotated counter clockwise and came to rest against the tree facing west.

V1 was traveling east on a 4 lane undivided roadway in lane 1 approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north on a 2 lane undivided roadway in lane 1 approaching the same intersection. V1 was traveling westbound on lane one of a two lane, two way, not physically divided roadway approaching an intersection. V1 was eastbound on a two-lane, divided highway with a grass median. V1 lost control and departed the right side of the roadway traveling in a clockwise yaw down an embankment. V2 came to rest on its wheels, facing a southwesterly direction on the right shoulder. V3 was driven to the right shoulder, where it came to rest on its wheels facing a southwes

V1 was negotiating a right curve, traveling north, in the first of two lanes on an undivided, two-way roadway. V1 departed the roadway on the left side and the front of V1 contacted a house.
