V1 was traveling east bound on a two lane, bidirectional, narrow roadway with a negative grade and a curve to the right. The roadway at the time was snow/ice covered. There was a steep positive grade north of the roadway and a steep negative slope protected by a guard rail south of the roadway.   V2 was plowing snow on the same road, approaching V1 from the opposite direction. V1 lost control and departed its lane of travel to the left, and departed the roadway to the left, where its frontal plane impacted an embankment. V1 rotated counter clockwise and rolled one quarter turn and on to its passenger side, sliding towards V2. V2 had come to a complete stop. V1's top plane impacted the plow of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway in the west bound lane, with V1 on its passenger side.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a two lane not physically divided two way road approaching a four leg intersection controlled by a stop sign. Vehicle 2 was traveling south on a two lane not physically divided two way road approaching the same four leg intersection controlled by a stop sign. Vehicle 1 entered the intersection and proceeded to turn left. Upon entering the intersection the front plane of Vehicle 2 contacted the left plane of Vehicle 1. Vehicle 1 rotated clockwise and departed the roadway on the right side. The front plane of Vehicle 1 contacted some shrubbery before coming to final rest off the roadway. Vehicle 2 continued south and came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling westbound on a four lane, two-way roadway passing through a four-way intersection in lane two. V2 was traveling southbound on a three lane, one-way roadway approaching the four-way intersection. V1's front plane contacted V2 left plane. V1 came to final rest at intersection. After initial impact with V1, V2 continued south where it rotated clockwise, before departing the right side roadway. V2 contacted the curb and a pedestrian crossing signal with an unknown plane before coming to final rest off roadway.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway negotiating a curve. V1 crossed the left lane line and began in a counter clockwise yaw. V1 departed the left roadside contacting a utility pole with its right plane. V1 then rotated clockwise and came to final rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway negotiating a curve. V1 departed the right road edge contacting a utility pole with its frontal plane. V1 continued off the roadway and contacted a second utility pole with its frontal plane. V1 then contacted a tree with its front plane. V1 began to roll primarily to the left 6 quarter turns in all down a slight embankment back onto the roadway. V1 came to final rest on the roadway on its roof

V1 was traveling eastbound on a 2 lane divided roadway in lane 1 approaching an intersection. V2 was stopped at the intersection facing northbound in lane 1 of a 2 lane undivided roadway. V1 swerved to the right to avoid a vehicle turning right from lane 2 at the intersection. V1 departed the roadway and the front of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V2 rotated clockwise and came to rest facing north. V1 came to rest facing east.

V1 was traveling southeast in lane one of a two lane roadway negotiating a left curve attempting to pass another vehicle. V1 departed its travel lane to the left then departed the left road edge in a clockwise yaw. V1's undercarriage contacted a ditch and V1 tripped and rolled left six quarter turns contacting a tree before coming to rest on it's top off the right road edge.

V1 was traveling east on a three lane divided roadway in lane one approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling east on a three lane divided roadway in lane one approaching an intersection. As V2 was slowing to a stop, the front of V1 contacted the rear of V2. V1 came to rest in lane one facing east. V2 came to rest in the intersection facing east.

V1 was traveling northbound in a single lane, one way roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling westbound in a single lane, one-way roadway approaching the same intersection. Both V1 and V2 entered the intersection at the same time. The frontal plane of V1 impacted the left side plane of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway: V1 facing north and V2 facing west.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane roadway in lane one. V2 was parked on the west side of the roadway. The front of V1 impacted the front of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in the area of impact, facing their original directions, on the west of the roadway.

V1 was traveling south on an off-ramp approaching a two lane stop sign at an intersection in lane one . V2 was traveling west on a non-physically divided three lane roadway in lane one. As V1 was passing through the intersection towards the south on-ramp, the left side of V1 was impacted by the front of V2. The momentum spun V1 clockwise and the left rear corner contacted the right front corner of V2. Both came to rest in the intersection facing southwest.

V1 was traveling west to south (making a left turn) through an intersection from a two-way, not physically divided trafficway, and was in lane 3 (of four lanes). V2 was traveling east through the same intersection from a two-way, not physically divided trafficway, and was in lane 2 (of five lanes). In the intersection, the front end of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V1 fled the scene without stopping. V2 came to rest on its wheels facing a northeasterly direction in the southeast quadrant of the intersection.

V1 was traveling east through an intersection from a two-way, not physically divided trafficway, and was in lane 2 (of five lanes). V2 was traveling north through the same intersection from a two-way, not physically divided trafficway, and was in lane 1 (of three lanes). In the intersection, the front end of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V1 came to rest on its wheels facing a northeasterly direction in the intersection, and east of V2. V2 came to rest on its wheels facing a northwesterly direction in the intersection, and west of V1.

V1 was traveling north on a two-way (not physically divided) trafficway in lane 1 (of four lanes) when it departed the road on the right and its front end came into contact with a pole.  V1 came to rest on its wheels facing a northerly direction atop the sidewalk on the east side of the trafficway.

V1 was traveling north bound, negotiating a slight curve to the right. V1 was in the three lane on a three lane roadway. There were three lanes north bound, including an on ramp/merge lane, divided by a median and a cable barrier guard rail and three lanes south bound including an off ramp/exit lane.The roadway at the time were slush covered and it was snowing. V1 left the roadway to the left, rotating counterclockwise in doing so. V1 struck the cable barrier with its frontal plane continuing to rotate through the cable barrier causing further damage to the right side, the top and the left side before coming to final rest facing north bound on the left side of the roadway.

V1 was traveling on a one-way, left turn lane controlled by a stop sign, attempting to cross over eastbound lanes and enter a business entrance. V2 was traveling eastbound on a physically divided roadway with three lanes traveling eastbound approaching the business entrance intersection. In the middle of the intersection the front of V2 contacted the right front of V1. V1 came to final rest facing southeast in the middle of the intersection. V2 continued eastbound after impact and came to final rest on the south shoulder facing east.

Vehicle 1 was traveling southbound on a two lane non-physically divided roadway in the the lane 1 position.  Vehicle 2 was traveling westbound on a a two lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position.  Both vehicles entered the intersection.  The left side of Vehicle 1 made contact with the front plane of Vehicle 2.  Vehicle 2 rotated counter clockwise coming to rest in the middle of the intersection facing southwest.  Vehicle 1 rotated clockwise coming to rest facing south near the southwest corner of the intersection.

V1 was traveling southbound on a two lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position.  V2 was traveling eastbound on a two lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position.  Both vehicles entered the intersection.  The right plane of V1 made contact with the front plane of V2.  V1 rotated counterclockwise 90 degrees coming to rest facing east at the southeast corner of the intersection.  V2 rotated clockwise 45 degrees departing the roadway striking utility pole.  V2 came to final rest shortly after pole impact facing south east.
Vehicle #1 was traveling north in lane one of a two-lane, undivided trafficway.  V1 lost control and departed the road to the left.  The front of V1 contacted a tree where it came to final rest.

V1 was traveling northwest in lane one of a two lane roadway. V1 departed the right road edge and the driver steered left to re enter the roadway but lost control. V1 then departed its travel lane to the left then departed the left road edge. V1's left plane contacted a tree where it came to final rest.

V1 was traveling northwest in lane one of a three lane undivided roadway, negotiating a left curve. V1 departed the roadway to the right and it's front plane contacted an embankment. V1 then went airborne for approximately 32m before it's undercarriage contacted a driveway, causing it to trip left. The undercarriage then contacted a utility pole as it began to roll. The vehicle then passed through two barbed wire fences before coming to final rest on it's left side in a field.

V1 was traveling southeast exiting a private drive attempting a left turn. V2 was traveling southwest in lane two of a five lane divided roadway. V1's left plane contacted V2's front plane. V1 then tripped and roll right two quarter turns coming to rest on the roof in the roadway. V2 came to rest at impact.

V1 was traveling southeast in lane one of a four lane undivided roadway, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling northwest in lane two of the same four lane undivided roadway, approaching the same intersection. V2 attempted a left turn. The front of V1 contacted the front of V2. Both vehicles continued to travel and the left plane of V1 contacted the right plane of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest in the intersection.

V1 was traveling south east in the #1 lane of a 3 lane divided roadway. V2 was traveling south east in the #2 lane of a 3 lane divided roadway. V1 was traveling in a merging lane and crossed over the gore point between the #1 and #2 lanes. V1 started to make a U-turn and the left of V1 impacted the front of V2. V1 came to rest in the center median area facing north. V2 came to rest in the gore point facing south east.

V1 was traveling south on a public parking lot, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling west in lane three of a four lane divided (no positive barrier) road, approaching the intersection with the parking lot exit. At the intersection, V1 attempted to turn left into the westbound lanes. Within the intersection, the front of V2 impacted the left side of V1. V1 rotated clockwise and came to rest in lane two facing west. V2 rotated clockwise and came to rest in lane three, facing north.
V1 was traveling eastbound on a two lane divided roadway in lane one. A deer attempted to cross the road and V1 impacted the deer with it's front. V1 came to rest on the shoulder facing eastbound.

V1 was traveling southbound on a two lane undivided two way roadway in lane one approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling eastbound on a two lane undivided two way traffic roadway in lane one approaching the same intersection. Within the intersection the front of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V2 came to rest facing northeast on the east side of the intersection. V1 rotated counter clockwise and came to rest in the intersection facing southeast.

V1 was traveling in a western direction on a two lane, non divided bidirectional roadway with a general north and south orientation. V1 left the roadway to the left rotating counter clockwise in doing so. V1's frontal plane impacted the bottom of a ditch. V1 continued to rotate counter clockwise, where its right plane impacted a utility pole, sheering the pole off. V1's right side then impacted a mail box, as it rotated. V1 crossed over a driveway area and impacted a ditch with its rear plane before coming to final rest on the left side of the roadway, facing east.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane, non-divided bidirectional roadway. V2 was traveling east on the same roadway. A large tree fell from the north side of the roadway, where it impacted V1's top plane, and V2's left plane. V1 came to final rest at the point of impact on the roadway. V2 began to rotate counter clockwise, where it rolled 4 quarter turns coming to final rest on its wheels facing east on the south side of the roadway. During the rollover, V2 impacted a traffic delineator post.

V1 was traveling eastbound, in lane 1 of a 3 lane roadway, while negotiating a curve to the left. An animal was in the roadway and vehicle swerved to miss. V1 exited the roadway to the right. V1's left side contacted a guardrail end and V1 began to rotate counterclockwise and travel south east off the roadway. V1's front and then V1's right side contacted a fence. The fence then contacted the top of V1 Vehicle came to final rest off of the roadway facing east.

V1 was traveling east in lane one of a two-lane undivided (two-way traffic) road, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south in lane two of a two-lane divided (no positive barrier) road, approaching the same intersection.  At the intersection V1 attempted to turn left into the northbound lanes. Within the intersection, the front of V2 impacted the left side of V1. V1 rotated clockwise and came to rest within the intersection, facing east. V2 rotated counter clockwise and came to rest within the intersection, facing south.

V1 was traveling northeast in lane two of a four-lane undivided roadway. V2 was traveling southwest in lane two of the same four-lane undivided roadway. V1 departed its travel lane to the left and its front plane contacted V2's front plane.

Vehicle #1 was traveling east in lane 1 of a two-lane, undivided roadway, negotiating a left curve. V1 departed the road to the right. The front of V1 contacted a tree (event 1). During maximum engagement, V1 slightly rotated clockwise. The rotation was interrupted when the right of V1 contacted a tree (event 2). V1 came to rest on the eastbound roadside facing east.

Vehicle 1 was northbound on a two way, two lane roadway.  Vehicle 1 departed the roadway to the left.  Vehicle 1 left plane struck a wooden fence post. Vehicle 1 rolled to the left onto its left side.  Vehicle 1 came to rest facing north on its left side.

Vehicle 1 was northbound on a two way, two lane roadway negotiating a left curve. Vehicle 1 left the roadway to the right and corrected back to the left. Vehicle 1 corrected back to the left and departed the roadway to the right. Vehicle 1 traveled down an embankment and contacted a field with front end. Vehicle 1 rotated clockwise and its left side contacted the ground. V1 continued to rotate clockwise and its back plane contacted the ground. V1 rotated clockwise and came to rest on the shoulder facing south.

V1 was westbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway negotiating a left curve. V1 departed its initial travel lane to the left then departed the roadway to the left. The front of V1 impacted an embankment and unknown diameter tree.  V1 rotated counterclockwise where the right plane contacted two (2) groups of unknown diameter trees.  V1 continued rapidly rotating counterclockwise, 360 degrees where V1 tripped over, right side leading. While sliding, during the 3rd, quarter turn of the roll, the undercarriage of V1 contacted a mailbox.  V1 then rolled left 1 quarter turn, coming to rest on its roof, off the roadway, near impact with mailbox.

V1 was eastbound on a four lane, two way, roadway divided by a grass median. V1 departed the right side of the roadway in a counter clockwise yaw and overturned right side leading. V1 came to final rest on its right side facing northeast.

V2 was stopped at an intersection in lane 1 of a 3 lane, 2 way roadway with center turn lane.  V1 was traveling eastbound in lane 1 of the same roadway.  The front plane of V1 contacted the back plane of V2.

V1 was traveling northwest on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a right hand curve in the roadway. A deer entered the roadway from the southern shoulder, and in an attempt to avoid the deer V1 departed the right hand (north) side of the roadway. V1 struck a snow/ice embankment with its frontal plane before coming to final rest off of the roadway.

V1 and V2 were traveling eastbound on a two lane roadway negotiating a left curve. V1 lost control after contacting a patch of ice. V1 departed its initial travel lane and then the roadway to the left. The left of V1 connected with an utility pole (event 1). V2, after contacting the same patch of ice, also departed its initial travel lane to the left then departed the left road edge. The left of V2 contacted the right of V1 (event 2). After this impact V1 rotated clockwise and began to travel backwards. The left of V1 contacted the pole a second time as it traveled rearward and rotated. The rear of V1 then contacted a broken brush line and came to rest facing south. V2 came to rest near V1 and also facing west.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane undivided roadway with a two-way left turn lane. V1 was negotiating a left curve when V1 departed the roadway to the right. The front of V1 contacted a tree where it came to final rest.

V1, V2, and V3 were all traveling southeast in lane 3, a left turn lane, on a 5 lane, two way, roadway. While traveling in the turn lane and prior to turning, V1's front plane contacted V2's rear plane. This impact then caused V2's front plane to contact V3's rear plane. All 3 vehicles came to final rest in lane 3, on the roadway, a short distance from their impacts.

V1, V2 , V3, and V4 were traveling south, in the third lane, on a seven lane, non-physically divided roadway. V4, V3 and V2 stopped due to traffic ahead.The front of V1 impacted with the rear of V2 (event 1). The impact forced V2 forward, and the front of V2 impacted with the rear of V3 (event 2). The impact forced V3 forward, and the front of V3 impacted with the rear of V4 (event 3).  V1,V2, V3, and V4 came to final rest in the original lane facing south.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two way roadway, in lane one. V2 was legally parked facing south on the same roadway on the west curb. V1 moved left of center and its front impacted the front of V2. Both vehicles came to rest near impact.

V1 was traveling north on a 2-lane roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south on a 2-lane roadway approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection and as V1 began a left turn, its front plane contacted the front plane of V2. V2 rotated clockwise, departed the road edge and came to rest in a grass median island facing west. V1 came to rest in the northwest corner of the intersection facing west.

V1 was traveling southwest on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a right hand curve in the roadway. V1 departed the left hand lane line and then the left hand side of the roadway (north) striking a tree with its frontal plane. V1 continued forward striking a tree with its frontal plane before coming to a frontal rest off of the roadway.

V1 was traveling north west in lane 1 on a two lane two way divided roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the left and struck a construction sign off the roadway and then returned to the roadway. The front of V1 contacted a guardrail off the roadway and came to final rest on the roadway facing northeast..

V1 was traveling south on a 2-lane roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling east in lane 2 on a 4-lane divided roadway approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection and the right side of V1 was contacted by the front of V2. V1 rotated counter-clockwise and V2 rotated clockwise and the right side of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V1 continued to rotate and came to rest in the eastbound lanes facing east. V2 departed the southeast corner of the intersection and came to rest on the roadside facing south.

V1 and V2 were traveling north on a five lane, barrier divided roadway. V1 was traveling in lane five, V2 was traveling in lane three. V1 departed the roadway to the left and the front of V1 impacted the barrier. V1 then re-entered the roadway to the right and the right side of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V1 then departed the roadway to the left and the front of V1 struck the center barrier a second time. V1 re-entered the roadway to the right and came to rest facing northeast. V2 moved off to the right shoulder and came to final rest facing north.

V1 was traveling south in the first lane of a two-lane, divided roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right, where right front tire impacted a curb. (Event 1) V1 traveled onto the grassy area and the front plane of V1 impacted a pole. (Event 2) After the impact, V1 rotated counterclockwise, and the right plane of V1 impacted a tree. (Event 3) V1 came to rest facing south.

V1 was traveling east on a three lane, two-way, stop sign controlled roadway, in lane two, turning left at the t-intersection.  V2 was traveling southeast on a four lane, two-way roadway, in lane two, passing through the intersection.  The front of V2 impacted the left side of V1 within the intersection.  V1 rotated counterclockwise after impact to come to rest facing west.  V2 came to rest just forward of impact.

V1 was traveling east in the first lane of a five-lane, non-divided roadway. V2 was traveling north in the second lane of a two-lane, non-divided roadway. Both vehicles entered the intersection with V1 proceeding straight and V2 attempting to turn left. The front of V1 impacted the left side of V2 in the intersection. V1 came to rest in the intersection, facing east. V2 came to rest in the intersection, facing north.

V1 was traveling westbound on a four lane, two-way, undivided roadway, making a left turn to head southbound. V2 was traveling eastbound on the same four lane, two-way, undivided roadway, as V1, crossing over a four-way intersection. The front plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2. V1 and V2 came to final rest at intersection facing southeast.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a two-lane, two-way, undivided roadway, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling southbound on a two-lane, two-way, undivided roadway, approaching the mentioned intersection with the north and south lanes controlled by a stop sign. The front of V1 contacted the right side of V2 in the middle of the intersection. As a result both vehicles departed the roadway on the southeast corner. The front of V1 contacted a tree located further southeast and came to final rest facing southeast. The front of V2 contacted a ditch and came to final rest further southeast facing southwest.

V1 was traveling southbound on a two lane, two-way, undivided roadway. V1 pulled to the right of the roadway onto a gravel roadway, to make a U-turn to travel northbound. V2 was traveling southbound on the same two lane, two-way, undivided roadway behind V1, prior to V1's U-turn. V2 continued traveling south as V1 executed a U-turn. The front plane of V1 contacted the right plane of V2. V1 came to final rest facing southbound off the right side shoulder. V2 came to final rest in-between lanes facing southbound.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a physically divided roadway with two-lane traveling in the east direction with a left curve. V1 was traveling in lane two attempting to change lanes when V1 lost control and departed the roadway on the right side. V1 continued eastbound off the roadway where the right plane struck a large wooden billboard. V1 came to final rest against the billboard facing northbound.

V1 was traveling north on a two-way, two lane road. As V1 was negotiating the slight left curve in the road, it departed the road to the right. The front of V1 impacted a tree with its frontal plane. Continuing forward, V1's undercarriage impacted a rock. The front of V1 then impacted two more trees before coming to final rest off the roadway facing northeast.

V1 was traveling south following a two-way, two lane road. V1 departed its original travel lane to the left, and then the roadway to the left. The front of V1 impacted a tree. The front of V1 impacted two more trees before coming to final rest on the left side of the roadway facing southeast.

V1 was traveling westbound on a 2 lane undivided roadway. V2 was legally parked on the north side of the same roadway. The front of V2 contacted the front of V2. V1 came to rest in the roadway. V2 did not move.

V1 was traveling west bound on a two lane non divided bidirectional roadway with a down hill grade, while negotiating a slight curve to the left. The roadway had a steep positive grade on the right side, and a steep negative grade on the left side. V1 attempted to avoid an unknown object in the middle of the roadway, where it left the roadway to the right. V1's frontal plane impacted the embankment, and a posted speed limit sign before coming to final rest partially in the west bound lane of travel.

All vehicles were traveling northbound on a 4 lane divided highway. V1 was traveling in lane 4, V2 was traveling in lane 2, and V3 was traveling in lane 1. V1 was attempting to change multiple lanes from lane 4 to the right shoulder. As V1 changed to lane 1 the front of V3 impacted the back of V1. V1 then rotated counter clockwise into lane 2. The front of V1 then impacted the right side of V2. V1 then rotated clockwise and came to rest in lane 1 facing north. V2 came to rest in lane 2 facing north. V1 came to rest in lane 1 facing north.

V1 was traveling north in lane two of a three lane divided (no positive barrier) straight trafficway. V1 lost directional control of the vehicle due to icy road conditions and started to rotate clockwise. V1 departed its lane of travel to the right and impacted a raised curb with its left front wheel. V1 departed the roadway to its right and impacted the face of a guard rail with its left side. V1 started to roll over for three quarter turns, left side leading. V1 went airborne during the roll over and impacted at least three trees with both sides of the vehicle as well as the roof. V1 came to rest on its left side, facing south.

V1 was traveling northbound in lane 1 of  a 2 lane roadway, while negotiating a curve to the left. V1 left the roadway to the right. V1's front contacted a fence. V1 continued forward and then V1's front contacted a rock post causing vehicle to yaw, counterclockwise. V1's right side then contacting a post. V1 straightened out while crossing a private driveway. V1 came to rest on northern side of driveway, off the roadway.

V1 was traveling south on a 2 lane, non-divided roadway, while negotiating a curve to the right. V2 was traveling on the same roadway, northbound, while negotiating a curve to the left. V1 crossed the left lane line. V1's front contacted V2's front. V1 then came to rest on the west side of the roadway. V2 began moving counter clockwise and went off the east side of the roadway, backwards. The back of V2's vehicle contacted an embankment. V2 came to rest at this point.

V1 was traveling north on an exit ramp from the interstate approaching an intersection in lane two of four. V2 was traveling west on the intersecting six lane roadway in lane one. Both vehicles entered into the intersection proceeding straight. The front of V1 contacted the left of V2. V2 came to final rest facing west in lane one. V1 continued on its path of travel.

V1 and V2 were traveling west on a five lane interstate. V1 was in the fourth lane and V2 was in the fifth lane. V2 began to change lanes from lane five to lane four. The left of V1 contacted the left of V2. V1 was redirected to the right where it came to final rest in lane three facing northwest. V2 was redirected to the left, departing its travel lane. The front of V2 impacted with the concrete jersey barrier where it came to final rest.

V1 was traveling west in lane one of a two-lane undivided roadway. V2 was traveling west in lane one of the same roadway, having moved from a street parking space on the eastbound side. The front plane of V1 contacted the back plane of V2. V2 came to final rest near impact. V1 continued, swerving right and departing the roadway to a paved driveway opening before contacting a tree with its right plane. Contact with the tree caused V1 to roll one quarter turn onto it's left side. V1 came to final rest on it's left side on the roadway.

V1 was traveling southwest on a two-lane undivided roadway, approaching a T-intesection. V1 continued to travel through the intersection and its front plane contacted a curb. V1 continued to travel a short distance and came to final rest in a residential yard.

V1 was traveling southeast exiting a private drive attempting a left turn. V2 was traveling southwest in lane two of a five lane undivided roadway approaching V1. V1's left plane was contacted by V2's front plane. Both vehicles came to rest near impact.

V1 was traveling westbound in the second lane of a two lane, one way roadway. V2 was traveling westbound in the first lane of a two lane, one-way roadway. V1 departed right from the second lane into the first lane. The frontal plane of V1 impacted the rear plane of V2. V1 continued forward, sideswiping its' right side plane to the left side plane of V2. The left side plane of V1 sideswiped the right side plane of V2 for a second time. V2 departed from the first lane into the breakdown lane off of the roadway to final rest. V1 departed from the second lane into the first lane and then departed the roadway on the left, coming to final rest in the breakdown lane, off the roadway.  Both V1 and V2 came to final rest off the roadway facing west.

V1 was traveling in a southwesterly direction through the left hand curve of the roadway, on a designated east/west, two-way, not physically divided trafficway, in lane 2 (of four lanes).  V1 departed its lane on the right and was then returned to it lane from the right.  Control over V1 was lost.  V1 skidded laterally in a clockwise rotation as it again departed its lane on the right, and then the road on the right, where its left front wheel/tire came into contact with the curb along the road edge (Event 1).  Outside of the trafficway, V1's front end came into contact with a tubular steel fence (Event 2) and then an adjacent chain-link fence (Event 3) [V1's left side also came into contact with the chain-link fence].  Debris from the chain-link fence was propelled into the right side of V2 (Event 4), which was parked facing a northwesterly direction in a parking area belonging to a business. V1 then overturned in the parking area (4 quarter turns, leading left - Event 5).  During the rollover, components fr

V1 was traveling west on a two-lane, two-way road while passing through an intersection. V2 was traveling south through the same intersection. The front of V1 impacted the left side of V2 causing both vehicles to rotate counterclockwise. V1 departed the right side of the road and its right side impacted a light pole where it came to rest. V2 came to rest in the intersection.

V1 was east bound on a two lane, non divided, bidirectional roadway, when a deer entered the roadway from the right. V1's frontal plane struck the deer. V1 came to final rest on the right side of the roadway.

V1 was traveling southbound in the #2 lane of a 5 lane divided highway. V2 was traveling southbound in the #1 lane of a 5 lane divided highway. V1 changed lanes to the right into the #1 lane. The right side of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V2 departed the roadway to the right and traveled up a dirt embankment. The front of V2 impacted a wall. V2 began rotating counter clockwise along the wall where the left side of V2 impacted a tree. V1 drove to the right shoulder and came to a stop facing south. V2 came to rest facing south off the roadway against the tree.

V1 was traveling eastbound in the number 1 lane of a 2 lane undivided roadway. V2 was traveling southbound in the number 1 lane of a 2 lane divided roadway. V1 and V2 were approaching an intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection at the same time and the left side of V1 impacted the front of V2. V1 rotated clockwise and came to rest facing southerly, south of the intersection, in the roadway. V2 rotated counter-clockwise and came to rest facing easterly in the intersection.

V1 was traveling westbound on a two lane, two-way roadway. V2 was traveling southbound on a two lane, two-way roadway passing though a four-way intersection. An unknown plane of V1 contacted the left plane on V2. V1 came to final rest within the intersection. V2 came to final rest facing southwest in the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling northbound on a five lane non divided roadway in the lane 2 position.  Vehicle 2 was traveling eastbound on a four lane one way roadway in the lane 2 position.  Both V1 and V2 entered the intersection at the same time proceeding straight. The front plane of Vehicle 1 made contact with the right plane of Vehicle 2. V1 departed the right side of the roadway and the left side of V1 side swiped the concrete median. V1 ended up continued backwards along the median where it came to rest facing south.

V1 was traveling north in the first lane on a five lane, two way undivided roadway with a center left turn lane, approaching an intersection.  V2 was traveling north on the same roadway, in the second lane.  V2 changed lanes to the right into lane one and stopped for the intersection.  The front of V1 contacted the back of V2.  Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway in lane one facing north.

V1 and V2 were traveling west on a six-lane, two-way roadway. The east/west travel lanes are delineated by a raised, curbed median. V1 and V2 were traveling in the third lane. V3 was traveling east on the same roadway in lane 2. V1 lost control on the wet pavement, and started to yaw counter-clockwise. The right side of V1 contacted the rear of V2 (Event 1). V1 entered the eastbound lanes. The right side of V1 contacted the front of V3 (Event 2). V1 then rotated rapidly counterclockwise and the right side of V1 then contacted the left side of V3 (Event 3). All vehicles came to final rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane, two way undivided roadway approaching an intersection.  V2 was traveling south on a five lane, two way with center turn lane undivided roadway approaching the same intersection.  At the intersection V1 attempted to turn left and the front of V2 contacted the left side of V1.  Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling westbound in the single lane, one-way roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling northbound in the first lane of a three lane, two way roadway approaching the same intersection. Both V1 and V2 entered the intersection at the same time. The left side plane of V1 was impacted by the frontal plane of V2. Both V1 and V2 came to rest in the roadway: V1 was facing west and V2 was facing north.

V1 was westbound on a 2 lane roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was southbound in lane 1 on a 3 lane roadway approaching the same intersection. In the intersection the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V1 rotated counter-clockwise and came to rest in the southwest corner of the intersection facing southwest. V2 rotated counter-clockwise and came to rest in the southbound lane facing north.

V1 was traveling southbound in lane two on a four-lane, two-way roadway approaching an intersection controlled by a traffic light. V3 was on the mentioned roadway stopped at a traffic light in lane one facing northbound. V2 was traveling eastbound on a two-lane, two-way roadway approaching the same intersection. In the intersection the front of V2 struck the right side of V1 which then led to a side slap where the right side of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V2 then rotates clockwise and departs the roadway where the front plane contacts two trashcans. V1 continues southbound where the front plane contacts the left side of V3. After contact with V1, V3 departs the roadway to the east where the right plane contacts a pole. V1 came to final rest on the northwest corner of the roadway. V2 came to final rest in the northbound lanes facing south. V3 came to final rest off the roadway facing north.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane, one-way roadway in lane one. V2 was traveling east on a two lane, one-way roadway, stopped at intersection waiting on the traffic light in lane two. V1 front plane contacted V2's right plane. V1 and V2 came to final rest at point of impact on roadway.

V1 was traveling west on a two-lane, two-way roadway approaching a four-legged sign controlled intersection. V2 was traveling north one a two-lane, two-way roadway approaching the same intersection. In the middle of the intersection the front plane of V2 contacted the left side of V1. Both vehicles came to final rest in the intersection; V1 was facing north, V2 was facing east.

V1 was traveling northwest on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway. V1 crossed over the left lane line and then departed the left road edge. The frontal plane of V1 contacted a guardrail. V1 then went airborne hitting a sign with its frontal plane. V1 hit a utility pole with an unknown plane while rolling, and hit a building before coming to final rest off the roadway on its side plane.

V1 was traveling east on a three lane, two way, undivided roadway. An unknown vehicle was traveling west on the same roadway. A piece of snow and ice fell from the unknown vehicle and contacted the windshield of V1. V1 came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling west on a four lane undivided roadway. V2 was was traveling south on a four lane undivided roadway. Both vehicle were approaching the same intersection. The right of V1 contacted the front of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest near the point of impact.

V1 was westbound on a two lane, two way, undivided traffic way. V1 departed the initial travel lane to the left then departed the left side of the roadway in a counter clockwise yaw. V1 traveled over a ditch while beginning to roll left side leading two quarter turns. V1 came to rest on its roof facing north.

V1 was traveling west in lane one, on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway and was negotiating a right curve in the roadway. V2 was traveling east on the same roadway and was negotiating a left curve in the roadway. In the curve of the roadway, V1's front plane contacted V2's left side plane. V2 then departed the roadway to the right, came to final rest with its RF, RR, and LF tires off of the roadway and the LR tire on the roadway, and was approximately 9 meters from the initial contact. V1 came to final rest on the roadway approximately 9 meters past the initial contact.

V1 was traveling south on a two-lane, two-way, snow covered road. V2 had just entered the same road from a parking lot heading south in front of V1. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2 and both vehicles came to rest in the parking lot on the east side of the road.

V1 was traveling south on a two-lane, two-way road when it departed the right side of the road and impacted a snow bank with its front plane. V1 came to rest in the snow off of the right side of the road.

V1 traveling south bound in lane one of a five lane, two-way, not physically divided roadway with a left turn lane. V2 traveling was also traveling in lane one of the same south bound roadway.  V1 rear plane was contacted by V2 front plane.

V1 was traveling northwest in lane one of a two lane roadway negotiating a right curve. V1 departed its travel lane to the left then departed the left road edge. V1's front undercarriage contacted a tree then V1 tripped and rolled left one quarter turn. V1's top was contacted by a tree during the roll. V1 came to rest on its left side off the left road edge.

V1 was traveling southeast in lane one of a two lane roadway negotiating a left curve. V1 departed it travel lane to the left then departed the left road edge on a bridge. V1 rolled left two quarter turns coming to rest in a creek bed on its top plane.

Vehicle 1 was eastbound on a two way, four lane, undivided roadway.  Vehicle 1 crossed the two westbound lanes and departed the roadway to the left.  Vehicle 1 left back plane struck the embankment as started to climb.  Vehicle 1 right front wheel dug into the dirt embankment as the vehicle neared the top of the embankment. After vehicle 1 crested the top of the embankment, the front plane struck the ground.  Vehicle 1 continued down into a ravine coming to rest facing north.  Right  plane and left front plane damage were unknown events or objects struck.

V1 was travelling South on a 2 lane 2 way not physically divided highway. V1 lost control on the snow and departed the roadway to the left while rotating counter clockwise. V1 tripped and rolled 4 quarter turns. V1 came to rest facing West.

Vehicle 1 was northbound on a two way, two lane, ice covered roadway.  Vehicle 2 was a tow truck parked on the same roadway in then northbound lane facing northbound.  Vehicle 2 was actively in the process of removing a vehicle from the ditch with it's flat bed tilted upward.  Vehicle 1 front plane struck the back of vehicle 2's flat bed ramp.  Vehicle 1 traveled up vehicle 2's flat bed and off the right side.  Vehicle 1 rolled two quarter turns coming to rest on its top facing west on the roadside.

V1 was southbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway approaching a four leg intersection. V2 was westbound stopped at the same four leg intersection. V1 made a left hand turn impacting the frontal plane of V2 with its frontal plane causing damage. V1 came to final rest in the eastbound lane of the eastern leg of the intersection facing southeast. V2 came to final rest at the point of impact facing west.

V1 was southbound on a two lane, two way, undivided rural traffic way. V1 departed the roadway to its right to avoid V2 that was oncoming northbound. The front of V1 then impacted four trees with the frontal plane continuing forward striking another tree with the frontal plane coming to rest at the final tree facing south. V2 was impacted by flying debris from V1 but continued to travel north away from the crash scene.

V1 and V2 were both traveling south in lane 3, on a 4 lane divided roadway, and were both approaching an intersection. V1 then slowed, turned left, departed its lane on the left side, and began to enter an intersection crossover area to make a U-turn. V2 then departed its lane to the left to avoid the slowing V1 vehicle. At the intersection crossover area, V1's left plane, contacted V2's front plane. Both vehicles came to final rest in the crossover at the intersection. When police arrived, V2 had moved to the parking lot of a convenience store on the opposite side of the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a three lane, undivided roadway, in lane two. turning left at the intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling west on the intersecting five, median divided trafficway, in lane four. Within the intersection, the front of V2 impacted the right side of V1. V1 rotated slightly counter-clockwise where it came to rest facing east. V2 continued off onto the NW corner where its front impacted a stop sign. V2 ran over the stop sign and then came to rest facing NW.

V1 was traveling southbound on a physically divided two lane highway in lane one. V2 was traveling on the same highway in lane two, next to V1. As V1 began to switch lanes into lane two, the left side of V1 impacted the right side of V2. V1 lost control, and spun out crossing both travel lanes coming to rest on the west side of the freeway facing south east. V2 came to rest on the right shoulder of the southbound lanes, facing south east.

V1 was westbound on a two-lane rural roadway approaching a four-way intersection. V2 was northbound a two-lane rural roadway approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection and the front of V2 contacted the right side of V1 (event 1). Subsequently, the right side of V1 struck the left side of V2 (event 2). Both vehicles departed the northeast quadrant of the intersection.   As both vehicles traveled off the roadway, the left side of V2 struck two sign posts (events 3 and 4), while V1’s right side impacted a utility pole (event 5). Finally, V2 rolled over two-quarter turns (event 6). Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadside, northeast of the intersection.

V1 and V2 were traveling eastbound on a two-lane, two-way roadway with V1 traveling behind V2. Traffic on the roadway was slow due to an emergency road closer further east. The front of V1 contacted the rear of V2, both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway at point of impact facing east.

V1 was traveling east on a one-way, three-lane roadway in lane one approaching an intersection controlled by a traffic light. V2 was traveling south on a one-way, five-lane roadway in lane three approaching the mentioned intersection. In the intersection the front of V2 contacted the left side of V1. After impact V1 came to final rest facing southeast near the southeast section of the intersection. V2 came to final rest toward the east side of the intersection facing southeast.

V1 was northbound on a 4 lane interchange area, on a physically divided trafficway. V1 departed the roadway to the left then reentered the roadway to the right. V1 began to yaw counter clockwise and exited the roadway again to the left. The front of V1 contacted a concrete traffic barrier. V1 continued to yaw and the rear of V1 contacted the same concrete traffic barrier and came to rest on the shoulder.

V1 was westbound on a 6 lane roadway, in lane 2 and approaching an intersection. V2 was southbound on a 4 lane roadway, in lane 2 and approaching the same intersection. In the intersection, the right side of V1 was contacted by the front of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in the westbound lanes.

V1 was traveling north on a four lane roadway in lane two approaching an intersection. V2 was heading west on a four lane roadway in lane two approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection proceeding straight. The right of V1 impacted with the front of V2. V1 began a clockwise rotation and departed the northwest roadway apex. The right tire of V1 impacted with the curb. V1 continued to travel northwest and the right of V1 impacted a building. V1 then traveled backwards rotating counterclockwise and the the back of V1 impacted a utility pole. V1 came to final rest facing southwest against the pole. After impact with V1 V2 began a clockwise rotation and departed the roadway northwest apex and contacted the left rear wheel on the curb. V2 came to final rest facing east off the roadway.

V1 was traveling northeast on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 crossed the left lane line, then returned back to the lane of travel. V1 then departed the right road edge. The frontal plane of V1 contacted two trees and came to final rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling west on a two-way, two lane road with a curve to the right, controlled by a stop sign. V2 was traveling north on a two way, two lane, divided road. At the intersection of these roads, V1 turned to its left and the front of V2 contacted the left side of V1.  Both vehicles came to final rest in the road, V1 facing south and V2 facing north.

V1 was traveling north in lane one of an interchange ramp of two highways. V2 was disabled and facing west in the interchange area from a previous impact. V1 departed to roadway to the left and the front of V1 impacted a traffic impact attenuator. The front of V1 then contacted the left side of V2. V2 rotated clockwise and came to rest with the lane of the ramp, facing northwest. V1 came to rest at the attenuator facing north.

V1 was traveling northbound exiting a parking lot making a left turn onto a three lane, two way, not physically divided roadway with a left turn lane. V2 was traveling westbound  in lane two of the same three lane, two way, not physically divided roadway with a left turn lane. V1 front plane contacted V2 left plane. Both vehicle came to rest on roadway.
V1 was southbound on a two lane, two-way, undivided roadway when a deer ran into its left side. V1 came to final rest on the right side (west) of the road facing south.

V1 was westbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 departed the right side of the road and struck a guardrail end with the frontal plane causing damage. V1 came to final rest at the point of impact facing west.

V1 was traveling north in lane four of a five lane straight divided (with positive barrier) roadway. V2 was traveling in the same lane ahead of V1. V2 was decelerating. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in their lane of travel, facing north.

V1 was traveling south east on a two-lane, two-way road. V2 was traveling on the same road in the opposite direction. V1 departed the left side of the lane and its front plane impacted the left plane of V2. Both vehicles rotated counterclockwise and came to rest in the road.

V1 was traveling south in on a 4 lane divided roadway approaching an intersection in lane 2. V2 was on the same road facing south stopped north of the intersection in lane 3. V1 departed it's lane to the left and the front of V1 impacted the back of V2. V1 then rotated counter clockwise and V1 rolled over right side leading 1 quarter turn. V1 came to rest facing southeast in lane 1 on it's right side. V2 came to rest in lane 3 facing south.

V1 was traveling westbound on a 2 lane divided roadway in lane 2 negotiating a slight right curve. V1 departed the roadway to the left into the grassy median. The front of V1 then impacted 3 small trees grouped in a line. V1 then rotated clockwise and returned to the roadway. V1 came to rest facing north partially in lane 1 of the roadway.

V1 was traveling  northeast in lane one of a four lane divided roadway. V1 departed its travel lane to the left then departed the left road edge. V1 then reentered the roadway and departed the right road edge and the front plane contacted a guardrail face. V1 then rotated and the back plane contacted the guardrail face.V1 came to rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling southeast in lane two of a seven lane divided roadway attempting to pass through an intersection. V2 was traveling northeast in lane one of a three lane roadway attempting to pass through the same intersection.V1's front plane contacted V2's left plane. Then, V1 rotated counter clockwise and its left plane contacted V2's left plane. Both vehicles came to rest in the intersection.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane two way undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling east on a two lane two way undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. In the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V1 came to final rest on the roadway. V2 traveled off the roadway to the right and the front of V2 contacted a utility pole off the roadway and came to final rest.

V1 was traveling northeast in lane two of a six lane roadway attempting to pass through an intersection. V2 was traveling southwest in lane three of a five lane roadway attempting a left turn at the same intersection. V1's front plane contacted V2's right plane. Both vehicles came to rest in the intersection.

V1 was traveling north in lane one of a two lane undivided roadway, attempting a left turn, starting from a stop sign. V2 was traveling east in lane one of a two lane divided roadway. The left plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2. Both vehicles came to rest on the roadway near impact.

V1 was traveling south on a divided trafficway (median strip without positive barrier) in lane 1 (of two lanes), when it departed its lane on the left, and then the road on the left.  In the median strip, V1's front end came in contact with a tree.  V1 entered the northbound travel lanes of the trafficway and began to rollover (leading left).  During the rollover, V1 made contact with a wood utility pole, a masonry wall, several shrubs and a tree, and another shrub, all along the roadside.  V1 completed its rollover (a total of 2 quarter turns) and came to rest on its top, facing a northerly direction, along the east road/curb edge of the trafficway.

V1 was traveling east, and was approaching an intersection from a two-way, not physically divided trafficway, and was in lane 2 (of five lanes).  V2 was stopped at the entrance to the same intersection, facing west, and was in lane 3 (of five lanes), of a two-way, not physically divided trafficway.  Both vehicles entered the intersection.  In the intersection, the front end of V1 came in contact with the front end of V2.  V1 came to rest on its wheels, facing a southeasterly direction, in the southeast quadrant of the intersection, and west of V2.  V2 came to rest on its wheels, facing a southwesterly direction, in the southeast quadrant of the intersection, and east of V1.

V1 was traveling southwest, on a six lane, two way median divided roadway approaching an intersection controlled by a traffic signal. V2 was traveling northwest on the same six lane, two way median divided roadway approaching the same intersection. At the intersection V2 attempted to turn left and the front of V1 contacted the right side of V2. Both vehicles came to a final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V2 was traveling behind V1. The frontal plane of V2 struck the rear plane of V1. V1 continued driving forward and pulled off the left side of the roadway. V2 came to rest near the point of impact, heading west, in its original travel lane.

V1 was traveling west on a non-physically divided two way road. V1 departed the right road edge and the front of V1 impacted an embankment. The front low portion of V1 then contacted the embankment as it began to climb. V1 continued to travel west along the embankment and the front of V1 then contacted rocks on the embankment that caused damage to all four wheels.V1 then traveled northwest down the side of the embankment and the front of V1 contacted the ground. V1 came to rest partially on and partially off the embankment facing in a southwest direction.

V1 was traveling north on a two way, two lane road with a curve to the left. V2 was traveling south on the same two way, two lane road. V1 departed its original lane to the left impacting the front of V2 with its frontal plane. Continuing forward, the left side of V1 impacted a rock wall off of the left side of the road. After impacting the wall, the right side of V1 was impacted by the front of V2. V1 rotated counterclockwise coming to final rest on the roadway facing northwest. V2 came to final rest partially off the roadway facing west.

V1 was facing west, turning left from a driveway onto a two lane, two-way, divided road. V2 was traveling northwest on the mentioned two way, two lane, divided road. As V1 was turning left, the front of V1 impacted the the front of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway; V1 facing west, V2 facing northwest.

V1 and V2 were both traveling west in lane one of a seven-lane divided roadway, with V1 ahead of V2. V1 stopped at an intersection and then began to back up. V2 was stopped behind V1 and V1's back plane contacted V2's front plane. Both came to final rest near impact.

V1 was traveling northwest in lane four of a divided roadway, passing through an intersection. V2 was traveling southeast in lane five of the same divided roadway, turning left. The front plane of V1 contacted the right plane of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest in the intersection close to impact.

V1, V2, and V3 were traveling west in lane two of a five-lane, non-divided roadway. The front plane of V1 impacted the back plane of V2 as V1 slowed. After initial impact, V2 moved forward, and the front of V2 impacted the back of V3. V1 came to rest at the point of initial impact. V2 came to rest at the point of impact with V3. V3 came to rest at the point of initial impact with V2.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a 5 lane, physically divided trafficway approaching a four-leg intersection controlled by traffic lights. Vehicle 2 was traveling south stopped at the intersection in the same lane of travel. The front of Vehicle 1 contacted the rear of Vehicle 2. Vehicle 1 and Vehicle 2 came to final rest on the road near the intersection.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north on a two lane not physically divided two way road. Vehicle 2 was traveling south on the same road. Vehicle 1 departed the lane on the left side. Vehicle 2 in a attempt to avoid contact traveled off the roadway on the right side. The front plane of Vehicle 1 contacted the left plane of Vehicle 2. Vehicle 2 rotated counterclockwise and came to final rest off the roadway facing east. Vehicle 1 continued north, departed the roadway on the left side rotated counterclockwise and came to final rest off the roadway facing west.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two way, undivided road. V2 was traveling south on the same road. The front plane of V1 struck the front plane of V2. V1 came to final rest in the center of the road facing east. V2 came to rest off the right side of the road facing northwest.

V1 was traveling east on a two way, two lane, roadway. V1 departed right side of the roadway and struck a fence with its frontal plane (event 1). V1 drove over the fence and continued east striking the fence a second time with its frontal plane (event 2). V1 drove over the fence a second time, drove back onto the roadway, departed the left side of the roadway, and struck a fence with its front plane (event 3). V1 drove over this fence and struck a tree with its frontal plane (event 4). V1 then struck another tree with its frontal plane (event 5). V1 came to rest at the point of impact with the second tree facing east.

V1 was traveling east bound on a two lane non divided bidirectional roadway, approaching a turn to the right, with a negative grade. V1 departed the roadway to the right side and overcorrected to the left. V1 then returned to the roadway, crossed both lanes of travel, and exited the left side of the roadway. V1 then traveled down a step embankment, before impacting a tree with its frontal plane. V1 rotated clockwise slightly and impacted a second tree with its left plane, before coming to final rest on the left side of the road.

V1 was west bound on a two lane, non divided bidirectional roadway. The road at this location is a straight stretch, with a positive incline, inclusive of a passing zone. A deer entered the roadway from the right in front of  V1. V1 was unable to stop, and impacted the animal with its frontal plane. V1 came to final rest on the right side of the roadway.

V1 was traveling east on a divided trafficway (median strip without positive barrier) in lane 2 (of two lanes). As the road curved right, V1 departed the road on the left, over-corrected right and began rotating clockwise. V1 returned to the road from the left, and departed its lane to the right, then departed the roadway on the right. V1 began rotating counter-clockwise. The right side of V1 contacted a concrete culvert, and then a fence, before V1 overturned (2 quarter turns, leading right). V1 came to rest on its roof, facing a northwesterly direction on the roadside.

V1 was traveling in a southwesterly direction, through the right hand curve of the roadway, on a designated north/south divided trafficway (median strip with positive barrier), when it departed the road on the right and its front end came into contact with the end of a guardrail.  V1 came to rest on its wheels facing a southerly direction on the roadside.

V1 was traveling north on a two-way, not physically divided trafficway in lane 2, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south on the same trafficway in lane 1 and was approaching the same intersection. V1 departed its lane to the left and entered the southbound lanes of travel.  V2 steered right at the intersection, attempting to avoid the crash. In the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the left of V2.  V2 then rotated counterclockwise and entered the west leg of the intersection. V1 entered a curbed median, and the right plane of V1 contacted a sign, then a utility pole. V1 came to rest on its wheels facing an easterly direction in the median. V2 continued north and came to rest on its wheels facing a northerly direction, northeast of V2.

V1 was traveling in a southwesterly direction on a divided trafficway in lane 2, when it departed the road on the left and overturned (6 quarter turns, leading left).  V1 came to rest on its roof facing a northerly direction in the median strip.
Vehicle 1 was traveling west in lane 1 on a 2-lane, one-way roadway.. The front of V1 contacted a deer in the roadway and V1 came to final rest on the right shoulder of the roadway.

V1 was traveling south in lane 2 on a 2-lane divided roadway. V2 was traveling south in lane 1 ahead of V1 on the same roadway. V1 entered lane 1 and the front of V1 contacted the back of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in lane 1 facing south.

V1 and V2 were travelling South on a 2 lane 2 way not physically divided roadway. V2 was stopped to turn into a parking lot. V1 front plane struck the back plane of V2. Both vehicle came to rest facing South.

Vehicle 1 (V1) was traveling west in lane two of a two-lane divided roadway toward an intersection. Vehicle 2 (V2) was traveling in the opposite direction approaching the same intersection. V1 began to turn left at the intersection and the right of V1 contacted the front of V2. Subsequently, the right side of V1 struck the left side of V2.  Both vehicles came to rest near the intersection, facing southeast.

V1 was traveling north east on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. A deer entered the road way crossing east to west. V1 avoided the deer, but lost control and departed the left road edge. V1 rolled two quarter turns and came to final rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling south on a 2 lane non divided roadway negotiating a left curve. V1 departed the roadway to the right and contacted a tree with its front plane. V1 rotated clockwise and came to rest partially on the roadway facing west. V1 then caught fire after final rest.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a 2 lane, non divided, roadway. V2 was traveling west on the same roadway. V1 departed it's lane of travel to the left. The front of V1 contacted the front of V2. Both vehicles came to rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling on east on a two-lane, two-way road. V3 and V2 were legally parked on the right side of the road facing east. V1 departed the right side of the road and impacted the rear of V3 and then the rear of V2. V1 came to rest in the roadway and V3 and V2 both came to rest on the right side of the roadway.
V1 was traveling south on a two-lane, two-way road. V2 was legally parked on the right side of the road facing south. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2. Both vehicles came to rest on the road.

V1 was traveling south in lane one on a two lane, two way, non-divided roadway. As V1 was negotiating a left curve in the roadway, the vehicle departed the roadway to the right and contacted a guardrail with its right side plane. V1 then re-entered the roadway, crossed the center line to the left, and departed it's lane on the left side. V1 then steered right, re-entered it's lane, and departed the roadway on the right side while rotating clockwise. V1 then contacted a tree with it's left side plane. V1 continued rotating clockwise and the left side plane contacted another tree before coming to final rest at the base of the trees facing west.

V1 was traveling southwest in lane one on a two lane, two way, non-divided roadway. V2 was legally parked on the right side of the roadway. V1 departed the roadway on the right side and it's front plane contacted V2's rear plane. After impact, V1 rotated in a clockwise direction and came to final rest. The vehicles final rest position was partially off the right side of the roadway, with the front end off of the roadway and the back end in lane one. V2 was pushed forward and came to final rest off of the roadway near where the vehicle had been legally parked.

V1 was traveling east approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered into the intersection proceeding straight. The right V1 was contacted by the front of V2. V1 began to rotate clockwise to and deflected off the curbing to the left. V1 then returned to the road and came to final rest on the roadway facing east. V2 began to rotate clockwise to the right and departed the roadway to the right before coming to final rest on a private driveway facing south.

V1 and V2 were traveling north on a two-lane, two-way, non-divided roadway, in lane one. The front plane of V1 impacted the back plane of V2. Both vehicles came to rest facing north, just forward of the point of impact.

V1, V2, and V3 were all traveling west in lane one on a two way, non divided, roadway. Due to traffic ahead, V3 had come to a stop and V2 was slowing to stop when V1's front plane contacted V2's back plane. This impact then caused V2's front plane to contact V3's back plane. All three vehicles came to final rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling southeast on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway, making a left turn. V2 was traveling northwest on the same roadway.  As V1 turned left, the front plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2. V1 rotated counter-clockwise and came to rest on the road facing east. V2 came to rest in the northeast corner of the intersection facing north.

V1 was traveling north on a two-way roadway with a single lane of travel in each direction. V2 was parked on the east side of the roadway facing north. V3 was parked in front of V2. The frontal plane of V1 made contact with the rear plane of V2. V1 then continued forward the frontal plane of V1 made contact with V3. All vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling north on a two-lane, two-way road. V2 was traveling south on the same road. V1 turned left into a gas station and the front of V2 impacted the right side of V1. This caused V1 to rotate clockwise and the right side of V1 impacted the right side of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in the road.

V1 was driving south on a two lane undivided roadway in lane one. As V1 was negotiating a curve, V1 lost control and began to rotate clockwise and departed the roadway to the right where the front area of the left side plane of V1 impacted an embankment. V1 continued to rotate clockwise along the embankment where the rear portion of the left plane of V1 came in contact with the embankment. While still rotating the momentum caused the front of V1 to lift in the air and the rear area of the right side plane of V1 contacted the embankment, then the right front wheel impacted the ground while the front end of V1 came down. V1 then departed the roadway while continuing to rotate clockwise and came to rest facing north in the northbound lane.

V1 was traveling West on a non-physically divided two-way road in lane one. Negotiating a curve at an unknown speed, V1 lost control and traveled off the right side of the road and impacted a barbwire fence then a tree. V1 continued down an embankment and began to rotate counter clockwise, then tripped over and rolled right. V1 came to rest on its roof facing south after completing 6-quarter turns.

V1 was traveling in the number 1 lane of a 2 lane undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V1 began to turn left. V1 departed the roadway to the right where the front of V1 impacted a brick wall. V1 came to rest facing easterly, off the roadway, against the brick wall.

V1 was traveling southbound in the number 1 lane of a 2 lane divided roadway. V2 and V3 were stopped facing south in the number 1 lane of the same road.   The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2.  The front of V2 then impacted the rear of V3.  After the impact with V2, V1 rotated counter-clockwise and came to rest facing north on the west shoulder. V2 after impacting V3 continued forward and to the left where V2 came to rest on the center median, partially blocking the number 2 lane. V3 came to rest facing south in the roadway.

V1 was traveling south on a three lane roadway in lane one. As V1 was negotiating a curve, V1 began to shake and the right rear tire of V1 broke off. V1 lost control and began to rotate counter-clockwise and the left rear tire contacted the west curbline. V1 continued skidding along the sidewalk when the right rear of V1 contacted a pole. After the impact with the pole, V1 spun clockwise and continued backwards across all lanes and the front tire of V1 contacted the east curbline before the rear of V1 contacted a fence. V1 came to rest on the east sidewalk facing north.

V1 was traveling southwest in lane one on a two lane roadway attempting to cross over an intersection. V2 was traveling southeast in lane two of a four lane divided roadway attempting to pass through the same intersection. V1's front plane contacted V2's left plane. V1 rotated counterclockwise, while V2 rotated clockwise in which caused  the vehicles to make contact in a side slapped with V1's right plane contacting V2's left plane. V1 came to rest in the intersection. V2 departed the right road edge and came to rest off the right road edge.

V1 was traveling southwest in lane three of a five lane divided roadway attempting to pass through an intersection. V2 was traveling southeast in lane two of a four lane divided roadway attempting a left turn at the same intersection. V1's front plane was contacted by V2's left plane. Both vehicles came to rest in the intersection near impact.

V1 was traveling northeast in lane one of a two-lane undivided roadway. V1was negotiating a slight curve in the road when it departed its travel lane to the left before returning to its original travel lane. V1 then began to rotate clockwise before departing the roadway and contacting two mailboxes with its left plane. V1 continued to travel and rotate, leading with the rear of the vehicle. V1's undercarriage contacted the ditch bottom and back plane contacted a collection of drainage rocks. V1's right side then contacted the ditch. V1 came to final rest off the roadway in the ditch.

V1 was traveling southwest in lane one of a two-lane undivided roadway, negotiating a right curve. V2 was traveling southwest in lane one of the same two-lane undivided roadway, stopped in traffic. The front plane of V1 contacted the rear plane of V2. V1 came to final rest near impact. Following the crash, V2 drove to a side road where it stopped.

V1 was traveling north on a divided trafficway (median strip without positive barrier) in lane 2 of three lanes and was approaching V2, which was traveling in the same direction, on the same trafficway, ahead in lane 2. In lane 2. The front end of V1 contacted the back end of V2. V1 then departed the road on the left and came to rest on its wheels, facing a northerly direction in the median strip. V2 continued north and came to rest on its wheels facing a northerly direction on the right shoulder.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane, two way, undivided trafficway, passing through a four leg intersection after stopping at a stop sign. V2 was traveling east on a two lane, two way, undivided trafficway with a left turn lane, passing through the same four leg intersection. The frontal plane of V1 struck the left side plane of V2. V1 came to rest in the eastbound lane facing east. V2 came to rest on the eastbound shoulder facing east.

V1 was traveling west in lane two over a bridge, on a two lane, physically divided roadway. Immediately after crossing over the bridge V1 departed the left side of the road in a counterclockwise rotation and struck the median cable barrier with its frontal plane. V1 continued rotating counterclockwise and its right side and back plane contacted the cable barrier. V1 came to rest in the grass median facing west.

V1 was traveling north in the third of three lanes on a positively divided roadway. While negotiating the right-curving road, V1 departed the roadway on the right side and the front of V1 contacted a concrete traffic barrier. V1 returned to the roadway, crossed through all lanes and departed the left side of the roadway. The front of V1 then contacted a guardrail. The left side of V1 contacted a concrete traffic barrier and came to rest off the roadway facing northwest.

V1 was southbound on a two lane, two way undivided roadway approaching a four leg intersection. V2 was westbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. The front of V1 impacted the right side of V2 causing damage. V1 came to final rest in the intersection facing southwest. V2 came to final rest in the intersection facing west.

V1 was eastbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V2 was westbound on the same roadway. V1 departed its travel lane to the left and V2 departed its travel lane to the right. The front of V1 impacted the front of V2 causing damage. Upon impact V2 rotated clockwise traveling off the right side (north) of the road traveling into a ditch and overturning left side leading. V2 came to final rest in the ditch facing east. V1 rotated clockwise and departed the north side of the road. During the impact the trailer of V1 became unattached and departed the north side of the road. V1 came to final rest in on the north side of the road facing southeast.

Vehicle #1 (V1) was traveling north on a two-lane, divided roadway, negotiating a right curve.  V1 lost control and began to rotate clockwise.  V1 departed the road to the right and the front of V1 contacted a guardrail.  V1 re-entered the road and then departed the road to the right again.  V1 came to rest on the right shoulder, facing north.
Vehicle #1 (V1) was traveling south on a highway when the front of V1 contacted an animal. V1 then departed the trafficway to the right where it came to final rest on the shoulder facing south.

Vehicle 1 was traveling eastbound on a two lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position. Vehicle 2 was traveling southbound on a two lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position. Both vehicles approached and entered a four way intersection. The front plane of Vehicle 1 made contact with the right side of Vehicle 2. Vehicle 1 rotated clockwise and Vehicle 2 rotated counter clockwise causing the left side of V1 to contact the right side of V2. V1 then departed the southeast apex contacting a light pole with the left plane. V1 came to rest facing south against the pole. Vehicle 2 departed the southeast apex and came to rest in a private yard facing south.

Vehicles 1 and 2 were both traveling northbound on a four lane, two way, physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position. Vehicle 2 slowed to make a right turn. The front plane of vehicle 1 made contact with the rear plane of vehicle 2. Vehicle 2 traveled across the east side of the intersection, departing the roadway and striking a stop sign pole. Vehicle 2 came to rest at the pole facing northeast. Vehicle 1 came to rest at the northern part of the intersection facing north.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a 4 lane two-way non-physically divided roadway in lane 1 position. Vehicle 2 was also traveling west on the same roadway in lane 2 position. V1 attempted to make a right turn into a business parking lot. V1 lost control and exited lane of travel on the left side. The left plane of V1 contacted the front of V2.  The vehicles then side slapped with the left of V1 contacting the right of V2 again.   V2 then crossed both eastbound lanes and exited the roadway on the left side.  V2's front contacted a tree and came to rest facing south west. V1 came to rest in the westbound lane number 2, facing west.

V1 was traveling west following a two-way, five lane road in the first lane of travel, approaching an intersection.  V2 was stopped in traffic in front of V1 on the same two-way, five lane road.  As traffic began in the intersection, the front of V1 impacted the back of V2.  Both vehicles came to final rest at impact in the roadway, facing west.

V1 was traveling northeast following a two-way, three lane road with a center turn lane. V2 was traveling in front of V1 on the same two-way, three lane road. V2 was slowing in the roadway due to stopped traffic ahead. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest at impact, in the roadway facing northeast.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a two lane, one way, physically divided roadway in lane 2. V1 moved to its left to avoid a non-contact vehicle entering into it's lane. V1 then departed roadway to the left striking a cable barrier with its front plane. V1 rotated clockwise as it engaged the cable barrier and the cables contacted the left side of V1. V1 came to rest facing west on the south road edge beside the cable barrier.

Vehicle #1 was traveling east in lane two of a five-lane, undivided highway with a two-way left turn lane. V1 departed the road to the left, and the front plane contacted a curb, then a utility pole. V1 came to rest off the north road edge facing east.

V1 was traveling north in the left turn lane on a divided roadway with three NB lanes and two SB lanes. V1 was approaching a 4-way intersection to turn left.  V2 was traveling south in lane two on an undivided five lane roadway approaching the same intersection.  As V1 turned left and V2 traveled straight through the intersection the front of V1 contacted the front of V2.  Both vehicles came to final rest near the point of impact in the middle of the intersection.

Vehicle #1 was traveling west, approaching a four way intersection. Vehicle #2 was traveling north, approaching the same intersection. V1 and V2 proceeded straight through the intersection, and the front plane of V2 contacted the left plane of V1. After impact V1 rotated counterclockwise and came to rest facing south in the intersection. V2 came to rest facing north past the impact point in the intersection.

V1 was traveling north in lane one on a two-way, four lane undivided roadway approaching a four-way intersection.  V2 was traveling west approaching the same intersection in lane two on a five lane undivided, two-way roadway. As V1 and V2 passed through the intersection the front of V1 contacted the left plane of V2.  V1 slightly rotated counterclockwise to final rest close to the AOI.  V2 rotated clockwise to final rest near AOI.

V1 was traveling east in lane 2 on a 3-lane roadway negotiating a right curve. A non-contact vehicle traveling west entered V1's lane. V1 steered left to avoid the non-contact vehicle and departed the curb edge contacting the curb with its left front wheel.
