V1 continued forward where its front plane contacted a bush then a rock wall. The left side of V1 contacted the rock wall and its front contacted a wood fence and came to rest facing east.

V1,2 and 3 were all traveling southbound on a five lane, two-way non-physically divided roadway in lane two. V1 was behind V2 and V2 was behind V3. V2 and V3 stopped and the front of V1 contacted the rear of V2. V2 moved forward and the front plane of V2 contacted the rear plane of V3. All Vehicles came to final res in lane two facing south.

Vehicles 1,2 and 3 were all traveling east in lane 2 on a 2-lane divided roadway. V1 was behind V2 and V2 was behind V3. V2 and V3 were traveling in slowing traffic. The front plane of V1 made contact with the rear plane of V2. In a chain reaction, the front plane of V2 made contact with the rear plane of V3. V3 continued without stopping. V1 departed the roadway to the left into the median where it contacted a cable barrier and came to rest facing east. V2 began rotated clockwise and came to rest facing southeast with its rear wheels just off the roadway.

V1 was traveling east on a three lane divided roadway in lane 3. V1 then departed the roadway to the left into the center median where it contacted a tree with it left side mirror. V1 then crossed the median and entered the on coming lanes of traffic. V1 then departed all lanes of traffic and departed the roadway to the left. The front left tire of V1 then impacted a raised curb. V1 continued off road and drove across a private driveway. The front of V1 then impacted a tree. V1 came to rest against the tree facing northeast.

Vehicle 1 was traveling in the eastbound lane of a two lane undivided roadway. Vehicle 2 was parked at the right curb of the roadway, and started to travel forward, entering into the eastbound lane. Vehicle 1 contacted its frontal plane with the left side plane of vehicle 2. Vehicle 2 rotated counter clockwise and the frontal plane of vehicle 1 was contacted by the left side plane of vehicle 2. Vehicle 1 then contacted the right side of V3 with its front as it yawed left side leading. Vehicle 1 entered into a rollover contacting vehicle 4, coming to rest on its top plane on the roadway.  Subsequently, the back of V3 (parked) contacted the front of (parked) V4 as it traveled rearward due to the impact with V1.  Then the back of V4 contacted the back of another parked vehicle on the north road edge as it traveled rearward during the impact.

V1 was southbound, in lane 3, on a 5 lane (2 way with middle turn lane) roadway and approaching an intersection. V2 was northbound on the same roadway, with 6 lanes and in lane 2. V3 was stopped at a stop sign facing west. Within the intersection the front of V1 contacted the front of V2. V2 moved to the right and the right side of V2 contacted the front of V3. All the vehicles came to rest in the roadway.

V1 was westbound on a 2 lane roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was northbound on a 2 lane roadway approaching the same intersection. Within the intersection the left side of V1 contacted the front of V2.

V1 was traveling east in lane two of a two-way, four lane roadway.  V2 was stopped in the roadway attempting to turn left to travel north, ahead of V1 in lane two of the same roadway.  The front plane of V1 made contact with the rear plane of V2.  V2 rotated counterclockwise and came to final rest on the roadway, in the eastbound shoulder, facing west.  V1 came to rest in the roadway, just east of the impact location.

Vehicle 1 was traveling northbound on a three lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position.  Vehicle 2 was traveling westbound on six lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 2 position.  Both vehicles entered the intersection.  The front plane of Vehicle 1 made contact with the left plane of Vehicle 2.  Vehicle 1 rotated counterclockwise coming to rest just after impact facing west in the northwest corner of the intersection.  Vehicle 2 came to final rest facing west also in the the northwest corner of the intersection.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west bound negotiating a curve on a two lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position.  Vehicle 1 departed the roadway to the left (south) side.  The front plane of Vehicle 1 made contact with a landscaped rock wall.  Vehicle 1 continued over the rock wall coming to rest facing west just after impact with the rock wall.

V1 was traveling north in lane 2 on a four-lane undivided roadway. V1 departed its lane of travel to the left and crossed the southbound lanes before departing the roadway on the left. The front of V1 contacted a block wall and came to final rest facing northwest.

V1, V2, V3, and V4 were traveling east on a five lane physically divided roadway in lane two. V3 and V4 began to slow for traffic ahead. V2 began to slow and steered slightly to the right. The front of V1 connected with the rear of V2 (event 1). V2 was then redirected to the right where the front and right connected with a guard rail (event 2 and 3). After impact, V2 was redirected again to the left. The left of V2 connected with the right of V3 (event 4). V3 connected with V4 on an unknown plane (event 5). V1 came to final rest in its lane of travel facing east. V2 came to final rest partially in lane 1 facing slightly northeast. V3 came to final rest straddling lanes two and three, also facing a northeasterly position. V4 came to final rest in lane three facing east.

V1 was approaching a four leg intersection while traveling west on a two lane, two way road, with a left turn lane. V2 was traveling west behind V1. V1 slowed to make a right turn and the frontal plane of V2 struck the back plane of V1. V1 departed the northwest corner of the intersection and struck a fence with its frontal plane. V1 came to rest at the point of impact with the fence heading northwest. V2 came to rest heading west in the westbound lane near the point of impact with V1.

V1 was traveling northbound in the first lane of a two lane, one-way positive divided roadway. V2 was traveling northbound in the first lane of a two lane, one-way positive divided roadway ahead of V1. The frontal plane of V1 impacted the rear plane of V2. Both V1 and V2 then departed right from the first lane into the breakdown lane, off the roadway, for final rest. V1 and V2 were facing north off the roadway at final rest.

V1 was traveling westbound in the second lane of a three lane, two-way roadway attempting to turn left at the approaching intersection. V2 was traveling eastbound in the second lane of a three lane, two-way roadway approaching the same intersection. As V1 attempted to turn left to continue traveling southbound through the intersection, the frontal plane of V1 impacted the frontal plane of V2 as both vehicles entered the intersection at the same time. V1 rotated counterclockwise slightly, with it's right side plane impacting the frontal plane of V2. As V1 continued traveling forward, it's right side plane impacted the frontal plane of V2 again. V1 came to final rest in the roadway facing southwest. V2 came to final rest in the roadway facing east.

V1 was traveling southwest in lane two of a four-lane divided roadway with positive barrier. V1 departed the road to the left and the front plane contacted a cable barrier. V1 continued to travel along the cable for a distance before coming to final rest against the cable barrier.

V1 and V2 were traveling northeast in lane one of a two lane roadway with V2 ahead of V1. V2 was attempting a U turn. As V1 approached V2 it departed its travel lane to the left and V1's front plane contacted V2's front plane. V1 continued forward and it front plane contacted V2's left plane. Both vehicles came to rest near impact.

V1 was traveling north on a two-lane, two-way road while passing through an intersection. V2 was traveling west on a two-lane, two-way road while passing through the same intersection. The front of V1 impacted the left side of V2 and both vehicles came to rest in the intersection.
V1 was traveling north on a two-lane, two-way road when a deer entered the road from the left. The front of V1 impacted the deer and V1 came to rest in its original travel lane.

V1 was traveling north on a one way access roadway. V1 departed the right road edge and its right front tire contacted a curb. V1 crossed left over the lane and its front plane then left side contacted a concrete barrier. V1 came to rest on the roadway facing north.

V1 was traveling east in the northbound lanes of a physically divided highway, in lane 2. V1 departed the roadway to the left and went forward. V1 approached a wall and continued forward, dropping down onto the roadway below. V1's front undercarriage contacted the ground. V1's rear undercarriage then contacted the ground. V1 continued off of that roadway and thru rocky median. V1 then reentered the roadway at the east bound lanes and came to rest partially on the median, facing northbound.

V1 was traveling east in lane four of a four lane divided roadway. V2 was traveling east on the same roadway in lane three. V1 departed its lane to the right and the front of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V2 crossed all lanes of traffic to the right and departed the road and entered a grass median. V2 then tripped and rolled right 6-quarter turns down the slope of the grass median and came to rest on its top facing southeast. V2 continued forward and came to rest on the roadway facing southeast.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a two lane undivided roadway in lane 1. V2 was traveling westbound on the same roadway in lane 1. V1 departed its lane and the front of V1 impacted the front of V2. V1 came to rest facing east bound and V2 came to rest facing westbound.

V1 was traveling northeast in the number 1 lane of a 5 lane undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling southeast in the number 1 lane of a 2 lane undivided roadway approaching an intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection. The front of V1 impacted the right side of V2. After the initial impact the left side of V1 impacted the right side of V2. V1 rotated clockwise and came to rest facing east in the intersection. V2 rotated counter-clockwise and came to rest facing north in the intersection.

V1 and V2 were negotiating a curve to the right in the #1 lane of a 3 lane divided highway. V2 came to a stop due to traffic. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2. Both V1 and V2 came to rest facing north east in the #1 lane.

V1 was traveling southbound straight, exiting a parking lot, entering the roadway V2 was traveling on. V2 was traveling westbound straight on an undivided two lane roadway. As V1 was exiting the parking lot, V1's frontal plane came into contact with V2's right side plane. Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling in a northeasterly direction on a designated north/south divided trafficway (median strip with positive barrier) in lane 3 (of four lanes), when a non-contact vehicle, which was traveling in the same direction, on the same roadway, ahead in lane 4, entered lane 3.  V1 was turned sharply to the right in response.  Control over V1 was lost, and V1 skidded laterally in a clockwise rotation.  V1 departed the road on the right, where its left side came into contact with an earthen embankment along the road edge.  V1 then overturned (1 quarter turn, leading right).  V1 came to rest on its right side, facing a westerly direction on the right hand shoulder.

V1 was traveling in a southeasterly direction on a designated east/west physically divided trafficway (median strip with positive barrier) in lane 4 (of five lanes) and was approaching V2, which was traveling in the same direction, on the same roadway, in lane 2, at a lower steady speed.  V1 was moved into lane 3, and then into lane 2.  In lane 2, the front end of V1 came into contact with the back end of V2.  V1 skidded laterally in a counter-clockwise direction and came to rest on its wheels, facing a northwesterly direction on the fog line separating the right hand shoulder from the roadway.  V2 was driven to the right hand shoulder and parked.

V1 was traveling west on a divided trafficway (median strip without positive barrier), in lane 2 (of two lanes), and was approaching a Non-Contact Vehicle and its Cargo (a Large Pickup Truck being towed via a Fixed Linkage), which was traveling in the same direction, on the same roadway, in lane 1 (of two lanes).  V1 departed its lane on the right, and its front end came in contact with an unknown plane of the towed Cargo.  V1 then departed the road on the left and overturned (8 quarter turns, leading left).  During the rollover, Occupant 2 was totally ejected.  V1 came to rest on its wheels, facing a northeasterly direction in the median strip.  The Non-Contact Vehicle and its Cargo was driven to the shoulder and parked.

V1 was traveling east on a divided trafficway (median strip with positive barrier), in lane 2 (of four lanes), and was approaching V2, which was traveling on the same roadway, ahead in lane 1 (of four lanes), at a lower steady speed.  V1 departed its lane on the right and its right side contacted V2's left side.  V1 then overturned (2 quarter turns, leading left), and came to rest on its roof, in lane 2, facing a southerly direction.  V2 continued on without stopping.

V1 was traveling west on a three lane, two way, undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. In the intersection, the left side of V1 contacted the front of V2. V1 then rotated counter-clockwise, and the left side of V1 contacted the left side of the trailer for V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling west on a, two lane, two way, undivided roadway, approaching a legally parked V2 on the right side. V1 departed the roadway to the right and the front of V1 contacted the back of V2. V1 came to final rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane non-physically divided roadway in lane one approaching a stop sign controlled intersection. V2 was traveling west on a three lane non-physically divided roadway in lane one approaching the same intersection. V1 began to make a left turn and the left side of V1 was contacted by the front of V2. V1 came to rest on the eastbound shoulder facing southeast and V2 came to rest on the eastbound shoulder facing southwest.

V1 was northbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway while negotiating a left curve. V1 departed the right side of the roadway, crossed a parking lot and a side street, before impacting a fence with the frontal plane. V1 continued through the fence impacting a tree with the frontal plane then the side of a house with the right plane. V1 then impacted the same house with the frontal plane.  V1 came to final rest at the final point of impact.

V1 was traveling southbound in the second lane of a two lane, one-way positive divided roadway ahead of V2. V2 was traveling southbound in the first lane of a two lane, one-way positive divided roadway.  V1 departed right to change lanes from the second lane into the first lane. The frontal plane of V2 impacted the rear plane of V1. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway facing south.

V1 was traveling east in lane 4 of 4 on a physically divided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was west in lane 3 of 4 on a physically divided roadway approaching the same intersection. Within the intersection the right side of V1 contacted the front of V2. After impact V1 departed the road onto a traffic island where the left side of V1 contacted a pole. Both vehicles came to rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling north on a 3 lane 2 way not physically divided roadway approaching a four way intersection. V2 was traveling east on the intersecting 3 lane 2 way not physically divided roadway. V1 and V2 entered the intersection proceeding straight and V1s front plane contacted V2s right plane. V1 came to rest facing north in the intersection. V2 came to rest facing east in the intersection.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east approaching a four legged intersection on a two lane, two way roadway protected by a stop sign. Vehicle 2 was traveling south approaching the same intersection on a two lane, two way, unprotected roadway. Vehicle 1 and Vehicle 2 entered the intersection going straight. The left plane of Vehicle 1 contacted the front of Vehicle 2. Both vehicles continue off the southeast corner of the intersection.  Vehicle 1 rolled over coming to final rest on its roof. Vehicle 2 came to rest facing east.  Both Vehicles came to rest on the south east corner of the intersection.

Vehicle 1 was backing out of a private drive onto a two lane, two-way, unprotected roadway with an attached trailer. Vehicle 2 was traveling east on the same two lane, two-way, unprotected roadway. Approaching the private drive that V1 was backing out of. The front/right side of Vehicle 2 contacted the back of Vehicle 1's trailer in a side swipe motion. Vehicle 1 came to final rest in the private drive and Vehicle 2 continued east, coming to final rest off the right side of the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north on a two lane, two way roadway negotiating a curve to the left. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway to the right and the the front of vehicle 1 contacted a culvert and then the front contacted a sign. Vehicle 1 continued forward and crossed over an intersecting roadway. Vehicle 1 rotated counter clockwise and the back of vehicle 1 contacted a house before coming to final rest off the roadway facing southeast.

V1 was traveling southbound, on a median divided roadway, with three lanes in the same direction, approaching an intersection. V1 was traveling in the second lane of the roadway. V2 was traveling southbound on the same median divided roadway and trailing V1 in the same lane of the three lane roadway. V2 entered lane three in an attempted to pass V1. V1 entered the same lane that V2 was traveling and the left side plane of V1 made contact with the front plane of V2. V2 continued forward in a counter clockwise direction making contact again with the left side plane of V1 with its right side plane. Both V1 and V2 came to a final rest partially off the roadway in the median.

V1 was traveling southwest on a four lane, two way, median divided roadway negotiating a left hand curve in the roadway. V1 began to rotate clockwise and departed the right hand side of the roadway contacting a guardrail face with its frontal plane. V1 continue along the guardrail rotating in a clockwise direction making contact with the guardrail again with its left side plane. V1 continued forward rotating in a clockwise direction and rolled left side leading. V1 came to a final rest on the roadway on its wheels facing west.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a six lane undivided roadway, approaching a four-legged intersection, intending to turning left.  Vehicle 2 was traveling east on a six lane undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. In the intersection the front of Vehicle 1 contacted the front of Vehicle 2.  Both Vehicle came to final rest within the intersection; Vehicle 1 facing south, Vehicle 2 facing southeast.

Vehicle 1 was approaching a four-leg intersection while traveling south on a lane-two of a divided three-lane roadway (two-through travel lanes and a channelized designated left turn lane).  Vehicle 2 was traveling north in the designated channelized left turn lane. There are two, through north travel lanes adjacent to the designated left turn lane. The driver of Vehicle 2 initiated a left turn sequence as the front plane of Vehicle 1 impacted the frontal plane of Vehicle 2. In response to the impact, Vehicle 1 was deflected off of the roadway at the southwest intersection quadrant. Vehicle 1’s undercarriage then contacted a drainage grate. Vehicle 1 came to final rest off the roadway facing south. Vehicle 2 rotated counterclockwise and departed the roadway to its left and came to final rest on the shoulder facing south.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south in lane two on a three lane, two way trafficway divided by a grass median and cable barrier. Vehicle 2 was traveling in lane three on the same trafficway going the same direction. Vehicle 1 departed the lane on the left side and the left plane of vehicle 1 contacted the front plane of vehicle 2.  Vehicle 2 departed its lane on the left side and traveled into the center median where the front plane contacted a sign and guardrail end before coming to final rest, facing south. Vehicle 1 came to final rest on the left shoulder facing south.

Vehicles #1, #2, #3, #4, #5 and #6 were all traveling west in the same lane. V3, V4, V5 and V6 stopped at an intersection. V2 began to slow. The front of V1 contacted the back of V2 (event 1). Impact forces directed V2 forward and the front of V2 contacted the back of V3 (event 2). V3 rotated clockwise and the left of V3 contacted the back of V4 (Event 3). In turn, the front of V4 contacted the back of V5 (Event 4) and the front of V5 contacted the back of V6 (Event 5).   After the first impact, V1 began to rotate counterclockwise and departed the road to the right. The right of V1 contacted a pole (Event 6).   V1 entered the intersecting roadway and came to rest facing east, partially in the crosswalk. V2 came to rest near event 2, partially in lane 2, facing southwest. V3 came to rest near event 3, facing north. V4 came to rest facing west in lane 2. V5 came to rest near event 5, facing west. V6 drove through the intersection and stopped facing west just past the intersection.  V2 came to rest near event 2,

V1 was traveling northeast in lane one of a two-lane undivided roadway. V1 departed its travel lane to the left and then departed the roadway to the left. V1 entered a ditch where it's front plane contacted the ground. V1 then contacted a tree stump in the ground through the front plane with it's left front wheel, causing it to begin to roll end-over-end. The rollover was interrupted when the top of V1 contacted a tree, causing the vehicle to rotate counterclockwise. V1 then came to final rest on it's left side in the ditch.

V1 was traveling southwest in lane one of a two lane roadway negotiating a left curve. V1 departed the right road edge and the front right plane contacted a tree. V1 rotated slightly and its right side contacted the tree again. V1 then rotated clockwise then tripped and rolled left three quarter turns coming to rest on the right plane in the roadway facing west.

V1 was traveling east in lane three of a five-lane undivided roadway, turning left at the intersection. V2 was traveling west in lane three of a six-lane undivided roadway, passing through the intersection. The right plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest near impact.

V1 was traveling northeast in lane one of a three lane roadway at a hill-crest. V1 lost traction on the wet roadway and departed its travel lane to the left crossed over the center lane then departed the left road edge while engaged in a clockwise yaw. V1's front plane impacted a ditch (Event 1) then the entire left side plane contacted the ditch embankment (Event 2). The top surface of the pickup box impact a tree (Event 3) as V1 rotated rapidly clockwise, coming to rest in the ditch, upright and facing south.

Vehicle 1 was traveling in the first of three southbound lanes of a six lane positively divided roadway. Vehicle 1 contacted a large rock that was in its travel lane, with it's undercarriage. Vehicle 1 came to rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling east on a five lane roadway in the third eastbound lane approaching an intersection. V2 was heading northbound in the second lane of three northbound lanes and initiated a left turn at the intersection of the roadway V1 was traveling. V2 struck the right side of V1 with the front plane. Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a four lane, painted median divided roadway, in lane one.  Vehicle 2 was legally parked on the south side of the roadway.  Vehicle 1 moved right and its front impacted the rear of Vehicle 2. All vehicles came to rest just forward of impact, still facing east.

V1 was traveling northbound in lane one on a six-lane, two-way roadway approaching an intersection controlled by a traffic light. V2 was traveling southbound in lane three on a five-lane two-way roadway intending to turn left and head eastbound at the mentioned intersection. In the middle of the intersection the front plane of V1 contacted the right side of V2. V1 came to final rest in the intersection facing north, V2 came to final rest facing south.

V1 was traveling southwest in lane one on a two lane undivided right curved roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling northwest in lane two on a four lane divided left curved roadway approaching the same intersection. V1 intended to turn right. After braking for the red traffic signal, V1 slid into the intersection on the iced covered roadway and the front of V2 contacted the left side of V1. V1 rotated counter-clockwise and departed the northeast corner of the intersection where its left side contacted a concrete wall. V1 came to rest near the wall facing southeast. V2 continued forward and came to rest on the roadway facing northwest.

V1 was traveling southbound on a 4 lane positive divided highway in lane 4. V1 lost control and departed the roadway to the left. The front of V1 impacted the concrete barrier. V1 came to rest facing south.

V1 was northbound on a four-lane divided road approaching a four-way intersection. V2 was southbound on the same road approaching the same intersection. V3 was eastbound turning south at the same intersection. V1 initiated a left turn at the intersection and its front end struck the front end of V2 (event 1). V2 departed the right side of the road and its front end struck a traffic signal pole (event 2). Debris from the crash struck V3 (event 3). V2 continued its path off the road and struck a safety barrier/fence with its front. V2 came to final rest in a PVA. V1 and V3 came to final rest in the roadway.

V1 and V2 were both traveling west bound on an 8-lane divided roadway. V1 was in lane 2 and V2 was in Lane 1. V1 traveled over the lane line to the right. V1's right side contacted V2's left side. V2 left the roadway to the right and came to rest. V1 came to rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling west in lane 2 on a two lane divided roadway. V2 was traveling on the same roadway in lane one of the westbound lanes. As V2 was merging into lane two, the frontal plane of V1 struck the rear plane of V2. V1 rotated clockwise, departed the left road edge and came to rest facing south in the grass median. V2 continued traveling west until it could exit the roadway.

V1 was traveling east on a two-lane, undivided roadway and approaching a bridge V2 was traveling west crossing the same bridge. V3 was traveling east, in front of V1 and also crossing the bridge. V1 struck the right side bridge barrier (event 1). V1 then crossed the center line and struck the left side bridge barrier (event 2). V1 continued traveling east in the westbound lane. The frontal plane of V1 struck the frontal plane of V2 (event 3). After the collision, a piece of debris struck the left of V3 (event 4). V1 came to final rest facing west in the westbound lane. V2 and V3 came to rest heading west in the eastbound lane.

V1 was traveling north on a two way, three lane, undivided roadway negotiating a right hand curve in the roadway. V1 departed the left hand lane line, continued forward departing the second left hand lane line, and then V1 departed the left hand side (west) of the roadway. V1 while off of the roadway contacted two piles of brush with its frontal plane and then contacted a bush also with its frontal plane. V1 came to final rest off of the roadway.

V1 was traveling westbound on a 2 lane divided roadway in lane 1. V1 departed the roadway to the right and the front of V1 impacted an impact attenuator. V1 pushed the attenuator into the concrete barrier and V1 came to rest facing west.

V1 was traveling southwest on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling east on a two way, two lane undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. V1 attempted to make a right hand turn but lost control crossing a median. The frontal plane of V1 contacted the left plane of V2. V1 continued on and the left plane of V1 contacted the left plane of V2. Both V1 and V2 came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 and V2 were traveling south on a two lane, one way, roadway. V1 was traveling in the first lane and V2 was traveling in the second lane. The frontal plane of V1 contacted the rear plane of V2.  V1 and V2 crossed the right lane line, then departed the western road edge. V1 and V2 came to final rest off the roadway.
V1 and V2 were both traveling south in the same lane of a divided highway. V2 was ahead of V1. The front of V1 struck the back of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling southwest on a 2 lane, non-divided roadway. V1 crossed all lane lines to the left and departed the roadway. V1's front end contacted the ground and V1 began yawing clockwise before tripping over. V1 rolled to the left 4 quarter turns before coming to rest on its' wheels.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was stopped at a red light at the same intersection. The front of V1 contacted the rear of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest near the point of impact.

V1 was heading north on a two lane undivided roadway. V1 went left of center and departed the roadway to the left. The front of V1 contacted a utility pole before coming to final rest at the bottom of a ditch line facing northeast.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west in lane two of a three-lane divided roadway without a positive barrier.  Vehicle 2 was traveling east in the left turn lane.  V2 began to turn left at an intersection and the front of V1 contacted the right of V2.  V1 came to rest partially on an island near the northwest corner, facing north.  V2 came to rest north of the intersection, facing east.

V1 was traveling North on a median divided two lane highway, negotiating a curve, in lane two.  V1 departed the roadway to the left and lost control. V1 re-entered the roadway and yawed clockwise across the northbound lanes and departed the roadway to the right.  The front of V1 impacted an ascending concrete embankment.. V1 continued onto and across the northbound on-ramp. The LR wheel impacted the ground and the LF wheel impacted a curb. V1 then began to rollover off the roadway. V1 completed 4 quarter turns before coming to rest on its wheels facing a southeasterly direction.

V1, V2, and V3 were heading west on a two-lane, two-way road that curved to the right approaching an intersection where V3 was leading all vehicles and V1 was trailing all vehicles.V2 stopped at the intersection to make a left turn and V3 stopped past the intersection due to backed up traffic. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2, swiping down the entire side and then proceeded to impact the rear of V3, before impacting a bridge rail where it came to rest. V2 and V3 both came to rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling in a northerly direction on a right curved, two-way, non physically divided trafficway.   V1 departed the end of the road and its front end came into contact with an earthen embankment.  V1 traversed the embankment then came to rest on its wheels facing a northeasterly direction in an open field outside the trafficway.

V1 was traveling northeast on a two-way, two lane road, approaching an intersection controlled by traffic lights. V2 was stopped in traffic on the same roadway in front of V1. V3 was stopped on the same roadway at the intersection, in front of V2. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2. The front of V2 then impacted the back of V3. All three vehicles came to final rest at impact on the roadway, facing northeast.

Vehicle #1 (V1) was traveling north on a two-lane undivided roadway, negotiating a right curve.  V1 lost control and departed the road to the left.  The left side of V1 contacted 2 trees.  V1 came to rest off the road to the left, facing northeast.

V1 was traveling east in lane one on a two lane divided roadway. V2 was traveling east directly in front of V1 when the front of V1 impacted the back of V2. V1 then departed the roadway to the left where it came to rest facing east in the grass median. V2 departed the road to the right where it came to rest on the shoulder facing east.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a two lane non-physically divided two way roadway attempting to crossover a four legged intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling west on a two lane non-physically divided two way roadway attempting to turn left at the same same intersection. Within the intersection, the front plane of Vehicle 1 contacted the right plane of Vehicle 2. Both vehicles came to final rest in the intersection.

V1 was traveling southwest, in lane one, on a two lane, two way, non-divided roadway. V1 lost control due to roadway conditions departing its travel lane and roadway to the left. V1 traveled down an embankment where it's front plane contacted a tree. V1 continued forward and contacted a second tree with its front plane before contacting a third tree with its right side plane. V1 came to final rest in a creek bed next to the third tree.

V1 was southbound on a two-lane roadway negotiating a curve right. A deer entered the roadway and V1 steered left to avoid the animal. V1 departed the left (east) side of the road and its left side contacted a tree (event 1). V1 continued to travel on the roadside, down an embankment, and its front struck a second tree (event 2) and third tree (event 3). V1 came to final rest against  the third tree.

V1 was traveling northeast in lane one on a two lane, two way, non divided, roadway when it departed the roadway on the right side. The vehicle then returned to the roadway and departed the roadway on the left side. The vehicle traveled across and down a grass embankment where its front plane then contacted a tree. V1 came to final rest against the tree, approximately 44 meters from the left roadway departure site. The vehicle also caught fire sometime after impact with the tree.

V1 was traveling westbound, on a median divided roadway, with two lanes in the same direction, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling northbound on a two way, two lane undivided roadway, approaching the same intersection as V1, with a stop sign. Both vehicles entered the intersection. The frontal plane of V2 contacted the left side plane of V1. V1 continued forward and came to a final rest on the shoulder on the northwest side of the roadway. V2 continued forward and came to a final rest off the northeast side of the roadway.

V1 was traveling west on a three lane two way roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling east on the same three lane two way roadway approaching the same intersection. In the intersection, V1 attempted a left hand turn and the front of V1 contacted the front of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane two way roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north on a two lane two way curb/grass median divided trafficway approaching the same intersection. In the intersection, the left side of V1 contacted the front of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was making a left turn from a two-lane, two-way roadway onto an intersecting two lane undivided roadway and departed the roadway to the right and contacted a brick pillar with its frontal plane. Vehicle 1 came to rest off the roadway to the right.

Vehicle #1 and vehicle #2 were traveling east on a two-lane divided road in lane one. V2 came to a stop in traffic. The front plane of V1 contacted the back plane of V2. Both vehicles came to rest near the impact area facing east in lane one.

Vehicle 1 was traveling northwest on a two lane, undivided, two-way roadway, approaching an intersection.  Vehicle 2 was traveling northeast on the intersecting two lane, undivided, two-way roadway, intending to turn left at the intersection.  Within the intersection, the front of Vehicle 1 contacted the right side of Vehicle 2.  Both vehicles came to rest within the intersection. Vehicle 1 came to rest facing north and Vehicle 1 came to rest facing west.

V1 was traveling south in lane two of a four lane divided roadway, negotiating a right curve. The right rear tire failed and V1 lost directional control of the vehicle and started to rotate counter-clockwise. V1 crossed all lanes to the left and departed the roadway into the grass median. V1 drove over the previously damaged cable barrier, crossed the grass ditch and entered the northbound lanes of the roadway. V1 then tripped and rolled 3-quarter turns right then 1-quarter turn left and came to rest on its top facing north. A passenger in the third row was partially ejected during the rollover sequence.

V1 was traveling south on a one lane divided roadway approaching an intersection to turn left. V2 was traveling west on a 4 lane roadway in lane 1, approaching the same intersection. Within the intersection the left side of V1 was contacted by the front of V2. V1 rotated clockwise and came to rest in the northwest corner of the intersection facing southwest. V2 continued forward and came to rest in the westbound lane facing west.

V1 was traveling south in the second of two lanes on a divided, two-way roadway entering a light controlled, three-legged intersection attempting to turn left. V2 was traveling east in the first of four lanes on a two-way roadway entering the same intersection as V1. Within the intersection, the right side of V1 contacted the front of V2. The vehicles rotated towards each other and the right side of V1 contacted the left side of V2 in a side-slap configuration. Both vehicles came to rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling south in the first of two lanes on an undivided, two-way roadway entering a four-legged intersection attempting to turn left. V2 was traveling east in the first of four lanes on an undivided, two-way roadway entering the same intersection as V1. Within the intersection, the right side of V1 contacted the left side of V2. The vehicles rotated towards each other and the right side of V1 contacted the left side of V2 in a side-slap configuration. After the initial impact, Vehicle 1 continued to rotate counterclockwise and came to rest within the intersection. Vehicle 2 rotated counterclockwise and departed the roadway on the southeast corner. The right side of V2 contacted the curb, a fence and a wooded sign before it came to rest east off of the roadway.

V1 was traveling east on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway. V1 departed the left hand lane line and then departed the left side (north) of the roadway. V1 contacted an embankment with its frontal plane. V1 came to final rest off of the roadway.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway approaching a three leg intersection. V2 was traveling north on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. V1 began to turn left at the intersection and the right side of V1 was contacted by the front of V2.. V1 came to final rest in the southbound lane facing north. V2 came to final rest on the right side of the road facing north.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a three lane, left curving, grass median divided roadway, in lane one.  Vehicle 1 departed the roadway to the right where it struck the grass ditch with its front.  Vehicle 1 continued off road, rotating slightly counter-clockwise and beginning a right side leading rollover.  During the rollover, the vehicle struck at least three trees before coming to rest on its top within a group of trees.  The vehicle rolled six quarter turns.  A tree came through the right front door below the right A pillar, exiting the top left windshield by the left A pillar.  The vehicle most likely struck several other smaller trees as it rolled.

V1 was traveling east on a five lane, non-divided, two-way roadway, in lane three, turning left into a business driveway.  V2 was traveling west on the same roadway, in lane one.  The right side of V1 was contacted by the front of V2.  V1 rotated counter-clockwise and came to rest in the westbound lanes facing northwest. V2 came to rest in the northwest corner of the intersection facing northwest.

Vehicle #1 was traveling south on a three-lane divided highway. V1 lost control and began to yaw counter-clockwise. V1 departed the road to the left, and the front plane of V1 contacted a cable barrier. V1's yaw rate increased, and the back plane of V1 contacted the barrier again. V1 continued to yaw, "rolling" down the barrier. The left plane of V1 contacted the barrier. V1 came to rest off road to the east.
V1 was traveling north on a two lane two way roadway. The front of V1 contacted a deer in the roadway. V1 came to final rest on the roadway.
V1 was traveling east on a three lane roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right and the front stuck a pole which then fell on top of the vehicle. V1 came to final rest off the roadway.

Vehicles 1 and 2 were traveling in the first southbound lane of a six lane positively divided roadway. Vehicle 1 was contacted on the back plane by the frontal plane of vehicle 2. After contact vehicle 1 came to rest on the roadway, vehicle 2 continued traveling and did not stop.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north on a three lane divided roadway in the left turn lane, attempting to turning left across the intersection with a driveway entrance. Vehicle 2 was traveling south on the same roadway and contacted the right side plane of vehicle 1 with its frontal plane. V1 departed the roadway and contacted a curb with it left rear tire before coming to rest. V2 came to rest in the roadway.

V1 was southbound on a 2 lane roadway when it departed the roadway to the right. V1 then re-entered the roadway, crossed all travel lanes and departed the roadway to the left. Then the front of V1 contacted a sign. V1 continued to travel, up an incline, and began to yaw clock-wise. V1 then rolled to the left 3 quarter turns. V1 occupant was fully ejected. V1 came to rest on its left side off of the roadway.
V1 was traveling south on a 2 way, non divided roadway. V1's front contacted a deer in the roadway . V1 came to rest on the shoulder to the right of roadway facing south.

V1 and V2 were traveling westbound on a four-lane, non-divided roadway in lane two approaching an intersection controlled by a traffic light. V1 was slowing in traffic attempting to turn left at the intersection. The front of V2 contacted the rear of V1. V1 and V2 came to final rest in the roadway facing west.

V2 was traveling northbound on a two-lane, two-way roadway in lane one approaching an intersection with east and west traffic controlled by a stop sign. V1 was traveling east one a two-lane, two-way roadway in lane one attempting a left turn to head south. In the middle of the intersection the front of V2 contacted the left side of V1. V1 came to final rest facing northeast in the north east quadrant of the intersection. V2 Departed the roadway to the Northwest and impacted a fire hydrant with its right side before coming to rest.
V1 was traveling northeast on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. The front of V1 impacted a deer causing damage. V1 came to final rest on the east side of the road facing north.

V1 was eastbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 steered right to avoid a tree limb in the road. V1 departed the left road edge in a counter clockwise motion. V1 impacted a ditch with the frontal plane then overturned right side leaning three quarter turns onto its left side before rolling one quarter turn back on its roof coming to rest facing north.

Vehicle 1 was westbound on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway.  Vehicle 2 was eastbound on the same roadway.  Vehicle 1 turned left to enter a parking lot.  Vehicle 2 front plane struck vehicle 1's right plane. Vehicle 1 came to rest in the parking lot on the south side of the roadway facing west.  Vehicle 2 came to rest in the roadway facing east.

V1 was traveling south on a physically divided two lane highway in lane two. V2 was traveling on the same physically divided two lane highway in lane one. Approaching an off ramp, V1 began to change lanes into lane one, but the right side of V1 impacted the front left of V2. V1 yawed clockwise and continued off the roadway where the right side impacted a tree. V1 came to rest on its wheels facing a southerly direction. V2 exited the off ramp and came to rest at an unknown location.

V1 was traveling south on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway. A deer entered the roadway from the eastern shoulder, and V1 attempted to avoid the deer in the roadway. V1 departed the right (west) side of the roadway contacting a cable barrier guardrail with its frontal and right side planes. V1 came to final rest partially off of the roadway on the shoulder.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south bound on a two lane non -physically divided roadway negotiating a left hand curve.  Vehicle 1 departed to the right striking a curb with the undercarriage.  Vehicle continued across the lawn of a private residence making contact with a bush planted next to a retaining wall.  Vehicle 1 dropped over the wall striking a mailbox encased in rock with its front plane.  Vehicle 1 continued traveling striking a landscaping barrel with its front plane.  The vehicle rotated clockwise on the longitudinal axis landing on the driver's side, and began sliding on the driver's side into the back of legally parked Vehicle 2.  The front plane of V1, again, made contact with the rear plane of V2.  V1 came to rest at contact with V2.  The vehicle was positioned on its left side facing south.  V2 was pushed forward a few feet where it came to rest facing south.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a 7 lane two way, physically divided road way in lane two position. Vehicle two was traveling the same direction in front of V1. As both vehicles approached an intersection V2 stopped and the front of V1 contacted the rear of V2. V1 and V2 came to rest facing south in lane two.

Vehicle 1 was traveling northbound on a two lane, two way, non-physically divided gravel roadway in lane 1 position. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway left side while negotiating a curve. Vehicle 1 traveled down a grassy hillside V1's front contacted a barbed wire fence. Vehicle continued down an embankment V1's front made contact with an embankment. V1 came to rest after impact.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north on a two lane, two-way, road in lane 1 position. V1 departed the roadway to the right and the left side of V1 contacted a guardrail end. V1 then rolled approximately 7 quarter turns over and off the guardrail before coming to rest on its passenger side facing south.

V1 was traveling northeast following a two-way, four lane road. V1 lost control departed the roadway to the right. V1 started to rotate clockwise, impacting a stump with its left side. Continuing in its clockwise spin, the left side of V1 impacted three trees before coming to final rest off the roadway facing west.

V1 was traveling north on an unlit two-lane, two-way road that curved to the right. V1 departed its lane to the left and then departed the left side of the road where its front plane impacted a guardrail end. V1 rotated slightly clockwise and its left side sideswiped a tree before coming to rest off of the left side of the road.

V1 was traveling in an easterly direction on a designated north/south divided trafficway (median strip with positive barrier) in lane 2 (of three lanes). V2 was traveling in the same direction on the same trafficway in lane 1 and was approaching V2. V1 departed its lane to the right and its right side contacted the left side of V2. V2 became momentarily stuck underneath V1 before it came to rest on its wheels facing a southeasterly direction on the right hand shoulder. V1 was driven to the right shoulder and parked.

V1 was traveling in a southwesterly direction through the left hand curve of the roadway on a designated east/west, two-way, not physically divided trafficway, and was in lane 1 (of six lanes). V1 departed the road on the right, where all four of its wheels/tires came in contact with the curb along the road edge, and its right side mirror came in contact with a metal pole supporting a sign. V1 traversed the sidewalk and traveled through a chain-link fence surrounding a parking area. In the parking area, V1's front end came in contact with a separate section of the same chain-link fence, and then a palm tree just beyond the fence. V1 rotated clockwise and its left side came into contact with the same separate section of fence. V1 came to rest on its wheels facing a northwesterly direction at the fence line.

V1 was traveling east through an intersection from a two-way, not physically divided trrafficway, and was in lane 1 (of five lanes).  V2 was traveling from west to south (making a left turn) through the same intersection from a two-way, not physically divided trafficway, and was in lane 3 (of five lanes).  In the intersection, the left side of V1 came into contact with the front end of V2.  V1 came to rest facing a southeasterly direction near the southeast corner of the intersection.  V2 came to rest facing a southwesterly direction just west of V1.

V1 and V2 were traveling north in lane two of a four-lane, two-way road. V3 was traveling south in lane two on the same road. V1 slowed down to make a left turn into a gas station when the front of V2 impacted its rear plane causing it to rotate clockwise. V1 came to rest between lane one and two facing south. V2 then crossed over the left lane line and its front plane impacted the left side of V3. V3 came to rest on its right side of the road facing south. V2 came to rest in its lane four facing west.

All vehicles were traveling northbound on a 3 lane roadway approaching an intersection. V3 had entered the intersection and stopped. V2 stopped just prior to entering the intersection. V1 then impacted the back of V2, pushing it forward into the intersection. The front of V2 then impacted the back of V3. All vehicles came to rest in lane 3 facing northbound.

V1 was traveling westbound in lane two of a four lane, not physically divided, two-way roadway. V2 was traveling eastbound in lane one of the same four lane, not physically divided, two-way roadway. V3 with trailer was traveling eastbound ahead of V2 in lane two of the same four lane, not physically divided, two-way roadway. V1 crossed the center line striking with his front plane the left plane of the trailer in tow by V3. V3 swerved to the right coming to final rest on the shoulder of the roadway. V1 continued traveling westbound in the eastbound lanes. V1 front plane contacted V2 front plane. V1 came to final rest facing south across the eastbound lane of the roadway. V2 rotated counter-clockwise tripping over at edge of pavement, rolled 1 quarter turn and came to final rest on the left plane off the roadway to the right.

V1 was east bound on a two lane non divided bidirectional roadway, with a downward grade, negotiating a curve to the left. V1 departed the roadway to the right, where its frontal plane impacted an embankment. V1's left plane then impacted the side of a ditch, before coming to final rest off the right side of the roadway in the ditch.

V1 was east bound on a two lane, non-divided, bidirectional roadway, negotiating a slight curve to the left. The roadway was bordered on the north side with a positive grade embankment, and with a guardrail and a negative grade embankment on the south side of the roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right, rotating counter clockwise, where it struck an embankment with its right plane causing V1 to roll right side leading.  V1 rolled 4 quarter turns and struck a tree with its right side before coming to final rest. V1 was at final rest, on its wheels, on the right side of the roadway.

Both vehicles were traveling northwest in lane 2 of a 3 lane roadway. V2 then began to change lanes to the right into lane 1. V1 then partially departed it's lane to the right and impacted the back of V1. Both vehicles came to rest facing northwest V2 in lane 1 and V1 in lane 2.

V1 was traveling north in lane one of a left curved three lane connection ramp of two highways, negotiating a left curve. V2, V3 and V4 were traveling in the same lane ahead of V1. V4 decelerated due to slow traffic ahead. The front of V3 impacted the rear of V4. V1 then impacted the back of V2 with its front. V2 was pushed forward and impacted the rear of V3 with its front. All vehicles came to rest in their lanes of traffic, facing north.

V1 was traveling southbound on a two lane, two-way roadway approaching a four-way intersection, controlled by a stop sign. V2 was traveling eastbound on a two lane, two-way roadway passing through the same intersection. V1's front plane contacted V2's left plane. V1 came to final rest further southbound on roadway at intersection. V2 came to final rest facing eastbound on roadway.

V1 was traveling southbound on a two lane, two-way roadway approaching a four-way intersection controlled by a stop sign for north and south directions. V1 was attempting a left turn when V1 lost control and departed the roadway on the right side. V1 then struck a utility pole with it's front plane before coming to final rest off roadway facing southbound.

V1 and V2 were traveling south on a six lane physically divided roadway. V2 stopped for traffic ahead. V1 attempted to avoid by changing lanes to its right. The left side of V1 contacted the rear of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.
V1 and V2 were traveling south on a four lane undivided roadway. V2 stopped and the front of V1 contacted the rear of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest near the point of impact.

V1 was traveling south on a two-way, two lane road in the right lane. V2 was stopped in front of V1 on the same two-way, two lane road. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2. V2 rotated counter-clockwise and came to final rest on the roadway facing southeast. After impact with V2, V1 departed the roadway to the right. V1 impacted a curb with its right front tire and a sign with its frontal plane before coming to final rest off the roadway facing south.

V1 was traveling southeast following a two-way, two lane road with a curve to the right. As V1 was negotiating the curve, it departed its travel lane to the left. Continuing forward, V1 departed the roadway to the left. The front of V1 impacted two trees before coming to final rest off the roadway facing south.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north on a two lane, two-way roadway in lane 1 approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling west on a two lane, two-way roadway in lane 1 approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection proceeding straight. The front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. After impact V2 rolled 2 quarter turns coming to rest on the north west corner of the intersection on it's top facing north east. V1 came to rest in the middle of the intersection after impact facing north.

V1 was traveling west (wrong way) on a physically divided trafficway (median strip with positive barrier) and was on the median shoulder.  V2 was traveling east on the same roadway, in lane 3 (of four lanes), and was approaching V1.  V1 entered onto the roadway and into V2's path.  In lane 3, the front end of V1 came into contact with the left side of V2.  V1 came to rest on its wheels, facing a westerly direction, on the median shoulder.  V2 came to rest on its wheels, facing an easterly direction, on the right hand shoulder, and east of V1.

V1 was traveling from east to north (making a left turn) through a "T" intersection from a two-way, not physically divided trafficway, and was in lane 1.  V2 was traveling south through the same intersection from a two-way, non-physically divided trafficway, and was in lane 2.  In the intersection, the left side of V1 came into contact with the front of V2.  V1 came to rest on its wheels, facing a southeasterly direction in the northbound travel lanes, south of the intersection.  V2 departed the road on the left, where its front left and front right wheels/tires came into contact with a curb, and its front end then came into contact with a pole.  V2 came to rest on its wheels, facing a southeasterly direction atop the curb and with its front end against the pole, north of V1.

V1 was traveling westbound in lane one on an two way, undivided two lane roadway. V2 was also traveling westbound in the same lane and direction in front of V1. V1's frontal plane came into contact with V2's rear end plane. Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling northbound on a two way roadway with a single lane of travel in each direction. V1 departed the roadway on the right side and the frontal plane of V1 made contact with the a pole. V1 came to final rest partially on the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling northbound on a two lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position.  Vehicle 2 was traveling westbound on a two lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position.  Both vehicles 1 and 2 entered into the intersection.  The front plane of V1 made contact with the left plane of V2.  Vehicle 1 began to rotate counter clockwise while V2 began to rotate clockwise.  The right plane of V1 made contact with the left plane of V2.  V1 came to final rest facing west in the northwest corner of the intersection.  V2 departed the intersection at the northwest location facing north.

V1 was traveling north in the third lane of a three-lane, divided roadway. V2, V3, and V4 were traveling north in the third lane on the same three-lane, divided roadway. V5 was traveling north in lane 2 of the same roadway.  The frontal plane of V1 impacted the back plane of V2. (Event 1) The frontal plane of V1 also impacted the back plane of V5. (Event 2) After the initial impact, the frontal plane of V2 impacted the back plane of V3, causing the frontal plane of V3 to impact the back plane of V4. V1, V2, V3, and V4 came to rest near the point of initial impact. V5 continued traveling north.

V1 was traveling south in lane one on a two lane median divided roadway. V2 was also traveling south on the same roadway in lane two behind V1. Both vehicles were negotiating a slight left hand curve in the roadway. While attempting to turn left to travel on a different roadway, V1 crossed the left lane line and  made contact with the right side plane of V2. V1 continued forward and came to a final rest on the right (west) side shoulder of the roadway. V2 continued forward and came to a final rest off the left (east) side of the roadway in the median.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane two way undivided roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the left and the front of V1 contacted a guardrail face. V1 then climbed on top of the guardrail and the left side of V1 contacted the guardrail face as V1 came to final rest off the roadway and on top of the guardrail.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane two way roadway. V1 lost traction and departed the roadway to the left and rolled to the left four quarter turns. V1 came to final rest off the north road edge facing south.

V1 was traveling east on a straight two-lane rural roadway. V2 was traveling in the opposite direction on the same road, which was covered in ice. The front of V1 struck the front of V2 in the westbound lane. Both vehicles came to final rest on the grass roadside.

V1 was traveling southbound on a two lane undivided (two way traffic) road in lane 1 approaching a stop sign. V2 was traveling westbound on a four lane undivided (two way traffic) road in lane two. At the stop sign V1 turned left, the front of V2 impacted the left side of V1. V1 rotated clockwise and came to rest in lane two of the four lane road facing westbound. V2 came to rest in lane two facing westbound.

Vehicle 1 was eastbound on a two lane, two way roadway.  Vehicle 1 departed the roadway to the right.  Vehicle 1 front plane struck a plastic reflector post.  Vehicle 1 traveled into ditch and rolled 8 quarters turns to the left.  While rolling, vehicle 1 back plane stuck a fence.  Vehicle 1 came to rest in a field facing west.
V1 was traveling north in lane 2 on a 3-lane divided roadway negotiating a left curve. The front of V1 contacted a deer in the road. V1 came to rest on the right shoulder.

V1 was travelling North on a 2 lane 2 way not physically divided roadway. V2 was legally parked and not occupied facing south. V1 departed the roadway to the left striking V2 Left plane with it's Front plane. V1 came to rest facing Northeast.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a two-lane, two-way roadway approaching a business entrance driveway. V2 was traveling westbound on the same roadway attempting a left turn into the business entrance. The front of V1 contacted the right side of V2 in the eastbound lanes. V1 came to final rest facing eastbound and V2 came to final rest partially on the driveway facing south.

Vehicle 1 was traveling in the westbound lane of a two lane undivided roadway, vehicle 2 was stopped in the same travel lane. The frontal plane of vehicle 1 contacted the back plane of vehicle 2. After contact vehicle 2 rotated counter clockwise and contacted a wooden post with its right side plane. Vehicle 2 then entered into a rollover event coming to rest on its top plane off the roadway. Vehicle 1 continued post contact and departed its' initial travel lane entering into the eastbound lane of travel and contacted its' frontal plane with the frontal plane of vehicle 3. Both vehicles 2 and 3 came to rest on the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a two-lane divided highway when it departed the right (west) side of the roadway and contacted a tree with its frontal plane. Vehicle 1 rotated clockwise and contacted a second tree with its left side plane.  V1 came to rest off the roadway.

V1 was negotiating a left curve, traveling north, on a two-way, two lane road. V1 departed the roadway to the right, returned to the roadway then departed its travel lane to the left. Continuing forward, V1 departed the roadway on the left. The front of V1 impacted a 27cm diameter tree before coming to final rest off the road facing north. The driver was fully ejected.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a two lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1 position approaching a 4 way intersection. V2 was traveling south on a 4 lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1 position approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection. The left side of V1 contacted the front of V2. Due to impact V1 rotated counter clockwise and rolled 2 quarter turns landing on its top facing north on the east side of the intersection. V2 came to rest facing south east in the intersection.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on two lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position, approaching a sign controlled intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling north on a two lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position, approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection. The front plane of Vehicle 1 made contact with the right plane of Vehicle 2. Vehicle 1 came to final rest on the northern portion of the intersection facing northwest. Vehicle 2 rotated counterclockwise coming to final rest at the northwest corner of the intersection facing west.

Vehicle #1 was traveling east in lane one of a two-lane, undivided roadway.  V1 end departed at a T-intersection.  The front of V1 contacted a ditch.  The undercarriage of V1 then contacted the ditch.  V1 continued forward and the front of V1 contacted shrub overgrowth.  The front of V1 then contacted a parked RV trailer.   V1 came to rest near this impact, facing east.

Vehicle #1 was traveling east in lane two of a two-lane physically divided trafficway.  V1 lost control and began to rotate counter-clockwise.  V1 departed its lane to the right.  V1 re-entered its lane and departed the road to the left.  The front of V1 contacted a cable barrier guardrail.  V1 continued to rotate counter-clockwise in contact with the guardrail, producing damage on the right and back planes.  V1 came to rest against the cable barrier, facing west.

V1 was traveling southbound on a two-lane, two-way roadway with V2 parked on the southbound lane shoulder. The front of V1 contacted the left side of V2 and continued southbound off the roadway where the front plane then struck a utility pole. V1 came to final rest off the roadway facing south. V2 came to final rest at point of impact facing south.

V1 was traveling west on two lane, two-way roadway approaching a private driveway. V2 was traveling south exiting a two lane, two-way private driveway.  The front of V2 made contact with the left side of V1.

V1 was traveling south on a rural gravel roadway, negotiating a left curve. V1 departed the right side of the roadway striking a culvert with its frontal plane. V1 then rotated counterclockwise and rolled, right side leading, three quarter turns coming to rest on its left side heading south.

V1 was heading north out of the parking lot and onto the roadway to head east. V2 was heading east on the five lane undivided roadway. The left of V1 connected with the right of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest facing in easterly direction near the point of impact.

V1 and V2 were heading south on a four lane divided interstate. V1 was traveling in lane four and V2 was traveling in lane one. V1 departed the roadway to the left. The front of V1 connected with the concrete median. V1 was then redirected to the right where it re-entered the roadway and crossed three lanes of the trafficway. The right of V1 connected with the front of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest near the point of impact.

V1 was traveling south bound on a four lane, physically divided roadway, with two lanes north bound and two lanes south bound. V1 was in the two lane. V1 departed the roadway to the left, where V1 impacted a ditch/culvert with its frontal plane, V1 rotated counterclockwise, where its back end impacted a cable barrier guard rail, before coming to final rest facing south bound on the left side of the roadway.

V1 and V2 were both traveling west on a two-lane road. V2 was stopped ahead of V1. V3 was traveling in the opposite direction on the same road. The front of V1 struck the back of V2 (event 1) causing V2 to overturn (event 2) two-quarter turns and come to rest on the westbound shoulder. Debris from the initial impact contacted the front of V3 (event 3). V1 came to rest within the westbound lanes facing a southerly direction. V3 came to rest in the eastbound lanes facing east.

V1 was traveling south on a divided trafficway (median strip with positive barrier) in lane 4 (of five lanes) and was approaching V2, which was disabled facing south, on the same roadway, ahead in lane 4. V3 was approaching V1 traveling in the same direction on the same roadway, also in lane 4. In lane 4, the front end of V1 contacted an unknown plane of V2. The front end of V3 then contacted the back end of V1. V1 came to rest on its wheels facing a southerly direction across lanes 4 and 5. V2 came to rest on its left side facing a southerly direction in lanes 3 and 4. V3 came to rest on its wheels facing a southerly direction in the center divider.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a 3 lane, two-way physically divided roadway in lane number 1. Vehicle 1 departed the road on the right side, and vehicle 1's front made contact with a guardrail. After the first impact, vehicle 1 was deflected left and departed the roadway to the left. Vehicle 1's front then made contact with the barrier wall on the north side of the roadway. After contact with the barrier, vehicle 1 rolled 6 quarter turns, right side leading, and came to final rest in the roadway on its top, facing northeast, in lane number 3.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a 5 lane median divided roadway in lane number 5, intending to make a left hand turn. Vehicle 2 was traveling north on a 5 lane median divided roadway in lane number 2. Vehicle 3 was stopped at the light  in lane number 1 waiting to head west. Vehicle 1's right side and vehicle 2's front made contact with each other in the intersection. After initial contact, vehicle 1  rotated counter clock-wise and went onto the sidewalk on the north east side of the intersection and continued forward and made contact with a wall on the north east side. Vehicle 2 was redirected, clockwise and made contact with vehicle 3's front end in lane number 1 facing west. Vehicle 1 came to final rest against the wall on the north east side. Vehicle 2 came to rest facing east, against vehicle 3 in lane 1.

V1 was traveling south west in the #1 lane of a 2 lane undivided roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right and the front of V1 impacted a light pole. V1 continued forward and V1 impacted some low hanging tree branches as it proceeded down an embankment. V1 continued forward and the front of V1 impacted a tree. V1 came to rest facing north west off the roadway against the tree.

V1 was traveling west in the #2 lane of a 3 lane divided highway. V2 was traveling west in the #3 lane of a 3 lane divided highway. V1 changed lanes into the #3 lane. V2 slowed due to traffic. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in the #3 lane facing west.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south in lane one on a five lane, two way trafficway divided by a grass median. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway on the right side and the front of vehicle 1 contacted a guardrail end. Vehicle 1 came to final rest off the roadway facing west.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east in lane one on a three lane two way roadway. Vehicle 2 was traveling east in front of vehicle 1 on the same roadway. Vehicle 3 was traveling east in front of vehicle 2 on the same roadway. Vehicles 2 and 3 stopped for traffic. The front plane of vehicle 1 contacted the back plane of vehicle 2. Upon impact vehicle 2 was pushed forward and the front plane of vehicle 2 contacted the back plane of vehicle 3. All three vehicles came to final rest on the roadway facing east.

V1 was traveling south on a three lane, two way, undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V1 made a right hand turn at the intersection and departed the left side of their initial travel lane and then departed the left side of the roadway. V1 contacted a cable barrier guardrail with its frontal plane. V1 came to final rest partially off of the roadway.

V1 was traveling west on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a left hand curve in the roadway. V1 departed the right (north) hand side of the roadway. V1 then returned to their initial travel lane, departed the left hand lane line, and then departed the left (south) hand side of the roadway. V1 then struck a pole with its frontal plane. V1 then continued forward rotating in a clockwise direction slightly before overturning three quarter turns. V1 then struck a group of shrubs with its top plane. V1 came to final rest partially on its left side and roof off of the roadway.

V1 was traveling northwest in lane one of a two-lane divided roadway with a positive barrier.  V2 and V3 were parked facing northwest on the left side of the same roadway.  V1 departed the road to the left.  The left plane of V1 contacted a guardrail face (event 1).  The front of V1 contacted the back of V2 (event 2).  This pushed V2 forward and the front of V2 contacted the back of V3.  V1's hitch failed and the back of V1 contacted the front of the trailer it had been towing (event 3).  V1 came to rest off the road to the left, facing north.  V2 came to rest on the roadway facing southeast.  V3 came to rest partially on the shoulder, facing south.

V1 was traveling west in lane 1 on a 3 lane divided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south in lane 1 on a 2 lane divided roadway negotiating a right curve approaching the same intersection intending to turn right.  As both vehicles entered the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V1 continued forward and came to rest in the westbound lane facing west. V2 rotated clockwise and came to rest in the northwest corner of the intersection facing west.

V2 and V3 were traveling northbound on a two lane divided road (positive barrier) in lane 2. V1 was abandoned in lane 2 facing westbound after a previous crash. The front of V2 impacted the left side of V1. V1 rotated counter clockwise and came to rest in lane 2 facing eastbound. V2 continued north and departed the roadway to the left and the front of V2 impacted a concrete bridge rail. The left side of V2 impacted the bridge rail and came to rest in lane 2 facing north. The front of V3 impacted the right side of V1. V1 rotated counter clockwise and the back of V1 impacted a guardrail. V1 came to rest partially in lane 2 facing east. V3 then departed the roadway to the right and the right side of V3 impacted a guardrail in a side swipe manner. V3 then returned to roadway and departed both lanes the left and the front of V3 impacted the concrete bridge rail. V3 came to rest in lane 2 facing north.

V1 was traveling south in the third of seven lanes on an undivided, two-way roadway. V2 was traveling south in the same lane behind V1. V3 was traveling south in the same lane ahead of V1. V3 stopped for traffic. The front of V1 contacted the back of V3. The back of V1 then contacted the front of V2. All three vehicles came to rest in the lane.

Vehicle 1 was traveling northwest on a two lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position.  Vehicle 2 was traveling northeast on a two lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position.  Both vehicles were approaching an intersection and entered at the same time.  The front plane of Vehicle 1 made contact with the right front plane of Vehicle 2.  Vehicle 1 rotated clockwise and Vehicle 2 rotated counter clockwise.  The left plane of Vehicle 1 then made contact with the right rear plane of Vehicle 2.  Vehicle 1 came to final rest at the south east corner of the intersection facing roughly east.  Vehicle 2 passed through the intersection and came to rest at the edge of the roadway facing east.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a two lane two way roadway, exiting a private parking lot to travel through an intersection. V2 was traveling west on a 5 lane two way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1 position. Both vehicles entered the intersection. The left of V1 contacted the front of V2. V1 came to rest in the center turn lane facing south west. and V2 came to rest also facing south west in the west bound lanes.

V1 was traveling northbound entering a traffic circle pattern intersection with two travel lanes heading north. V2 and V3 were traveling eastbound on a four-lane roadway passing through the traffic circle, V2 was in lane one and V3 was in lane two. V1 entered the traffic circle and continued northbound where the left plane struck the front plane of V2 in a sideswipe type pattern. V1 continued forward where the front plane of V1 struck the right plane of V3. After the impact with V3, V1 veered to the right where V1 departed the roadway on a traffic island on the northeast quadrant of the intersection and the front plane struck a light pole. V1 came to final rest against the light pole, V2 came to final rest at point of impact, and V3 came to final rest in the northwest quadrant facing northeast.

V1 V2 and V3 were traveling north on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway, with V1 leading, followed by V2 which was being followed by V3. The frontal plane of V3 struck the rear plane of V2. Then the frontal plane of V2 struck the rear plane of V1. V1 came to rest near the point of impact heading north. V2 departed the roadway to the right and came to rest off the roadway heading north. V3 came to rest near the point of impact with V2 heading north.

V1 was traveling east in the number 1 lane of a 2 lane undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south in the number 1 lane of a 2 lane undivided roadway approaching an intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection. The front of V1 impacted the right of V2. V2 rotated clockwise and to the south where it departed the roadway and the right side of V2 impacted a pole. V1 came to rest facing southerly on the east side of the intersection. V2 came to rest facing northerly on the south part of the intersection against the pole.

Vehicle 1 was traveling westbound in the fifth lane of a nine lane median divided trafficway turning left within the intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling in the second eastbound lane of the same roadway crossing the intersection. The frontal plane of vehicle 2 contacted the right side plane of vehicle 1. Both vehicles came to rest in the intersection.

Vehicles 1 and 2 were in the third westbound travel lane of a three lane median divided roadway. Vehicle 2 decelerated within its travel lane and was contacted on the back plane by the frontal plane of vehicle 1, both vehicles came to rest on the roadway.

V1 was northbound on a 4 lane roadway approaching a 4 way intersection attempting to turn left. V2 was southbound on the same roadway approaching the same intersection. Within the intersection, the right side of V1 contacted the front of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling west in the first of two lanes on a undivided, two-way roadway. V2 was parked facing west along the north curb. The front of V1 contacted the back of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in the road.

V1 was traveling east in the second of four lanes on a positively divided, two-way roadway. V2 was traveling east in the third lane on the same roadway. V1 changed lanes to the left and the front of V1 contacted the back of V2. V2 departed the roadway on the left side as it rotated counter-clockwise and the front of V2 contacted the concrete traffic barrier. V2 continued to rotate counter-clockwise and the right side contacted the concrete barrier. V2 came to rest facing east on the roadway. Vehicle 1 departed the south side of the road a came to rest off the roadway facing north. V1 then was engulfed in a fire.

V1 and V2 were traveling west in lane one of three on a physically divided roadway in an interchange area, V3 was in lane two on the same roadway. The front of V1 contacted the rear of V2. V2 then traveled into lane 3 and the front of V3 contacted the rear of V2. V1 continued to travel west post impact. V2 and V3 came to rest facing west off the south road edge.

V1 and V2 were traveling southbound on a two-lane, two-way roadway with V1 traveling behind V2. V2 was slowing for traffic when the front plane of V1 contacted the back plane of V2. Both vehicle came to final rest at point of impact facing south.

V1 was traveling north west on a 3 lane divided roadway in lane 3.  V1 crossed over two lanes to the right where lane 1 diverged from lanes 2 and 3. V1 then departed the left road edge where it contacted a tree with its front plane. The tree broke away and contacted the top of V1.
