V1 continued forward as it rotated clockwise and contacted a tree with its right side. V1 continued to rotate clockwise and contacted a tree with its left side. V1 came to rest off the road facing north.

V1 was traveling southeast on a two lane, two-way roadway crossing over a four-way intersection. V2 was traveling westbound on a two lane, two-way roadway. The front plane of V1 contacted V2 left plane. V1 came to final rest further south after impact on roadway. V2 came to  final rest further westbound on roadway.

Vehicles 1 and 2 were traveling east on a 4 lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1 position. V1 was behind V2. The front of V1 contacted the rear of V2. V2 came to rest still facing east in the lane of travel. V1 came to rest still facing east on the shoulder of the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a two-way, not physically divided roadway in lane number 1 , approaching a four-leg intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling west on a two-way, not physically divided roadway in lane number 1 approaching the same intersection.  Vehicle 1's front made contact with Vehicle 2's right side within the intersection. Vehicle 2 rotated clockwise and initiated a six (6) quarter-turn rollover sequence, coming to rest on its roof panel and adjacent to the southwest intersection quadrant. Vehicle 1 came to rest facing south in lane number 1.

V1 was traveling north, on a median divided roadway, with four lanes in the same direction, approaching a traffic signal controlled intersection. V2 was traveling west on a two-way, three lane undivided roadway, approaching the same intersection as V1. Both vehicles entered the intersection, with V2 attempting to turn left and V1 proceeding straight and the frontal plane of V1 contacted the left side plane of V2. Both vehicles came to a final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling northbound on a two way, two lane undivided roadway, approaching an intersection with a stop sign. V2 was traveling westbound in lane one, on a median divided roadway, with three lanes in the same direction, approaching the same intersection as V1. Both vehicles entered the intersection. The frontal plane of V2 contacted the right side plane of V1. V1 continued forward rotating in a counter clockwise direction making contact with V2's left plane with an unknown plane of V1. V1 continued forward departing the north side of the roadway striking an unknown plane of V3 parked in a commercial parking lot with its frontal plane. V1 came to final rest off of the roadway. V2 continued forward rotating in a clockwise direction and came to final rest on the north side of the roadway.

V1 was traveling west, on a median divided roadway, with two lanes in the same direction, passing through a traffic signal controlled intersection. V2 was traveling south on a two-way, three lane undivided roadway, approaching the same intersection as V1. V2 made a right hand turn onto the same roadway that V1 was traveling on. V1 was trailing V2. The front plane of V1 made contact with the rear plane of V2. Both V1 and V2 came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling westbound in lane two of a 4 lane, two way, undivided roadway.  V2 was traveling southbound on a two way undivided roadway approaching a T-intersection.  V1 and V2 entered the T-intersection simultaneously, and the front plane of V1 contacted the left plane of V2.

V1 and V2 were both traveling eastbound on a four lane, undivided roadway (two way traffic) in lane one. V2 was traveling ahead of V1 and attempted to turn right into a private drive. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2. V2 rotated clockwise and came to rest facing south in the private drive. V1 came to rest in lane one facing east.
V1 was traveling north on a two lane divided highway. The front of V1 contacted a deer in the roadway. V1 came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling south on a three lane, two way, divided roadway turning left at an intersection. V2 was traveling north on a three lane, two way, divided roadway approaching the same intersection. In the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the front of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway.

V1 and V2 were both traveling east in lane two on a two lane, positively divided roadway. V2 began to slow due to traffic ahead when V1's front plane contacted V2's rear plane. Both vehicles came to final rest, in lane two, on the roadway.

V1 and V2 were traveling northeast on a two way, two lane undivided roadway, approaching an intersection. V1 was trailing V2. V2 began to turn left at the intersection. The frontal plane of V1 made contact with the rear plane of V2. V1 and V2 came to a final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling north in lane 1 on a 2-lane divided roadway. V1 attempted to pass another and steered into lane 2. V1 then steered right and departed the right road edge while rotating clockwise where its front plane contacted an embankment and shrubbery. V1 continued to rotate clockwise and its left side contacted the embankment. V1 began to rotate counter-clockwise then tripped and rolled left 2-quarter turns where it came to rest on its top partially in the roadway facing southeast. The driver was partially ejected during the rollover sequence.

V1 was traveling southbound in lane 1 of a 2 lane, two-way, not physically divided roadway approaching an intersection. V1 departed the roadway to the right while traveling forward. V1's front plane contacted a stop sign and utility pole. V1 came to final rest off the roadway at the utility pole.

V1 was exiting a parking lot westbound on lane 1 of a 2 lane, two-way, not physically divided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling northbound on lane 3 of a 4 lane, two-way, divided roadway with both left and right turn lanes approaching the same intersection. V1 and V2 enter the intersection simultaneously. V1's left plane was contacted by V2's front plane.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 departed their initial lane of travel to the left, and then departed the roadway to the left. The front of V1 contacted a guardrail end off the roadway, and then the right side contacted a guardrail face. V1 came to final rest off the roadway with its front against a tree.

V1 was traveling west on five lane, two way, undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling east on a five lane, two way, roadway with a center turn lane, approaching the same intersection. V1 attempted a left hand turn in the intersection. The front of V1 contacted the front of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling west down a two-lane, two-way hill approaching a T-intersection. V1 traveled through the intersection and impacted an embankment with its front plane. V1 came to rest on the side of the road.

V1 was traveling northbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway in lane one. V1 departed it's lane to the left, then departed the roadway to the left. V1 began to yaw in a clockwise rotation. V1 then began to rollover left side leading. The left side of V1 impacted a chain link fence while rolling over. V1 then impacted the ground landing on it's top as it made contact with a utility box and the fence. The front of V1 then impacted a tree and the top of V1 impacted a metal fence pole. V1 then completed it's five quarter turns left side leading and came to rest on it's driver's side, off of the roadway facing southeast.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane roadway negotiating a right curve. V2 was traveling east on a two lane roadway negotiating a left curve. V3 was traveling west behind V1.  V1 departed its lane to the left and impacted the left side of V2. The impact caused V2 to rotate counter-clockwise and cross over into the westbound lane where the front of V2 impacted the front of V3. V1 continued in a westerly direction without stopping. V2 rotated counter-clockwise and came to rest partially in the westbound lane and the north shoulder facing a northeasterly direction. V3 came to rest partially in the westbound lane and the north shoulder facing a northwesterly direction.

V1 was traveling northeast in lane 1 of a two lane, two way, undivided roadway, when it encountered two deer in the road. V1 was traveling west on a non-physically divided five lane road in lane one approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south on a non-physically divided three lane off ramp, in lane three, approaching an intersection to turn left. As V2 entered the intersection the front of V1 was impacted, by the right side of V1, that was passing through the intersection. V1 came to rest within lanes one and two in the west side of the intersection facing a westerly direction. V2 came to rest within the intersection, facing a southwest direction.

V1 was traveling north on a non-physically divided two-lane highway in lane two. V1 traveled off the west road edge into a dirt grass median. V1 returned back to the roadway, as it initiated a clockwise rotation, crossing both lanes and ultimately departing the east road edge into a dirt grass embankment. V1 was leading with its right side plane when it tripped, initiating a four-quarter turn rollover sequence. V1 came to rest on it's wheels, facing a northwest direction.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a two lane, one-way not physically divided roadway in lane number one. Vehicle 2 was legally parked on the north shoulder  of the road. Vehicle 1's front and vehicle 2's rear end made contact with each other. Vehicle 1 came to rest facing west against vehicle 2 rear end. Vehicle 2 came to final rest in it's original location.

V1 was traveling northbound in the second lane of a four lane, two-way roadway. V2 was traveling southbound in the first lane of a four lane, two-way roadway. V1 attempted to turn left in the roadway towards a driveway entrance to travel west. The right side plane of V1 was impacted by the frontal plane of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway facing south.

Vehicle 2 was traveling west on a 6 lane, two-way, physically divided roadway in lane 2 stopped at an intersection. Vehicle 1 was traveling west bound on the same 6 lane physically divided roadway in the lane 2 position behind V2. The front plane of Vehicle 1 made contact with the rear plane of Vehicle 2. Both vehicles came to final rest facing west at impact.

V1 was traveling northeast on a two-way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a right hand curve in the roadway. V2 was traveling southwest on the same roadway as V1, negotiating a left hand curve in the roadway. V1 departed the left lane line and its frontal plane contacted the frontal plane of V2. V1 proceeded forward departing the western side of the roadway and contacting a cable barrier guardrail. V1 came to final rest off of the roadway while V2 came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling southwest in lane one of a two lane roadway negotiating a right curve. V1 departed its travel lane to the left then departed the left road edge. V1 contacted a tree with its front plane then rolled right two quarter turns. V1 came to rest on its top plane off the left road edge.

V1 was traveling northwest exiting a private drive attempting to make a right turn. V2 was traveling northeast in lane one of a three lane divided roadway in lane one approaching the private drive. V1's left plane contacted V2's front plane. Both vehicles came to rest in the roadway near impact.

V1 was traveling northwest in lane 1 on a 2 lane, non divided roadway and approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling east in lane 2 of a 4 lane roadway with a 2 way turn lane and approaching the same intersection. Within the intersection, V1 turned left. V1's front contacted V2's front. Both vehicles came to rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling northbound on a 5 lane major highway in lane 4. V1 attempted to change lanes into lane 5. V1 then departed the roadway to the left and the front of V1 impacted the concrete barrier. The left side of V1 then contacted the barrier. V1 then deflected off the barrier to the right and crossed all 5 lanes of traffic to the right. V1 then departed the roadway to the right and the front of V1 impacted a tree. V1 came to rest facing east against the tree.

V1 was traveling east in lane two of a two lane divided roadway. V1 departed the roadway to its right. The front of V1 impacted the concrete pillar of a bridge. V1 rotated counter clockwise around the pillar and the right side of V1 impacted the concrete traffic barrier . V1 came to rest facing southeast.

V1 was traveling westbound on a two way roadway with a single lane of travel in each direction. V2 was traveling southbound in the right lane of a two way roadway with a two lanes of travel in each direction. At the intersection, the right side plane of V1 made contact with the frontal plane of V2 . Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling westbound on a two way roadway with a single lane of travel in each direction. V2 was traveling southbound in the third lane of a divided roadway with a total of four lanes. In the intersection, the right side plane of V1, made contact with the frontal plane of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling north making a left turn in the second lane one a three-lane roadway. V2 was traveling straight west in lane two on a five-lane roadway. V3 was waiting at a red light on an adjacent three-lane roadway. V1's right plane came into contact with V2's front plane. Upon that impact, V2 veered off to the right and V2's front plane came into contact with V3's front plane. All vehicles came to final rest in the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was southbound on a two way, two lane roadway.  Vehicle 2 was southbound on the same roadway.  Vehicle 1 had struck a wheel in the roadway damaging it's right front tire.  Vehicle 1 was slowing and moving to the southbound shoulder.  Vehicle 2 swerved into the northbound lane to miss the tire Vehicle 1 had just stuck.  Vehicle 2 returned back to the southbound lane striking Vehicle 1's back plane with its front plane. Vehicle 1 rotated clockwise coming to rest facing northwest in the southbound lane. Vehicle 2 rolled four quarter turns to the left.  Vehicle 2 struck the northbound guardrail as it completed it's fourth quarter turn with the back under carriage.  Vehicle 2 came to rest facing southwest in the northbound lane.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane physically divided highway in lane one. V2 was traveling north on a two lane physically divided highway in lane one in front of V1. An unknown vehicle began to enter the highway from the shoulder causing V2 to begin braking. V1 also began braking. The front of V1 contacted the back of V2. Both vehicles came to rest a short distance from impact in the travel lane.

Vehicle 1 was traveling in the northbound second lane of a four lane, median divided, roadway. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway to the left and entered into the grass median. Vehicle 1 rolled, left side leading, four quarter turns and came to final rest, on its wheels in the median.

V1 was traveling northeast in lane one of a two lane roadway negotiating a right curve. V1 departed the right (east) road edge and went into a clockwise rotation. The left front wheel of V1 separated from contact with the ground.  V1's left plane contacted a culvert. V1 then contacted two trees with its right plane before coming to final rest off the right (east) road edge.

V1 was traveling north on a four lane street in lane four waiting to make a left turn. V2 was traveling south on a four lane street in lane three approaching the same intersection as V1. As V1 attempted the left turn the right side of V1 impacted the front of V2. V1 came to rest in the intersection facing west. V2 came to rest in the intersection facing south.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west in lane two of a five lane, not physically divided roadway. Vehicle 1 drove left of center, continued off road to the left and vehicle 1's front end collided with a pole. Vehicle 1 continued west and came to rest on the south shoulder and lane five of the roadway.

V1 was west bound on a two lane non divided roadway approaching a 3 way intersection. V1 departed the end of the roadway, and entered a culvert, where it rolled two quarter turns, right side leading, coming to final rest on its roof in the drainage culvert..

V1 was traveling east in the second of two lanes on a positively divided, two-way roadway. V1 departed the roadway into the gore where the front contacted two delineator posts. V1 continued forward in a slight yaw contacting an impact attenuator with its left side. V1 then crossed an exit lane in a counter-clockwise yaw before the right rear contacted a concrete traffic barrier. V1 started to roll with its right side leading. V1 contacted a light pole on the left side of the roadway with its top before rolling over four-quarter turns coming to rest on its top facing southeast.

V1 was traveling west in lane 2 on a two-way divided roadway, approaching a bridge. V1 departed the roadway into the median on the left side and the front of V1 contacted a concrete wall. V1 rotated counter-clockwise and came to rest on the roadway facing south.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a 2 lane undivided roadway in lane 1 approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling southbound on a 4 lane divided roadway in lane 1 approaching the same intersection. During the intersection the front of V1 impacted the right side of V2. V2 then departed the roadway to the right and the front right tire impacted a raised curb. V2 then continued off road and the right side of V2 impacted a tree in a sideswipe manner. The front of V2 then impacted a wooden utility pole. V2 came to rest facing southbound against the utility pole. V1 rotated clockwise and came to rest facing east.

V1 was traveling westbound on a 5 lane undivided roadway with a middle 2 way turn lane in lane 2. V1 departed it's lane to the left and crossed the middle turn lane and both eastbound lanes, then departed the roadway to the left. V2 was parked and unoccupied facing south in a private driveway. The front of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V2 rotated counter clockwise and came to rest facing east. V1 continued off road and the front of V1 impacted a tree. V1 came to rest facing southwest against the impacted tree.

V1 was traveling northwest on a two way, two lane undivided roadway. V1 departed the right hand (east) side of the roadway contacting a cable barrier guardrail with its frontal and right side planes. V1 came to final rest on the eastern shoulder of the roadway.

V1 was traveling east on a 2-lane divided roadway turning left at an intersection. V2 was traveling south in lane 2 on a 4-lane roadway approaching the same intersection. The left side of V1 was contacted by the front of V2. V1 rotated counter-clockwise and came to rest in the intersection facing north. V2 came to rest in the intersection facing south.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a 2-lane roadway when it departed the right road edge and its right front tire contacted a concrete culvert. V1 continued forward and its front plane contacted a 2nd concrete culvert then its right side contacted a ditch connected to the culvert. V1 continued forward where its front plane contacted a wooden mailbox post. V1 rotated clockwise and its left rear tire and rim contacted the road surface. V1 came to rest in the southbound lane facing northwest.

V1 was southbound on a two way dirt/gravel roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right and its front contacted a barbed wire fence. V1 then rolled 2 quarter turns and came to rest on its top facing southeast..

V1 was southbound on a 2 way roadway when V1 departed the roadway to the left. V1 over-corrected back to the left, crossed all traffic lanes and exited the roadway to the left. The front of V1 contacted a sign. V1 continued to travel and began to yaw clockwise. V1 tripped and began to roll to the left. V1 rolled 6 quarter turns coming to rest on its top off of the roadway. While V1 was in a roll, occupant 1 was fully ejected.

V1 was traveling northbound on a two-lane, two-way roadway approaching a four-way intersection controlled by a stop sign for the north and south travel lanes. V2 was traveling eastbound on a two-lane, two-way roadway approaching the mentioned intersection. V3 was traveling westbound on the same roadway as V2 attempting a left turn at the intersection to travel south. V1 was attempting a left turn to head west when the front plane of V2 contacted the left side of V1. After impact with V1, V2 went into westbound lanes and the left plane contacted the left plane of V3. V1 came to final rest facing northeast, V2 partially in the westbound lane facing east, and V3 facing west in its original travel lane.

V1 was traveling northbound on a two-lane, two-way, roadway with a left curve. V2 was legally parked on the west side of the roadway facing south. V1 departed its lane to the left side where the front plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2. After impact with V1 the right side of V2 contacted a mailbox off the roadway. V1 came to final rest facing north in the southbound travel lanes. V2 came to final rest facing south partially off the roadway.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane highway with a non-physically divided dirt/grass median in lane one, of the southbound lanes. V2 was traveling south on a non-physically divided dirt/grass median two lane highway in lane one. V3 was traveling south on the same non-physically divided two lane highway in lane one, and V4 was traveling south on the same non-physically divided highway in lane two. Driving the wrong way the front left of V1 impacted the front left of V2. After impact, V1 began to rotate counter-clockwise across lane two and continued off of the east road edge into the dirt/grass median where V1 rolled left four quarter turns. After impact, V2 began to rotate counter-clockwise off of the west road edge. V1 came to rest on its wheels facing a easterly direction. V2 then impacted an embankment, and came to rest facing a southerly direction. Approaching the accident, V3 and V4's front impacted an unknown object due to the moving debris from the initial impact. V1 was traveling southbound in the right lane of a two way roadway with three lanes of travel. V1 departed the roadway on the right side and the frontal plane of V1 made contact with a pole. V1 came to rest partially off the roadway.

V1 was traveling west on a 2-lane roadway negotiating a left curve. V1 departed the right road edge while rotating counter-clockwise and its front plane contacted a metal pole. V1 continued to rotate counter-clockwise and came to rest on the roadside facing north.

V1 was stopped at a stop sign facing north in lane two of a three lane undivided roadway waiting to make a left turn. V2 was traveling east on a 5 lane undivided roadway in lane one approaching an intersection. V1 began to make a left turn when the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V2 began to rotate clockwise and the front left wheel contacted the south curbline,  V2 then tripped over to the left. During the roll, the right side of V2 contacted a pole. V2 completed 4 quarter turns before coming to rest on its wheels in a driveway facing southeast.V1 came to rest in the middle of the intersection in lane one facing northeast.

V1 was traveling in a southeasterly direction through the right hand curve of the 3 lane roadway when it departed the road on the left and its left side came into contact with the face of a guardrail in two separate areas.  Past the end of the guardrail, V1 entered the downward sloping median strip and overturned (8 quarter turns, leading right).  V1 came to rest on its wheels facing a northwesterly direction in the median strip.

V1 was traveling in a northeasterly direction on a designated north/south divided trafficway (median strip without positive barrier) in lane 1 (of two lanes), when it departed the road on the right. V1 overturned (7 quarter turns, leading right) and its right side contacted a drainage tube support pole. During the rollover, occupants 3 and 4 were totally ejected. V1 came to rest on its left side, facing a southerly direction on the roadside.

V1 was traveling west on a not physically divided trafficway in lane 2, when a pedestrian entered its path (traveling from south to north).   The front end of V1 came into contact with the pedestrian.  V1 came to rest on its wheels facing a westerly direction along the curb line at the north edge of the road, west of the impact location.

V1 was traveling northeast in the #1 lane of a 2 lane roadway. V1 departed its lane to the left and continued until it departed the roadway to the left. The front of V1 impacted a dirt embankment. V1 continued forward and the front of V1 impacted a fence. As V1 traveled through the fence, the fence debris contacted the lower right side of V1.   V1 continued forward and came to rest facing north in a field.

V1 was traveling east in lane one on a three lane, median divided roadway, and was approaching a single lane exit ramp for the roadway. As V1 began to exit the roadway and negotiate a right curve on the exit ramp, the vehicle departed the roadway on the left side and drove into a grass median. V1 then traveled across the median and contacted the rear face of a guardrail with its front plane. V1 continued forward through the guardrail, traveled across an entrance ramp lane, and contacted a second guardrail face with it's front plane. V1 then rotated in a counter clockwise direction and the vehicle's right side plane contacted the guardrail before coming to final rest. The vehicle came to final rest off of the roadway, facing north, and was approximately 5 meters past the final impact.

V1 and V2 were both traveling west on the same two-lane roadway. V2 was ahead of V1. V2 slowed for a Non-Contact Vehicle in its lane making a turn. The front of V1 struck the back of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling west on a two-lane, two-way road. V2 was traveling east on the same road. V1 turned left into a shopping plaza and the right side of V1 was impacted by the front of V2.  V1 rotated counter-clockwise and came to rest in the parking lot and V2 came to rest in the road.

V1 was traveling east going down a hill on a two-lane, two-way gravel road. V1 departed the left side of the road where it impacted many small trees with the front and a rock with its undercarriage before contacting a large tree. V1 came to rest off of the left side of the road against the large struck tree.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a 7 lane, two way, median divided roadway, in lane number 4 turning left. Vehicle 2 was traveling east on the same roadway in lane two. Vehicle 1's front end and Vehicle 2's left side made contact in the intersection. V1 came to final rest in the intersection, facing south. V2 came to final rest in the intersection, facing southwest.

Vehicle 1 was southbound on a two way, three lane roadway.  Vehicle 2 was southbound on the same roadway.  Vehicle 1 made a left turn to travel eastbound on different roadway.  Vehicle 1 front plane struck the front plane of vehicle 2.  Vehicle 1 came to rest in the roadway facing southeast.  Vehicle 2 came to rest facing north in the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was northbound on a two way, two lane roadway.  Vehicle 1 departed the roadway on the north side of a T intersection.  Vehicle 1 front plane struck a street sign post.  Vehicle 1 traveled through a yard and over a tire retaining wall striking the front undercarriage.  Vehicle 1 continued north striking a tree with its front plane.  Vehicle 1 dropped of a small mound striking the front undercarriage.  Vehicle 1 continued forward, striking unknown objects with the front plane, right side plane, and the front plane again.  Vehicle 1 came to rest facing northeast in a grassy field.

V1 was traveling North on a 2 lane 2 way not physically divided roadway. V2 was traveling East on a 2 lane 2 way not physically divided roadway. V1 and V2 entered the intersection and V1's front plane contacted V2 right plane, then V1 rotated clockwise, and V2 rotated counterclockwise, V1 Left side contacted V2 Right side, in a side slap manner. Both vehicles came to rest facing Northeast.

V1 was traveling east in lane one of a five lane dry roadway with a center two way left turn lane.  V1 had been involved in a previous crash approximately 800ft west of this impact. V1 continued to drive east after the first crash. V2 was stopped in traffic in lane one ahead of V1.  The front of V1 contacted the rear plane of V2.  Both vehicles came to final rest in lane one facing east.

V1 was exiting a parking lot heading south to make a left turn onto a one way three lane roadway. V2 was eastbound in lane one of the one way road.  The front plane of V2 contacted the right plane of V1.  Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway near impact.

V1 was traveling westbound on a two-lane roadway. V2 was traveling southbound on a one-lane, one-way intersecting roadway. The east and west lanes were controlled by a stop sign, and the south lane controlled by a one-way sign. In the middle of the intersection the front plane of V2 contacted the right side of V1. After impact both vehicles came to final rest in the intersection with V1 facing west and V2 facing south.

Vehicle 1 was traveling northbound on a 3 lane non-physically divided roadway making a left had turn from the lane 2 position at an intersection.  Vehicle 2 was traveling southbound on a 4 lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 2 position passing through the intersection.  The front plane of Vehicle 1 made contact with the front of Vehicle 2.  Vehicle 1 came to final rest facing northwest near the center of the intersection.  Vehicle 2 traveled southwest and departed the southwest road edge. The front of V1 contacted the curb at the apex with the right front and right rear wheels. V2 came to final rest facing south off the west road edge.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a two lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1 position approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling west on a 3 lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 2 position approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection. V1 was attempting to make a left turn. V2 was attempting to travel straight through. The right side of V1 contacted the front of V2. V1 came to rest facing north at the north side of the intersection. V2 came to rest facing north west in the intersection.

Vehicle 1 was traveling eastbound on a 2 lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position.  Vehicle 2 was traveling southbound on a 3 lane non-physically divided roadway.  Both vehicles entered the intersection at the same time.  The front plane of Vehicle 1 made contact with the right plane of Vehicle 2.  Vehicle 1 came to final rest facing south at the southern portion of the intersection.  Vehicle 2 diverted to the left departing the roadway making contact with a curb and chicken wire fence before coming to rest facing south on a residential lawn.

V1 was traveling north on a two-lane road negotiating a curve left. Another vehicle was traveling on the same road in the opposite direction. Cargo from the southbound vehicle fell onto the roadway and into the northbound travel lane. The loose cargo bounced directly in the path of V1. The cargo impacted the front end and left side of V1. V1 came to rest on the northbound shoulder. The other vehicle did not stop at the scene.

V1 was northbound exiting a driveway and entering a four-lane roadway. V2 was eastbound on that four-lane roadway. As V1 entered the road, the front of V2 struck V1's  left side. Both vehicles came to rest on the roadway facing northeast.

V1 was traveling north on an undivided two lane street, stopped at a stop sign, waiting to turn left at an intersecting road. V2 was traveling east on that intersecting road, approaching the intersecting street. V1 initiated a left turn and its front end struck the front end of V2. V1 came to rest in a parking lot, facing an unknown direction. V2 came to rest within the north and southbound lanes facing easterly direction.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north, in lane one of a two lane, two-way, non-divided roadway.  A bicyclist entered the roadway and the front of Vehicle 1 struck the bicyclist.  Vehicle 1 came to rest just forward of impact, still facing north in lane one.  The bicyclist landed on the hood and windshield after being struck.

V1 was traveling in a northern direction on a two lane, non-divided, bidirectional roadway, passing through an intersection. V2 was traveling in a western direction on a two lane, non-divided, bidirectional roadway passing through the same intersection. V1's right plane impacted V2's frontal plane twice. V1 rotated counter clockwise where its right plane impacted the left plane of V2. V2 departed the roadway to the right, where its frontal plane impacted a utility pole. The utility pole sheered off and impacted the left side of V2. V2 returned to the roadway, where it came to final rest. V1 came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling south in the second of four lanes on an undivided, two-way roadway. V2 was traveling north in the second lane of the same roadway approaching V1. V1 departed the lane on the left side and entered the northbound lanes. V2 departed its lane on the left side, attempting to avoid V1. V1 returned to its original travel lane and the left side of V1 contacted the front of V2. Both vehicles departed the west side of the road and came to final rest.

V1 was negotiating a left curve traveling north in the second of two lanes, on a positively-divided, two-way highway. V2 was ahead of V1 in the same lane. V3 was ahead of V2 in the same lane. The front of V1 contacted the rear of V2, pushing V2 forward into the rear of a trailer being pulled by V3.

V1 was originally traveling Northwest bound on a 5 lane roadway, in lane 2. V2 was traveling South east bound on the same roadway, in lane 1. V1 made a left turn across the path of V2. V2's front contacted V1's right side. Both vehicles came to rest within the roadway.
V1 and V2 were both traveling westbound ,on a 2 lane, undivided roadway. V2 was stopped in the roadway. V1's front contacted V2's rear. Both vehicles came to rest within the roadway.

V1 was traveling westbound on a two-lane, two-way roadway approaching an intersection controlled by stop signs in the east and west directions. V2 was traveling southbound on a one-way, two-lane roadway approaching the intersection. In the middle of the intersection the front plane of V2 contacted the right side of V1. After impact V1 entered a counterclockwise rotation and the right rear and right front wheels impact the curb on the southwest corner. V1 came to final rest against the southwest curb facing east. V2 came to final rest in the roadway facing southwest.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south in lane three on a three lane two way trafficway divided by a grass median and cable barrier. An object fell from an unknown vehicle traveling south in front of vehicle 1. The object contacted the front plane and vehicle 1 came to final rest on the shoulder facing south.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a non-physically divided two lane, two-way roadway. Vehicle 2 was traveling west on the same roadway. Vehicle 1 departed the lane of travel on the left side and the front plane of Vehicle 1 contacted the front plane of Vehicle 2. Vehicle 1 came to final rest on the roadway facing east. Vehicle 2 came to final rest on the roadway facing west.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north in the third lane of a four lane roadway. Vehicle 2 was traveling on the same roadway in the same direction in lane two. Vehicle 1 departed its lane to the right and the front right of Vehicle 1 contacted the left rear of Vehicle 2. Vehicle 2 then departed the roadway on the left side of the roadway. The front of Vehicle 2 contacted a cable barrier and came to final rest off of the roadway.facing north.

Vehicle 1 Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a two lane, two way roadway approaching a bridge. As the driver of Vehicle 1 was negotiating a right curve, Vehicle 1 departed right side of the roadway where its right side plane and right front wheel impacted the bridge rail end (Event 1). The right quarter-panel swiped the bridge rail during separation (Event 2) as Vehicle 1 initiated a left side rollover sequence (Event 3). The roof or top plane impacted the south bridge rail on the opposite side of the roadway (Event 4) before coming to final rest, facing west.

V1 was westbound on a 4 lane roadway in lane 2 approaching a 4 way intersection. V2 was southbound stopped at a stop sign waiting to crossover at the same intersection. V3 was eastbound on the same 4 lane roadway in lane 2. Within the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V1 then spun clockwise and the left side of V1 contacted the front of V3. All vehicles came to rest in the roadway.

V1 and V2 were both traveling north on a positively-divided, three lane roadway. V1 was in the second lane, and V2 was in the first lane. V1 departed it's lane on the right side and the right side of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V1 then veered left, crossing through all lanes and departed the left side of the roadway. The front of V1 contacted the concrete barrier. V1 then rolled over from right to top for four quarter turns and came to rest in the roadway. V2 came to rest on the shoulder.

V1 was traveling southwest in lane one of a two lane roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling southeast in lane one of a two lane roadway approaching the same intersection. As both vehicles proceeded straight through the intersection V1's front plane contacted V2's left plane. Both vehicles came to rest near impact.

Vehicle 1 and vehicle 2 were  traveling west on a two lane, physically divided roadway, in lane one, approaching an intersection. Prior to the intersection, the front of vehicle 1 contacted the rear of vehicle 2.  Both vehicles came to rest just forward of impact, still facing west.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a two-way, not physically divided roadway in lane number 2, attempting to make a left turn into a private drive. Vehicle 2 was traveling east in lane one of the same roadway. Vehicle 1's right side and vehicle 2's front made contact. Vehicle 1 came to rest in the private drive facing southwest. Vehicle 2 came to final rest in their original lane, just forward of impact, facing east.

Vehicle 1 was traveling in the east in lane No. 1of a two-lane, undivided roadway. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway to the right and contacted a culvert with its right front tire (Event 1). V1 continued traveling east and contacted the ground with its frontal plane (Event 2) at a driveway downslope. V1 became airborne and while off of the ground, the frontal plane impacted a tree (Event 3). V1 initiated a rapid clockwise rotation, rolling three-quarter turns (Event 4), coming to rest on its right side plane.

V1 was traveling northbound on a two lane roadway in lane one.  V2 was traveling northbound behind V2.  V1 travelled along the right side of V2 as V2 was making a right turn onto a side street.  The right side of V2 struck the left side of V1 in a sideswipe type of impact.  V1 and V2 came to rest in the roadway facing northbound.

V1 was traveling south on a two way, six lane roadway in the first southbound lane.  V2 was stopped in the same lane heading the same direction.  V1 struck V2 in the rear plane with the front plane of V1.  Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane, two-way roadway approaching a T-intersection. V2 was traveling on the same road in the opposite direction.V3 was traveling westbound, stopped on the intersecting road. V1 initiated a left turn at the intersection and its front plane contacted V2's front plane. After that event, V2 continued northeast and its front plane impacted V3's front plane.  V1 came to final rest on the roadway facing southeast. V2 came to final rest on roadway facing northeast. V3 came to final rest on roadway facing west.

V1 was traveling north in lane one of a three lane divided (with positive barrier) highway. V2 was traveling east on a three lane divided (no positive barrier) roadway, which was an underpass under the highway. V1 departed the roadway to the right. The front of V1 impacted an arrow board on the right side of the road. The arrow board was pushed to the side and tilted. Part of the display board impacted the top of V1. V1 continued to drive off the road, down a grass embankment and impacted the metal pole of a fence. V1 then entered the roadway V2 was traveling on. The front of V2 impacted the left side of V1. V1 and V2 rotated clockwise and the left side of V1 impacted the right side of V2.  V1 came to rest on the roadway facing northeast. V2 came to rest facing northeast.
V1 and V2 were traveling west on a three lane roadway passing through an intersection. The front of V1 contacted the back of V2 within the intersection. V1 and V2 came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was negotiating a downhill curve to the right while traveling east on a two-lane, two-way road. V1 departed the right left side of the road and struck two trees with its front plane. V1 rotated clockwise and struck a tree with its left plane. V1 came to rest off of the left side of the road in the woods heading south.

V1 was heading north on a two lane undivided roadway. V2 was heading south on the same roadway. Both vehicles were negotiating a curve. V1 departed its travel lane to the left. The front of V1 contacted with the left of V2. V2 was redirected to the right were the front contacted a stone wall before it came to final rest facing a southwestern direction. V1 came to final rest slightly north of the first impact facing north.

V1 was traveling west out of a private driveway. V2 was traveling north on an unmarked roadway with curbside parking. The left of V1 contacted the front of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest near the point of impact.

V1 was southbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway approaching a 4-leg intersection. V2 was eastbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. V1 attempted to make a right turn (west) when its front end struck the left side of V2. V1 came to final rest near the point of impact facing southwest. V2 came to final rest near the point of impact facing east.

V1 was traveling westbound in the first lane of a seven lane, two-way, positive divided roadway. V1 turned right onto the single lane ramp to continue traveling northbound . The ramp had a right curvature. V1 departed the roadway on the left. The frontal plane of V1 impacted the guardrail face. As V1 rotated clockwise from the initial impact, the rear plane of V1 impacted the guardrail face. V1 re-entered the roadway and came to final rest facing southeast.

V1 was traveling north on a non-physically divided two-way road in lane one negotiating a curve right. V2 was traveling south on the same non-physically divided two-way road in lane one negotiating a curve left. V1 departed its travel lane to the left where the front of V1 impacted the front of V2. After the impact, both vehicles spun clockwise where the back of V1 impacted a dirt embankment off the west road edge and the back of V2 impacted a rock wall off of the east road edge. V1 came to rest on its wheels facing a southeasterly direction and V2 came to rest on its wheels facing northwesterly direction.

V1 was traveling northbound on a divided two lane roadway in lane one. For unknown reasons, V1 moved into lane two and lost control while steering back into lane one. V1 began to rotate in a clockwise direction as it departed the east road edge and started to roll left side leading. The left side of V1 impacted a barbed wire fence as it continued to roll 6 quarter turns and came to rest on its roof in a field facing east.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V2 was traveling east on the same roadway. V1 turned left towards a private driveway and the right side of V1 was contacted by the front of V2. V1 rotated counter-clockwise as V2 rotated clockwise and the right side of V1 contacted the left side of V2. Both vehicles came to rest facing south at the entrance to the driveway.

V1 was traveling west on a two-lane undivided roadway in lane one. V2 was traveling east on a two-lane undivided roadway in lane one. V3 was traveling east on a two-lane undivided roadway in lane one behind V2. V1 crossed over into the east bound lane where the front of V1 impacted the right side of V2.  V1 continued in the eastbound lane where the front of V1 impacted the front of V3. After the impact with V3, V1 rotated clockwise and came to rest on the south road edge facing south west. After the impact with V1, V2 crossed over the westbound lanes while spinning in a clockwise direction then departed the road edge where the front of V2 impacted a ditch and came to rest in the ditch facing north east. After the impact with V1, V3 rotated in a clockwise direction and came to rest straddling the north road edge and westbound lane, facing south east.

V1 was traveling east exiting a driveway. V2 was traveling south in the #2 lane of a 5 lane undivided roadway. The left side of V1 impacted the front of V2. V1 rotated counter clockwise and departed the roadway to the east. V2 continued south east and departed the road to the east. The front of V2 impacted a sign. V2 continued forward and the front of V2 impacted a concrete bollard. V2 continued forward and began rotating clockwise where the front of V2 impacted a fire hydrant. V2 continued rotating where the left impacted a concrete bollard. V1 came to rest partially on the east shoulder facing south. V2 came to rest in a parking lot facing south with the front of V2 against the fire hydrant.

V1 was traveling northwest on a two way, three lane road, in the first lane of travel, approaching a four way intersection. V2 was stopped at a stop sign, traveling west on a two-way, two lane road, approaching the same intersection. As V2 was starting in traffic, the right side of V1 impacted the front of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway; V1 facing northwest, V2 facing north.

V1 was traveling in a western direction on a two lane, non-divided, bidirectional roadway, negotiating a slight curve to the left. V1 lost control due to road conditions and departed the roadway to the left rotating counter clockwise, where it's frontal plane impacted a guardrail. V1 continued to rotate counter clockwise, and rolled one quarter turn onto its right side. V1 came to final rest on its right side on the roadway.

V1 was traveling east on a two-lane, two-way roadway approaching a sign controlled four-legged intersection. V2 was traveling north on a two lane, two-way roadway approaching the same intersection. V1 entered into the intersection. The right of V1 contacted the front of V2. Following this initial impact, V1 rotated counterclockwise and V2 rotated clockwise. The right of V1 contacted the left of V2. V1 departed the road to the left. The front of V1 contacted an utility pole where it came to final rest. V2 departed the road to the right. The front of V2 contacted a landscaping fence. V2 then rolled backwards, re-entering the road and departing it to the right. The back of V2 contacted an embankment where it came to rest.

V1, V2, and V3 were traveling west on a four lane interstate in the right lane. V1 and V2 began to slow for traffic ahead. The front of V3 contacted the rear of V2. V2 was then redirected forward. The front if V2 contacted the rear of V1. V1 was redirected to the right were is came to final rest on the shoulder. V2 and V3 came to final rest near the points of impact.

V2 was traveling south on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V2 came to a stop in its initial travel lane. V1 was following V2. The frontal plane of V1 struck the back plane of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest near the point of impact heading south.

V1 was traveling east in lane 1 on a 5-lane, two way, undivided roadway, with a two way left turn lane, passing through a four leg intersection. V2 was traveling south on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway, passing through the same four leg intersection. The front plane of V1 impacted the right side plane of V2. V1 rotated clockwise and came to rest on the roadway facing southeast. V2 departed the southeast corner of the intersection and struck a curb with its undercarriage, and then a guy wire with its front plane.  V2 came to rest off the roadway facing southeast, just southeast of the intersection at the point of impact with the guy wire.

V1 was traveling north in lane four of a five lane one-way roadway, approaching an intersection. V1 passed through the intersection and departed the road to the left. V1 drove over a traffic island, crossed the U-turn lane of a highway service road and departed the road to the north. The front of V1 impacted a concrete wall. V1 rotated counter clockwise and impacted the concrete wall with its right side. V1 came to rest at the wall, facing southwest.

V1 was traveling in a western direction on a two lane, non divided, bidirectional roadway. A deer entered the roadway, where V1's frontal plane impacted the deer. The deer rotated down the left side of V1, where it impacted the left side of V1.  V1 departed the roadway to the right, where its frontal plane impacted a culvert. V1 came to final rest on the right side of the roadway.

V1 was traveling in an eastern direction on a two lane, non divided bidirectional roadway negotiating a slight curve to the left, when a deer entered the roadway from the left. V1 impacted the animal with its frontal plane. The deer then rotated and impacted the right side of V1. V1 came to final rest on the right side of the roadway.

V1 and V2 were traveling north on a two-lane, two-way road approaching and intersection. V1 stopped for traffic stopped at a light. The front of V2 impacted the rear of V1. Both vehicles came to rest at the point of impact.

V1 was traveling west on a divided, two-lane, two-way road while passing through an intersection. V2 was traveling south on a two-lane, two-way road passing through the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection and the front of V2 impacted the right side of V1. Both vehicles came to rest on the western leg of the intersection in the roadway.

V1 was heading south on an unmarked two lane roadway. V2 was heading east on a two lane undivided roadway. V1 entered into the intersection to make a left turn. The right of V1 contacted the left of V2. V1 was redirected to the left. V1 came to final rest near the curb. V2 also came to initial rest near its initial point of impact.

V1 was traveling north bound on a two lane, lease roadway. V1 was negotiating a sharp curve to the left, when it departed the roadway to the right. V1 traveled down a steep embankment, where its frontal plane impacted a tree. V1 rotated counter clockwise, and rolled over 3 quarter turns right side leading, where it impacted two trees. The second tree interrupted the roll causing V1 to roll 1 quarter turn to the left. V1 came to final rest on its top on the right side of the roadway.

V1 was traveling east through a four leg intersection on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway, with a left curve. V2 was traveling south through the same four leg intersection and making a left turn. The frontal plane of V2 struck the left side plane of V1. V1 came to rest heading east on the southeast corner of the intersection. V2 came to rest heading east in the middle of the intersection.

V1, V2, and V3 were traveling westbound on a three-lane roadway with a two-way left turn lane in lane two. V1 and V2 were stopped in traffic when the front plane of V3 contacted the back plane of V2. V2 was then pushed forward where the front plane of V2 contacted the back plane of V1. All vehicles came to final rest at point of impacts facing west.

V1 was traveling southbound on a two-lane, two-way roadway. V2 was traveling northbound. V1 departed its lane to the left side where the front plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2. V1 came to final rest facing southbound at point of impact in the northbound lane. V2 came to final rest partially off the roadway facing north.

V1 was traveling eastbound in the first lane of a two lane, two-way roadway. V1 approached a T-intersection and continued forward. V1 departed the roadway. The frontal plane of V1 impacted a metal pole. V1 continued forward impacting the curb with it's frontal plane. V1 continued travel forward on sidewalk rotating slightly clockwise, impacting a fence with it's frontal plane. V1 came to final rest after impacting the fence on an asphalt area. V1 came to final rest off the roadway facing east.

V1 was traveling westbound in a single lane, one-way roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling southbound in the first lane of a two lane, two-way roadway approaching the same intersection as V1. Both V1 and V2 entered the intersection at the same time. The frontal plane of V1 impacted the left side plane of V2. Both V1 and V2 came to final rest in the roadway: V1 was facing west and V2 facing south.

V1 was traveling south on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a right hand curve in the roadway. V2 was traveling east on the same roadway as V1 negotiating a left hand curve in the roadway. V1 began to slide longitudinally and departed the left hand lane line. The front plane of V1 contacted the left plane of V2. V1 and V2 both came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling northbound in the third lane of a three lane positive divided, one-way roadway approaching an off ramp. V2 was traveling northbound in the second lane of a three lane positive divided, one-way roadway approaching the same off ramp. V1 departed to the right from the third lane into the second lane in an attempt to get onto the off ramp. The right side plane of V1 impacted the left side plane of V2. Both V1 and V2 came to final rest in the roadway: V1 was facing north and V2 was facing east.

Vehicle 1 had been involved in a prior crash event, and was backing from the third travel lane and entered into the fourth travel lane of a six lane positively median divided roadway. Vehicle 1 contacted its back plane with the frontal plane of Vehicle 2 which was traveling in the fourth travel lane. Vehicle 1 continued backing and departed the roadway crossing the median. Vehicle 1 entered the opposite lanes of travel and contacted its back plane with the back plane of Vehicle 3, which was traveling in its second travel lane. Vehicle 1 continued its path of travel and departed the roadway to the left and contacted a tree with its right plane and a second tree with its back plane V1 came to rest off the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling in the eastbound lanes of a nine lane grass median divided roadway and was in the third travel lane of five on the roadway.  Vehicle 1 changed lanes to the right to pass an emergency vehicle, and was contacted on its back plane by the frontal plane of Vehicle 2.  Both vehicles came to rest on the roadway.

V1 was eastbound on a 1 lane, one way ramp/interchange when V1 departed the roadway to the left. The front of V1 contacted a guardrail. V1 then climbed the guardrail at which time the undercarriage of V1 made contact with the guardrail. V1 ultimately came to rest on top of the guardrail.

V1 was northbound on a 4 lane physically divided roadway, in lane 4, when V1 began to yaw clockwise, departed the roadway to the right and the front of V1 contacted a concrete traffic barrier. V1 continued to yaw and the left side of V1 contacted the same barrier, twice. Continuing to yaw, the back of V1 contacted the same barrier, twice. Continuing to yaw the right side of V1 contacted the same concrete barrier before V1 came to rest partially blocking lane 1.

V1 was traveling southbound in lane two, on a three lane, one-way roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling westbound in lane two, on a four lane, two-way roadway passing through the same intersection as V1. The left plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2. After the first impact V1rotated clockwise slightly while V2 rotated counter-clockwise causing the vehicles to impact a second time, V1 left to V2 right. V1 continued to travel off the roadway where V1 front contacted a curbed traffic island on the southwest apex of the intersection. V1 continued to travel onto the traffic island where the front of V1 struck a pedestrian signal  before coming to final rest facing southwest Partially off the traffic island. V2 came to final rest on roadway facing south.

V1 was traveling northeast on a two-lane roadway approaching an intersection controlled by a stop sign for the east and west travel lanes. V2 was traveling northwest on a two-lane roadway approaching the mentioned intersection. V1 proceeded through the intersection where the front plane of V2 contacted the right side of V1. V1 came to final rest in the roadway facing northeast, V2 came to final rest in the roadway facing west.

Vehicle 1 was traveling westbound on a two lane, one way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1 approaching an intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling southbound on a two lane, one way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 2 approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection proceeding straight. The right side of V1 contacted the front of V2. Both vehicles came to rest facing south west in the intersection parallel to each other.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a two lane, two way, non-physically divided road approaching an intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling west on a 5 lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 2 approaching the same intersection. V1 entered the intersection turning to its left and V2 proceeded straight. The front of v1 contacted the right side of V2 in the intersection. After impact V2 began to yaw left side leading and rolled onto its left side coming to rest in the east bound lanes facing northwest. V1 came to rest after impact facing south in the intersection.

Vehicle 1 was traveling eastbound on a two lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane one position. Vehicle 2 was traveling southbound on a two lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position. Both vehicles approach and entered a four way intersection at the same time. The front plane of V1 contacted the right plane of V2. V1 rotated in a clockwise rotation and V2 rotated in a counter-clockwise rotation as a result the left side of V1 contacted the right side of V2. Both V1 and V2 came to final rest facing southeast in the southeast corner of the intersection.

Vehicle 1 (V1) was traveling west in lane two of a divided highway.  A non-contact vehicle (NCV) was traveling on the same roadway in lane one. The NCV began to move into lane 2.  V1 steered left to avoid contact and departed the road to the left.  The front of V1 contacted a cable barrier guardrail. V1 rotated clockwise and the left of V1 contacted the cable barrier guardrail.  V1 came to rest in the median, facing west.

V1 was headed southeast making a u-turn on a multi lane roadway. V2 was headed eastbound in lane two on a multi lane roadway, traveling straight, when V1's frontal plane came into contact with V2's front right corner and side. Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a five lane, physically divided roadway in lane number 5. Vehicle 1 traveled off the left side of the road and its front end made contact with the concrete barrier. Vehicle 1 came to final rest partially in its original travel lane, next to the barrier.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane divided roadway in lane one. V1 departed the roadway to the right and contacted a plastic Utility Marker with its front plane. V1 steered left and  rotated counter-clockwise as it traveled down a slight embankment where its right side contacted a chain link fence. The fence also contacted the top and left planes of V1. V1 came to rest on the roadside facing east.

V1 was traveling south on a two-lane non physically divided roadway approaching an intersection. V1 was traveling south on a two-lane non physically divided roadway approaching an intersection in front of V1. V2 began to make a left turn and the front of V1 impacted the left side if V2. Both V1 and V2 came to rest on the east shoulder facing an easterly direction.

V1 was traveling north bound on a two lane, non-divided bidirectional roadway. When a deer entered the roadway from the left, V1's frontal plane impacted the animal. V1 came to final rest on the right side of the roadway.

Vehicle 2 was traveling eastbound on 3 lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position intending to pass through an intersection. Vehicle 1 was traveling westbound on a 5 lane non physically divided roadway in the lane 3 position intending to make a left hand turn. The front plane of V1 made contact with the front left corner of V2 in the intersection. Vehicle 1 spun counter clockwise coming to rest against a curb facing southeast. Vehicle 2 spun clockwise coming to rest south of the intersection facing southwest.

V1 was traveling southbound in the first lane of a two lane, two-way roadway. A deer began crossing the roadway from the left. The front plane of V1 contacted the deer. V1 came to rest on the right shoulder.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane, undivided, roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south on a two lane, undivided, roadway, approaching the same intersection.  In the intersection, the right side of V1 contacted the front of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling north, on a 5 lane, two-way undivided roadway in lane number 3. Vehicle 1 attempted to turn left onto an intersecting roadway and the front of V1 contacted with the curb on the west side of the road. V1 continued forward and the front of V1 then contacted a pole. V1 came to rest facing west against the pole.

V1 was traveling northeast on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a right hand curve in the roadway. A deer entered the roadway from the eastern shoulder and the frontal plane of V1 contacted the animal in the roadway. V1 came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling northbound in the number 1 lane of a 4 lane one-way roadway, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling westbound in the number 3 lane of a 4 lane divided roadway, decelerating for an intersection. V1 was preparing to turn right and began their turn. V1 continued forward where the front of V1 impacted a curb. V1 continued forward where the front of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V1 pushed V2 to the right and rearward. V1 came to rest facing northerly in the westbound number 2 lane. V2 came to rest facing west in the number 3 westbound lane.

V1 was traveling eastbound in the right lane of a two way roadway with a total of three lanes. V2 was legally parked on the south side of the roadway facing eastbound. V1 departed the roadway on the right and the frontal plane of V1 made contact with the rear plane of V2. V1 came to final rest on the roadway. V2 remained parked off the roadway.

V1 was traveling southbound on a two way roadway with a single lane of travel in each direction. V2 was traveling westbound in the right lane of a two way of roadway with two lanes of travel in each direction. At the intersection, the frontal plane of V2 made contact with the left side plane of V1. V1 came to final rest on the roadway. V2 left the scene of the crash.

V1 was traveling north in lane two of a undivided roadway with two-way center turn lane. V2 was exiting a parking lot and turning on the same undivided roadway as V1, heading south. Both V1 and V2 entered the two-way center turn and the front plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest inside the center turn lane.

V1 was traveling southeast in lane two of a four-lane undivided roadway. V2 was ahead of and in the same travel lane as V1, stopped while waiting to turn left. The front plane of V1 contacted the back plane of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest in the intersection close to impact.

V1 was traveling northeast in lane three of a five lane roadway attempting a left turn. V2 was traveling southeast in lane two of a five lane divided roadway attempting to pass through the intersection. V1's front plane contacted V2's front plane. Both vehicles came to rest in the intersection near impact.

V1 was traveling north on a physically divided roadway in the 1st travel lane. V1 departed the roadway to the left contacting a curb with the front and rear rims. V1 then crossed the roadway to the right where it impacted a concrete jersey barrier with it right side. This contact caused V1 to enter a clockwise rotation and roll with its left side leading. V1 rolled 4-quarter turns and impacted the Jersey barrier with its left side before coming to rest on its wheel facing south.

Vehicle 1 was traveling in the first of three southbound travel lanes of a three lane median divided roadway. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway to the right and contacted a fallen tree with its frontal plane. Vehicle 1 traversed the log and continued traveling off road contacting a tree with its frontal plane, rotating and contacting a second tree. Vehicle 1 came to rest off the roadway.

V1 was southbound on a 3 lane physically divided roadway in lane 2. V2 was was on the same roadway facing northbound on the east-side shoulder. V2 was disabled on the shoulder due to a previous event. As V1 approached V2, V1 began to yaw counter-clockwise. V1 then departed the roadway to the left and the front of V1 contacted a cement barrier then the right side of V1 contacted the front of V2. The right side of V1 then contacted the left side of V2. Both came to rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling north on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway. V1 departed the right road edge driving over a small hill. V1 then went airborne for approximately 6 meters before landing on the ground on its wheels. V1 then continued forward striking a stone wall with its front plane. While V1 was striking the stone wall, airborne debris contacted the top plane of V1. V1 then rotated clockwise 180 degrees before coming to final rest off of the roadway facing south.

V1 was traveling southeast bound, in lane 2. The roadway was a 5 lane, non physically divided roadway, with a 2 way turn lane. V1 traveled across all the lanes to the left and exited the roadway. V1 then rolled, right side leading, 4 quarter turns before coming to rest on its wheels, off of the roadway.
V1 and V2 were traveling southwest, in lane 1 on, a 2 lane roadway. V1 stopped to turn left and V2 continued forward. V2's front contacted V1's rear plane. Both vehicles came to rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. negotiating a left curve. V1 lost control and began a counter clockwise yaw. V1 crossed the left lane line and continued off the left road edge. V1 then rolled, left side leading, four quarter turns before coming to final rest off the roadway on its wheels.

V1 and V2 were traveling south in lane 4 on a four-lane divided roadway. V2 slowed for traffic ahead. The front of V1 contacted the back of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest near the point of impact facing south.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north on a 2-lane roadway with a slight right curve. V1 departed the left road edge, traveled a distance crossing 2 private driveways then vaulted over a ditch where its front plane contacted a shallow embankment. V1 continued forward and vaulted over a pile of asphalt pieces. V1 roled end-over-end and came to rest on its top facing south.

V1 was traveling south on a 2-lane roadway. V1 departed its travel lane to the left. Continuing forward, V1 departed the roadway to the left, impacting an embankment with its front end. V1 continued forward where its left plane contacted a large tree. V1 rotated counter-clockwise then rolled right 2-quarter turns down the embankment and came to rest on its top in the northbound lane facing south.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a 5 lane, two way roadway in lane 2 approaching an intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling north on a 3 lane, two way roadway in lane 1 approaching the same intersection. Vehicle 3 was traveling west on a 5 lane, two way roadway in lane 1 at the intersection stopped at a traffic light. Vehicles 1 and 2 entered the intersection at the same time. The front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V2 rotated clockwise continued northwest and the front of V2 contacted the front of V3. V1 came to rest in the intersection facing north west. V2 came to rest after impact with V3, and V3 came to rest at Impact with V2.

Vehicles 1 and 2 were traveling northbound on a two lane physically divided roadway. Vehicle 1 approached an intersection departed lane of travel right side attempting to make a wide U-Turn. The front of Vehicle 2 made contact with the left side of Vehicle 1. Vehicle 1 came to final rest facing west while Vehicle 2 came to rest facing north. Both came to rest in the middle of the intersection.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on 5 lane physically divided roadway in lane 1 position. Vehicle 1 departed lane of travel left side then departed roadway left side. The front of V1 contacted a  raised curb median. V1 continued forward on the median and the front of V1 contacted a breakaway reflector. V1 continued forward and the front of V1 contacted a sign on the raised median. V1 then moved to its right, departing the raised median and came to final rest on the roadway facing west.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north on a two lane, two-way, non-physically divided roadway in lane one approaching a T intersection. V1 entered the intersection attempting to turn right. V1 departed roadway into a deep ditch and began to roll over. The left side of V1 then impact the opposite side ditch wall and came to rest on its left side against the ditch facing east.

V1 and V2 were both traveling south bound on a 3 lane roadway, with a 2 way turn lane. V1 came over hill crest and V2 was stopped. V1's front contacted V2's rear. V1 came to rest on the roadway. V2 came to rest off the roadway to the right.

V1 was traveling south on a 2 lane, non marked roadway, while negotiating a curve to the left. V1 went off the roadway to the right and the front of V1 contacted a small tree. V1 continued straight and then overturned 2 quarter turns, striking a fence and tree while overturning. V1 came to rest off the roadway, on it's roof.

V1 was proceeding east in the second of four lanes on a divided, two-way roadway approaching a four-legged intersection. V2 was proceeding north in the first of five lanes on a one-way roadway entering the same intersection. Within the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. After the initial impact, Vehicle 1 rotated counterclockwise and came to rest within the intersection. Vehicle 2 rotated clockwise, departed the roadway on the northeast corner and the back of V2 contacted a pole. V2 came to rest facing south against the pole.

V1 was traveling east in the third of eight lanes on a left curved, undivided, two-way roadway entering a four-legged intersection. V2 was traveling north in the second of three lanes on a two-way, undivided roadway entering the same intersection. V3 was stopped facing west in the fourth of eight lanes on a right curved, undivided, two-way roadway at the intersection. As V1 and V2 proceeded straight through the intersection the right side of V1 contacted the front of V2. V1 rotated clockwise after impact and departed the lane on the left side. The right side of V1 then contacted the left side of V3. All vehicles came to rest in the roadway near their final points of impact.

V1 was traveling SE on a 2-lane, 2-way roadway attempting to turn right at an intersection.  V2 was traveling NE on a 2-lane, 2-way roadway attempting to turn left at the same intersection.  Within the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the front of V2.  Both vehicles came to rest within intersection.
V1 was westbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. The front plane of V1 impacted a deer causing damage. V1 came to final rest on the north side of the road facing west.

Vehicle 1 was eastbound on a two way, two lane roadway and stopped in the roadway. Vehicle 2 was eastbound on the same roadway behind V1. The front of V2 contacted the back of vehicle 1. Both vehicles came to rest in the eastbound travel lane.

Vehicle 1 was northbound on a two way, three lane roadway.  Vehicle 1 traveled across two lanes to the left and departed the roadway to the left.  Vehicle 1 front plane struck a guardrail. Vehicle 1 right plane struck the guardrail as Vehicle 1 traveled through it. Vehicle 1 rotated counter clockwise and slid down a steep embankment.  Vehicle 1's back plane struck unknown object(s).  Vehicle 1 left and right planes struck bushes and came to rest facing east.

Vehicle #1 was traveling southbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. Vehicle #2 was traveling northbound on the same roadway. Vehicle #1 left its travel lane to the left and entered into Vehicle #2's travel lane. The frontal plane of Vehicle #1 contacted the frontal plane of Vehicle #2. Both Vehicles came to rest on the roadway.

V1 was northbound on a 2 lane physically divided roadway in the number 1 lane when an animal (deer) ran into the roadway. V1 avoided the animal by steering right where it departed the road and contacted an embankment and a bush then went airborne over a wire fence and contacted the ground with its undercarriage and came to rest facing northeast.

Vehicles 1, 2 and 3 were southbound on a three lane undivided roadway with a center turn lane. V1 was behind V2 and V2 was behind V3. V3 and V2 stopped and the front of V1 contacted the rear of V2. V2 then moved forward and the front of V2 contacted the rear of V3. All vehicles came to rest facing north in their original travel lane.

V1 was traveling westbound on a two lane, two-way, undivided roadway. V1 avoided a deer on the road, and lost control, V1 departed the left lane, V1 continued west where it departed the left side roadway. V1 then struck a tree with it's front plane, and caught on fire after initial impact. V1 came to final rest on the left side off roadway.

V1 was traveling southbound traveling on a divided entrance way with one lane traveling in the southbound direction and two lanes in the northbound direction. V1 was attempting a left hand turn to travel eastbound when the front plane struck a pedestrian in a wheelchair. V1 came to final rest further eastbound facing east.

V1 was traveling southbound on a two lane, two-way, undivided roadway, making a left turn at a four-way intersection, attempting to travel westbound. The right plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2. V1 and V2 came to final rest facing southeast after impact at intersection on roadway.

Vehicle 1 was westbound on a two way, six lane roadway turning left through an intersection.  Vehicle 2 was eastbound on the same roadway traveling through the same intersection.  Vehicle 2 front plane struck vehicle 1's right plane.  Vehicle 1 came to rest facing southwest in the roadway.  Vehicle 2 came to rest facing east in the roadway.

Vehicles 1 and 2 were traveling eastbound on a two lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position. The front plane of Vehicle 1 made contact with the rear plane of Vehicle 2.
