Vehicle 2 spun 180 degrees to right coming to final rest facing north. Vehicle 2 continued traveling south and departed the roadway left making contact with two separate light poles. Vehicle 2 then made contact with the right side plane of Vehicle 3 with its front plane. Vehicle 1 came to final rest on the left side of the roadway against a curb facing southeast. At some point a sheared light pole fell causing damage to Vehicle 4.

Vehicles 1,2,& 3 were all traveling east on a 4 lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway in the lane 2 position. V1 was behind V2 and V2 was behind V3. V3 stopped in the roadway waiting to make a left turn into a private drive. V2 slowed behind V3. The front of V1 contacted the rear of V2. V2 was then pushed forward into the rear of V3. All vehicles came to rest at impacts.

V1 was traveling south, on a two lane two way undivided roadway, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling east on a three lane two way undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. In the intersection, the right side of V1 contacted the front of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling north on a two way, four lane road, in the first lane. V1 traveled through an intersection and was negotiating the slight curve in the road. V1 entered a construction zone, leaving the roadway to the right. The front of V1 impacted an impact attenuator before coming to final rest on the roadway, facing north.

V1 was traveling north on a two-lane, two-way road that curved to the right. V1 departed the right side of the road and its front plane impacted a rock wall. V1 came to rest off of the right side of the road.

V1 was traveling south on a one-way exit ramp. V1 was negotiating the right curve when it departed the left road edge and its front plane contacted a signpost then a breakaway pole. V1 rotated clockwise as it traveled down an embankment and its front left side contacted a tree. V1 then rolled left 1-quarter turn and its back left side and top contacted 2 separate trees. V1 came to rest on its left side facing north.

V1 was heading north on a two lane undivided roadway. V2 was heading south on the same roadway.  V1 departed its lane of travel to the left The front of V1 connected with the front of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest near the point of impact.

V1 was traveling southwest on a 2 lane non divided roadway. V1 left it's travel lane to the left and then departed the roadway, also to the left. V1's front contacted a post and then a pole before coming to final rest off of the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a two-lane, non-physically divided roadway in lane one. Vehicle 1 traveled off the right side of the roadway and struck several trees before coming to final rest facing south.

Vehicle 1 and Vehicle 2 were traveling northeast in lane three on a three lane two way trafficway physically divided by a grass median. Vehicle 1 drove off the left side of the roadway, traveled back onto the roadway, and the front of Vehicle 1 contacted the back of Vehicle 2. Vehicle 1 and 2 came to final rest on the side of the roadway facing northeast.

V1 was traveling eastbound in the second lane of a four lane, two-way roadway. V2 was traveling eastbound ahead of V1, in the same second lane of the four lane, two-way roadway. V2 stopped in the second lane, waiting for traffic, in an attempt to turn left into a parking lot. The frontal plane of V1 impacted the rear plane of V2. Both V1 and V2 were at final rest in the roadway: V1 facing east and V2 facing northeast.

V1 was traveling west in the number 3 lane of a 4 lane divided roadway, stopped at an intersection. V2 was traveling east in the number 4 lane of a 4 lane divided roadway, stopped at an intersection preparing to turn left. Both vehicles entered the intersection. The front of V1 impacted the front of V2. V1 rotated clockwise slightly and the left side of V1 impacted the front of V2. V1 came to rest facing northwest in the intersection. V2 rotated counter-clockwise and came to rest facing northwest in the intersection, south of V1.

V1 was traveling east in the number 2 lane of a 5 lane divided roadway. V2 and V3 were stopped in the number 2 lane of a 5 lane divided roadway facing east. V4 was stopped in the number 4 lane of a 5 lane divided roadway, facing east. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. V1 continued forward where the right side of V1 impacted the rear of V3. The force of the impact with V1 pushed V2 forward and to the right where the front of V2 impacted the back of V3. V2 came to rest facing southerly behind V3. After swiping V3, V1 continued northerly across the number 3 lane and the front of V1 impacted the back of V4. V1 came to rest facing northerly in the number 3 lane. V3 came to rest facing easterly in the number 2 lane. V4 came to rest facing easterly in the number 4 lane.

V1 was traveling southbound in the first lane of a two lane, two-way roadway. V2 and V3 were legally parked, not in transport and facing south. V1 departed the roadway on the right. The frontal plane of V1 sideswiped the rear plane of V2. V1 then re-entered left into the first lane. V1 departed the roadway on the right again. The right side plane of V1 sideswiped the left side plane of V3. V2 and V3 were at final rest from impact facing south. V1 re-entered left into the first lane, where it came to final rest facing southeast.

V1 was traveling north on a divided 3- lane roadway in lane 2 and was approaching V2, which was traveling in the same direction, on the same roadway, ahead in lane 1. V1 came to rest on its wheels facing a northerly direction on the left shoulder. V2 left the scene.

V1 was traveling east in the second of four lanes on a positively divided, two-way roadway. V2 was traveling east in the same lane ahead of V1. V3 was traveling east in the third lane of the same roadway. V1 and V2 departed the lane on the let side to avoid debris in the road. The front of V2 contacted the debris then the front of V1 contacted the back of V2. The back of V1 then contacted the front of V3. V1 moved left across the fourth lane and departed the roadway on the left side. The front of V1 contacted the concrete traffic barrier. The left side of V1 then contacted the front of V3 a second time. All vehicle came to rest on the roadway.

V1 was southbound in lane 2 of 4 on an undivided two-way roadway. V1 departed its lane to the left and the front of V1 contacted the curb of an island. The front of V1 then contacted a marker post and then sign post. V1 began to yaw counter-clockwise and then rolled 4 quarter turns, striking a curb with its right side while in a roll, coming to rest on its wheels.

V1 was heading northeast on a three lane undivided roadway approaching an intersection to make a left turn. V2 was heading south on a four lane undivided roadway to continue straight through the intersection. V1 entered into the intersection to make a left turn. The left of V1 contacted the front of V2. V2 was redirected slightly to the right. The front of V2 connected with an utility pole before coming to final rest south of the intersection and facing southeast.

V1 and V2 were on a 5 lane roadway with a 2 way left turn lane. V1 was traveling northbound, in lane 2 of the southbound lanes. V2 was traveling in lane 2, in the southbound lanes, of the same roadway. V1 moved to the center lane to the right. V2 moved to the center lane to the left. V1's front contacted V2's front. Both vehicles came to rest in the roadway.

V1, V2 and V3 were all traveling west on a 2 lane non divided roadway. V2 and V3 were at a stop in the roadway. V1's front contacted V2's back plane. V2's front plane then contacted V3's back plane. All vehicles came to rest in the roadway.

V1 was eastbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V2 was westbound on the same roadway. The front plane of V1 struck the front plane of V2. V2 came to final rest near the point of impact facing west. V1 was pushed backwards after the impact and it departed the north side of the roadway. The rear plane of V1 struck a tree as it came to final rest partially off the road facing southeast.

V1 was northbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway negotiating a left curve. A deer entered the roadway as V1 swerved right to avoid the deer V1 departed the right side of the roadway impacting a tree with the right plane. V1 came to final rest at the point of impact facing west.

V1 was traveling southwest in lane one of a two-lane undivided roadway, negotiating a left curve. V1 departed the roadway to the right. V1's front plane contacted a tree. V1 rotated clockwise and came to final rest partially off the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling eastbound negotiating a left curve on a 2 lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position.  Vehicle 1 departed the roadway right side making contact to a pole with the front plane.  Traveling on, Vehicle 1 made contact with the ground and a fence while rolling 6 quarter turns before coming to final rest on its roof facing north.

V1 was Traveling south west on a two lane one way highway. V1 crossed the left lane line and continued off the left side of the highway. V1 contacted the guard rail and and came to final rest on the highway.

V1 and V2 were traveling south on a two lane two way, undivided roadway. V1 was turning into a driveway and the frontal plane of V2 contacted the right plane of V1. V1 and V2 came to final rest off the roadway.

Vehicle 1 and Vehicle 2 were traveling northeast on a three lane roadway. The front of Vehicle 2 contacted the back of Vehicle 1. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway to the left and came to final rest facing northeast. Vehicle 2 came to final rest on the roadway facing northeast.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a two lane two way roadway. Vehicle 2 was stopped in front of vehicle 1 going the same direction on the same roadway. The front plane of vehicle 1 contacted the back back plane of vehicle 2. Upon impact vehicle 2 departed the roadway on the right side, and came to final rest off the roadway facing southeast. Vehicle 1 continued forward and came to final rest on the roadway, in lane one facing east.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a two lane undivided roadway approaching a three legged intersection. Vehicle 1 entered the intersection going straight and departed the roadway. The front of Vehicle 1 contacted a group of small saplings.   V1 continued forward and contacted a tree with the right side.  V1 came to final rest facing west off of the roadway.

V1 was traveling northbound on a two lane non divided roadway (two way traffic) in lane one approaching an intersection. At the intersection a deer attempted to cross the roadway from the east. The front of V1 impacted the deer. V1 came to rest facing north. The deer came to rest in the ditch east of the roadway.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a two lane undivided roadway, (two way traffic) in lane one approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling northbound on a 3 lane undivided roadway, (two way traffic) in lane one approaching the same intersection. Prior to the intersection V1 departed it's lane to the left to pass a vehicle stopped at the intersection. V1 continued into the intersection and the front of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V1 rotated counter clockwise and V2 rotated clockwise. The right side of V1 and the left side of V2 impacted in a side slap manner. V1 was traveling northeast in lane one of a two-lane undivided roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right and continued to travel off the roadway. V1's front plane contacted a pole and came to final rest against the pole.

V1 was traveling west approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling southwest approaching the same intersection. V1's front plane contacted V2's front plane. V1 came to rest in the intersection. V2 rotated clockwise, tripped and rolled left two quarter turns coming to rest in the intersection.

V1 was traveling west in lane one, stopped in a median break, waiting to pass through the intersection. V2 continued to travel southwest on the roadway, before departing the roadway to the left. V2's left plane contacted a ditch and came to final rest in the ditch.
V1 was traveling northwest in lane one of a two lane roadway. V1 departed the right road edge and the front under carriage contacted a culvert. V1 came to rest off the right road edge.

V1 was traveling north in lane one on a two lane, two way, roadway. V1 then departed the roadway on the right side and contacted a tree with its front plane. The vehicle came to final rest against the tree and was approximately 17 meters from the point of roadway departure.

V1 & V2 were both traveling northeast in lane one on a two lane, two way, roadway. V2 turned left at an intersection to travel north on another roadway when V1 entered lane two to pass V1. At the intersection, V1's front plane contacted V2's left side plane. V1 and V2 both came to final rest in lane two a short distance from the point of contact.

V1 was traveling south exiting a parking lot on a two-way, undivided driveway. V2 was traveling east on lane 1 of a 2 lane, two-way, not physically divided roadway. V1 entered the roadway making a left turn while V2 was traveling in the same direction. V1's front plane contacted V2's left plane.

V1 was traveling south in lane 4 of a 4 lane, two-way, physically divided roadway with a left turn lane approaching an intersection, intending to turn left. V2 was traveling north in lane 1 of the same roadway. V1 and V2 entered the intersection simultaneously. V1 front plane contacted V2 left plane.

V1 and V2 were traveling south in lane 1 on a 3-lane divided roadway. V2 slowed for traffic. V1's front contacted V2's back plane. V2 then left the roadway to the right. V2's front contacted a concrete barrier. V2's right side then contacted the same barrier. V2 came to rest on the paved shoulder facing south, while V1 came to rest in the roadway facing south.

V1 was traveling southeast on a median divided four lane roadway, in lane 1.  V2 was traveling ahead of V1 in the same lane.  The front of V2 contacted the rear of V2.  Both vehicles came to rest on the west shoulder.

V1 was traveling east on a divided trafficway (median strip with positive barrier) in lane 2 (of four lanes) when it departed the roadway on the right, where the front end of V1 contacted two signs. V1 was traveling north in the center turn lane of a three lane roadway.  V2 was traveling south on the same roadway in lane 1.  As V1 made a left turn at the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2.  V1 came to rest in the intersection.  V2 departed the road to the west and came to rest on a sidewalk.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north on a 6 lane, two-way not physically divided roadway in lane number 1. Vehicle's 2, 3 and 4 were stopped in traffic, on the same roadway in lane number 1. This caused a chain reaction, and vehicle 6's front made contact with vehicle 1's rear end. Vehicle 1's front made contact with vehicle 2's rear end again, and vehicle 2's front was pushed into vehicle 3's rear end.

Vehicles 1,2,3,4  were all traveling west on a two-way,6 lane, physically divided roadway in lane number 5. Vehicle 1's front end made contact with vehicle 2's rear end. V2 was pushed forward and the front of V2 contacted the rear of V3.  Vehicle 4's front end made contact with vehicle 1's rear end. All 4 vehicles came to final rest in their original lanes.

V1 was heading north in the #3 lane of a 5 lane divided roadway. V2 was heading south in the #4 lane of a 5 lane divided roadway. Both vehicles entered an intersection. V2 turned left to head east. The front of V1 impacted the right side of V2. V1 continued forward and came to rest facing north in the middle of the intersection. V2 rotated clockwise and came to rest facing south in the middle of the intersection.

V1 was traveling westbound in the number 1 lane of a 2 lane undivided roadway. V2 was traveling eastbound in the number 1 lane of a 2 lane undivided roadway. V1 departed its lane to the left and entered the eastbound lanes. The front of V1 impacted the front of V2 and rode up the hood. V1 pushed V2 rearward and southerly where the rear of V2 impacted a wall. V1 rotated counter-clockwise after the impact with V2 and came to rest facing southerly in the eastbound lane. V2 came to rest facing northerly on the south shoulder.

V1 was traveling north on a two way, two lane road with a slight curve to the right. As V1 was negotiating the curve, it departed the roadway to the left where its front end struck a utility pole (event 1). V1 rotated clockwise and its left side impacted a fire hydrant (event 2). The utility pole fell on top of V1 (event 3) before it came to final rest off the roadway facing north.

V1 was traveling west bound on a two lane non-divided, bidirectional roadway. V1 was negotiating a curve to the left, with a negative grade to the roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right, where its frontal plane impacted a large tree. V1 rotated clockwise, and rolled four quarter turns coming to final rest on its wheels in the roadway.

V1 was traveling south east on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway negotiating a right curve. The road was icy and wet. V1 crossed the left lane line and departed the left road edge. The left plane of V1 contacted a tree. V1 continued and the frontal plane contacted a tree. V1 came to final rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was heading southwest on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. V1 crossed paths with V2. The frontal plane of V2 contacted the right plane of V1. V1 and V2 came to final rest on the roadway.
V was heading west in lane one of a two-lane divided roadway. V1departed the roadway to the right. The front of V1 contacted an utility pole where it came to final rest.

Vehicle #1 was traveling north in lane three of a five-lane, two way, non-divided traffic way approaching a light controlled four-legged intersection attempting to turn left. In the intersection, V1 turned left and the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V1 came to rest in the roadway facing west. V2 came to rest in the roadway facing southeast.

V1 was following V2 westbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V2 slowed down to make a right turn.  As V1 attempted to avoid V2 by steering right, the front of V1 impacted the right side of V2.V1 continued forward as V2 rotated counter-clockwise and the left side of V1 contacted the right side of V2. V1 came to rest on the roadway facing southwest. V2 came to rest on the roadway facing southwest.

V1 was west bound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 departed the right side of the roadway striking a guardrail end with its frontal plane. V1 then returned to the roadway briefly before departing the right side of the road again striking the guardrail face with the right side plane causing damage. V1 continued off the road and traveled down an embankment before coming to final rest on the north side of the road, facing north.

V1 was traveling eastbound in the number 1 lane of a 2 lane undivided roadway, exiting a private parking lot, preparing to turn left. V2 was traveling northbound in the number 2 lane of a 5 lane undivided roadway. V1 entered the roadway and began to turn left. V1 crossed both southbound lanes and the two-way left turn lane and entered the number 2 northbound lane. The front of V2 then contacted the right side of V1. V1 was pushed forward and to the left where it came to rest facing northerly. V2 traveled forward and to the right and came to rest facing northwest, to the east of V1.

V1 was traveling south in the first lane of a two lane, one-way positive divided roadway. A deer entered the roadway from the right into the first lane. The frontal plane of V1 impacted the deer. V1 came to final rest in the first lane of the roadway facing south.

V1 and V2 were traveling southwest bound on a 2 lane roadway. V1 slowed to turn right. V1's front contacted V2's back plane. V2 then yawed clockwise and went off of the roadway to the left. V2's left then contacted a tree before coming to a final rest off of the roadway. V1 came to rest off of the roadway as well.

Vehicle #1 (V1) was traveling north in lane one of a two-lane undivided roadway.  V1 departed the right side (east) of the road and its front contacted a barbed wire fence.  The vehicle came to final rest off the roadway and caught fire.
Vehicle 1 was traveling south in lane one of a two-lane undivided roadway when a fire began in the engine compartment.  V1 came to rest on the roadway, still facing south.

Vehicle 1 was traveling southeast in lane 3 on a 3-lane divided roadway. V1 departed the road to the left into the grass median. The front of V1 contacted a light pole. V1 began a counter clockwise rotation before coming to final rest facing a northeast direction in the median.

V1 was traveling southeast in lane two of a four-lane undivided roadway approaching an intersection and attempting an left turn. V2 was traveling northwest in lane one of the same roadway and passing through the same intersection. The right plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2. V1 rotated clockwise and came to final rest on the roadway facing southwest. V1 came to final rest on the roadway in their initial travel lane.

V1 was traveling south on lane one of a five lane divided roadway attempting to pass through an intersection. V2 was traveling west in lane one of a four lane divided roadway attempting to make a left turn at the same intersection. V1's front plane contacted V2's right plane. Both vehicles came to rest in the roadway near impact.

V1 was traveling northwest in lane one of a two-lane roadway. As V1 crested the hill, it departed the roadway to the right before returning to the roadway. V1 then crossed both travel lanes and departed the roadway to the left. V1 then crossed a ditch while airborne and then it's front plane contacted 3 tree. V1 came to final rest on the trees, having driven up them.

V1 was traveling northeast in lane one of a two lane roadway attempting to pass through an intersection. V2 was traveling northwest in lane one of a two lane roadway attempting to pass through the same intersection.V1's front plane contacted V2's left plane. V1 came to rest in the intersection. V2 came to rest just past the intersection.

V1 was traveling northeast in the number 3 lane of a 5 lane divided interstate. V1 departed its lane to the right. V1 continued departing lanes to the right until departing the roadway on the right side. The front of V1 impacted a pole. V1 continued forward and the front of V1 impacted a tree. The engine compartment of V1 then caught fire. V1 came to rest against the tree facing north.

V1 was traveling westbound in the number 1 lane of a 2 lane undivided roadway negotiating a right curve. V1 departed the roadway to the right. V1 began to steer left to regain control and the right side of V1 impacted a tree. V1 rotated clockwise and came to rest facing northerly.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane non-physically divided roadway in lane one. V2 was traveling south on a two lane non-physically divided roadway in lane one. V1 crossed into the southbound lane where the front of V1 impacted the front of V2. V1 rotated clockwise and came to rest in both lanes facing east. V2 rotated counter-clockwise and came to rest in both lanes facing east.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane divided roadway in lane one. V2 was traveling north on the same roadway in lane two. V1 attempted to change lanes to its left and the left side of V1 impacted the right side of V2. V2 then continued to its left and into the center median where the left side impacted the cement barrier twice. V1 did not stop the scene. V2 came to rest in the center median facing north.

V1 was traveling east on a one-way, 1-lane off-ramp behind V2. V2 was stopped on the off-ramp in front of V1 and V3 was stopped in front of V2. The front of V1 contacted the back of V2 then the front of V2 was pushed into the back of V3. All vehicles came to rest in the area of impact facing east.

V1 was traveling east in lane 2 of a multi-lane divided interstate roadway. A non-contact vehicle moved into lane two and caused V1 to move right, departing the roadway to the right shoulder.  V1 struck the guardrail face with an unknown plane. V1 came to rest on the right shoulder facing east.

V1 was traveling southeast on a two lane, two way roadway, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling northwest on a two lane, two way roadway, approaching the same intersection.  V1 attempted to make a left turn at the intersection and the right side of V1 struck the front plane of V2.  V1 continued traveling and the right side of V1 struck the front of V2 a second time.  V2 continued traveling and the front of V2 made contact with a utility pole.  V2 came to final rest off of the roadway. V1 came to rest in the intersection.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north on a 5 lane, two-way not physically divided roadway, in lane number 3, approaching an intersection. Vehicle 1 initiated a left turn at the intersection. Vehicle 1 struck the curb on the northwest corner of the intersection with its front/right. The vehicle continued off road where its front impacted a wall. Vehicle 1 came to final rest against the wall.

V1 was traveling northbound in the number 1 lane of a 2 lane undivided roadway. V2 was parked facing northbound on the east shoulder. V1 departed the roadway to the right where the front of V1 impacted a bush. The front of V1 then impacted a brick planter box. V1 rotated counter-clockwise after impacting the wall and began heading back towards the roadway where the front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. V2 rotated clockwise and came to rest facing north, partially on the sidewalk. V1 came to rest facing north on the east shoulder.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a curved two lane non-physically divided road approaching a protected four legged intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling south on a two lane non-physically divided road approaching the same intersection, unprotected. Vehicle 1 entered the intersection, the front of Vehicle 2 contacted the right side of Vehicle 1. Vehicle 2 departed the roadway in the southwest corner of the intersection, struck two traffic signs, rolled over four quarter turns and came to final rest facing south. Vehicle 1 also departed the roadway in the same corner, coming to final rest near a ditch line facing southwest.

Vehicle 1 was traveling southwest on a three lane roadway with a median protected by a guard cable, Vehicle 2 was parked on the berm on the right side of the same roadway. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway on the right side, crossed the gore area of an on-ramp and the on-ramp itself, and departed the on ramp to the right.  The front of Vehicle 1 contacted the back of Vehicle 2's trailer. Vehicle 1 came to final rest underneath Vehicle 2.

V1 was traveling south in lane 1 on a 2-lane divided roadway. A slower non-contact vehicle was traveling in front of V1. V1 steered right to avoid the non-contact vehicle. V1 departed the right road edge, traveled down an embankment and its front plane contacted a ditch. The right side of V1 contacted the embankment. V1 rotated clockwise and its top plane contacted overhanging branches. As V1 continued to rotate clockwise, its right side contacted the embankment then its back plane contacted the opposite embankment. V1 came to rest in the ditch facing north.

V1 was traveling westbound, on a 2 lane roadway and negotiating a curve to the left. V1 departed the road edge to its right. V1 went into a ditch and its front contacted the ground. V1 then rolled left and the front of V1 contacted a pole as it began to roll. V1 continued to roll left side leading before coming to rest on its roof partially in the westbound travel lane the side roadside. V1 then caught on fire.

V1 was traveling west on a two-lane, divided road making a left turn onto a main road. V2 was traveling south on a three-lane, two-way road with a center turn lane. The right side of V1 impacted the left side of V2 and both vehicles came to rest in the road.

V1 was traveling southeast in the first of three lanes on a divided, two-way roadway entering a light controlled, four-legged intersection. V2 was traveling southwest in the second of five lanes on a two-way roadway entering the same intersection as V1. Within the intersection, the left side of V1 contacted the front of V2. The vehicles rotated towards each other and the left side of V1 contacted the right side of V2 in a side-slap configuration. After the initial impact, Vehicle 1 rotated clockwise and came to rest in the roadway. Vehicle 2 rotated counterclockwise and came to rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling north in the second of five lanes on a positively divided, two-way roadway. V2 was traveling north in the first lane of the same roadway. V1 departed it's lane on the right side and the right side of V1 contacted the front of V2. The vehicles rotated towards each other and the right side of V1 contacted the left side of V2 in a side-slap configuration. After the initial impact, V1 and V2 departed the roadway on the right side and came to rest off the roadway.

V1 was southbound on a two lane, two way, undivided rural roadway. V1 departed its initial travel lane to the left then departed the left side of the roadway. V1 overturned right side leading two quarter turns. V1 then impacted a utility pole with an unknown plane causing damage. Upon impact V1 then rotated counter clockwise coming to rest on its roof facing south.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south in lane three on a six lane not physically divided two way roadway, approaching a four leg intersection with a traffic light. Vehicle 2 was traveling south in lane four on the same roadway approaching the same intersection.
