V1 and V2 were westbound in lane 2 of a a two way, five lane roadway with middle turn lane. V2 stopped and the front of V1 contacted the rear of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in the roadway.

V1 and V2 were southbound on the same 3 lane physically divided roadway. V1 was stopped in lane 3. V2 was also in lane 3 when V2 began to yaw counter-clockwise. The rear of V1 contacted the right side of V2. V1 was then pushed forward, crossed all travel lanes and the front of V1 contacted a cement traffic barrier coming to rest in an on ramp lane. The left side of V2 contacted a concrete traffic barrier and came to rest on the shoulder facing south.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a three-lane, two-way roadway traveling in lane two. V1 was approaching a T-shaped intersection. V2 was traveling northbound on a three-lane, two-way roadway in lane two. V2 was approaching the T-shaped intersection with a stop sign controlling the northbound traffic. In the middle of the intersection the front plane of V1 contacted the left side of V2. After initial impact the right side of V1 contacted the left side of V2 in a side slap manner. Both V1 and V2 came to final rest off the roadway facing northeast.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a two-lane, two-way roadway, traveling in lane one. V2 and V3 were both stopped in traffic facing eastbound on the same roadway. The front of V1 contacted the rear of V2. As a result V2 was pushed forward where the front of V2 contacted the rear of V3. All vehicles came to final rest on the roadway facing eastbound.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north on on a two lane, two way roadway in lane 1 approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling east on a 2 lane two way roadway in lane 1 approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection proceeding straight and the front of V1 contacted the right side of V2 in the intersection. V2 then rotated clock wise and came to rest facing west on the east side of the intersection. V1 came to rest in the roadway facing north.

V1 was westbound on a 2 way roadway when V1 departed the roadway to the left and the front of V1 contacted a utility pole and the struck utility pole fell over and contacted the top of V1. V1 continued to travel and the front of V1 contacted 2 trees and came to rest.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a five-lane, two-way roadway approaching a T-intersection. V2 was traveling southbound on a two-lane, physically divided roadway. V2 was making a left turn to head east. In the middle of the intersection the front plane of V2 contacted the right side of V1, after initial contact the right side of V2 contacted the left side of V1 in a side slap manner. V1 came to final rest partially off the roadway facing east, V2 came to final rest in the roadway facing east.

V2, V3, V4, V5, and V6 were all stopped at a traffic light on a one-way, three-lane roadway heading west. V2 was in lane one, V4 in lane three and V3, V5, and V6 in lane two. V1 was traveling westbound in an unknown lane where the right side of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V1 continued westbound where the front plane contacted the back plane of V3. This impact caused V3 to push forward into the back plane of V5. V3 also was pushed to the left from impact with V1 where the left plane contacted the right plane of V4 which was stopped next to V3. V5 was pushed forward and the front plane of V5 contacted the back plane of V6. V1 came to final rest in lane two facing northwest, while all other vehicles came to final rest near initial point of impacts.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on two-way physically divided roadway in lane number 6. Vehicle 2 and Vehicle 2 were traveling on the same roadway going east in lane number 6. Vehicle 4,5,6 were traveling in the same direction on the same roadway in lane number 5. Vehicle 1's front end made contact with vehicle 2's rear. Vehicle 2's front end was pushed into vehicle 3's rear end. Vehicle 2's right side made contact with vehicle 4's front end. Vehicle 3's right side made contact with vehicle 5's left side. Vehicle 2 continued going straight and making contact with vehicle 6 rear end.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south in the second lane of a 5 lane, two way median divided roadway. Vehicle 2 was traveling north on the same roadway in the third lane. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway to the left and the front of Vehicle 1 contacted a sign in the median. Vehicle 1 then entered the northbound lanes and the front of Vehicle 1 contacted the front of Vehicle 2. Vehicle 1 came to final rest on the roadway facing north. Vehicle 2 came to final rest on the roadway facing south.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south in lane two of two of a not physically divided, two way road roadway attempting to crossover an intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling north in the left turn lane on the same roadway attempting to turn left at the same intersection. Avoidance maneuvers by both vehicles resulted in the front of V1 contacting the left side of V2.  Then V2 rapidly rotated clockwise, where the left side of V2 contacted the right side of V1.  V1 came to rest facing northwest within intersection and V2 came to rest facing south in the northbound travel lanes.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a two way, two lane roadway approaching a five leg intersection controlled by a stop sign. Vehicle 2 was traveling north on a two way, two lane roadway approaching the same intersection with no traffic controls. Both vehicles entered the intersection going straight. Within the intersection the front plane of Vehicle 2 contacted the right plane of Vehicle 1. Vehicle 1 rotated clockwise and came to final rest facing west on the east side of the intersection. Vehicle 2 rotated clockwise and came to final rest within the intersection facing east.

Vehicle 3 was traveling west in lane one on a five lane one way trafficway divided by a grass median, approaching a three leg intersection controlled by a traffic light. Vehicle 2 was traveling west in lane one behind vehicle 3 on the same trafficway approaching the same intersection. Vehicle 1 was traveling west in lane one behind vehicle 2 on the same trafficway approaching the same intersection. Vehicle 4 was traveling west in lane 2 on the same trafficway approaching the same intersection. Vehicles 2 and 3 were stopped for the red light when the front plane of vehicle 1 contacted the back plane of vehicle 2. Upon impact flying debris contacted the right plane of vehicle 4. The front plane of vehicle 2 then contacted the back plane of vehicle 3. Vehicles 1, 2, 3, and 4 came to final rest on the roadway facing west.

V1 and V2 were both traveling west on a six lane undivided road negotiating a curve left. V1 was in lane two and V2 was in lane one.  V1 departed its lane to the right and its right side contacted the left side of V2 (event 1). V1’s right side struck V2’s left again (event 2) before both vehicles departed the road. V2 departed the road on the right, where its right and left front wheels/tires contacted a curb (events 3 and 4). The front end of V2 then contacted fence (event 5) and a bus stop shelter with its front (event 6) before coming to rest on its wheels facing a westerly direction on the roadside. V1 departed the roadway on the right where its front right wheel/tire contacted a curb (event 7) before coming to rest on its wheels facing a southwesterly direction on the right shoulder.

V1 was traveling in a southwesterly direction, through the left hand curve of the roadway, on a designated east/west, two-way, not physically divided trafficway (with two-way left turn lane), in lane 1 (of three lanes), and was approaching V2, which was legally parked along the road edge, facing a southwesterly direction.  V1 departed the roadway on the right, and its front end came in contact with the left side of V2's trailer.  V1 rotated clockwise, then came to rest on its wheels, facing a northeasterly direction in its original travel lane, alongside V2.  V2 remained at rest in its original position.

Vehicle #1 was traveling east on a two-way, four lane, undivided road, that curved left. As V1 approached an intersection, the road straightened out. V1 was in lane two as it entered the intersection, but continued in a left curving path. V1 departed two lanes to the left, then departed the road to the left on the NE corner. The LF tire, then the RF tire contacted the curb. The front plane of V1 contacted a breakaway pole, then an electrical box. V1 continued off-road for a short distance, then came to rest off-road.

V1 was traveling in a southwesterly direction, on a designated north/south divided trafficway (median strip without positive barrier), in lane 1 (of three lanes).  V1 departed its lane on the left and entered lane 2, then lane 3.  V1 was steered to the right, and control was lost.  V1 skidded laterally in a clockwise rotation and departed the road on the right, where its left side came in contact with a wood post supporting a sign.  V1 then overturned (2 quarter turns, leading left) and came to rest on its roof, facing a northeasterly direction on the roadside.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north on a 4 lane two-way physically divided roadway in the number 2 lane. Vehicle 2 was traveling on the same roadway in the number 3 lane. V1's front end made contact with V2's right side while in the number 3 lane.  V1 began a clockwise yaw and departed the roadway to the right before coming to final rest.  V2 began a clockwise yaw and rolled 6 quarter turns, left side leading, before coming to final rest on its top in the travel lanes.
V1 was traveling east on a two-lane, two-way road that curved the right. V1 departed the road to the left side where its front plane impacted a tree. V1 came to rest off of the left side of the road.

V1 was traveling north in the #1 lane of a 5 lane divided roadway. V1 departed the lane to the right while beginning to rotate clockwise. V1 departed the roadway to the right where the left front, then the left rear wheel impacted a curb. V1 began to roll over leading left where the left side impacted a tree. V1 continued rotating clockwise and the right side impacted a wall. V1 continued rotating clockwise and came to rest on its roof facing south on the road side.

V1 was traveling westbound in the number 1 lane of a 3 lane divided roadway, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling eastbound in the number 3 lane of a 3 lane divided roadway, preparing to turn left at an intersection. V3 was traveling southbound in the number 1 lane of a 2 lane divided roadway, preparing to turn right at an intersection. V1 and V2 entered the intersection. The front of V1 impacted the right side of V2. V2 rotated counter-clockwise and started heading northwest where the front of V2 impacted the front of V3. V1 came to rest facing westerly in the intersection. V2 came to rest facing northerly on the north side of the intersection. V3 came to rest facing northerly, north of the intersection.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 departed the right side of the roadway and struck a utility pole with the frontal plane. V1 continued west, crossing over a north/ south roadway, striking a stop sign with its frontal plane. V1 came to rest near the point of impact with the stop sign heading west.

V1 was traveling west following a one way divided roadway. V1 departed its original travel lane to the left attempting to pass another vehicle. V1 lost control and departed the roadway to the left. The front of V1 impacted a cable barrier guardrail with the cable also contacting the top and left planes. V1 came to final rest on the shoulder of the roadway facing west.

V1 was traveling west on a non-physically divided two way road in lane one, negotiating a left curve. V1 traveled off the right road edge and returned back to the roadway, where V1 lost control. V1 traveled across the eastbound lane yawing in a counterclockwise motion and then departed the eastbound road edge where the back of V1 impacted a metal fence. V1 continued along the fence, then rolled left four quarter turns, where the left front of V1 impacted another fence pole. V1 continued to roll up and over another metal fence, where V1 continued to rolled right three quarter turns. V1 came to rest on it's left side facing a easterly direction

Vehicle 1, vehicle 2, and vehicle 3 were traveling north in lane one of four lane, barrier divided roadway. Vehicle 3 was stopped due to traffic, V2 was slowing down behind V3. Vehicle 1's front impacted vehicle 2's back. Vehicle 2's front than made contact with vehicle 3's back. All vehicles came to rest just forward of  impact, facing north, in lane one.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north on a 4 lane physically divided roadway in lane number 1. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway to the right, and vehicle 1's front made contact with a concrete barrier.  The pole then separated from its base and contacted the roof of V1.  Vehicle 1 continued forward and made contact with a pole with its left side, coming to final rest against the pole.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane non-physically divided roadway in lane one negotiating a right curve.  V1 departed the right road edge and the front right side of V1 impacted a rock wall. V1 then re-entered the roadway and began to rollover left side leading, with two quarter turns. V1 came to rest on it's roof in the northbound lane facing an westerly direction.

V1 was traveling south on a non-physically divided three lane highway in lane three, approaching an intersection to make a left turn, to travel east. V2 was north on a non-physically divided two lane highway in lane two, approaching the same intersection. As V1 attempted a left turn, its right side collided with the front of V2 (event 1). Subsequently, the right side of V1 struck the left side of V2 (event 2). V1 then traveled off the right road edge of the southbound lanes, where the front of V1 impacted a chain linked fence (event 3). V1 came to rest against the fence, on its wheels, facing a northerly direction. V2 also traveled off the right road edge of the southbound lanes in a clockwise manner, and came to rest on its wheels facing a southerly direction.

V1 was traveling west on a 3 lane physically divided roadway, in lane 1, and approaching an interchange. V1 departed the roadway to the right. V1's left side contacted a guard rail face. V1 continued forward. The front of V1 contacted a sign before coming to final rest off of the roadway.

V1 was traveling southwest while negotiating a curve to the right on a two-lane, two-way road. V1 departed the road to the left side when its front plane impacted a tree. V1 came to rest at the point of impact.

V1 was northbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 departed its initial travel lane to the left then departed the left side of the roadway. V1 traveled into a ditch then up an embankment impacting three trees with the frontal plane. V1 came to final rest near the point of impact facing northwest.

V1 was traveling eastbound in the first lane of a two lane, two-way roadway, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling northbound in the first lane of a two lane, two-way roadway, approaching the same intersection. V2 was attempting to turn left to continue traveling westbound. V1 and V2 entered the intersection at the same time. The frontal plane of V1 impacted the left side plane of V2.  V2 rotated counterclockwise in the roadway before coming to final rest facing west. V1 continued north departing the roadway on the right. The frontal plane of V1 impacted a metal guardrail face. As V1 rotated slightly counterclockwise, the left side plane of V1 impacted the same guardrail face. V1 continued forward with the left side plane impacting the same metal guardrail face again. V1 continued forward impacting it's frontal plane into the wooden guardrail before coming to final rest. V2 came to final rest off of the roadway facing northeast.

V1 was traveling southbound in the first lane of a two lane, two-way roadway, with a right curvature. V1 departed left into the second lane and then departed left off of the roadway. The frontal plane of V1 impacted a rock wall structure. V1 came to final rest off of the roadway facing south.

V1 was negotiating a curve to the left while traveling west on a two-lane, two-way road. V1 departed the right side of the road when its right side impacted a tree. The front of V1 then impacted a utility pole, causing it to rotate clock-wise and rollover left side leading three quarter turns. The undercarriage of V1 then impacted a tree, coming to rest on its passenger side off of the right side of the road.

V1 was traveling south on a two-lane, two-way road when it departed the right side of the road and struck a cable guardrail barrier with its front plane. V1 came to rest off of the right side of the road.

V1 was traveling in a southwesterly direction, through the right hand curve of the roadway, on an exit ramp from the Interstate, and was in lane 1 (of one lane).  V1 departed the road on the left and traversed the median between the exit ramp and the entrance ramp, the entrance ramp itself, and the shoulder to the right of the entrance ramp.  V1's front end then came in contact with the face of the guardrail bordering the aforementioned shoulder.  V1 came to rest on its wheels, facing a northwesterly direction alongside the guardrail.

V1 was traveling east on a two-way, not physically divided trafficway, in lane 1 (of two lanes), when it departed the road on the right.  On the roadside, V1's front end came in contact with a fire hydrant and a chain-link fence.  V1 came to rest on its wheels, facing a southerly direction in an empty field south of the trafficway.

V1 was traveling west on a 2-lane divided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south on a 1-lane divided roadway approaching the same intersection intending to turn left. Both vehicles entered the intersection and the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V1 continued forward and departed the median curb edge and its front plane contacted a metal sign post. V1 came to rest near this impact facing west. V2 rotated clockwise and came to rest on the roadway facing west.

V1 was traveling east in lane 1 on a three lane roadway with a two way center turn lane approaching a driveway entrance. V2 was traveling north on a two way, two lane driveway stopped at the intersection of the main roadway. V1 departed the road to the right and the driveway entrance and the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V1 came to rest on the driveway facing southeast. V2 rotated clockwise and came to rest at the southeast corner of the driveway facing northeast.

V1 was traveling north bound on a two lane, non divided, bidirectional roadway, negotiating a right hand curve, with a negative grade. V1 departed the roadway to the right. It then returned to the roadway, crossing both lanes of travel and departed the roadway to the left, where it rolled over into a ditch. V1 impacted a small tree, and a fence before it came to final rest on the left side of the roadway on its passenger side.

V1 and V2 were both traveling south on a two lane, non-divided bidirectional roadway negotiating a slight curve to the left. V1 was behind V2. V2 slowed to make a left turn into a driveway. V1's frontal plane impacted V2's rear plane. V1's right plane then impacted V2 as it passed by V2. V1 then departed the roadway to the right, where its frontal plane impacted a ditch, before coming to final rest. V2 came to rest on the right side of the road.

V1 was traveling northwest in lane one of a one-way interstate off-ramp, approaching an intersection and attempting a left turn. V2 was traveling northeast in lane one of a five-lane divided roadway, negotiating a right curve. V3 was traveling in lane two of the same roadway, slightly behind V2. The front plane of V1 contacted the right plane of V2. V1 then rotated clockwise and the left plane of V1 contacted the right plane of V2. The impact pushed V2 into lane two, and the left plane of V2 contacted the front plane of V3. V1 departed the roadway and came to final rest in the median. V2 and V3 came to final rest on the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north travel on a 2-lane undivided roadway. Vehicle 1 was pulling off the roadway to stop on the soft shoulder. As Vehicle 1 was coming to a stop, it was unable to do so, and began to furrow into the soft ground. Vehicle 1 continued attempting to stop and was braking until it came to the edge of the culvert system, where the frontal plane departed the surface and began to fall over the edge. As Vehicle 1 left any supporting surface, the vehicle entered into a flip over as it fell into the waterway contacting the roof of the vehicle with the water. Vehicle 1 then began to submerge and while doing so rolled onto its left side until coming to rest at the bottom of the waterway.

Vehicle 1 was travelling in the first northbound travel lane of a four lane median divided trafficway. A deer was in the roadway and was contacted by the frontal plane of vehicle 1. Vehicle 1 came to rest on the roadway.

V1, a farm tractor was stopped, facing south on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 had a large piece of mowing equipment attached to the rear. V2 was traveling south on the same roadway. The frontal plane of V2 impacted the back plane of V1's attached mowing equipment causing damage. V1 came to rest headed south in its initial travel lane. V2 rotated clockwise, crossed the center line, and came to rest in the middle of the roadway heading southwest.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 contacted a deer with its frontal plane in the travel lane, causing damage. V1 came to final rest east of the point of impact in its initial travel lane facing east.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a four lane, two-way roadway in lane one. V2 was traveling northbound on a two-way, physically divided roadway entering a four-way intersection, in lane one. V1's front plane contacted V2's left plane. V1 and V2 came to final rest on roadway facing northeast.

V1 and V2 were traveling north west in the #2 lane of a 2 lane divided roadway. V2 was traveling in front of V1 and began to slow due to traffic. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2. Both vehicles came to rest facing north west in the #2 lane.

V1,V2, and V3 were traveling southbound in the #3 lane of a 3 lane divided roadway. V2 and V3 came to a stop due to traffic. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2. V2 was pushed forward and the front of V2 impacted the back of V3. All three vehicles came to rest in the #3 lane facing south.

Vehicle 1 was traveling Southeast on a 5 lane physically divided roadway in the lane 3 position making a left hand turn in an intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling Northwest on 4 lane physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position passing through the intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection at the same time. The right plane of Vehicle 1 made contact with the front plane of Vehicle 2. Vehicle 1 came to final rest facing Northeast on the on-ramp of the intersection. Vehicle 2 came to final rest facing Northwest just after impact in the middle of the intersection.

V1 was traveling east in lane 1 on a 2-lane divided roadway directly behind V2 when the front of V1 contacted the back of V2. V1 rotated counter-clockwise the tripped and rolled right on the paved shoulder. V1 completed 2-quarter turns and came to rest on its top on the grass roadside facing south. Occupant 2 of V1 was partially ejected during the rollover sequence. V2 rotated counter-clockwise as it departed the left road edge into the grass median where its right side contacted a cable barrier. V2 came to rest near the cable barrier facing west.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a two lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1 position negotiating a left curve. V1 departed roadway right side. The front of V1 contacted a delineator post. V1 traveled across an intersection north and south bound roadway. V1 continued east off the roadway. The front of V1 contacted a sign. V1 continued east fishtailing. V1 then began a primarily right side roll for 8 quarter turns. During the roll V1 struck a fence and a utility post with unknown planes before coming to rest facing west on its wheels.

V1 was traveling north on a two way, two lane road. V2 was traveling south on the same two-way, two lane road. V3 was traveling south behind V2, on the same two-way, two lane road. V1 departed its original travel lane to the left impacting the right side of V2 with its frontal plane. V1 departed the roadway to the left. Continuing forward, V1 re-entered the roadway on the right, impacting the right side of V3 with its frontal plane. The impact caused V3 to rotate counterclockwise. V1 and V3 came to final rest off the roadway facing east. V2 came to final rest in the roadway facing south.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway, with a left hand curve. V1 departed the right side of the roadway. V1 struck four headstones with its frontal plane. V1 then rolled, four quarter turns, right side leading. During the roll sequence V1 struck another tombstone with its right side plane. V1 came to rest on its wheels heading west.
V1 and V2 were negotiating a right curve on an exit ramp. The front of V1 contacted the back of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest near the point of impact.

V1 was heading west on a four lane divided roadway without a positive barrier. V2 was heading east on the same roadway. V1 departed its travel lane to the left. The front of V1 contacted the front of V2. Impact forces caused V1 to rotate counter clockwise. V1 the departed the roadway to the left where it came to final rest facing northeast. V2 came final rest facing southeast.

V1 was traveling south through a left hand curve on a not physically divided (two-way) trafficway in lane 1 (of two lanes) and was approaching V2, which was traveling north through a right hand curve on the same roadway in lane 1. V1 departed the road on the right and was returned to the road from the right, where control over V1 was lost and it began to rotate counterclockwise. V1 departed its lane on the left and the front end of V2 contacted the right side of V1. V1 then began to rotate clockwise and overturned (2 quarter turns, leading right then left). V1 came to rest on its wheels facing an easterly direction in lane 1. V2 came to rest on its wheels facing a westerly direction on the roadside, north of V1.

V1 was traveling north in lane one of a seven lane undivided (two-way traffic) roadway, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling west in lane one of a four lane undivided (two-way traffic) roadway, approaching the same intersection. Within the intersection the right side of V1 was impacted by the front V2. V1 rotated clockwise and moved further north, coming to rest in lane one of the northbound lanes, facing northeast. V2 rotated clockwise and came to rest within the intersection, facing northwest.

V1 was negotiating a curve to the right while traveling on a two-lane, two-way road. A deer entered the road from the right and the front of V1 impacted the deer. V1 came to rest on the right side of the road.

V1 was traveling west on a two-lane, two-way road approaching a rotary. V2 was traveling in the rotary intending to depart the rotary on the north exit. V1 entered the rotary and the left side of V1 impacted the right side of V2. The left side of V1 then side-slapped the right side of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in the rotary.

V1 was traveling east in the second of two lanes on a positively divided, two-way roadway. V2 was traveling east in the first lane of the same roadway. V1 changed lanes to the right and the back of V1 contacted the front of V2. V1 rotated clockwise as it departed the roadway on the right side. V1 rolled left to top for four quarter turns and came to rest south of the roadway. V2 came to rest on the roadway ahead.

V1 was traveling southeast on a two-lane, one-way roadway. V1 departed the roadway on the right side. V1's right front tire contacted the curb. V1 continued southeast and struck a light pole with it's front plane. V1 continued on and struck a tree with it's front plane before coming to final rest off roadway.

V1 was northbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway stopped at a four leg intersection. V2 was westbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. As v1 continued through the intersection the front of V1 impacted the left side of V2 causing damage. Upon impact V1 rotated counter clockwise coming to final rest in the intersection facing northwest. V2 rotated counter clockwise coming to final rest in the intersection facing southwest.

V1 was southbound on a two lane, two way roadway divided by a grass median making a left turn to travel east. V2 was northbound on the same roadway. The front of V2 impacted the right side of V1 causing damage. Upon impact V1 rotated counter clockwise coming to final rest in the intersection facing northeast. V2 rotated clockwise coming to final rest in the intersection facing east.

V1 was traveling south in the #1 lane of a 5 lane divided roadway. V1 departed the road to the right. The front right tire of V1 impacted a curb. V1 continued forward where the front left tire of V1 impacted a curb. V1 continued forward where the undercarriage of V1 impacted a curb. V1 continued forward across a sidewalk where the front right tire of V1 impacted a curb. V1 continued forward where the left front tire of V1 impacted a curb. V1 continued forward where the undercarriage of V1 impacted a curb. V1 entered into a planter area where the front of V1 impacted a collection of small bushes and shrubbery. V1 continued forward where the front of V1 impacted a tree. V1 continued forward where the front of V1 impacted a bush. V1 continued through the tree and bush into a parking lot area where the front of V1 impacted a cement bollard. V1 rotated clockwise and came to rest facing south west in the parking lot.

V1 was traveling westbound in the number 1 lane of a 3 lane undivided roadway, preparing to turn right. V1 began to turn right to go northbound. V1 began to lose traction. V1 departed the roadway to the left where the front of V1 impacted a curb. V1 continued forward where the front of V1 impacted the curb again. V1 rotated counter-clockwise and came to rest facing westerly on the center median.

V1 was traveling north following a two way, four lane road, with a slight curve to the right. V2 was stopped in traffic, in front of V1, on the same two way, four lane road. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway facing north.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane divided roadway in lane two. V2 was traveling north on a two lane divided roadway in lane two in front of V1. V3 was traveling north on a two lane divided roadway in lane two in front of V2. Due to traffic slowing ahead, the front of V2 impacted the rear of V3, then the front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. All three vehicles came to rest in lane two facing north.

V1 was traveling south on a physically divided, two lane off ramp in lane two, behind V2. V2 was traveling south on the same physically divided, two lane off ramp in lane two, slowing down in front of V1. Due to heavy traffic, the front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. V2 then was pushed forward, towards the east shoulder, where the left front of V2 impacted a guardrail. V1 came to rest within the number two lane facing a southerly direction. V2 came to rest in the number two lane facing south.

Vehicle 1 and Vehicle 2 were traveling east on a two-way physically undivided roadway in lane one. Vehicle 2 was stopped ahead of V1. The front of Vehicle 1 contacted the back of Vehicle 2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway facing east.

V1 was traveling westbound on a two-way, two-lane roadway. V1 attempted to avoid an animal in the roadway and as a result departed the roadway on the right side. The front plane of V1 contacted three trees before coming to final rest off the roadway facing northwest. The last tree struck fell ontop of the top plane of V1 at final rest.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a two lane, two-way, median divided roadway approaching a roundabout intersection. V1 departed traffic way left side onto a median striking a crosswalk sign with its front end. V1 came to rest at impact facing east.

Vehicle 2 was traveling in the lane 2 on a 3 lane divided traffic-way at an intersection attempting to turn left. Vehicle 1 was traveling east in the lane 2 position on the same roadway behind V2. The front plane of Vehicle 1 made contact with the rear plane of Vehicle 2. Both V1 and V2 came to rest at impact facing east.

V1 was traveling west bound on a two lane, non-divided, bidirectional roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right, where its frontal plane impacted a guardrail end. V1 rotated counter clockwise, and rolled one quarter turn, passenger side leading.  V1 came to final rest on its passenger side in a creek bed.

V1 was traveling south on a two-way, two lane, right curved road, approaching a three way intersection. As V1 was negotiating the curve, it departed its travel lane, crossing over an intersecting roadway. V1 departed the road on the right impacting a curb with its frontal end. Continuing forward, the front of V1 impacted three shrubs. Before coming to rest, the front of V1 impacted a large tree. V1 came to final rest up against the tree, off of the roadway, facing southwest.

V1 and V2 were both traveling south on a three-lane, one-way road. V1 was in lane two and changed lanes to the left into lane three where V2 was traveling. The left side of V1 contacted the right side of V2. V2 departed the roadway on the left side and the front of V2 contacted a pole.

V1 was northbound on a two lane, two way, undivided, rural roadway. V1 departed the right side of the road traveling into a field in a counter clockwise yaw. V1 struck a tree with the right side plane causing damage. V1 then rotated off the tree impacting another tree with the frontal plane causing damage. V1 came to final rest at the second point of impact facing northeast.

V1 was northbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway crossing a four leg intersection. V2 was eastbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. The front of V2 struck the left side of V1 causing damage. Upon impact V1 rotates counter clockwise coming to final rest in the northbound lane of the intersection facing south. V2 continued off its initial travel lane coming to final rest on the southeastern portion of the intersection facing east.

V1 was traveling north in lane one of a two-lane undivided roadway, attempting to turn left at an intersection. V2 was traveling east in lane one of a two-lane undivided roadway, attempting to pass through the same intersection. The left plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2. Both vehicles came to rest close to impact on the roadway.

V1 was traveling northeast negotiating a right curve. V2 was traveling southwest negotiating the same curve to the left. V1 departed its travel lane to the left. V1's front plane contacted V2's front plane Both vehicle came to rest near impact with V2 partially off the roadway.

V1 was traveling east in lane one of a seven-lane divided roadway.  Prior to event 1, occupant 1 intentionally exited the vehicle, resulting in injury.  V1 then departed the roadway to the right and its front plane contacted a pole. V1 then rotated clockwise and it's left side contacted a curb. V1 came to final rest partial on the roadway.

V1 was traveling southeast in lane one of a divided roadway attempting to make a right turn and pass through an intersection. V2 was traveling southeast in lane one of a two lane roadway attempting to pass the the same intersection. V1's right plane contacted V2's front plane. The vehicles side slapped with V1's right plane contacting V2's left plane. Both vehicles came to rest in the intersection.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north on a 3 lane median divided intersection in lane number 3 intending to make a U-turn. Vehicle 2 was traveling south on a 6 lane two-way, non-physically divided trafficway approaching the same intersection in the number 3 lane.  Vehicle 1's right side and vehicle 2's front made contact with each other. After initial contact, Vehicle 2's right plane side slapped Vehicle 1's front. Vehicle 1 came to rest facing NE in lane number 3. Vehicle 2 came to rest facing south in lane number 1.

V1 and V2 were traveling north in lane no. 1 of a two-lane, physically divided roadway. V1 was behind V2 and the front of V1 impacted the back of V2. V1 lost power and then rolled backwards, departing the right road edge. V1 initiated a four-quarter turn rollover sequence coming to rest on its wheels and facing north. V2 came to rest on the right shoulder.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a 2-lane roadway. Vehicle 2 was legally parked facing east on the right side of the same roadway. The right side of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V1 rotated clockwise then rolled 2-quarter turns and came to rest on its top in the roadway facing south.

Vehicle #1 was traveling south on a two-way, two-lane road. V1 departed the road to the right and the front end of V1 contacted a utility pole. V1 rotated sharply clockwise and turned over six quarter turns to the left. V1 came to rest in the road.

V1 was facing eastbound on the parking shoulder on the south curb side attempting to pull out.V2 was traveling eastbound on a two way roadway with a single lane of travel in each direction.  As V1 entered the roadway, the left plane of V1 made contact with the right plane of V2. V1 came to rest partially on the roadway. V2 came to rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling northbound on a two way roadway with a single lane of travel in each direction. V2 was parked on the east side curb facing northbound. V1 departed the roadway on the right side and the frontal plane of V1 made contact with the rear plane of V2. V1 came to final rest partially on the roadway. V2 came to final rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling southwest in the number 1 lane of a 1 lane freeway on-ramp, negotiating a curve to the right. V1 departed the roadway to the right where the front of V1 impacted a pole. V1 came to rest facing westerly on the north shoulder.

V1 was traveling south in the #1 lane of a 2 lane roadway. V1 observed a pedestrian in the middle of the road. V1 steered right off the road to the right. The front of V1 impacted a fence where it came to rest facing south.

V1 was traveling west on a non-physically divided two-way highway in lane one. V1 departed the its travel lane to the left, then returned to its original travel lane. V1 departed the roadway on the right side, where the left side of V1 impacted a tree. The momentum of V1 spun counter-clockwise down the embankment and the rear of V1 impacted another tree. V1 came to rest down the embankment facing a southerly direction.

V1 traveling west on a non-physically divided two way road, approaching a left curve in lane one. For an unknown reason V1 was unable to negotiate the curve, and departed the right side of the roadway, where the front of V1 impacted an embankment. The momentum caused V1 to  begin to roll right six quarter turns, coming to rest on its roof facing a southerly direction.

V1 was southbound on a two lane, two way, undivided rural roadway approaching a four leg intersection. V2 was westbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. V1 attempted to cross through the intersection as the front of V2 impacted the left side of V1 causing damage. V1 rotated counter clockwise and departed the southwest corner of the intersection coming to final rest on a wooden traffic barrier facing northwest. V2 followed V1 off the southwestern edge of the roadway impacting a wooden traffic barrier with the left front wheel continuing off the road coming to rest facing southwest.

V1 was eastbound on a two lane, two way, undivided rural roadway. V1 departed the road to the left impacting a ditch with the frontal plane. Subsequently, V1 overturned, with its right side leading, 6-quarter turns coming to rest on its roof facing north.

V1 was traveling south in lane three of a five lane divided roadway attempting to pass through an intersection. V2 was traveling northeast in lane one of a two lane roadway attempting to make a left turn a the same intersection. V3 was stopped in traffic northbound in lane two at the same intersection. V1's front plane contacted V2's left plane. V1 came to rest partially in the median facing south. V2 went into a counter clockwise rotation and departed its travel lane and its rear plane contacted V3's front plane. Both V2 and V3 came to rest in the intersection.

V1 was traveling northeast in lane one of a two-lane undivided roadway attempting to turn left through a median pass-through. V2 was traveling southeast in lane three of a six-lane divided roadway. V1's left plane contacted V2's front plane. Then, V1 rotated clockwise and its left plane contacted V2's right plane. Both vehicles came to rest in the intersection.

V1 was traveling northwest in lane three of a seven lane divided roadway attempting to pass through an intersection. V2 was traveling southeast in lane one of a two lane roadway attempting to pass through the same intersection. V1's front plane contacted V2's left plane. V1 came to rest near impact. V2 veered right and the RF wheel contacted the curb on the median. V2 then tripped and rolled right one quarter turn coming to final rest on its right plane.

V1 was traveling northeast in lane one of a two-lane undivided roadway attempting to turn left through a median pass-through. V2 was traveling southeast in lane three of a six-lane divided roadway. V1's left plane contacted V2's front plane. Then, V1 rotated clockwise and its left plane contacted V2's right plane. V1 came to final rest in the roadway. V2 then crossed the northbound lanes and departed the roadway. V2 traveled off the roadway a distance before its front plane impacted a ditch. V2 came to final rest in the ditch.

V1 was traveling east on a two-lane roadway approaching a right curve. V1 departed the road to the left and its front plane contacted a sign post. V1 continued forward and its front plane contacted a 2nd sign post. V1 rotated counter-clockwise and continued down a shallow embankment and its left front wheel contacted the far side of a ditch. V1 continued forward and came to rest in a dirt field facing east.

V1 was traveling southwest in lane 1 of a 2 lane, two way, roadway. A deer entered the roadway from the right and V1's front plane contacted the deer. V1 came to final rest in lane 1 on the roadway and was approximately 15 meters from the initial contact with the deer

V1 and V2 were both traveling southwest, in lane 4, on a 5 lane, non-positively divided roadway. V2 was stopped in traffic and V1's front plane contacted V2's back plane. Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway.

V1 and V2 were traveling east on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway in lane one negotiating a slight left hand curve in the roadway, V1 was trailing V2. V2 began to turn right into a private driveway. The frontal plane of V1 made contact with the right side plane of V2. V1 continued forward crossing the left lane line and departed the left side (north) of the roadway striking a tree with its frontal plane. V1 came to a final rest off of the roadway facing east. V2 rotated clockwise and departed the southwest corner of the intersection where its left side contacted a mailbox post. V2 came to rest off of the roadway facing west.

V1 and V2 were traveling west on the same two lane two way divided roadway. V1 was in the second lane and V2 was in the first lane, V1 departed their initial lane of travel, the the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V1 then departed the roadway to the left while rotating counter-clockwise yaw and the right side of V1 contacted the guardrail post on the other side of the grass median and came to final rest.

V1 and V2 were traveling north east on a two lane two way divided trafficway. V1 departed their initial lane of travel to the right and the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V1 departed the roadway to the right and the front of V1 contacted a concrete traffic barrier. V2 departed the roadway to the right and the right side of V2 contacted a concrete traffic barrier, then crossed over to the left side of the roadway and the front of V2 contacted a concrete traffic barrier. Then the left side of V2 contacted a concrete traffic barrier and came to final rest off the roadway. V1 continued in a clockwise rotational yaw and the back of V1 contacted a concrete traffic barrier, and came to final rest off the roadway.
V1 was traveling west on a rural roadway. V1 departed the left side of the roadway striking a ditch with its frontal plane. V1 came to rest headed west at the point of impact.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a 4 lane, two-way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 2 approaching an intersection. Vehicle 2 is traveling east on a 4 lane, two-way, non- physically divided roadway in lane 2 approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles enter the intersection. V1 attempted to make a left turn. The front of V2 contacted the front of V1. V1 came to rest facing south in the intersection V2 came to rest facing southeast in the intersection.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a 4 lane, one way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 4 position. V1 departed roadway left side striking a curb with its wheel. V1 continued onto the sidewalk where the front of V1 contacted the corner of a building before coming to rest on the sidewalk and against the building facing west.

Vehicle 1 was traveling southbound on a six lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 3 position.  Vehicle 2 was traveling westbound on four lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position.  Both vehicles entered a four way intersection at the same time.  The right plane of Vehicle 1 made contact with the front plane of Vehicle 2.  Vehicle 1 rotated counter clockwise and Vehicle 2 rotated clockwise.  The vehicles slapped together with the right rear plane of Vehicle 1 making contact with the left plane of Vehicle 2.  Both vehicles came to final rest facing southeast near the the south side of the intersection.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane undivided roadway. V2 was parked facing west on the right side of the road. When navigating a curve to its left, the front of V1 contacted the rear of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest near the point of impact on the roadway.
V1 was traveling north and turned westbound in lane one of a two lane, one-way roadway. V2 was parked westbound on the side of lane one of the same roadway. V1 front plane contacted V2 rear plane.

V1,V2, and V3 were all traveling south in lane three on a six lane divided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 had stopped in the roadway due to traffic ahead that was stopped at a traffic signal. V1's front plane then contacted V2's rear plane. After impact, V1 then rolled backwards and it's back plane struck the front plane of V3, which had come to a stop for the traffic ahead. All three vehicles came to final rest in lane three facing south on the roadway.

V1 was traveling southeast in lane one of a two lane, two way, non-divided roadway, and had come to an intersection of a four lane roadway. V2 was traveling south, in lane three on a four lane, non-positively divided, roadway. As V1 entered the intersection, V1's left plane contacted V2's front plane. V1 came to final rest with its front plane off of the roadway and its rear plane in lane 3 of the roadway. V2 came to final rest in lane three of the roadway.

V1 and V2 were traveling north on a two way, two lane undivided roadway. V1 was behind V2. V2 began slowing for a non contact vehicle that was attempting to turn left into a private driveway. The frontal plane of V1 made contact with the rear plane of V2. V1 and V2 came to final rest on the roadway facing north.

V1 was traveling east in lane two of a four-lane undivided road. V2 was traveling west in lane two of the westbound lanes of the same straight road. V1 swerved to the left in order to avoid hitting an animal crossing it's lane of travel. V1 entered the oncoming lanes of traffic. V1 steered to the right in order to get back into its original lane of travel. V2 swerved to the left in order to avoid impacting V1. The front of V1 impacted the front of V2. Both vehicles rotated clockwise. V1 came to rest in the westbound lanes facing southeast. V2 came to rest within the westbound lanes facing north west.

V1 was stopped at a red light in lane three of a five lane one-way service road of a highway, facing east. V2 was ahead of V1. V2 started to move but came to a complete stop after a short distance. V1 started to accelerate as well and impacted the back of V2 with its front. Both vehicles came to final rest in lane three facing east.

V1 was parked on the east side of lane one of a two lane, two-way, not physically divided roadway. V2 was parked in front of V1 on the east side of lane one of a two lane, two-way, not physically divided roadway. V3 was traveling northbound in lane one of a two lane, two-way, not physically divided roadway. V3 right plane side swiped V1 left plane. V3 continued traveling forward. V3 right plane side swiped V2 left plane.

V1 was west bound on a two lane non divided bidirectional roadway. A deer entered the V1's travel path from the left. V1 departed the roadway to the right, where it struck a small tree with its right plane. V1 traveled through thick brush, impacting the brush with its frontal plane and its left plane. V1 continued down a small culvert, where it impacted two large boulders with its undercarriage.  V1 crossed the culvert where its frontal plane impacted the rock embankment. An unknown object impacted the back plane of V1. V1 came to final rest in the culvert.

V1 was traveling north on a two-way, two lane roadway with a curve to the left. V1 departed the roadway to the right, impacting a mailbox with its front end. V1 continued forward off of the road and the front of V1 impacted a tree. V1 rotated clockwise and came to rest facing northeast.

V1 was traveling southwest following a two-way, two lane road in right lane. V1 swerved right to avoid a deer in the roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right impacting a culvert with its frontal plane. V1 came to final rest on the side of the road, in a ditch, facing southwest.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V2 was traveling east on the same road way. V2 crossed the left lane line, the frontal plane of V2 contacted the left plane of V1. V2 continued on contacting a guardrail with its left plane. Both V1 and V2 came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V2 was traveling west on the same roadway. V1 began to rotate counter-clockwise, departed its lane to the left and the front plane of V1 struck the front plane of V2. V2 rotated clockwise, departed its right road edge where its right side contacted a guardrail face. V1 rotated counter-clockwise, departed its right road edge where its right side contacted a guardrail face. V1 came to rest straddling the eastbound fogline facing north. V2 came to rest on the shoulder of the westbound lane facing west.

V1 and V2 were both traveling eastbound on a 2 lane, non divided roadway. V2 had slowed for a vehicle turning. V1 continued forward. V1's front contacted V2's back plane. Both vehicles came to rest on the roadway, facing east.

V1 was traveling north in Lane 1, of a 4 lane divided highway and approaching an off ramp. V2 was on the same roadway, in Lane 2. V1 was exiting highway to the right and then swerved left. V1 then crossed all lanes to the left while slightly yawing clockwise. V1's front contacted a concrete barrier. V1 then rotated clockwise contacting the concrete barrier again with its left rear. V1 reentered the roadway and traveled across 3 lanes where the right side then contacted V2's left side. Both vehicles came to rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling  west on a five lane, two-way, undivided roadway, in lane two.  V1 traveled off road to the right where the front of V1 struck a pole and came to rest, partially off the roadway, facing northwest.

V1 was traveling south on a two-lane, non-divided roadway. The frontal plane of V1 impacted a deer that was crossing the roadway from east to west. V1 came to rest south of the point of impact facing south on the road edge.

V1 was traveling north on a five lane, undivided, two-way roadway, in lane three, turning left at an intersection. V2 was traveling south, in lane one, on the same roadway, passing through the intersection. V3 was stopped, facing east, in lane one of the intersecting roadway. The front of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V2's right front then contacted the front of V3. V1 came to rest within the intersection, facing southwest. V2 and V3 came to rest in the roadway just south of their impact.

V1 was traveling east on a two-lane, undivided  roadway. V2 was traveling west on the same two-lane, undivided roadway. V1 departed its initial lane of travel and entered the eastbound travel lane. The right side of V1 was impacted by the front of V2. Both vehicles rotated counterclockwise as the right side of V1 engaged the left side of V2 in a sideslap type impact. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane two way undivided roadway. V2 was traveling west on the same two lane two way undivided roadway. V1 departed their initial lane of travel to the left. The front of V1 contacted the front of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway approaching an intersection with another two lane, two way, undivided roadway. Vehicle 1 traveled through the intersection and departed the roadway contacting a tree with its frontal plane. After contact Vehicle 1 rotated counter clockwise and contacted a tree with its right side plane. Vehicle 1 came to rest off of the roadway.

Vehicle 2 was traveling westbound in lane 3 of a 3 lane median divided roadway attempting to turn left at an intersection. Vehicle 1 was traveling eastbound in lane 3 of same roadway attempting to crossover the same intersection. The front of V1 contacted the right side of V2, both vehicles came to rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling westbound on a two-way, five-lane roadway in lane two. At the time of the crash the roadway was covered in snow. V1 lost control and departed its lane to the left, V1 then returns to its lane on the left and continued to travel through lane one before departing the roadway to the right. The left plane of V1 contacted a utility pole causing V1 to rollover 4 quarter turns right side leading. During the rollover the top plane contacted a mailbox. V1 came to final rest off the roadway in a parking lot on its wheels facing north.

Vehicle #1 was traveling west in lane one of a two-lane, undivided roadway. Vehicle #2 was legally parked facing west on the north side of the same road. V1 departed the roadway to the right and the front of V1 contacted the back of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest close to the point of impact facing west.

Vehicle #1 was traveling east in lane one of a divided trafficway without a positive barrier.  V1 lost control and departed the road to the right.  The front of V1 contacted a tree.  V1 came to rest off the road to the right, facing southeast, partially in a pond.

Vehicles #1 and #2 were traveling south on a two-way, two-lane road. The front plane of V1 contacted the back of V2's trailer. V2 rotated clockwise as its trailer rotated counter-clockwise. V2 departed the road to the right, and the front plane of V2 contacted a tree. V2's trailer "whipped" around in a jackknife motion. V2 came to rest off-road to the west. V1 came to rest on the right shoulder.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a 2 lane non divided roadway. V2 was traveling on the same roadway, westbound. V1 traveled to its left into the westbound travel lane to avoid stopped vehicles in the eastbound travel lane. The front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V1 then rotated counterclockwise and came to rest facing west on the north roadside. V2 came to rest facing west on the north roadside west of the impact area.

V1 and V2 were traveling southbound in lane one on a two way, two lane undivided roadway. V1 a working police vehicle changed lanes to the left. V2 initiated a left turn into a private driveway and the frontal plane of V1 made contact with the left side plane of V2. V1 continued forward leaving the left side of the roadway and down a steep embankment where V1 began to roll left side leading, overturning seven quarter turns. V1 during the roll sequence impacted two utility poles with its right side plane and then came to final rest off the roadway. V2 continued forward and came to a final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling north on a five lane, undivided roadway in lane one negotiating a curve to the left. V1 departed the roadway to the right and struck a curb with its right front tire. The front of V1 then struck a guardrail with its front and the curb with the right rear tire. V1 maintained contact with the guardrail and began to rotate counter-clockwise and onto its right side while traveling down the guardrail. V1 then rolled one quarter turn to the right and the top of V1 near the backlight header struck a wooden utility pole. V1 rotated clockwise, around the pole, and began to roll onto its top. V1 then struck a fence and a green utility box while rolling over. V1 continued across a private driveway, coming to final rest on its wheels, facing south where it backed into a grouping of trees where it came to rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling south in the third lane of a five-lane roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north in the second lane on the same roadway. At the intersection V1 turned to its left and the front of V2 impacted the right of V1. After impact V1 rotated clockwise and V2 moved forward and clockwise and the right side of V1 contacted the right side of V2. V1 came to rest facing south in the intersection. V2 came to rest facing north in the intersection.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two-way, undivided roadway passing through a four-way intersection. V2 was traveling west on an intersecting two lane, two-way, undivided roadway also passing through the same intersection. The front of V1 contacted the left plane of V2.  V1 rotated and continued north.  The back plane contacted the left plane of V3 which was parked on the east curb facing north. V1 came to final rest facing south in the roadway. After the initial impact V2 rotated counter-clockwise and departed the northwest corner of the roadway. The right rear wheel struck the concrete curb.  The front of V2 contacted a stop sign post and wooden fence.  V2 came to final rest facing north off the road.

V1 was travelling south on a 5 lane 2 way not physically divided roadway. V2 was travelling east on a 5 lane 2 way not physically divided roadway. V1 and V2 entered the intersection and the front plane of V2 struck the right plane of V2. V1 and V2 came to rest facing southwest.

Vehicle #1 was traveling north approaching an intersection on a three-lane, two-way road, in lane two. Vehicle #2 was traveling east on an intersecting two-lane, two-way road. Both vehicles entered the intersection, and V1 began to turn left. The front plane of V2 contacted the left plane of V1. Both vehicles came to rest on the road.

Vehicle #1 and Vehicle #2 were traveling eastbound in lane one of a two-lane undivided roadway.  V2 began to slow to turn into a parking lot and the front of V1 contacted the back of V2.  Both vehicles came to rest near impact, facing east.
Vehicle #1 was traveling north in lane one of a two-lane, undivided roadway.  The front of V1 contacted an animal.  V1 came to rest near impact, facing north.

V1 was traveling south on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway. V1 swerved left to avoid two deer entering the roadway from the eastern shoulder. V1 departed the left hand lane line and then the left (east) side of the roadway. V1 then reentered the roadway, reentered their initial travel lane, and then departed the right hand (west) side of the roadway. V1 contacted a utility pole cable support with its frontal plane. V1 continued forward a short distance contacting another utility support pole cable, an embankment, and an unknown object with its frontal plane. V1 then contacted a utility pole with its left side plane before coming to final rest off of the roadway.

V1 was traveling west on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a left hand curve in the roadway. V1 departed the right (north) side of the roadway contacting a stop sign pole with its frontal plane. V1 then continued forward and contacted a utility pole with its frontal plane, a small pole with its frontal plane, and another small pole with its left side plane. V1 then proceeded forward a short distance before contacting a guardrail face with its frontal plane. V1 continued along the face of the guardrail before reentering the roadway for a short distance. V1 then partially exited the right side of the roadway a second time where it came to final rest partially off of the roadway.

Vehicle #1 was traveling north on a two-lane, two-way road. A pile of dirt was in the middle of a driveway to the right, lapping over into the travel lanes. The front plane of V1 contacted the pile of dirt. V1 departed the road to the right, and the right plane of V1 contacted a utility pole. The front plane of V1 contacted a guy cable attached to the pole. V1 came to rest off the road to the east.

V1 was traveling south in the #3 lane of a 5 lane divided roadway. V2, V4, and V5 were all stopped facing north in the #3 lane of a 5 lane divided roadway. V3 was stopped facing north in the #2 lane of a 5 lane divided roadway. V1 traveled through an intersection and departed its lane to the left. The front of V1 impacted the front of V2. V2 was pushed back and the back of V2 impacted the front of V4. V1 traveled into the #2 lane where the front of V1 impacted the front of V3. V4 was pushed back and the back of V4 impacted the front of V5. V1 came to rest between the #2 and #3 lanes facing south east. V2 came to rest between the #2 lane and #3 lane facing north. V3 came to rest in the #2 lane facing north. V4 came to rest in the #3 lane facing north. V5 came to rest in the #3 lane facing north.

V1 was traveling south on a two-lane, two-way road in front of a department store. V1 turned left to enter a parking aisle when it departed the left side of the road. The front of V1 impacted a sign pole. V1 came to rest at the point of impact.

V1 was traveling northeast on a two-lane undivided roadway. V2 was stopped facing northwest on a four-lane intersecting roadway. V1 began to turn right. The front of V1 contacted the left of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest near the point of impact.

V1 was traveling northeast on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a left hand curve in the roadway. V1 departed the right hand (south) side of the roadway contacting a cable barrier guardrail with its frontal and right side planes. V1 continued forward striking a pole with its frontal plane before continuing off of the roadway driving across a private driveway. V1 entered into a private lawn before striking an embankment with its frontal plane. V1 came to final rest off of the roadway.

V2 was traveling east on a two lane, two way road following a non-involved vehicle. V1 was traveling east on the same road behind V2. V2 was slowing down as the non-involved vehicle was slowing to make a right turn. The front of V1 struck the rear of V2. V1 came to rest near the point of impact heading east. V2 came to rest in the westbound lane heading northeast.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a two lane, two way roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south also on a two lane, two way roadway approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection at the same time and the front of V2 contacted the right side of V1. V2 then rotated clockwise and V1 rotated counter-clockwise causing the right side of V1 to contact the left side of V2 before coming to rest. Both vehicles came to rest facing southwest in the intersection.
V1 was traveling north on a two lane, one way highway. A bird crossed the path of V1 and contacted the windshield. V1 came to final rest on the the highway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a two lane two way dirt road. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway on the right side, while engaged in a clockwise rotation. The front plane then contacted a tree. Vehicle 1 then overturned (left side leading) four-quarter turns in a ditch. Vehicle 1 came to final rest off of the roadway facing west.

V1 and V2 were both traveling southeast on a two lane, two way, non divided roadway. V2 then came to a stop and began to back up into a driveway when V1's front plane contacted V2's left side plane. As a result of this contact, V2 rotated clockwise and departed the roadway to the right into a ditch. The vehicle's front plane then contacted a fence post before coming to final rest off of the roadway. V1 came to final rest in the roadway, in lane one.

V1 was traveling west in lane one on a two lane, positively divided, roadway. As the vehicle negotiated a slight left curve in the roadway, V1 departed the roadway to the right side and contacted a sign pole with its front plane. As a result of this contact, the pole was sheared off and it contacted the front hood of V1 and then intruded into the right side windshield. The vehicle continued traveling forward and contacted the end of a guardrail with its front plane. The vehicle then traveled approximately 22 meters down the length of the guardrail and contacted 6 guardrail posts with the vehicles front plane. The right side of V1, then contacted the guardrail face. V1 rotated clockwise and came to final rest on the right side of the roadway.
