V1 was traveling north in lane two of a two lane, two way, grass median divided roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the left. V1 returned to the roadway, and began a counter clockwise yaw. V1 rolled to the right four quarter turns and came to final rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling southbound in the first lane on a two lane, two way undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling westbound in the first lane on a three lane divided roadway approaching the same intersection. At the intersection V1 attempted to turn left and the front of V1 impacted the right side of V2. V2 rotated clockwise and departed the roadway to the left into the center median. V2 then rolled over 4 quarter turns, left side leading, coming to rest on it's wheels facing north. V1 came to rest in the intersection facing south.

V1 and V2 were traveling northbound on a two lane positively divided highway. V1 was traveling in lane two, V2 was in lane one. V1 changed lanes to the right, the front of V1 impacted the back of V2. Both vehicle's came to rest on the right shoulder facing north.

V1 was eastbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 departed the south side of the road impacting a utility pole with its frontal plane causing damage. V1 then continued eastward coming to final rest in a private drive facing east.

V1 was westbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway following behind V2. V2 attempted to make a left turn. The front plane of V1 struck the rear plane of V2 causing damage. V1 came to final rest in the eastbound lane facing south as V2 came to final rest in a driveway on the southside of the road facing south.

V1 was traveling north on a two-way, not physically divided trafficway in lane two (of five lanes). V2 was traveling east to south (making a right turn) from a driveway and was in lane 2 (of two lanes). V1 crossed all travel lanes and departed the roadway on the left where its left front wheel/tire contacted a curb (Event 1). V1 continued traveling in a northerly direction on the sidewalk, where its front end contacted two separate shrubs (Events 2 and 3), and its left front tire contacted a curb (Event 4). V1 then crossed a driveway, and its front end contacted the right side of V2 (Event 5). V2 was pushed in a northerly direction, where its left side contacted a curb and then a wall (Events 6 and 7). V1 rotated counter-clockwise and its right side contacted a sign (Event 8). V1 also struck a building with its front before it came to rest on its wheels facing a southerly direction in lane 4. V2 came to rest on its wheels facing a northeasterly direction in the driveway.

V1 was traveling west on a divided trafficway (median strip with positive barrier) in lane 3 (of four lanes) when it departed the road on the right. The front end of V1 contacted two separate trees. V1 came to rest on its wheels facing a northwesterly direction on the roadside.

Vehicle #1 was traveling east in lane one of a two-lane, undivided roadway, negotiating a right curve.  V1 departed the road to the left and the front of V1 contacted a tree.  V1 came to rest near impact.

V1 was eastbound on a two lane divided highway when a deer entered the roadway. The front end of V1 struck the deer and the deer landed on top of the windshield. V1 came to final rest on the right side shoulder facing east.

V1 was stopped facing eastbound in the number 4 lane of a 4 lane divided roadway, preparing to turn left at an intersection. V2 was traveling westbound in the number 3 lane of a 5 lane divided roadway, approaching an intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection. The front of V1 impacted the front of V2. V1 rotated counter-clockwise and came to rest facing northerly in the intersection. V2 continued forward and to the right and came to rest facing northwesterly in the intersection.

V1 was traveling eastbound in the number 3 lane of a 5 lane undivided roadway, in the two-way left turn lane preparing to turn left. V2 was traveling eastbound in the number 1 lane of a 5 lane undivided roadway, approaching an intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection. The front of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V2 rotated counter-clockwise and came to rest facing east in the number 1 westbound lane. V1 came to rest facing northerly to the east of the intersection.
Vehicle #1 was traveling northwest in lane one of a two-lane divided roadway without a positive barrier.  The front of V1 contacted an animal.  V1 came to rest near impact, still facing northwest.

V1 was traveling in a south western direction on a two lane, bidirectional roadway. V1 was negotiating a slight curve to the left, with a positive grade, when it departed the roadway to the right. V1's frontal plane impacted two trees. The vehicle then impacted a third tree with its frontal plane causing it to sheer off, and impact the top and the right plane of V1. V1 then impacted a fourth tree with its frontal plane, and rotated clockwise, where its left plane impacted a warning sign. V1 impacted an unknown object with its left plane and an unknown object with its right plane, before coming to final rest on the right side of the roadway, partially obstructing the initial lane of travel.

V1 was heading east on a four lane physically divided interstate in lane two. V1 departed is initial lane of travel to the left twice. V1 departed the roadway to the left. The front of V1 contacted the concrete jersey barrier.  V1 was redirected to the right and the left plane of V1 impacted the concrete jersey barrier.  V1 reentered the roadway. V1 crossed three lanes. V1 came to final rest facing generally east in lane one.

V1 was traveling south on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway approaching an intersection with a stop sign. V2 was traveling east in lane two on a median divided roadway, with four lanes in the same direction, approaching the same intersection V1. Both vehicles entered the intersection and the right side plane of V1 was contacted by the front plane of V2. Both V1 and V2 continued forward rotating in a counter clockwise direction and came to final rest off of the southeast side of the roadway.

V1 was traveling northbound on a two way, two lane undivided roadway, approaching an intersection with a stop sign. V2 was traveling westbound, on a median divided roadway, with two lanes in the same direction, approaching the same intersection as V1. Both vehicles entered the intersection. The frontal plane of V1 contacted the left side plane of V2. V1 continued forward in a counter clockwise direction and came to final rest on the shoulder on the south side of the westbound roadway. V2 continued forward rotating in a slight clockwise direction and came to a final rest off of the northwest side of the roadway.

V1 and V2 were traveling east in lane 2 on a 2- lane divided roadway with a grass median. V2 braked for an animal in the roadway and the front plane of V1 contacted the back plane of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest forward of impact, in lane two, still facing east.

V1 was traveling east on a 2-lane roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north on a 2-lane roadway approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection and the right side of V1 was contacted by the front of V2. V1 rotated counter-clockwise as V2 rotated clockwise and the right side of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V1 departed the northeast corner of the intersection and came to rest in a grass yard facing northeast. V2 came to rest on the roadway facing northeast.

V1 was traveling north in the #1 lane of a 2 lane undivided roadway. V2 was traveling south in the #1 lane of a 3 lane undivided section of the roadway. V1 departed their lane to the left and was traveling north in the southbound lane. V2 steered left to avoid the collision with V1. V1 steered right back into the northbound lane. V1 continued right and departed the roadway to the right. The front of V1 impacted a light pole. V1 continued forward and began rotating counter clockwise. V1 began to roll over through a ditch. V1 exited the ditch while rolling over and the right side of V1 impacted a gate. V1 continued north and landed on a barbed wire fence on its roof facing west where it came to rest. V2 after steering left departed the roadway to the left. The front of V2 impacted a reflector. V2 then rolled over into a ditch. An unknown part of V2 impacted a sign post. V2 came to rest on its roof at the bottom of the ditch facing south.

V1 and V2 were traveling east on four lane, divided roadway without a positive barrier. V2 stopped at an intersection, and the front of V1 contacted the back of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 and V2 were both traveling northbound on a two lane, divided roadway in lane two. V2 was traveling ahead of V1. V2 slowed for traffic ahead and the front of V1 impacted the back of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in lane two facing northbound.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a 3 lane, two-way, median divided roadway in lane number 1. Vehicle 2 was traveling south on the same roadway in lane number 1 slowing in traffic. Vehicle 3 was traveling south, in lane number 1 stopped in traffic. Vehicle 1's front made contact with vehicle 2's rear end. The initial impact, caused vehicle 2 to  be pushed forward into the back of vehicle 3. All vehicle's came to final rest in there original lanes.

V1 was traveling north following a two-way, two lane road with slight curve to the left. V1 was approaching a four way intersection. V2 was traveling east on a two-way, two lane road, approaching the same four way intersection. The front of V1 impacted the right side of V2 in the middle of the mentioned intersection. V1 came to final in the roadway, facing northwest. V2 came to final rest near impact, in the roadway, facing east.

V1 and V2 were both traveling south in lane one of a four lane divided trafficway approaching an intersection. V2 was ahead of V1 attempting to make a right turn at the intersection. V1's front plane contacted V2's rear plane. V1 came to rest in the roadway. V2 departed the roadway to the right and the front plane contacted a stop sign. V2 continued off road and the front plane contacted a culvert. V2 came to rest off the roadway against the culvert.

V1 was traveling east in lane one of a two-lane undivided roadway. V1 was turning left at a T-intersection. V2 was traveling northeast in lane one of a two-lane undivided roadway, approaching the same intersection. V1's right plane contacted V2's left plane. V2 then departed the roadway to the right. V2 then fell into a ditch, causing the vehicle to rotate counterclockwise and roll to the right. V2's right plane contacted the ground and then it came to rest back on to it's wheels in the ditch. V1 came to final rest in the roadway near impact.

V1 was traveling south in lane one of a two-lane undivided roadway, negotiating a left curve. V1 departed the roadway to the right. V1 tripped right side leading while off the roadway and completed two quarter turns. V1 came to final rest on its roof in a ditch.

V1 was traveling west exiting a private drive attempting a left turn. V2 was traveling northeast in lane two of a five lane roadway negotiating a right curve. V1's left plane was contacted by V2's front plane. Both vehicles came to rest near impact in the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling in the first of four southbound lanes, on a positively divided roadway. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway to the right and contacted a guard rail with its frontal plane. Vehicle 1 then reentered the roadway and crossed all four southbound travel lanes and departed the roadway on the the left contacted a concrete barrier with its frontal plane and came to rest on the shoulder of the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling southbound on a two lane undivided roadway approaching the intersection with another two lane undivided roadway. Vehicle 1 entered the intersection and experienced an end-departure, leaving the roadway, passed through a ditch, impacted the ground, and struck a tree with its frontal plane. Vehicle 1 came to rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling east in an unknown lane on a 2-lane divided roadway negotiating a left curve. V1 departed the roadway on the right side where the front plane struck a utility pole. After contact with the utility pole V1 rotated clockwise then tripped and rolled 8 quarter turns on the roadside and came to rest on its wheels facing west. The driver was ejected during the rollover sequence.

Vehicle 1 was traveling northeast on a one-lane, divided roadway. Vehicle 2 was also traveling northeast and was ahead of Vehicle 1 and stopped in traffic. Vehicle 3 was traveling behind Vehicle 1 and decelerating on the same roadway in lane one. The front of Vehicle 3 impacted the rear plane of Vehicle 1 (Event 1) and the front of Vehicle 1 subsequently impacted the rear of Vehicle 2 (Event 2). All three vehicles came to final rest in lane 1 and facing northeast.

V1 was traveling northwest on a two way, two lane undivided roadway negotiating a slight left hand curve in the roadway. A deer entered the roadway from the left hand side of the roadway. V1 contacted the deer with its frontal plane and then its right side plane. V1 came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling east on a two way, two lane undivided roadway. V1 began to lose control and departed the left hand lane line; V1 then proceeded to depart the left hand (north) side of the roadway. V1 contacted an embankment with its frontal plane. V1 then proceeded forward a short distance contacting the embankment a second time with its frontal plane. V1 then began to leave the embankment over a private driveway contacting a culvert pipe and some rocks with its frontal plane. V1 exited the embankment and went airborne a short distance before contacting a second embankment with its undercarriage. V1 came to final rest off of the roadway.

V1 and V2 were both traveling east in lane two of a two-lane divided road, approaching a three way intersection. V2 was stopped ahead of V1 at the intersection when the front of V1 impacted the back of V2. V1 continued forward as a hit and run vehicle. V2 came to final rest near impact, on the roadway, facing east.

V1 and V2 were heading east on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 crossed the left lane line and stopped to get the mail. V1 then turned right crossing both lane lines. V1 crossed paths with V2. The frontal plane of V2 contacted the right plane of V1. Both vehicles came to rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling south in lane three of a four lane divided (no positive barrier) roadway, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling west in lane two of a two lane service road, approaching the same intersection. Within the intersection, the front of V2 impacted with the left side of V1. V1 rotated clockwise and came to rest within the intersection, facing southwest. V2 rotated counter clockwise and came to rest within the intersection, facing southwest.

V1 was northbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 departed the left side of its travel lane, then departed the left side of the roadway. V1 impacted a pole with its frontal plane causing damage. V1 came to final rest at the point of impact after rotating counter clockwise facing north west.

Vehicle 1 was traveling eastbound on a two lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position.  Vehicle 1 departed the roadway on the north side coming to final rest in a ditch facing northeast.

Vehicles #1 and #2 were traveling southeast in lane one of a two-lane, divided roadway without a positive barrier.  V1 was behind V2.  V2 stopped.  V1 began to rotate clockwise and the left of V1 contacted the back of V2.  Both vehicles came to rest near impact, V1 facing southwest and V2 facing southeast.

V1 was traveling north in the first of five lanes on an undivided, two-way roadway. V2 was traveling north in the second lane on the same roadway. V1 attempted to make a u-turn and departed the lane on the left side. The left side of V1 contacted the front of V2.

V1 was traveling east in the third of four lanes on a positively-divided, two-way freeway. V1 began to travel to the right, causing the driver to over-correct to the left until the front of V1 struck the middle concrete traffic barrier. V1 contacted the concrete barrier a second time with the left side. V1 came to rest off the roadway.

V1 and V2 were traveling southwest in lane three on a four lane, positively divided roadway. V2 decelerated quickly and steered left due to other stopped traffic ahead, and departed the roadway, to the left, where its front plane contacted a guardrail. After that event, V1's front plane contacted V2's back plane.V1 came to final rest in lane three a short distance from the initial contact. V2 came to final rest with its front plane off of the roadway left and its back plane in lane four.

V1 and a Non-Contact Vehicle (NCV) were both traveling northeast on a two lane, positively divided roadway. The NCV was in lane two and V1 was in lane one. V1 then traveled down into and along a ditch line for approximately 175 meters before its front plane contacted a tree. After this contact, V1 continued traveling forward and contacted a second and third tree with its front plane. After the third impact, V1's left side entered the concrete ditch. This caused the vehicle to roll over 1/4 turn onto its left side plane, where the vehicle came to final rest.

V1 was traveling west in lane one of a two-way, three lane roadway, approaching an intersection.  V2 was traveling south in lane two on a three lane, two-way median divided roadway, approaching the same intersection.  V3 was traveling south in lane one of a three lane, two-way roadway median divided roadway.  Upon entering the intersection, the front plane of V1 made contact with the left plane of V2.  After the initial impact, the right plane of V2 made contact with the left plane of V3.  V1 came to final rest in the roadway facing north east. V2 and V3 came to rest on the roadway, facing north east.

V1 was traveling in lane two, northeast bound, on a four-lane undivided roadway and approaching intersection. V2 was traveling in lane two, southeast bound, on a five-lane undivided roadway and also approaching intersection. V1 stopped at the stop sign and then proceeded into intersection. Within the intersection, V1's left side was impacted by the frontal plane of V2. Both vehicles then contacted again, V1's left side to V2's right side. V1 came to rest on the roadway. V2 traveled off of the roadway. V2's front then contacted a shrub. V2 then came to final rest off of the roadway.

V1 and V2 were both traveling in Lane 3, north bound, of a 3 lane physically divided roadway. V2 slowed for traffic and V1's front contacted V2's back plane. Both vehicles came to rest on the roadway.
Vehicle #1 was traveling north in lane one of a two-lane roadway.  The front of V1 contacted an animal.  V1 came to rest on the right shoulder, facing north.
Vehicle #1 was traveling east in lane one of a two-lane, undivided roadway.  The front of V1 contacted an animal.  V1 came to rest near impact, still facing east.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two way undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling west, on a one way roadway, approaching the same intersection. In the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 and V2 were traveling on the same three lane two way without a positively divided roadway, with V1 in the middle lane and V2 in the right lane. V1 attempted a right hand turn in front of V2. The right side of V1 contacted the front of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling eastbound on a two lane non-physically divided roadway.  Vehicle 2 was traveling northbound on a 5 lane physically divided trafficway in the lane 1 position.  Both Vehicles 1 and 2 entered the intersection.  The right plane of Vehicle 1 made contact with the front plane of Vehicle 2.  Vehicle 1 was pushed through the intersection coming to final rest facing south east.  Vehicle 2 traveled through the intersection coming to final rest facing northwest.

V1 was traveling southbound on a 2 lane roadway while negotiating a curve to the left. V1 departed the roadway to the right. V1's right side contacted a fence. V1's front then contacted a fence. Finally V1's back plane contacted and unknown object. V1 came to rest off of the roadway.

Vehicle #1 was traveling southeast in lane two of a two-lane, divided roadway without a positive barrier.  Vehicle #2 was stopped facing southeast in the same lane at a traffic signal.  V2 started forward from the signal. The front of V1 contacted the back of V2's trailer.  Both vehicles came to rest near impact.

V1 was south bound on a two lane, non-divided bidirectional roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right, where it traveled up an embankment, and rolled onto its left side. V1 came to final rest on its left side on the roadway.

V1 was traveling east in lane 1 on a two lane, two way roadway and was turning left at an intersection to travel north on a three lane roadway. V2 was traveling south in lane 2 of a three lane, two way, non-divided roadway and was approaching an intersection. At the intersection, V1's left side plane contacted V2's front plane. After impact, V1 rotated in a clockwise direction and came to final rest partially in the roadway, facing south, approximately 13 meters from the initial contact. V2 rotated in a counter clockwise direction and traveled approximately 81 meters past the initial contact. The vehicle then came to final rest, facing south, with its right side tires in lane one on the three lane roadway.

V1 was traveling northbound in lane one of a two lane, two way undivided roadway.  V1 departed the roadway to the right and struck a large rock (event 1) with the front plane.  V1 then returned to the roadway and departed the roadway to the left where the front plane contacted a tree.

V1 was traveling north on a 2-lane roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling west on a 2-lane roadway approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection and the right side of V1 was contacted by the front of V2. V1 rotated counter-clockwise, departed the westbound edge of roadway then returned to the roadway and traveled across the westbound and eastbound lanes where it departed the eastbound road edge and contacted a street sign post. V1 came to rest on its original roadway facing southeast. V2 came to rest on the roadway facing west.

V1 was traveling northbound on a three lane, divided roadway approaching an intersection in lane one. V2 was traveling northbound on a two lane, undivided (two way traffic) roadway in lane one. At the intersection V1 attempted to turn right, V2 continued straight. The front of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V1 rotated counter clockwise and came to rest in the intersection facing north. V2 rotated counter clockwise and came to rest in lane two north of the intersection facing south.

V1 and V2 were both traveling south on a two lane, divided roadway in lane one. V2 was traveling ahead of V1. The front of V1 impacted the back of the trailer of V2. V1 came to rest in lane one facing south. V2 came to rest on the right shoulder after impact facing south.

V1 was traveling west in lane 2 on a one-way, two lane road . V1 departed  the roadway to the left and its front plane contacted a guardrail face. V1 continued forward off of the road where its front plane contacted a large boulder and came to rest. V1 then experienced a major fire.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway following V2. V2 slowed to make a right hand turn. The frontal plane of V1 contacted the rear plane of V2. Both Vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two way undivided roadway. V1 crossed the left lane line and began in a clockwise rotation. V1 re-entered the original travel lane and crossed the right lane line. V1 departed the right road edge and the left front tire contacted a curb. V1 continued yawing left side leading and the front of V1 contacted a stop sign. V1 continued to yaw left side leading and rolled one quarter turn to the left. The left side of V1 contacted and sign and V1 came to final rest off the roadway on its left side facing south.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a two-lane not physically divided two-way road, approaching a four-leg intersection controlled by a red flashing traffic signal. Vehicle 2 was traveling east on a two-lane not physically divided two-way road, approaching the same four-leg intersection controlled by a yellow flashing traffic signal. Upon entering the intersection the front plane of vehicle 2 contacted the right plane of vehicle 1. After impact vehicle 1 rotated clockwise and the back plane of vehicle 1 contacted a guardrail face. Vehicle 1 came to final rest on the edge of the roadway. Vehicle 2 came to final rest within the intersection on the roadway.

Vehicle #1 was traveling north on a two-lane divided roadway in lane 2, approaching a T-intersection. Vehicle #1 was traveling north on the same roadway in lane 1. V2 came to a stop in traffic. V1 changed lanes to the right. The right plane of V1 contacted the left plane of V2.

V1 was traveling east on a divided trafficway (median strip with positive barrier) in lane one (of three lanes) when it departed the road on the right and its right front wheel/tire contacted a curb, followed by its front end contacting a paddle marker and a chain link fence. V1 then rotated clockwise and its left side contacted the same fence. V1 came to rest on its wheels facing a southeasterly direction on the roadside.

V1 was traveling east (wrong way) on a divided trafficway (median strip with positive barrier) in lane 4 (of four lanes) and was approaching V2, which was traveling west on the same roadway, and in the same lane.  In lane 4, the front end of V1 came in contact with the front end of V2.  V1 and V2 rotated clockwise.  V1 came to rest on its wheels, facing a westerly direction in lane 4, and east of V2.  V2 came to rest on its wheels, facing a northeasterly direction in the median shoulder, and west of V1.

V1 was traveling in a southeasterly direction on a designated north/south, two-way, not physically divided trafficway, in lane 1 (of two lanes), and was approaching V2, which was traveling in the opposite direction, on the same roadway, in lane 1 (of two lanes).  V1 departed its lane on the left, and its front end came into contact with the front end of V2.  Both vehicles rotated counter-clockwise.  V1 came to rest on its wheels, facing a northerly direction in the roadway.  V2 came to rest on its wheels, facing a southerly direction on the roadside, and northeast of V1.

V1 was traveling south on a not physically divided trafficway with two-way left turn lane, in lane 2 (of five lanes), when it departed its lane on the left. V1 skidded longitudinally (with no rotation) in the two-way left turn lane, where its front end then came in contact with a reboundable traffic delineator (with sign), a curb, and a palm tree - all encompassed within a landscaped median strip. V1 came to rest on its wheels facing southerly in the landscaped median strip, with its front end against the palm tree.

Vehicle 1 was exiting a private drive attempting a right turn. Vehicle 2 was traveling west on a 6 lane two-way non physically divided roadway in lane 3. The left side of V1 was contacted by the front of V2. V1 rotated clockwise and came to rest in the westbound lanes facing southwest. V2 came to rest in its original lane facing west.

V1 was traveling east in lane one of a two-lane undivided roadway, negotiating a right curve. V2 was traveling northwest in lane one of the same two-lane undivided roadway. V1 departed its travel lane to the left and the front plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2. V1 continued to travel and departed the roadway to the left. V1's undercarriage contacted a ditch and then came to final rest off the roadway. V2 departed the roadway to the right and contacted a tree and came to final rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling northeast in lane one of a two lane roadway negotiating a left curve. V1 departed the right road edge and the front plane contacted a ditch. V1 then tripped and rolled two quarter turns coming to final rest on its top off the right road edge.

V1 was traveling southeast in lane one of a four lane divided roadway negotiating a left curve. V1 departed the right road and its front left plane contacted a tree, then its front right contacted another tree. V1 rotated clockwise and tripped and rolled right 1/4 turn, V1 then contacted a tree with its back plane before rolling left back onto its wheels.

V1 was in lane two of a three-lane undivided roadway, turning left. V1 departed its travel lane to the right, then departed the roadway to the right. V1's front plane contacted a small tree, then continued to travel forward off the roadway. V1's front plane then contacted another tree, where it came to final rest.

V1 was traveling northwest on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a left hand curve in the roadway. V1 departed the right (northeast) side of the roadway entering onto a cemetery property before striking an embankment with its frontal plane. V1 then continued forward and contacted a utility pole guy-wire with its frontal plane. V1 then proceeded forward a short distance before contacting a concrete and marble bench with its frontal plane. V1 continued forward striking numerous copper flower urns with its frontal plane. Continuing further through the cemetery, V1 struck a sign post with its front plane and then proceeded forward across the entrance driveway to the cemetery striking shrubbery with its front plane. V1 continued forward striking a concrete column with its front plane and came to final rest off of the roadway.

V1 was traveling northeast on a median divided roadway, with two lanes in the same direction, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling southwest, on the same median divided roadway as V1 approaching the same intersection as V1. V1 attempted a left hand turn at the intersection and the frontal plane of V1 made contact with left side plane of V2. V1 continued forward rotating in a slight counter clockwise direction and came to final rest on the roadway. V2 continued forward and departed the right (west) side of the roadway and began to rotate in a counter clockwise direction. V2 came to final rest off of the roadway facing east.

V1 was traveling west on a divided trafficway (median strip without positive barrier), in lane 2 (of three lanes), when it departed its lane on the right, and then the road on the right.  On the roadside, V1's front end came in contact with a flexible roadside guide post.  V1 continued in a westerly direction on the roadside, where it came in contact with / drove through a barbed wire fence (unknown plane).  Outside of the trafficway, V1 traveled through the air and descended into a ditch, where its front end contacted the ditch side.  V1 came to rest on its wheels, facing an easterly direction, in the open desert terrain, outside of the ditch.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane divided roadway in lane two behind V2. V2 began to slow due to traffic ahead and the front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. Both V1 and V2 came to rest in lane two facing south.

V1 was traveling northbound in lane two of a two-lane, divided roadway. V1 departed its lane to the right and continued off the roadway on the right side. The front of V1 impacted a barbed wire fence. V1 continued forward and the left wheel impacted a tree or stump. V1 continued forward and down into a ditch where the front of V1 impacted a ditch. V1 exited the ditch and became airborne and initiated a rollover sequence, leading with its right side. V1 completed four-quarter turns coming to rest on its wheels and facing southerly.

V1 and V2 were traveling south east in the #1 lane of a 2 lane undivided roadway. V3 was traveling North West in the #1 lane of a 2 lane undivided roadway. V2 slowed to a stop to make a turn. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2. V1 continued forward, rotated counter clockwise, and rolled over leading right. V2 continued forward while rotating counter clockwise departing the lane to the left. The front of V2 impacted the left side of V3. V1 came to rest on its driver side in the #1 lane facing northeast. V2 came to rest on the north shoulder facing east. V3 rotated counter clockwise and came to rest facing west off the roadway to the north.

V1 was traveling in an easterly direction on a divided trafficway (median strip with positive barrier), in lane 2 (of three lanes), when it's left rear tire suffered a rapid loss of air. Control over V1 was lost. V1 departed the road on the right, where it then passed through a barbed wire fence. V1 came to rest on its wheels, facing a southeasterly direction in the open desert terrain, outside of the trafficway.

V1 was traveling east on a divided trafficway (median strip with positive barrier), in lane 1 (of four lanes), and was approaching V2, which was legally parked on the right shoulder, facing east. V1 departed the roadway on the right, and its front end contacted the back end of V2. V1 came to rest on its wheels facing east in lane 1. V2 came to rest on its wheels facing east on the shoulder. V1 was then involved in a second, unrelated crash.

V1 was traveling eastbound in the first lane of a two lane, two-way roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling southbound in the first lane of a two lane, two-way roadway approaching the same intersection. Both V1 and V2 entered the intersection at the same time. The frontal plane of V1 impacted the right side plane of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway: V1 facing east and V2 facing southeast.

V1 was traveling west in the first of two lanes on an undivided, two-way road approaching a right curve. V2 was traveling south in the first lane on the same road as V1 approaching a left curve. While negotiating the curve, V1 departed its lane on the left side and the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in the road.

V1 was traveling westbound on a four-lane, two-way roadway, in lane two approaching a T-shaped intersection. V2 was traveling southbound on a two-lane, two-way roadway, in lane one. V2 was turning left at the T-intersection intending to head eastbound. The front of V1 contacted the left side of V2 in the middle of the intersection. V1 and V2 came to final rest at point of impact, V1 in the roadway facing north and V2 in the roadway facing south.

V1 was traveling east in lane two on a one-way, two lane, off ramp. V2 was traveling north in lane two on a three lane, non-positively divided roadway. At the intersection, V1's front plane contacted V2's left side plane. As a result of this impact, V2 began to rotate in a clockwise direction and its left side plane contacted V1's rear plane. As a result of this contact, V1 continued forward and its front plane contacted a traffic light pole. V1 came to final rest against the light pole, and V2 came to final rest in the intersection, facing south.

V1 was traveling north on a two-lane undivided road, negotiating a left curve, when a deer entered the roadway. V1 steered left and departed the west side of the road where it struck a large rock with its front end. V1 continued to strike an embankment and a small tree with its front end. V1 rolled right two quarter turns before coming to final rest on its top plane partially on the road. Its rear end was in the roadway and its front end was off the roadway.

V1 was traveling northbound, on a median divided roadway, with two lanes in the same direction. V1 lost control of the vehicle and departed the right hand side of the roadway impacting a ditch with its frontal plane. V1 continued forward rotating in a clockwise direction and contacted its left rear corner on the raised edge of an asphalt driveway. V1 continued forward while rotating and contacted a tree with it left side plane before coming to a final rest off of the roadway facing south.

Vehicle 1 was traveling westbound in the eastbound lane of a two lane undivided roadway, Vehicle 2 was traveling eastbound in the eastbound lane on the same roadway. Vehicle 2 departed its travel lane to avoid contact and entered into the oncoming westbound lane. Vehicle 1 contacted the frontal plane of Vehicle 2 with its frontal plane. Vehicle 2 came to rest in the travel lane of the roadway. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway to the left and contacted a tree with its frontal plane. Vehicle 1 continued traveling and contacted a second tree with its frontal plane. Vehicle 1 reentered the roadway and rolled right side leading for two quarter turns. Vehicle 1 came to final rest on the roadway on its top plane facing south in the westbound travel lane.

V1 was southbound on a two lane physically divided roadway when V1 departed the roadway to the left and the left side of V1 contacted a concrete traffic barrier portion of a bridge. V1 continued to travel and the front of V1 contacted a sign. V1 then departed the roadway to the left and came to rest in the median, off of the roadway.

V1 was eastbound on a 7 lane roadway approaching an intersection, turning left. V2 was westbound on a 7 lane roadway approaching the same intersection. V3 was stopped southbound on a 7 lane roadway at the same intersection. Within the intersection the right side of V1 contacted the front of V2. After impact, the rear of V1 contacted the front of V3. All vehicles came to rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling westbound on a three lane, two-way roadway in lane one directly behind V2. V2 was traveling westbound on a three lane, two-way roadway in lane one. V2 was stopped in traffic waiting for traffic signal to change. V1 front plane contacted V2 back plane. V1 and V2 came to final rest at point of impact on roadway.

V1 was traveling southbound on a two lane, two-way roadway. V2 was traveling westbound on a two lane, two-way roadway passing through a four-way intersection. V1 left plane contacted V2's front plane. After initial impact V1 rotated clockwise before coming to final rest facing west on roadway. After initial impact V2 departed the roadway on the left side, contacted the curb with it's wheels, contacted a utility pole, traffic sign, with it's left plane. V2 contacted a business sign before coming to final rest off roadway. V1 came to final rest on roadway facing west in the westbound lanes.

V1 and V2 were traveling westbound on a two-lane, two-way roadway. V1 was traveling behind V2. V2 was slowing to turn left at a T-shaped intersection to head northbound. V1 attempted to pass V2 to V2's left where the front plane of V1 contacted the left plane of V2. V2 came to final rest in the roadway facing north while V1 continued westbound after impact.

V1 and V2 were traveling westbound on a four-lane, two-way roadway. V1 was traveling in lane one, V2 in lane two. V2 was attempting a left turn into a shopping center entrance, when V1 changed lanes to the left and the front plane of V1 contacted the back plane of V2. V1 came to final rest at point of impact and V2 came to final rest in the eastbound lanes facing west.

V1 was traveling north on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south on the same roadway approaching the same intersection as V1. While in the intersection V1 attempted to make a left hand turn onto an intersecting roadway, the right plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2. V1 and V2 came to final rest partially off of the roadway in a private parking lot off of the southern edge of the intersection.

V1 was traveling south on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a right hand curve in the roadway. V1 began to rotate in a clockwise direction departing the left hand lane line, returning to the right hand lane, and then departing the right hand (west) side of the roadway. V1 then contacted a sign post with its left side plane. V1 continued to rotate contacting a cluster of trees with its frontal plane. V1 then contacted two more clusters of trees with an unknown plane before contacting a tree and a cluster of small trees with its left side plane. V1 then rolled one quarter turn on to its driver side before it's roll was interrupted. V1 contacted a cluster of trees and one larger tree that was partially uprooted with its left plane where it came to final rest against them off of the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling northbound on a two lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position.  Vehicle 2 was traveling westbound on a two lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position.  Both vehicles entered the uncontrolled intersection at the same time.  The right plane of Vehicle 1 made contact with the front plane of Vehicle 2.  Vehicle 1 began rotating in a clockwise rotation turning onto its left side plane where it came to final rest just north of the intersection facing northeast.  Vehicle 2 came to final rest just after impact in the intersection facing west.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a 3 lane, two way, non-divided roadway in lane 1 approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling west on a 3 lane, two way, non-divided roadway in lane 1 approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection when V1 attempted to make a left turn. The front of V1 contacted the front of V2. V1 came to rest after impact facing north V2 came to rest facing North West.

Vehicles 1 and 2 were both traveling northbound on 7 lane physically divided roadway in the lane 2 position. Vehicle 1 was behind V2. Vehicle 2 had stopped in the roadway for a red light. The front plane of Vehicle 1 made contact with the rear plane of Vehicle 2. Vehicles 1 and 2 came to final rest facing north just after impact.

V1 was traveling south on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a right hand curve in the roadway. V1 departed the left hand lane line and then departed the left side (east) of the roadway. V1 continued to drive off road contacting a fence with its frontal plane. V1 then contacted a culvert also with its frontal plane before coming to final rest off of the roadway.

V1 was traveling west on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a left hand curve in the roadway. V2 was traveling east on the same roadway as V1 entering a right hand curve in the roadway. V1 departed the left hand lane line and the frontal plane of V1 contacted the frontal plane of V2. The front of V1 then contacted the left rear of V2. V2 proceeded forward entering the shoulder of the roadway before coming to final rest on the roadway partially on the shoulder. V1 proceeded forward after the initial impact and departed the southern shoulder of the roadway striking the face of a guardrail with its frontal plane. V1 came to final rest partially off of the roadway against the face of the guardrail.

V1 was exiting a parking lot to make a right onto a northbound roadway. V2 was heading north in lane two of a four lane undivided roadway. V3 was parked in lane one facing north.The front of V1 impacted with the right of V2 (event 1). V1 was redirected to the right and the right of V1 impacted the left of V3 (event 2). V1 came to final rest near the second point of impact. V2 came to final rest in lane two facing north. V3 came to final rest in lane one near its point of contact.

V1 was traveling north on a six lane undivided roadway in lane three entering into an intersection. V2 was traveling south on the roadway in lane four preparing to make a left turn. V3 was traveling west on a four lane undivided roadway in lane one stopped at the traffic light. The front of V1 connected with the right of V2 (Event 1). V1 was redirected to the right. The front of V1 connected with the left of V3 where it came to final rest (Event 2). V2 was also redirected to the right where it came to final rest in lane one in the northbound lane. V3 came to final rest at the point of impact.

V1 was traveling west in lane one of a two-lane divided (no positive barrier) roadway, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north in lane three of the connecting three lane divided (no positive barrier) right curved roadway, approaching the same intersection. At the intersection, V1 attempted to turn left into the southbound lanes. Within the intersection, the front of V1 impacted the right side of V2. V1 rotated clockwise and came to rest within the intersection, facing northwest. V2 rotated counter clockwise and came to rest within the intersection facing northwest.

V1 was traveling north in lane one of a four lane undivided (two-way traffic) roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right, drove down an embankment and hit a pile of rocks and dirt with its undercarriage. V1 went airborne and impacted the top of a parked vehicle with its undercarriage. V1 started to roll left while in the air and landed on the trailer of a parked vehicle with its left side. V1 rolled back onto its wheels and started to rotate counter clockwise. The left side of V1 impacted the back of a parked vehicle facing east. V1 started to rotate clockwise and rolled over onto its roof via its right side. V1 slid on its roof and kept rotating clockwise. While on its roof, the left side of V1 impacted the front of another parked vehicle facing west. V1 rotated counter clockwise on its roof  and came to rest against a sheet metal fence, laying on its roof facing southwest. During the impact with V2, debris from either vehicle flew off and impacted another parked vehicle.

Vehicle #1 was traveling northwest on a two-lane, two-way road. V1 departed the road to the left, and the front plane of V1 contacted a utility pole, then a sign post. V1 continued off road before its left plane contacted a tree. V1 came to rest off-road to the northeast.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a two lane, one way roadway in lane 1 position. A Deer attempted to cross the roadway from the south. The front of V1 contacted the deer. V1 was able to pull over on the shoulder of the roadway after impact with the Deer.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a 3 lane, two way, non-physically divided road way in lane 2 position approaching an intersection attempting to make a left hand turn. V2 was traveling west on a 4 lane, two way, median divided trafficway in lane 2 position approaching the same intersection attempting to continue straight through. Both vehicles entered the intersection. The front of V1 contacted the front of V2. V1 came to rest after impact facing north/ east in the intersection. V2 came to rest just after impact facing north west.

Vehicle 1 was traveling northbound on a two lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position.  Vehicles 2 and three were legally parked facing south.  The front plane of Vehicle 1 made contact with an unknown plane of Vehicle 2.  After impact, Vehicle 1 continued traveling north making contact with the front plane to the front plane of Vehicle 3.  Vehicle 1 deflected off Vehicle 3 coming to rest facing north shortly after of impact.

V1 was traveling south on a two-way, two lane undivided roadway, approaching a sign controlled intersection. V2 was traveling east, on a median divided roadway, with four lanes in the same direction, approaching the same intersection as V1. Both vehicles entered the intersection. The frontal plane of V2 contacted the right side plane of V1. V1 continue forward rotating in clockwise direction and came to a final rest on the southeast side of the roadway. V-2 continued forward rotating in a counter-clockwise direction and came to a final rest off the southeast side of the roadway.

V1 was traveling northbound on a two way, two lane undivided roadway, approaching an intersection with a stop sign. V2 was traveling eastbound, on a median divided roadway, with four lanes in the same direction, approaching the same intersection as V1. Both vehicles entered the intersection. The frontal plane of V1 contacted the right side plane of V2. Both vehicles came to a final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling east in lane one of a two lane, not physically divided, two-way roadway approaching a sign controlled intersection. V2 was traveling north in lane two of a three lane, two-way, not physically divided roadway with a left turn lane approaching the same intersection. V1 and V2 entered the intersection simultaneously. V2 front plane contacted V1 left plane.

V1 was traveling south bound in lane two of a four lane, two-way, physically divided roadway with a grass median. A deer entered the roadway from the grass median left of the roadway. V1 front plane contacted the deer.

V1 was traveling west in the #1 eastbound lane on a three-lane, two-way roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south in lane 2 on a four lane two way roadway approaching the same intersection. V1 turned right at the intersection, crossed into opposing lane and the front of V1 contacted the front of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in the area of impact.

V1 was traveling east on a three lane two way undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north on a three lane two way roadway approaching the same intersection. In the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling northbound on a 2 lane divided highway in lane 2. V1 departed the roadway to the left , the front of V1 then impacted a cable barrier. V1 continued northbound in the grass median along side the guardrail and came to rest north of the impact area facing north.

V1 was traveling east negotiating a right curve on a 2 lane undivided roadway in lane 1. A deer entered the roadway from the south and the right side of V1 contacted the deer. V1 came to a controlled stop on the roadside east of the impact facing east.

V1 was traveling southbound in the first lane of a two lane divided roadway, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling northbound in the second lane of a two lane divided roadway, approaching the same intersection as V1. V2 attempted to turn left to continue traveling westbound. Both V1 and V2 entered the intersection at the same time. The frontal plane of V1 impacted the right side plane of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling eastbound in the first lane of a two lane, two-way roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling northbound in the first lane of a two lane, two-way roadway approaching the same intersection as V1. Both V1 and V2 entered the intersection at the same time. The frontal plane of V1 impacted the left side plane of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway: V1 facing east and V2 facing northeast.

V1 was traveling southwest in lane one of a two lane roadway approaching an intersection attempting a left turn. V1 departed the right road edge and the front plane contacted a fence. V1 continued forward and the front plane contacted a sign. V1 continued forward and the front plane contacted a tree where it came to rest.

V1 was traveling southwest in lane one of a two lane roadway attempting to pass through an intersection. V2 was traveling northwest in lane two of a four lane divided roadway attempting to pass through the same intersection. V1's left plane contacted V2's front plane. Subsequently, the left side of V1 struck the left side of V2. V1 departed the roadway into the median where it came to rest. V2 came to final rest in the roadway just past impact.

V1 was traveling southeast in lane two of a four-lane divided roadway, passing through an intersection. V2 was traveling northwest attempting a left turn at the same intersection. V3 was stopped facing northeast, at the intersection. The front plane of V1 contacted the right plane of V2. V1 came to final rest on the roadway in the intersection. The front plane of V2 then contacted the front plane of V3. Both vehicles came to final rest at the location of impact 2.

V1 was traveling east in the first of two lanes on an undivided, two-way roadway. V2 was was parked on the north curb facing west. V1 was involved in a previous accident and attempted to depart the location. The front of V1 contacted the front of V2. Both vehicles came to rest at impact.

V1 was traveling west on a non-physically divided two way road in lane one. V2 was traveling east on the same non-physically divided two way road in lane one. V1 negotiating a right curve, turned into the eastbound lanes and the front of V1 impacted the front of V2. Both vehicles stuck together in the eastbound lanes. V1 came to rest facing a northeasterly direction and V2 came to rest facing a southwesterly direction.

V1 was traveling south on a physically divided three lane highway in lane one, behind V2. V2 was traveling south in the same physically divided three lane highway in lane one and was stopped for traffic. The front of V1 contacted the rear of V2. V2 came to rest facing south on the right shoulder, and V1 came to rest between lane one and two, facing south.

V1 was traveling south on a non-physically divided two way road in lane one. V1 crossed into the northbound lane and in an attempt to steer back into the southbound lane, V1 over corrected and traveled off the right road edge. V1 continued on the roadside and impacted a bush with its front plane. V1 continued forward, steered left then tripped and rolled 4-quarter turns and came to rest on its wheels facing northeast. During the rollover, the right side of V1 contacted a wire fence.

Vehicle #1 was traveling south on a two-way, two-lane road with street parking on both sides. Vehicles #2 and #3 were legally parked facing south on the same road. V1 departed the road to the right, and the right side plane of V1 contacted the left side plane of V2. V1 rapidly rotated clockwise as the frontal plane sustained contact without separation to V2. V1 came to rest on the road and in contact with V2.  V2 came to rest with its right wheels off road.

V1 was traveling southbound on a four lane, two way, median divided roadway. V1 departed the right hand (west) side of the roadway striking a fence post of a chain link fence with its front plane. V1 continued forward making additional contact with the fence with its right side plane and undercarriage. V1 continued forward through the chain link fence and through an electric fence striking both fences with its front plane. V1 continued forward into a field off of the roadway. V1 continued forward through the field attempting to return to the roadway. V1 then struck both the electric fence and the chain link fence again with its frontal plane. V1 came to a final rest partially on the shoulder of the roadway.

V1 was traveling north in lane 3 of a 5 lane, not physically divided, two-way roadway with a left turn lane, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south in lane 1 of the same roadway. V1 turned left at the intersection and the right side of V1 contacted the front of V2.
V1 was stopped at a controlled intersection on a four lane median divided roadway, facing north.  V2 was traveling north in the same lane as V1.  The front plane of V2 contacted the rear plane of V1.

V1 and V2 were traveling east in the same lane of travel on a six lane two way not positively divided roadway approaching an intersection. Before passing through the intersection the front of V1 contacted the back of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling west in lane two of a three lane divided (with positive barrier) highway, negotiating a left curve. V2 was traveling on the same highway in lane three. V1 changed lanes to the left in order to avoid a collision with a stalled vehicle ahead in it's lane. The front of V2 impacted the rear of V1. V1 started to rotate clockwise and rolled over onto its left side. V1 slid a short distance on its left side, before it came to rest in lane two, facing north. After impact with V1, V2 rotated clockwise and came to rest in lane three, facing northwest.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 departed the right road edge and its frontal plane contacted a utility pole. V1 then began to rotate counterclockwise and roll right. The top of V1 then contacted the pole support wire and as V1 continued to roll right side leading the left side of V1 contacted two trees. V1 came to rest on its wheels near the right road edge.
V1 was traveling north east on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 departed the right road edge and the frontal plane of V1 contacted two trees. V1 came to final rest off the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west in lane 1 on a 4 lane not physically divided two way road approaching a bridge with concrete barriers on both sides. While negotiating a curve to the left vehicle 1 departed the lane on the right side and the front plane contacted the concrete barrier on the right side of the road. The right plane of vehicle 1 then contacted the right side barrier a second time before coming to final rest on the shoulder facing west.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south in lane three on a three lane two way trafficway, divided by a grass median and cable barrier. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway on the left side and the front then left plane of vehicle 1 contacted a cable barrier. Vehicle 1 came to final rest on the paved shoulder facing south.
V1 was traveling eastbound on a 2 lane, non divided, roadway. V2 was legally parked on roadway. V1's front contacted V2's rear. V1 came to rest on the roadway east of point of impact.

Vehicles 1 and 2 were traveling north on a two-lane, two-way roadway. V2 came to a stop, waiting to turn left at an intersection. The front plane of V1 contacted the back plane of V2. V1 came to rest on the right shoulder. V2 came to rest on the road.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west in lane-five of an undivided six-lane roadway approaching a four-leg intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling south in lane-two of an undivided three-lane roadway, approaching the same intersection.  Vehicle 1 entered the intersection starting from a left turn lane. Vehicle 2 was within the intersection making a left turn. The front of Vehicle 1 contacted the front left corner of Vehicle 2. Vehicle 1 and 2 came to final rest within the intersection; Vehicle 1 facing south and Vehicle 2 facing southeast.

Vehicle 1 was traveling southwest on a two-lane, two-way roadway, approaching an intersection with no traffic controls, intending to turn right. Vehicle 2 was traveling east on an intersecting two-lane,  two-way roadway with a stop sign. Within the intersection, the front of Vehicle 1 impacted the front of Vehicle 2. Vehicle 1 continued forward where it came to final rest facing west. Vehicle 2 rotated clockwise and moved northwest and came to rest facing southeast.

V1 was traveling west in lane two of a seven lane divided (with positive barrier) major highway. V1 departed its lane of travel to the right and crossed the merging lane of an entrance ramp. V1 started to rotate clockwise and departed the roadway to the right. V1 went up an embankment, crossed the two lane service road to the north of the highway and departed it to the north. V1 kept rotating clockwise and impacted the wooden post of a sign with its front. The left side of V1 impacted the other wooden post of the same sign. This post broke and fell onto the roof of V1. V1 kept rotating clockwise and came to rest a short distance west of the sign, facing east.

V1 was traveling east in lane one of a four lane divided (with positive barrier) major highway. V2 was traveling in lane one of a two lane interchange ramp, which merged with lane one of the highway. At the point were the ramp merged with the highway, V2 merged into lane one. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. V2 started to rotate clockwise and departed the roadway to the south. The front of V2 impacted a concrete traffic barrier. V2 bounced off the barrier and came to rest in lane one, facing southwest. After the impact with V2, V1 did not come to a stop and kept driving eastbound.

V1 was eastbound on a two lane. two-way, undivided roadway stopped at a four leg intersection. V2 was northbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. As V2 crossed through the intersection the front of V2 impacted the right side of the V1 causing damage. V1 ad V2 then rotated clockwise toward the northeast portion of the intersection. During the rotation the back of V1 impacted the right side of V2 causing damage. V1 departed the roadway impacting a ditch with its back plane and coming to rest at the point of impact facing south. V2 came to final rest facing south on the roadway facing south.

V1 was southbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway pulling a farm implement. V2 was northbound on the same roadway. The left side of V1's pulled unit impacted the front of V2 then the left side of v2 causing damage. V1 came to final rest at the point of impact facing south. V2 came to final rest just north of the point of impact facing north.
V1 and V2 were traveling east on a two-lane, two-way road. V1 stopped in the road and the front of V2 impacted the rear of V1. V2 came to rest at the point of impact and V1 fled the scene.

V1 was heading east on a seven lane one-way trafficway approaching an intersection. V2 was heading north on a five lane undivided trafficway approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection, and the front of V1 impacted  the left of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest near the point of impact.

V1 was traveling south on an unmarked two lane, two way roadway. V2 and V3 were parked on the west side of the road facing south. V1 moved to its right and the front of V1 impacted with the rear of V2. V1 than begin a clockwise rotation and came to final rest facing west in the middle of the roadway. V2 was redirected forward at impact and the front of V2 impacted with the rear of a second parked vehicle.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane, two way roadway. V1 steered right to avoid deer in the roadway. V1 departed the right side of the roadway in a clockwise yaw, striking an embankment with its frontal plane. V1 then rolled two quarter turns, left side leading, and came to rest on its top facing northeast.

V1 was traveling north through a four-leg intersection on a two-lane, two-way, undivided roadway. V2 was traveling west through the same intersection on a two-lane, two-way, undivided roadway. The frontal plane of V2 struck the right side plane of V1. V1 rotated rapidly in a clockwise fashion, departing the northwest intersection quadrant. The right front wheel/rim was damaged due to contacting a drainage ditch (Event 2) and V1 came to rest facing north west. V2 also rotated clockwise and came to rest heading east, off the northwest corner of the intersection.

V2 was traveling south on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 was traveling south behind V2 on the same roadway. The frontal plane of V1 struck the rear plane of V2. Both vehicles departed the right side of the roadway after impact. V1 came to rest heading west. V2 came to rest heading south.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 lost control and began in a clockwise yaw. V1 departed the west road edge and the front of V1 contacted a ditch. V1 continued to rotate clockwise and tripped and rolled one quarter turn onto its left side. V1 came to final rest off the roadway on its left side facing north.

V1 and V2 were both traveling south in lane two on a four lane divided roadway, approaching an intersection. V2 had stopped due to traffic ahead when V1's front plane contacted V2's rear plane. Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane, undivided roadway, approaching an intersection. V1 departed the roadway to the right a stuck a culvert prior to the intersection. V1 came to final rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling east on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a right hand curve in the roadway. V1 departed the right hand side of the roadway (south) and struck a tree with its frontal plane. V1 then proceeded to rotate in a clockwise direction before coming to final rest off of the roadway facing west.
Vehicles #1 and #2 were traveling west in lane three of a three-lane divided roadway without a positive barrier.  V1 braked to avoid a non-contact vehicle. The back of V1 contacted the front of V2.

V1, V2, and V3 were traveling westbound in the number 1 lane of a 2 lane undivided roadway. V3 was stopped due to traffic ahead. V2 was slowing due to traffic ahead. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. The force of the collision pushed the front of V2 into the rear of V3. All three vehicles came to rest facing westerly in the number 1 lane.

V1 was traveling southeast on a two way, two lane undivided roadway negotiating a slight right curve in the roadway and approaching a hill crest. V2 was traveling on the same roadway as V1 but in front of V1. V2 stopped in the roadway due to a school bus and the front plane of V1 contacted the rear plane of V2. V2 moved forward slightly before coming to final rest on the roadway. V1 after contacting the rear plane of V2 continued off of the roadway striking an embankment with an unknown plane. V1 came to final rest off of the roadway.

V1 was traveling east on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a left hand curve in the roadway. A deer entered the roadway and in an attempt to avoid the deer V1 departed the right hand (south) side of the roadway and contacted a cable barrier guardrail with its frontal plane. V1 proceeded to travel down approximately 150 feet of cable barrier guardrail before contacting a sign post with an unknown plane. V1 then came to final rest off of the roadway.

V1 was traveling west on a five lane two-way road approaching a four-way intersection. V2 was traveling east on the same road approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection and V1 initiated a left turn. The front of V1 impacted the front of V2. Continuing forward, the left side of V1 impacted the left side of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest in the intersection.

V1 was traveling northeast in lane 2 of a 4 lane, two way, non-divided roadway and had stopped at a stop sign at an intersection. V2 was traveling southeast in lane 3 of a 4 lane divided roadway and was approaching an intersection.. At the intersection, V1's front plane contacted V2's right side plane. Both vehicles came to final rest a short distance from the contact.

V1 was traveling southeast in lane one on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. A large tree on the right side of the road then fell across the roadway in front of V1. V1's front plane contacted the tree and came to final rest in front of the tree, after pushing the tree approximately 4-5 meters.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south an a two lane undivided roadway approaching an intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling east on a two lane undivided roadway, approaching the same intersection. Vehicle 2 turned left to travel north. The front of Vehicle 1 contacted the left side of Vehicle 2. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway on the right, coming to final rest facing south. Vehicle 2 departed the roadway off the left side and came to final rest after the right plane contacted an underground utility marker.

V1 was traveling westbound approaching an intersection in lane 2 of a 2 lane, two-way, physically divided roadway with both a right and left turn lane. V2 was traveling northbound in lane 4 of a 5 lane divided roadway approaching the same intersection. V1 traveling westbound crossed through the intersection and V2 front plane contacted V1 left plane.

V1 was traveling north in lane 3 of a 3 lane on a divided roadway with a left turn lane approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south in lane 1 of a 3 lane, divided roadway with a left turn lane approaching the same intersection. V1 turned left and both vehicles entered the intersection simultaneously. In the intersection the front plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2. V2 continued forward and contacted the right plane with the guardrail on the southwest corner of the intersection before coming to rest. V1 came to rest facing south on the roadway.

V1 was traveling south bound on a two lane, non-divided, bidirectional roadway passing through an intersection. V2 was east bound on a two lane, non-divided, bidirectional roadway, turning left passing through the same intersection.  Both vehicles entered the intersection, with V1 initiating a left turn.  V1's frontal plane impacted V2's frontal plane. V1 continued south bound, where it came to final rest in the north bound lane of travel. V2 rotated clockwise, and traveled south bound where it came to final rest in the south bound lane of travel.

V1 was traveling behind V2 heading North in lane 1 of a 6 lane, two-way, physically divided roadway with a left turn lane. As both V1 and V2 approached an intersection V1 front plane contacted V2 rear plane.

V1 and V2 were heading southwest on a three lane undivided roadway. V2 was in lane two preparing to make a left turn. V1 lost control and departed its travel lane to the left. The front of V1 connected with the rear of V2. V1 was redirected to the right and began a counter clockwise rotation. V1 departed the roadway to the right and the back of V1 contacted a tree. V1 came to rest in contact with the tree, facing northeast. V2 was redirected to the left and came to final rest along the curb line of an intersecting roadway.

V1 and V2 were heading west in lane two of a four lane undivided roadway. V3 was heading east in lane one on the same roadway. V2 was slowing to make a left turn. The front of V1 connected with the rear of V2 (event 1). V2 was redirected to the left. The front of V2 connected with the front of V3 (event 2). V1 came to final rest near the point of impact facing west. V2 and V3 came to final rest near the point of impact.

V1 was traveling in a southern direction on a two lane, non divided, bidirectional rural roadway. V1 struck a large tree which had fallen into the roadway with its frontal plane. V1 came to final rest in a small drainage ditch on the right side of the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on 5 lane, barrier  divided roadway in lane two. Vehicle 1 left  its lane to the left, crossing over all the other lanes of travel, continuing off road where its left side impacted the concrete barrier. Vehicle 1 continued down the concrete barrier making contact with its left side. Vehicle 1 came to rest facing east, on the shoulder, against the barrier.
V1 and V2 were traveling in the westbound lane on an undivided, two-way roadway. V1 attempted at a u-turn. The left side of V1 contacted the front of V2.

V1 was negotiating a curve to the left while traveling east on a two-lane, two-way road. V1 departed the left side of the road and its front plane impacted a traffic delineator and a guardrail end. V1 came to rest  off of the left side of the road with the guardrail completely penetrating V1 through the longitudinal axis.

V1 and V2 were traveling east on a five lane interstate with a positive barrier. V1 was in lane one and V2 was preparing to merge from the entrance ramp. The right of V1 impacted with the left of V2. V1 was then redirected to the left and crossed four lanes of traffic. The front of V1 connected with the jersey barrier before coming to final rest. V2 came to final rest facing east on the right shoulder near the point of impact.

Vehicle 1 was traveling northbound on a two lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position.  Vehicle 1 departed roadway right side making contact to a legally parked camper with its front plane.  The camper was pushed forward into a legally parked vehicle.  Vehicle 1 came to final rest in the roadway facing north just after impact with the camper.  The camper was at final rest facing north.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north on a 5 lane, two way, divided roadway in lane 1 position approaching a intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling east on a 4 lane, one way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 2 approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection proceeding straight and the front of V2 contacted the left side of V1. After impact V1 rotated counter-clockwise departing the northwest apex and the rear of V1 contacted a pole. V2 came to rest at impact 2 facing south. V2 came to rest after impact 1 in the intersection facing north east.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a 3 lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1 position approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north on a 3 lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1 position approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection. The right side of V1 contacted the front of V2. V2 came to rest just after impact facing north east. V1 came to rest just after impact facing south east in the south east corner of the intersection.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east in lane 2 on a one-way 4 lane roadway. Vehicle 2 was traveling south in lane 2 on a 4 lane divided roadway. Both vehicles entered the intersection at the same time. The front of Vehicle 1 contacted the right side of Vehicle 2. Vehicle 2 rotated counter-clockwise slightly, departed the median curb edge where its left front tire contacted the curb. V2 continued forward and its left side sideswiped a metal sign post and came to rest in the median facing east. V1 continued forward and came to rest in the northeast corner of the intersections facing northeast.

V1 was traveling south following a two way, two lane road with a curve to the right. As V1 was negotiating the curve, it departed the roadway to the right. V1 began to spin counterclockwise off the roadway impacting a utility pole with its right side. After impact, V1 rotated clockwise and continued forward coming to final rest off the roadway facing south west.

V1 was traveling in an eastern direction, on a two lane, non divided, bidirectional roadway, negotiating a curve to the left. V1 departed the roadway to the right and traveled down a slight embankment. V1's frontal plane impacted a sign post and and its right plane impacted a flag pole. V1 then rolled left side leading, and impacted a tree with its top plane. Occupant 1 was partially ejected. V1 came to final rest on its left plane on the right side of the roadway.

V1 was traveling north on a four lane, two way roadway. V2 was traveling south on a four lane, median divided roadway. V1 was exiting a parking lot making a left turn, attempting to travel westbound on a four lane, two-way, undivided roadway. V1 was traveling eastbound on a five lane, two-way roadway in lane one approaching a four-way intersection. V2 was traveling eastbound on a five lane, two-way roadway in lane one ahead of V1. V2 was stopped at the four-way intersection waiting for the traffic light. The front plane of V1 contacted the back plane of V2. V1 and V2 came to final rest at point of impact on roadway.

V1 was traveling south on a one-way, four-lane roadway approaching an intersection controlled by a traffic light. V1 came to final rest in the intersection facing south.

V1 was south on a 6 lane roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was stopped at a red light at the same intersection. V2 entered the intersection and the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in the intersection in travel lanes.

V1 was southbound on a 5 lane roadway (with 2 way middle turn lane) in the number 1 lane. V1 attempted a right  turn on to a non paved roadway when the left side of V1 contacted a stop sign. V1 was heading south down an entrance onto the interstate. V1 departed the roadway to the right.  The front of V1 impacted a guardrail end.  V1 then rotated clockwise and the left side of V1 impacted the guardrail.  V1 came to rest on the west roadside facing north.

V1 was traveling west in lane four of a four lane divided (no positive barrier) road, approaching an intersection. V1 was traveling west in the third of three lanes, on a two-way, right curved roadway divided by a grass median. V2 was traveling east along a left curve in the third of three lanes on the same road. V1 was east bound on a two lane, non divided, bidirectional roadway, negotiating a slight curve to the right. A deer entered the roadway from the south side of the roadway, where the frontal plane of V1 impacted the animal. V1 came to final rest on the south side of the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a two lane, two-way, undivided roadway.  Vehicle 1 departed the left curb edge where its front plane contacted a stop sign post. Vehicle 1 continued forward, crossed a sidewalk and contacted a fence with its front plane and came to rest facing northeast.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north on a six lane not physically divided two way road. Vehicle 2 was traveling in front of vehicle 1 on the same road. Vehicle 2 slowed for traffic and the front plane of vehicle 1 contacted the rear plane of vehicle 2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 and V2 were traveling westbound on a two-lane, one-way roadway in lane two. V2 was stopped at the traffic light controlling the four-way intersection while V1 was traveling behind V2. The front of V1 contacted the back of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest at point of impact facing westbound.

V1 & V2 were both traveling west in lane one on a one lane, median divided, roadway. V2 had stopped in the roadway due to an accident ahead when V1's front plane contacted V2's rear plane. Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway near the point of impact.

V1 was traveling northwest in lane one on a two lane roadway negotiating a left curve. A deer approached from the right side of the road and into the path of the vehicle. V1 attempted to pass V2 on the left, when V2 attempted to turn left into a private driveway. The front of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V1's right side then impacted V2 left side. V1 and V2 departed the roadway to the left, where both vehicles came to a final rest.

V1 was traveling east on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a right hand curve in the roadway. V1 departed the left hand lane line and then the left (north) side of the roadway. V1 contacted a tree with its left side plane. V1 then traveled a short distance where it then contacted a tree with its frontal plane. V1 came to final rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling north on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a left hand curve in the roadway. V1 departed the right hand side of the roadway briefly, re-entered their initial travel lane, and then lost control entering into a counter clockwise rotation. V1 then departed the left hand lane line, and then departed the left (west) side of the roadway. V1 rolled one quarter turn right, slid a brief distance while on its side, and then rolled one more quarter turn onto its roof. V1 came to final rest off of the roadway.

V1 was traveling northbound in the number 3 lane of a 5 lane undivided roadway with a two-way left turn lane. V2 was traveling southbound in the number 1 lane of a 5 lane undivided roadway with a two-way left turn lane. V1 began to make a left turn into a private driveway.
