The front of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V1 came to rest facing west in the between the southbound number 1 and 2 lanes. V2 then impacted the curb with the right front tire before coming to rest facing southerly in the number 1 lane.

V1 was traveling southwest in lane one of a two-lane roadway, starting to go straight through an intersection after stopping for a stop sign. V2 was traveling east in lane two of a three-lane roadway, passing through the same intersection. The right plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2. V1 and V2 came to final rest in the roadway close to impact.

V1 was traveling southeast in lane one of a three lane roadway approaching an intersection to make a right turn and travel southwest. V2 was parked off of the right road edge of the southwest leg of the intersection. V1 made the right turn then departed the right road edge and the front plane contacted the rear plane of V2. V1 came to final rest in lane one near impact. V2 came to rest near impact.

V1 was headed northwest on a 7 lane physically divided roadway, in lane 4 and approaching intersection. V2 was headed southeast on a 6 lane undivided roadway, in lane 3 and also approaching intersection. Within the intersection, V1 was turning left and V2 was going straight. V1's front plane contacted V2's front plane. V1 then spun around and side slapped V2. Both V1 and V2 came to rest in the south bound lanes.

V1 was traveling west on a two-lane rural roadway when it departed the right (north) side of the road. V1’s front end struck a ditch/culvert, followed by its right side scraping along the ditch/culvert. V1 came to final rest on the roadside facing west.

V1 was traveling east in lane three of a four lane divided (no positive barrier) roadway, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south in lane one of a two lane undivided (two-way traffic) roadway, approaching the same intersection. At the intersection V2 turned left into the eastbound lanes of traffic. Within the intersection the front of V1 impacted the back of V2. V1 started to rotate clockwise and rolled over left side leading for two quarter turns onto its roof. V1 slid on its roof further east and came to rest in lane three facing south. After the impact with V1, V2 drove off the roadway and stopped on the paved shoulder south of the eastbound lanes of traffic.

V1 was traveling south following a two way, two lane roadway, approaching a four way intersection. V2 was traveling in front of V1, on the same two way, two lane road. At the intersection, V2 attempted to take a left. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest at impact, both facing south.

V1 was traveling south on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling west on a two way, three lane, undivided roadway approaching the same intersection as V1. V1 attempted to cross over the intersection and the front plane of V1 contacted the right side plane of V2. V1 rotated briefly in a clockwise direction before coming to final rest on the roadway. V2 began rotating in a counter clockwise direction before departing the south side of the roadway. V2 then contacted the ground with both right wheels (Events 2 and 3) before coming to final rest off of the roadway.

V1 was traveling north on a two way, two lane roadway, with a northbound left turn lane, passing through a four leg intersection. V2 was traveling west on a two way, two lane roadway, with a westbound left turn lane, passing through the same four leg intersection. The frontal plane of V2 struck the right side plane of V1. V2 came to rest heading west in its original travel lane. V1 rotated clockwise and struck an unknown plane of V3, which was stopped in the southbound lane of the same intersection, with its right side plane. V3 stayed at final rest at the point of impact. V1 came to rest heading southeast, at the point of impact with V3.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east in lane two of a four-lane, two-way, non-physically divided roadway. Vehicle 2 was on the same roadway in front of V1 and stopped in traffic. The Front of V1 contacted the rear of V2. Both vehicles came to rest still facing east on the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling eastbound on a two lane non-physically divided roadway entering an intersection to turn left. Vehicle 2 was traveling southbound on the intersecting four lane physically divided traffic-way in the lane 1 position. Both vehicles entered the intersection and the front of V2 contacted the left side of V1. Vehicle 1 came to final rest facing east in the center of the intersection. Vehicle 2 came to final rest facing southeast in the southwest portion of the intersection.

Vehicle 1 was traveling  south on a two lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1 position approaching an intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling on a 5 lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1 position approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection at the same time. The front of V1 contacted the right side of V2. V1 rotated in a clockwise rotation v2 rotated in a counter-clockwise rotation and the left side of v1 contacted the right side of v2. V1 continued to rotate in the clockwise rotation almost making one full turn. V1 departed roadway in the south west corner of the intersection striking a concrete cinderblock barrier before coming to rest in a yard facing south east. V2 after impact #2 also traveled off the south west corner of the intersection striking a large landscaping rock located at the corner of a yard. V2 continued traveling south west striking a cinderblock barrier with its left front wheel and then finally striking concrete steps that lea

V3 was stopped on a two lane, two way roadway, with a left turn lane. V2 was stopped behind V3. V1 was traveling south in the same lane as V3 and V2. The frontal plane of V1 struck the back plane of V2. The frontal plane of V2 then struck the rear plane of V3. All three vehicles came to rest in their initial travel lane, heading south, near the point of impact.

V1 was traveling south on a two way, two lane roadway in the southbound lane negotiating a right curve.  V1 crossed both lanes to the left and departed the left road edge where its front plane contacted a pole. V1 rotated clockwise as it crossed a ditch and its left side contacted a tree. V1 rotated counter-clockwise and its left side contacted another tree causing V1 to roll right 2-quarter turns. V1 came to rest on its top in the northbound lane facing south. The driver was completely ejected during the rollover sequence.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a two lane two way roadway, approaching a four leg intersection with no traffic controls. Vehicle 2 was traveling south on a two lane two way roadway approaching the same intersection controlled by a stop sign. Vehicle 3 was traveling north on the same roadway as vehicle 2, approaching the same intersection controlled by a stop sign. Within the intersection, the front plane of Vehicle 1 contacted the right plane of Vehicle 2. Upon impact vehicle 2 rotated clockwise and the left plane of Vehicle 2 contacted the front plane of Vehicle 3. Vehicle 1 traveled off the right side of the roadway, came to final rest facing east and caught fire. Vehicle 2 came to final rest on the roadway facing west. Vehicle 3 came to final rest on the roadway facing north.

Vehicle #1 was traveling north, negotiating a right curve, in lane one of a two-lane, undivided roadway.  Vehicle #2 was traveling south in lane one of the same roadway.  V1 departed its lane to the left and the front of V1 contacted the front of V2.   V1 began to rotate counter-clockwise and departed the road to the right.  V1 came to rest facing southwest, near impact, partially on the roadway.  V2 began to rotate counter-clockwise and departed the road to the right.  V1 came to rest near impact, facing northeast, partially on the roadway.

V1 was traveling west in lane four of a four lane divided (with positive barrier) left curved highway. V2 was traveling ahead of V1 in the same lane. V3 was traveling ahead of V1 in the next lane to the right. V1 attempted to change lanes and pass V2 on the right. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. V1 continued and impacted the rear of V3 with its front. V1 continued to drive and did not stop. After the first impact, V2 rotated counter clockwise and came to rest in lane four, facing west. After the impact with V1, V3 rotated clockwise, crossed all lanes of traffic and impacted a concrete traffic barrier with its front. V3 bounced off the barrier, rotated clockwise and came to rest in lane three, facing northeast.

Vehicles #1 and #2 were traveling south on a two-lane, two-way road. V1 pulled into the parking lane to the right, then began a U-turn. The left plane of V1 contacted the right plane of V2. Both vehicles came to rest on the road.

V1 was traveling eastbound in the first lane of a three lane, one-way roadway. V2 was traveling eastbound in the first lane of the same three lane, one-way roadway, ahead of V1. V1 departed the roadway on the right onto the shoulder/breakdown lane. V1 re-entered the roadway on the left into the first lane, behind of V2. The frontal plane of V1 then impacted the rear plane of V2. V1 was at final rest in the first lane of the roadway facing east. V2 rotated clockwise and departed the roadway on the right. The frontal plane of V2 impacted the guardrail face. V2 rotated slightly counterclockwise, sideswiping it's right side plane with the guardrail face. V2 re-entered the roadway on the left and came to final rest in the first lane facing east.

V1 was traveling north, on a four lane two way undivided roadway, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling west, on a three lane one way roadway, approaching the same intersection. Within the intersection, the right side of V1 contacted the front of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north on a two lane, two way, not divided roadway, approaching an intersection. Vehicle 1 began to turn right at the intersection and continued off road on the northeast corner where it contacted a hill and a tree with its front. The vehicle came to rest at the tree, facing northeast.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a two lane not physically divided two way road approaching a 3 leg intersection controlled by a stop sign. Vehicle 1  continued forward trough the intersection and departed the roadway at the road end. The front plane of vehicle 1 struck a ditch and came to final rest off the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north on a right curving, not divided, two-way roadway in lane one, approaching a three legged intersection. Vehicle 1 turned right at the intersection and began traveling east. The left front tire of Vehicle 1 contacted the curb on the left side of the roadway, disabling the vehicle. Vehicle 1 came to final rest facing east in the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north in lane 3, on a 3 lane one way trafficway divided by a grass median and cable barrier. Vehicle 2 was traveling north in lane 2 on the same trafficway. Vehicle 1 lost control due to water on road, rotated counterclockwise, departed the roadway on the left side and the front plane contacted a cable barrier. Upon impact vehicle 1 continued to rotate counterclockwise returned to the roadway and the front plane contacted the left plane of vehicle 2. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway on the left side again and the back plane contacted a cable barrier a second time. Vehicle 1 came to final rest off the roadway facing northwest. Vehicle 2 did not stop and continued north.

V1 was traveling west in lane one on a three lane, two way, roadway. As the vehicle was negotiating a left curve, a deer entered the roadway. V1 steered to the right to avoid the deer and departed the roadway on the right side. The vehicle then steered to the left to re-enter the roadway and it's right rear tire contacted a guardrail end. V1 then began to rotate in a clockwise direction and it's front plane contacted the guardrail face. The vehicle then rolled over one quarter turn onto it's left side and came to final rest in the middle of the roadway. The vehicles final rest position was approximately 51 meters past the rollover initiation point.

V1 was traveling east in lane one on a two lane, two way, roadway. As the vehicle was negotiating a left curve in the road, V1 departed the road on the right side and traveled on the grass shoulder of the road for approximately 70 meters. V1 then steered left and re-entered the road from the right, traveled across both travel lanes, and departed the road on the left side while rotating counter-clockwise. V1 then contacted a ditch embankment with it's left front plane. V1 continued to rotate counter-clockwise and its right plane contacted a ditch. V1 rotated clockwise as it traveled across a dirt drive then entered a ditch where it rolled right 2-quarter turns and came to rest on its top facing north.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north in lane three on a six lane, two way trafficway divided by a concrete barrier. Vehicle 2 was traveling in front of vehicle 1 in the same direction on the same the same trafficway. Vehicle 3 was traveling in front of vehicle 2 in the same direction on the same the same trafficway. The front plane of vehicle 1 contacted the back plane of vehicle 2. Vehicles 1 and 3 then departed the lane on the left side and the front plane of vehicle 1 contacted the back plane of vehicle 3. All three vehicles came to final rest on the shoulder facing north.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west in lane two on a three lane one way roadway approaching a three leg intersection controlled by a traffic light. Vehicle 2 was stopped at the red stop light traveling in front of vehicle 1 in the same direction on the same roadway. The front plane of vehicle 1 contacted the back plane of vehicle 2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway facing west.

V1 was traveling east from a parking lot crossing through both north and south bound lanes of traffic to enter another drive on the east side of an intersection. V2 was traveling north on lane 1 of a 4 lane, two-way, physically divided roadway with a left turn lane approaching the same intersection. V1 and V2 entered the intersection simultaneously. V1 right plane contacted V2 front plane. Both vehicle came to rest off the East edge of the roadway.

V1 and V2 were traveling south in lane two of a four lane, two way, undivided roadway approaching an intersection. An EMS vehicle approached the intersection from the west side and V2 stopped. In the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the back of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 and V2 were traveling south on a three lane, two way, not positively divided roadway approaching an intersection. Before entering the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the back of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling southbound in lane 4 of a 4 lane, two-way, physically divided roadway with a left turn lane approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north bound in lane 1 of a 4 lane, two-way, physically divided roadway with a left turn lane approaching the same intersection. V1 entered the intersection attempting to make a left turn. V2 simultaneously entered the same intersection. V1 right plane contacted V2 front plane.

V1 was traveling north bound on a three lane, non divided, bidirectional roadway, with two lanes north bound and one lane south bound approaching an intersection.  V1 was attempting to cross traffic and turn left. V2 was traveling south bound on the same roadway. V1's frontal plane impacted the frontal plane of V2. V1 came to final rest on the west side of the roadway and V2 came to final rest in the south bound lane.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a 5 lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 3 approaching an intersection to make a left turn. Vehicle 2 was traveling east on a 5 lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1 approaching the same intersection. V3 was stopped north on a 3 lane, two way, non-physically divided road way in lane 1 at the intersection. V1 and V2 entered the intersection at the same time. The front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V1 came to rest after impact facing south. V2 due to impact rotated counter clockwise and the right rear side of V2 contacted the left front of V3 before coming to rest. V3's final rest was at impact.

V1 was traveling west on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a left hand curve in the roadway. A dog entered the roadway and in an attempt to avoid the dog V1 steered right and departed the right (north) side of the roadway contacting a signpost with its frontal plane. V1 continued forward down an embankment and then contacted a culvert also with its frontal plane. The back of V1 then contacted the associated ditch. V1 came to final rest off of the roadway facing west.

V1 was traveling southwest following a two-way, four lane road, in the second lane, approaching a three way intersection. V2 was traveling northeast following a two-way, four lane roadway, in the second lane, approaching the same three way intersection. On the third leg of the intersection, V3 was stopped in traffic, facing north on a two-way, divided trafficway in the first lane. As V1 was attempting to take a left at the intersection, the front of V1 impacted the front of V2. After impact, V1 began to spin counterclockwise impacting the front of V3 with its right side. V1 caught fire before coming to final rest in the intersection facing northeast. After impact with V1, V2 spun clockwise up onto a median, impacting a pole with its left side before coming to final rest on the median facing west. V3 came to final rest at impact facing north.

V2 was traveling north on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a right hand curve in the roadway. V2 then made a left hand turn to enter a private driveway and began backing into the roadway in order to turn around to travel south. V1 was traveling north on the same roadway as V2 and approaching the same private driveway V2 was exiting in reverse. The frontal plane of V1 contacted the left side plane of V2. V1 came to final rest on the roadway while V2 came to final rest partially off of the roadway.

Vehicle 1 and Vehicle 2 were traveling north on a six lane, two-way, grass median divided road, in lane three. Vehicle 2 was traveling behind Vehicle 1, which was towing a trailer. At the intersection, Vehicle 1 came to a stop at the traffic control light and the front plane of Vehicle 2 contacted the back plane of the trailer being towed by Vehicle 1. Both vehicles came to final rest just forward of impact.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a two lane, two way roadway, approaching a three leg intersection with no traffic controls. While attempting to negotiate a curve to the right vehicle 1 traveled off the left side of the roadway. Vehicle 1 continued forward, the front plane struck a utility box, a sign, and rotated counterclockwise and overturned 4 quarter turns before coming to final rest off the roadway facing east..

Vehicle 1 was traveling south on the two-way, two-lane undivided roadway same roadway in lane one. A vehicle was backing out of a private drive into the path of V1 from the right. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway on the right side and the front of Vehicle 1 contacted a mailbox. Vehicle 1 came to final rest on the side of the roadway facing south.

V1 was negotiating a left curve traveling north in the fourth of four lanes on a divided, two-way trafficway entering an intersection attempting to turn left. V2 was negotiating a right curve traveling south in the first of four lanes on a divided, two-way trafficway entering the same intersection as V1. V3 was stopped facing east at the intersection. Within the intersection, the right side of V1 contacted the front of V2. V1 rotated counterclockwise and the front of V1 contacted the front of V3.

V1 was traveling west in the third of five lanes on an undivided, two-way roadway entering a light controlled, four-legged intersection attempting to turn left. V2 was traveling east in the second of five lanes on an undivided, two-way roadway entering the same intersection as V1. Within the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the front of V2. V1 rotated counter-clockwise and came to rest in the intersection facing south. V2 came to rest in the southeast corner of the intersection facing east.

V1 was traveling in a northeasterly direction, on a designated north/south divided trafficway (median strip without positive barrier), in lane 1 (of two lanes), when it departed the roadway on the right and was then returned to the roadway from the right.  Control over V1 was lost.  V1 skidded laterally in counter-clockwise rotation and departed the road on the left, where it then overturned (4 quarter turns, leading right).  During the rollover, Occupant 1 was totally ejected.  V1 came to rest on its wheels, facing a southwesterly direction in the median strip.

V1 was traveling in a northeasterly direction on a designated north/south divided trafficway (median strip without positive barrier) in lane 1 (of two lanes) and was approaching V2, which was traveling in the same direction, on the same roadway, and in the same lane, at a lower steady speed.  In lane 1, the front end of V1 came into contact with the back end of V2.  V1 became temporarily entangled with V2, and control over both vehicles was lost.  V2 departed the road on the right, where it then overturned (unknown number of quarter turns, leading right).  During its rollover, V2 (unknown plane) came into contact with a fence at the edge of the trafficway.  V1 disconnected from V2 and also departed the road on the right.  V1 came to rest on its wheels facing a northeasterly direction on the roadside, southwest of V2.  V2 came to rest on its right side, facing a southwesterly direction at the fence line.

V1 was traveling north in lane 4 on a 4-lane physically divided roadway. V2 was traveling north on the same roadway in front of V1. V3 was traveling on the same roadway in front of V2. The front of V1 contacted the back of V2 pushing the front of V2 into the back of V3. V1 rotated, departed the left road edge and its back plane contacted a concrete barrier. V1 came to rest on the paved shoulder facing north. V1 rotated and came to rest in lane 4 facing east. The final rest of V3 is unknown.

V1 was traveling from south to east (making a left turn) through an intersection from a two-way, not physically divided trafficway, and was in lane 1 (of two lanes). V2 was traveling east through the same intersection from a two-way, not physically divided trafficway (with two-way left turn lane), and was in lane 2 (of five lanes). V3 was traveling west approaching the same intersection from a two-way, not physically divided trafficway (with tow-way left turn lane), and was in lane 1 (of five lanes). In the intersection, the front end of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V2 rotated counterclockwise and entered the path of V3. East of the intersection, the right side of V2 contacted the front end of V3. V2 and V3 departed the road on the right, where the right front wheel/tire of V2 contacted the curb along the road edge, and V2's front end then contacted a tree. V1 came to rest on its wheels facing an easterly direction along the curb line (at the south road edge), east of the intersection. V2 came to rest on

V1 was traveling from west to south (making a left turn) through an intersection from a two-way, not physically divided trafficway, and was in lane 1 (of two lanes).  V2 was traveling north through the same intersection from a two-way, not physically divided trafficway, and was in lane 1 (of two lanes).  V3 was traveling south, approaching the same intersection from a two-way, not physically divided trafficway, and was in lane 1 (of two lanes).  In the intersection, the front end of V1 came in contact with the right side of V2.  V2 then entered the path of V3, and in the intersection, their front ends made contact.  V1 came to rest on its wheels, facing a southwesterly direction, in the intersection.  V2 came to rest on its wheels, facing a northerly direction, in the intersection, and northwest of V1.  V3 came to rest on its wheels, facing a southerly direction, in the intersection, and north of V2.

V1 was traveling northbound on a two way roadway with a single lane of travel in each direction. V2 was traveling in the same direction in front of V1. V3 was traveling in the same direction in front of V2. The frontal plane of V1 made contact with the rear plane of V2. The frontal plane of V2 made contact with the rear plane of V3. All vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling east in the first lane of a one-way, three-lane roadway. V2 was traveling east in the second lane of the same, one way, three-lane roadway. As V1 was changing lanes to the left, the frontal plane of V1 made contact with the right side plane of V2. Continuing forward, the left side of V1 impacted the right side of V2. After the impact, V1 departed the roadway to the right where it contacted a bush with its frontal plane. V2 came to rest in the roadway.
Vehicle #1 was traveling north on a two-way, two-lane road. V1 departed the road to the right, and the front plane of V1 contacted a utility pole. V1 came to rest partially off road to the east.

V1 was traveling east on a non physically divided two way street in lane one. V2 was legally parked on the right side of the eastbound street. V1 moved to its right and the front of V1 contacted the rear of V2, after the impact V1 overturned onto its left side. The initial impacted caused a chain reaction where the front of V2 impacted the rear of a legally parked vehicle in front of it, then the front of this vehicle impacted the rear of a parked vehicle in front of it. V1 came to rest on its left side in the eastbound lane facing east. V2 and the other parked vehicles all came to rest in the parking area facing southeast.

V1 was traveling southwest in lane one of a two-lane undivided roadway attempting to pass through an intersection. V2 was traveling southeast in lane two of a four-lane undivided roadway, attempting to pass through the same intersection. The right plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2. V2 came to final rest just past the intersection on the roadway. V1 departed the roadway after impact 1 and its front plane contacted a pole. V1 came to final rest off the roadway.

V1 and V2 were traveling eastbound, V1 was traveling behind V2, on a two-lane, two-way roadway negotiating a left hand curve. V3 was traveling westbound approaching the curve. V3 departed its lane on the left side where the front plane then struck the left side of V1, V3 continued forward and the front plane struck the front plane of V2. After the impact with V3, V1 departed the roadway and the right side struck the face of a guard rail. V1 came to final rest partially off the roadway facing northeast, V2 came to final rest at impact with V3, and V3 came to final rest in the eastbound lanes facing west.

Vehicle 1 was stopped at the intersection while in the southbound thru lane of a four lane undivided roadway. Vehicle 1 proceeded across the intersection, crossing the five lane median divided roadway. Vehicle 1 entered the eastbound lanes of travel and contacted the right side plane of vehicle 2 with its frontal plane. Vehicle 2 continued to travel rotating counter clockwise and entered into a rollover event onto its right side plane. During the rollover event vehicle 2 contacted a sign with its coming to rest on its right side plane in the eastbound lanes. Vehicle 1 rotated clockwise and came to rest within the intersection.

Vehicle 1 was traveling northbound in the second travel lane of a five lane, two way, roadway. Vehicle 2 was traveling westbound on an intersecting roadway making a turn left. Vehicle 1 attempted to avoid a collision by steering left but the front of Vehicle 2 struck the right side of Vehicle 1 (Event 1.) Vehicle 2 came to rest on the roadway. Vehicle 1 continued northbound entering into the southbound lanes. Vehicle 1 ran off the left side of the road. The front of Vehicle 1 impacted a mailbox (Event 2.) Vehicle 1 then started to roll eight quarter turns (Event 3.) Vehicle 2 came to final rest in the southbound lanes. Vehicle 3 ran over debris the roadway causing damage to the undercarriage (Event 4.) Vehicle 3 came to rest in the northbound lanes.

V1 was traveling northbound on a two-lane, two-way roadway approaching a four-way intersection. V2 was traveling eastbound on a four lane, two-way roadway passing through a four-way intersection, traveling in lane one. The front plane of V1 contacted the right plane of V2. V1 came to final rest further north on roadway. V2 came to final rest on roadway facing southeast.

V1 was traveling westbound on a physically divided trafficway with three lanes traveling westbound and three traveling eastbound. V1 lost control and departed the roadway on the right side where the front plane struck a wooden road sign. V1 continued eastbound off the roadway and came to final rest facing north.

V1 was traveling southbound on a three lane, two-way roadway, and V1 loss control. V1 departed the right side roadway and struck a sign. V1 then struck trees with its front right plane then rotated clockwise and contacted the tree line again before continuing to rotate and contacting the trees with the left plane. V1 then came to final rest off road.

V1 was traveling northeast on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway. A deer entered the roadway from the left hand (north) side of the roadway. V1 contacted the deer with its frontal plane; V1 then came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling west on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway. A deer entered the roadway from the southern shoulder, and V1 struck the deer with its frontal plane. V1 came to final rest partially on the roadway on the shoulder of the roadway.

V1 and V2 were both traveling north in lane three of a three-lane highway. V1 was ahead V2 when it departed the icy road on the left (west) side of the highway. V1 came to a stop in the grass median. V2 also departed the highway in the direction of V1. The front end of V1 struck the left side of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest in the median.

V1 and V2 were both traveling west in lane one on a two lane, two way, roadway. V2 was decelerating due to stopped traffic ahead and V1's front plane contacted V2's back plane. Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway a short distance from the initial contact.

Vehicle 1 was northbound on a two way, two lane roadway.  Vehicle 2 and Vehicle 3 were southbound on the same roadway.  Vehicle 2 was towing a trailer.  Vehicle 1 began rotating across the roadway striking vehicle 3 left plane with Vehicle 1's front plane.  Vehicle 1 continued to rotated northbound striking vehicle 2's front plane with Vehicle 1's left plane.  The trailer towed by V2 disconnected and impacted the rear plane of V2.  Vehicle 1 came to rest in the roadway facing east.  Vehicle 2 came to rest facing south in the roadway.  Vehicle 3 came to rest facing south on the southbound shoulder.
V1 and V2 were travelling South on a 5 lane 2 way not physically divided roadway. V2 was stopped for traffic light. V1 front plane struck V2 rear plane. Both vehicles came to rest facing South.

V1 was travelling North on a 2 lane 2 way not physically divided roadway. V2 was travelling West on a 2 lane 2 way not physically divided roadway. V3 was travelling South on a 2 lane 2 way not physically divided roadway. V1 entered the intersection and was struck on the right plane by V2 front plane. V2 pushed V1 front plane into V3 front plane. V1 came to rest facing East. V2 came to rest facing Northwest. V3 came to rest facing South

V1 was traveling southeast in lane one of a two lane undivided roadway. V1 was turning right when it departed the roadway to the left. V1's left plane contacted a pole twice before coming to final rest off the roadway in a ditch.

V1 was traveling east on a non physically divided two way highway in lane one, behind V2. V2 was traveling east on a non-physically divided two way highway in lane one, in front of V2. Due to traffic ahead, V2 came to a stop. V1 traveling at unknown speed, was unable to stop and the front of V1 impacted the rear of V2, as V1 steered right to avoid the impact. V1 and V2 came to rest on the east shoulder of the highway facing east.

V1 was entering the roadway from a driveway west bound across the north bound travel lane. V2 was traveling north on a two lane non-physically divided roadway in lane one.  As V1 entered the roadway, the front of V1 contacted the right side of V2. V1 came to rest in lane one facing north. V2 came to rest in the southbound lane facing north.

V1 was traveling east on a non physically divided four lane street in lane one. V2 was traveling west on a non physically divided four lane street in lane two. V1 attempting to change lanes to lane two, crossed into the westbound lanes and the front of V1 impacted the front of V2. V1 and V2 came to rest in the middle of the street facing a southerly direction.

V1 was traveling south west in the #1 lane of a 2 lane undivided roadway. The road curved left where V1 continued straight and departed the road. The front of V1 impacted a curb. V1 continued forward where the front impacts a bollard/post. V1 continues forward while rotating clockwise where the front of V1 impacts a bush. V1 continues to rotate where the front of V1 impacts a gas main. V1 came to rest facing west with the front of V1 against the gas main.

V1 and V2 were traveling north in the #1 lane of a 3 lane divided highway. V2 came to a stop due to traffic. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2. V1 continued forward left of V2 and began to rotate clockwise. V1 began to roll over leading with its left side. V1 came to rest on its wheel facing east between the #2 and #3 lanes. V2 came to rest still in the #1 lane facing north.

V1 was traveling eastbound in the first lane of a two lane, one-way divided roadway. V1 departed right from the first lane into the breakdown lane, in an attempt to take the off-ramp to continue travel southbound. Two non-contact vehicles were stopped in the breakdown lane. V1 then re-entered the roadway on the left into the first lane to avoid impact with those two vehicles. V1 then entered left into the second lane and then departed the roadway on the left. The frontal plane impacted a curb. V1 started to rotate clockwise, sideswiping the left side plane with the curb. V1 re-entered the roadway on the right and then crossed both the second and first lane and entered the off-ramp. The frontal plane of V1 impacted the jersey barrier. V1 came to final rest on the off ramp facing south.

V1 was traveling southwest in lane two on a two lane, positively divided roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right where its front plane contacted a utility pole. V1 rotated clockwise and came to final rest in the roadway, facing northeast. The vehicle was positioned across lanes one and two and was approximately 12 meters from the initial contact with the utility pole.

V1 was traveling northeast on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a left hand curve in the roadway. V2 was traveling southwest on the same roadway negotiating a right hand curve in the roadway. As V1 and V2 were negotiating the curve the front plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2. V1 and V2 came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling westbound in the first lane of a two lane, two-way roadway approaching the intersection. V2 was traveling southbound in the first lane of a two lane, two-way roadway approaching the same intersection as V1. Both V1 and V2 entered the intersection at the same time. The right side plane of V1 was impacted by the frontal plane of V2. As V2 rotated slightly clockwise it impacted the right side plane of V1 again. Both V1 and V2 came to final rest in the roadway: V1 facing west and V2 facing south.

V1 was traveling southbound in the first lane of a two lane, two-way roadway. V1 was attempting to take a left onto an intersecting roadway to continue traveling eastbound. As V1 took a left, it departed the roadway on the right. The frontal plane impacted a curb (Event 1.) V1 then began to rollover onto it's right side plane (Event 2.) The right side plane came into contact with the ground, as it made two quarter turns. V1 came to final rest off the roadway on it's top plane. The occupant seated in the right front seat was partially ejected from the vehicle.  The rear plane of V1 impacted an unknown object. (Event 3.)

Vehicle 1 was eastbound on a two way, two lane roadway.  Vehicle 2 was eastbound on the same roadway waiting to make a left turn.  Vehicle 1 front plane struck vehicle's 2 back plane.  Vehicle 1 and 2 came to rest facing eastbound in the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was northbound on a one way, two lane roadway.  Vehicle 1 swerved left across lane two.  Vehicle 1 swerved right and back to the left.  Vehicle 1 rotated counter clockwise into the median.  Vehicle 1 rolled, to the right, six quarter turns coming to rest on its top in the median facing south.

V1 and V2 were traveling north on a three-lane, two-way road approaching an intersection. V2 stopped at the intersection and the front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. Both vehicles came to rest at the point of impact.

V1 was traveling north on a two-lane, two-way road passing through an intersection. V2 was traveling east passing through the same intersection. V3 was traveling west through the same intersection. V1 and V2 entered the intersection at the same time and the front of V2 impacted the left side of V1. V1 continued northeast and its front plane impacted the front of V3 as V3 entered the intersection. All three vehicles came to rest in the intersection.

V1, V2, V3, and V4 were traveling north in the #1 lane of a 2 lane undivided roadway. V2, V3, and V4 came to a stop due to traffic. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2. V2 was pushed forward where the front of V2 impacted the back of V3. V3 was pushed forward where the front of V3 impacted the back of V4. V1 came to rest facing north in the #1 lane. V2 came to rest facing north in the #1 lane. V3 came to rest facing north in the #1 lane partially on the right shoulder. V4 came to rest facing north in the #1 lane.

V1 was traveling southbound in the number 1 lane of a 1 lane off-ramp. V1 departed the roadway to the left where the front of V1 impacted a plastic reflector post. V1 continued forward and the front of V1 hit a second plastic reflector post. V1 continued off the roadway rotating counter-clockwise where the front of V1 impacted a concrete culvert. V1 came to rest facing southerly in a ditch.

V1 was traveling south in lane 1 of a 3 lane, physically divided, two-way roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north in lane 4 of a 4 lane physically divided roadway with a left turn lane, approaching the same intersection.  As V2 made a left turn the front of V2 contacted the left of V1.  V1 rotated clock-wise and contacted a pole with the right plane before coming to final rest.

V1 was traveling northwest in lane one of a two lane roadway approaching a "T" type intersection. V1 departed the roadway forward through the intersection and the front plane contacted a tree. V1 came to rest off the roadway against the tree.

V1 was traveling northwest in lane two of a four-lane undivided roadway, negotiating a right curve. V2 was traveling south in lane two of the same roadway, negotiating a left curve. V1 departed it's travel lane to the left and the front plane of V1 contacted the left plane of V2. V1 came to final rest on the roadway north of impact and V2 came to final rest on the roadway south of impact.

V1 was traveling north in lane one of a two-lane undivided roadway, passing through an intersection. V2 was traveling southwest in lane one of a two-lane undivided roadway, passing through the same intersection. The front plane of V1 contacted the left plane of V2. V1 rotated counterclockwise and the right plane of V1 contacted the left plane of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway near impact.

V1 and V2 were traveling southwest in lane one of a five lane roadway negotiating a curve with V2 ahead if V1. V2 was decelerating to make a right turn into a private drive. V3 was stationary facing southeast in lane two of the three lane private drive waiting to make a left turn. V1's front plane contacted V2's rear plane. V1 came to rest in the roadway just past impact. V2 was pushed forward and its front plane contacted V3's left plane. V2 and V3 came to rest near impact.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south in lane one on a two lane, median with positive barrier divided roadway. A vehicle traveling in lane two was towing a trailer that lost one of its wheels. Vehicle 1 attempted to avoid this debris in the roadway and lost control. Vehicle 1 began to rotate clockwise and traveled off the roadway to the right. Vehicle 1 first struck a delineator post with its left side. Vehicle 1 continued off road where its left side struck a metal sign post. Vehicle 1 came to rest at the post, off of the roadway facing northwest.

V1, V2, and V3 were all westbound in the same lane of a two-lane road. V3 was the lead vehicle and stopped when the front of V2 struck its back end. Subsequently, V1’s front struck the back of V2. All three vehicles came to final rest on the road near the impact of impact.

V1 was traveling west on a two-lane, two-way roadway approaching the crest of a hill. V2 and V3 were traveling east on the mentioned roadway with V3 traveling behind V2. V1 departed its lane to the left side where the front plane struck the front plane of V2. After impact with V1 the front plane of V3 contacted the back plane of V2. V1 came to final rest in the roadway partially in the east lanes facing southwest. V2 came to final rest in the east lane facing east. V3 came to final rest near point of impact with V2 facing east.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a two lane roadway in lane one, approaching a highway exit ramp. V2 was traveling on the exit ramp in lane one of two lanes attempting to turn left and head west. In the intersection, the front plane of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V1 came to final rest in the roadway facing northeast and V2 came to final rest in the roadway facing north.

V1 was traveling south in lane two on a five lane, two-way roadway approaching an intersection.  V2 was traveling east in lane two on a six lane, divided roadway approaching the same intersection as V1.  V1 was turning left to travel east at the intersection when the front of V2 made contact with the right side of V1.  V1 and V2 came to final rest in the roadway.

V1 was heading north on a three-lane divided roadway in lane two. V1 departed its initial travel lane to the left, then the roadway. The front of V1 connected with the concrete barrier. V1 began a counter clockwise rotation as it climbed up the concrete traffic barrier. V1 rolled over to the right. V1 completed approximately 10 quarter turns before coming to final rest. V1 came to final rest approximately 230 feet north from point of impact on its top.

V1 was traveling north in lane 1 on a 5-lane roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling west in lane 1 on a 2-lane roadway approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection and the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V1 came to rest in the intersection facing northwest. V2 came to rest in the intersection facing northwest.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane, two-way roadway, approaching an intersection.  A NCV was traveling north on the same roadway approaching the intersection. At the intersection the NCV attempted a left turn and V1 steered to the right and departed the roadway. The front plane of V1 then contacted a curb.  V1 came to final rest off the roadway facing south west.

V1 was traveling north east on a two lane, two lane, undivided dirt road. V1 crossed over the road to the left departing the left road edge. The frontal plane of V1 contacted a cluster of trees. V1 came to final rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling south, leaving a business parking lot with the intention to pass through an intersection. V2 was traveling west in lane two of a four lane divided (with positive barrier) roadway, approaching the intersection. Within the intersection, the front of V2 impacted the left side of V1. V1 rotated counter clockwise and came to rest within the intersection, facing southeast. V2 came to rest with in the eastbound lanes, facing southwest.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane two way grass median divided trafficway in the second lane. V1 departed the roadway to the left, and the front of V1 contacted the ditch in the grass median. V1 returned to the opposite direction of the roadway and then departed that roadway to the left. V1 came to final rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane two way grass median divided roadway. The front of V1 contacted a non-stationary object which fell from another vehicle traveling in front of V1 on the roadway. V1 came to final rest in the roadway facing north.

Vehicle 1 was traveling in combination with a trailer westbound on an eight lane, median divided roadway in the first travel lane entering an intersection with a two lane non-divided roadway. Vehicle 2 was traveling south crossing the intersection and was contacted on the left side plane by the frontal plane of Vehicle 1. Vehicle 2 rotated clockwise after contact and its left side plane contacted the right side plane of Vehicle 1. Vehicle 1 came to rest on the roadway facing west. Vehicle 2 came to rest in the northwest corner of the intersection facing northwest.

V1 and V2 were southbound in the number 2 lane on a 3 lane physically divided roadway, which was snow covered. V1 began to overtake V2 on the left and began to yaw (unknown direction) and the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2, then the right of V1 contacted the left of V2. V1 continued to depart the roadway to the left and the front of V1 contacted a concrete barrier.

V1 was southbound on a 3 lane roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was westbound on a 4 lane, with a 2 way turn lane, roadway approaching the same intersection. Within the intersection the front of V1 contacted the front of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in the roadway.

V1 and V2 were traveling northbound on a two-lane, two-way roadway. V1 was traveling behind V2 in lane one when the front plane of V1 contacted the back plane of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway facing north.

V1 was traveling southbound on a three lane, two-way roadway passing through a T-shaped intersection. V2 was traveling eastbound on a two lane, two-way roadway, attempting to make a right turn. V1's front plane contacted V2's left plane. V1 came to final rest facing southbound on roadway. V2 came to final rest on roadway facing southbound.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north on a two lane, two-way roadway, in lane one. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway on the left and the front plane contacted a mailbox. Vehicle 1 continued forward and its front struck a ditch before overturning onto its right side where it came to final rest off road.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a three lane, grass median and cable barrier divided roadway, in lane one. Vehicle 1 departed the right side of the roadway. As V1 rotated clockwise, it tripped and rolled one-quarter turn left and came to rest on its left side facing north.

Vehicle #1 (V1) was traveling south in lane one of a two-lane divided trafficway without a positive barrier.  The front of V1 contacted an animal.  V1 came to rest near impact on the right shoulder, still facing south.

V1 was traveling east, following a two way, two lane road, in the first lane. V2 was traveling in front of V1 on the same two way, two lane road. V2 stopped in traffic. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway facing east.

Vehicle 1 and vehicle 2 were traveling east on a five lane, barrier divided roadway. Vehicle 1 was in lane one, vehicle 2 was in lane two. Vehicle 1 departed its lane of travel to the left and its front made contact with the rear of vehicle 2. Vehicle 2 departed its lane and continued onto the left shoulder where its left side impacted the concrete barrier. Vehicle 1 came to rest facing east in lane two. Vehicle 2 came to rest on the left shoulder, facing east against the barrier.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a 2- lane roadway approaching an intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling south on a 2- lane intersecting roadway. Both vehicles entered the intersection and the front of V1 contacted the right side of V2. V1 rotated clockwise as V2 rotated counter-clockwise and the left side of V1 contacted the right side of V2. V1 departed the southeast corner of the intersection and came to rest partially in a ditch facing north. V2 departed the southeast corner of the intersection as it rotated clockwise and its left side contacted a metal post. V2 came to rest partially in a ditch facing west.

Vehicles 1 and 2 were traveling north on a two lane, two-way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1 position. V1 was behind V2. V2 was stopped in traffic attempting to make a left turn. The front of V1 contacted the rear of V2. V1 came to rest just after impact. Final rest for V1 is just forward of the impact area.

V1 was traveling east in the westbound lanes of a positively divided, 7 lane roadway. V2 was traveling west on the same roadway, in lane 5. V1 traveled right, initating a U-turn and made contact with V2. The front plane of V1 struck the front plane of V2.  V1 rotated clockwise and V2 rotated counterclockwise.  The left side of V1 impacted the right side of V2.  Both vehicles came to rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling north in the first of three lanes on a divided, two-way roadway. V2 was traveling north in the same lane ahead of V1. V3 was traveling north in the same lane ahead of V2. The front of V1 contacted the back of V2. V2 was pushed forward and the front of V2 contacted the back of V3. All three vehicles came to rest. on the road in the original lane of travel.

V1, V2, V3, V4, were all southbound in lane 3 of 4 on a divided roadway. As traffic conditions slowed the front of V1 contacted the rear of V2. V4 came to a stop and the front of V3 contacted the rear of V4 pushing V4 forward and the front of V4 contacted the rear of V1. All vehicles came to rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling west in the first of three lanes on a positively divided, two-way highway. V2 was traveling west in the second lane of the same roadway, and stopped for traffic. V1 changed lanes to left. The front of V1 contacted the back of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in the roadway.

V1 and V2 were traveling northwest on a four lane divided roadway without a positive barrier.  V1 was in lane two and V2 was in lane one. V2 departed its initial travel lane to the left. The right of V1 contacted the left of V2 (event 1). V1 was redirected to the left where is started a counter clockwise rotation. V1 completed an 180 degree rotation before departing the roadway to the right. The back of V1 contacted a lamp pole (event 2) where is came to final rest facing southwest. V2 came to final rest near the point of impact.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway, through a four leg intersection. V2 was traveling west on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway, through the same four leg intersection. The frontal plane of V2 struck the right side plane of V1. V1 came to rest north of the intersection heading north. V2 came to rest west of the intersection heading west.

Vehicle #1 (V1) was traveling east in lane 4 of a four-lane divided trafficway without a positive barrier. Vehicle #2 (V2) was traveling west in lane 3 of the same trafficway.  Both vehicles entered the intersection. V1 began to make a left turn. The front of V1 contacted the left of V2. V1 came to final rest north near the point of impact. V2 came to final rest facing west also near the point of impact.

V1 was eastbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 departed the right side of the roadway impacting a guardrail face with the frontal plane causing damage. V1 then returned to the right side of the roadway and departed the travel lane to the left then went off the left side of the road. V1 then impacted another guardrail with the frontal plane causing damage. V1 came to final rest on the north side of the road facing east.

V1 was traveling west on a non-physically divided two way road in lane one, stopped at a stop sign at an intersection. V2 was traveling north on a non-physically divided two way road in lane one, approaching the same intersection. V1 was attempting a left turn when the left side of V1 was impacted by the front of V2. V1 rotated counter-clockwise, departed the southbound road edge then rolled 2-quarter turns right and came to rest on its top on the roadside facing south. V2 came to rest on the southbound roadside facing north.

V3, V1, and V2 were traveling east in order on a physically divided road with a positive barrier in lane one of two. V3 slowed due to sun glare and the front of V1 impacted the rear of V3. V3 departed the right side of the road and its right side impacted a guardrail. The front of V2 impacted the rear of V1.  All three vehicles came to rest in the road.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a 5 lane two-way non-physically divided roadway in lane number 2. Vehicle 2 was traveling south on a 5 lane two-way non-physically divided roadway in lane number 1. The Front of V2 contacted the left side of V1. Vehicle 1 came to rest in lane 4 facing northeast. Vehicle 2 came to rest in lane number 5 facing southeast.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. A deer crossed the road from the right, crossing paths with V1. The frontal plane of V1 contacted the deer. V1 came to final rest on the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north on a 3 lane, median divided roadway, in lane number 2. Vehicle 2 was traveling west on the intersecting one-way, not physically divided roadway, in lane number 2. Within the intersection, vehicle 1's right side and vehicle 2's front made contact with each other. Vehicle 1 came to rest in lane number 3 facing northwest. Vehicle 2 came to rest in their original lane facing west.

V1 was traveling west in lane 3 of a 3 lane physically divided, two-way roadway with a left turn lane approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling east in lane in lane 2 of a 4 lane, two-way, physically divided roadway with both right and left turn lanes approaching the same intersection. V1 turned left and entered the intersection simultaneously with V2. V1 right plane was contacted by V2 front plane.

V1 was traveling northbound on a two lane undivided two way traffic roadway in lane one. V1 departed its lane to the left and the roadway to the left. V1 rotated counter clockwise down an embankment and rolled over right side leading 3 quarter turns. V1 roll was interrupted by the undercarriage of V1 impacting a fence. V1 came to rest against the fence on it's left side facing southbound.

V1 was traveling northbound on a two lane undivided road (two way traffic) approaching a T intersection. V1 continued straight through the intersection and departed the roadway as an end departure. The front left and front right tires and undercarriage impacted the raised median. V1 came to rest facing northbound partially on the raised median.
V1 was traveling north, on a two lane, two way undivided roadway. The front of V1 contacted a deer in the roadway. V1 came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling north in the second of four lanes on an undivided, two-way road. V1 departed the lane on the left side, crossed through the southbound lanes and departed the roadway on the left side. The front of V1 contacted a fire hydrant. V1 continued off the roadway and contacted a pole. V1 came to rest off the road.

V1 was northbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 departed its initial travel lane to the left then the roadway to the left. V1 went airborne off a culvert impacting the frontal plane on the north side of the ditch causing damage. V1 then rolled left side leading two quarter turns onto its top. V1 came to final rest on its roof facing north.

V1 was traveling southwest in lane one of a two lane roadway. V1 departed the right road edge to avoid a non contacted vehicle and the undercarriage contacted a ditch. V1 came to rest off the right road edge.

V1 was traveling southwest in lane two of a five lane divided roadway attempting to pass through an intersection. V2 was traveling southeast in lane two of five lane divided roadway attempting to pass through the same intersection. V1's front plane contacted V2's left plane both vehicles came to rest near impact.

V1 was passing through an intersection while traveling west on a two-lane, two-way road with an incline. V2 was negotiating a curve to the left and passing through the same intersection while traveling south on a two-lane, two-way road. The right side of V1 impacted the left side of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in the intersection.

V1 was passing through a four-way intersection while traveling south on a two-lane, two-way road. V2 was passing through the same intersection while traveling east on a two-lane, two-way road. The front of V2 impacted the right side of V1. V1 came to rest on the southern road while V2 came to rest on the eastern road.

V1 was traveling in a southwesterly direction on a designated north/south divided trafficway (median strip without positive barrier), in lane 1 (of two lanes) when it departed the roadway on the right and was then returned to the roadway from the right. Control over V1 was lost. V1 skidded laterally in a counter-clockwise rotation and departed the road on the left, where it then overturned (8 quarter turns, leading right). During the rollover, Occupant 1 was totally ejected. V1 came to rest on its wheels, facing a northeasterly direction in the median strip.

V1 was traveling north through an intersection from a two-way, not physically divided trafficway, and was in lane 2 (of four lanes). V2 was traveling west through the same intersection from a two-way, not physically divided trafficway, and was in lane 1 (of five lanes). In the intersection, the front end of V2 contacted the right side of V1. V1 then rotated counter clockwise and the right side of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V1 continued in a southwesterly direction, where its left front wheel/tire contacted a curb. V1 came to rest on its wheels facing a southwesterly direction against the southern curb of the western leg of the intersection. V2 came to rest on its wheels facing a southwesterly direction in the northwestern quadrant of the intersection.

V1 was traveling east on a divided trafficway (median strip without positive barrier), in lane 2 (of two lanes), when it departed the road on the left, and was then returned to the road from the left.  Control over V1 was lost.  V1 skidded laterally in a counter-clockwise rotation and departed the road on the left, where it then overturned (8 quarter turns, leading right).  During the rollover, both Occupants were totally ejected.  V1 came to rest on its wheels, facing a westerly direction, in the median strip.

V1 was traveling north, on a two lane, two way undivided roadway. A deer was in the roadway and V1 departed the roadway to the left and it's front contacted a utility pole. V1 came to final rest off the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east in lane one on a two lane two way roadway. Vehicle 2 was traveling west on the same roadway. Vehicle 1 turned left into a private drive and the front plane of vehicle 1 contacted the left plane of vehicle 2. Upon impact vehicle 1 rotated counterclockwise and came to final rest facing northwest in its original travel lane. Vehicle 2 continued forward, departed the roadway on the right side, traveled down a ditch, and came to final rest off the roadway facing west.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north in lane one on a five lane two way roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right and the right front wheel of V1 contacted a curb. Vehicle continued forward and the front plane contacted a utility pole. Upon impact vehicle 1 rotated clockwise, overturned and contacted a fence. Vehicle 1 rolled eight quarter turns before coming to final rest off the roadway facing east.

V1 was traveling NB on lane 1 of a 2 lane, two-way, not physically divided roadway approaching a sign controlled intersection. V2 was traveling EB on lane 1 of a 2 lane, two-way, not physically divided roadway approaching the same intersection. V1 and V2 both entered the intersection simultaneously. V1’s left plane was contacted by the front plane of V2. V1 and V2 traveled while still connected, approximately 40ft off the roadway coming to final rest in a bean field.

V1 was traveling North on lane 1 of a 2 lane, two-way, not physically divided roadway approaching a sign controlled intersection. V2 was traveling West in lane 1 of a 2 lane, two-way, not physically divided roadway approaching the same intersection. V1 and V2 entered the intersection simultaneously. V1 front plane contacted V2 left plane. Both vehicle came to rest in the intersection.

V1 was traveling west on a three lane two way undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south on a four lane two way undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. In the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the right side of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 and V2 were traveling south on a two lane, two way undivided roadway approaching an intersection. In the intersection the front of V1 contacted the back of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling southeast in lane one of a two lane roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling southwest in lane one of a two lane roadway approaching the same intersection. V1's left plane contacted V2's front plane. V1's left plane then side slapped V2's right plane. V1 departed the right road edge and its under carriage contacted a ditch. V2 tripped and rolled right two quarter turns and contacting a power pole as it departed its left road edge. V2 came to final rest on its top.

V1 was traveling northeast in lane one of a two lane roadway approaching an intersection. V1 was attempting a left turn. V2 was traveling southeast in lane one of a two lane roadway approaching the same intersection. V1's front plane contacted V2's right plane. Both vehicles came to rest near impact.

V1 was traveling west in lane 2 on a 5 lane undivided roadway, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north turning left to go west in the number 2 lane of a 3 lane undivided roadway at the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection. The front of V1 impacted the right of V2. V2 rotated clockwise and came to rest facing north in the westbound lanes. V1 continued forward and began climb up the side of V2 and rolled right an unknown number of turns and came to rest in the westbound lanes facing west.

V1 was traveling south on a 5 lane roadway, in lane 3 and approaching an intersection. V1 left the lane to the right and continued off of the roadway, becoming airborne. V1's undercarriage contacted the ground in the southbound lanes of intersecting roadway. V1 then tripped and began to roll over concrete barrier. V2 was traveling northbound, in lane 3. V1's undercarriage contacted V2's top plane. V1 continued to roll and came to final rest on the roadway, in lane 1. V2 came to final rest on the shoulder.

V1 was traveling south in lane one of a two lane divided (with positive barrier) left curved downhill roadway, negotiating a curve. V1 departed the roadway to the right. V1 drove partially on the right shoulder before returning to the roadway to the original lane of travel where V1 started to rotate counter clockwise. V1 departed that lane and the roadway to the left while rotating counter clockwise. The front of V1 impacted the face of a guard rail. V1 kept rotating counter clockwise and impacted the sinking guard rail again with its front right. V1 continued to move south while in a counter clockwise rotation and  entered a raised median. V1 started to roll over right side leading for at 8 quarter turns before it impacted a light pole on the median with its right side. V1 came to rest at the pole facing east.

V1 was traveling north in lane one of a three lane divided (no positive barrier) straight highway. V1 departed the highway to the right. The driver was able to steer back onto the highway. V1 crossed lane one and lane two before the driver corrected the vehicle again to the right. V1 crossed all lanes to the right and departed the highway to the right. V1 crossed over a grass area before impacting a tree with its front. V1 rotated clockwise around the tree before coming to rest at the tree facing northeast.

V1 was traveling southbound in lane 2, on a 3 lane, one way roadway and approaching an interchange. V2 was traveling on the same roadway, in lane 3. V1 changed lanes to the left. V1's back contacted V2's front. Both vehicles came to rest on the roadway.

V1 was east bound on a two lane, non divided bidirectional roadway, when a deer entered the roadway from the north side. The deer was hit by a tractor trailer travelling west which redirected the deer into V1. V1's frontal plane impacted the animal. The animal rotated down the left side of the vehicle, and impacted the left side of the vehicle. V1 came to final rest on the right side of the roadway.

V1 was traveling west in the first of two lanes on a two-way road divided by a median. V1 veered off to the right, leaving the road and the front of V1 struck a light pole and then a fence and then multiple shrubs, until coming to a rest.

V2 was traveling south on a two way two lane undivided roadway. V1 was traveling north on the same roadway as V2. V1 departed the left hand lane line. V2 in an attempt to avoid V1 departed the left hand lane line, and the right side plane of V2 contacted an unknown plane of V1. V1 and V2 both came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling southbound on a four lane, undivided roadway in lane two approaching an intersection. V2 was northbound on a three lane, undivided roadway in lane two approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection and the front of V2 impacted the right side of V1. Both vehicles came to final rest in the intersection.

V1 was traveling southbound on a two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a left curve. V1 departed the roadway to the right, the front of V1 impacted a tree. The impact caused the tree to shear and the tree fell on top of V1. V1 came to rest facing south.

V1 was traveling northeast on a four lane, two way, median divided roadway. The front right tire of V1 failed while traveling on the roadway causing V1 to lose control. V1 proceeded to depart their initial travel lane over the left hand lane line, returned to their initial travel lane, and then departed the right hand side of the roadway. V1 struck a sign with its right side plane before coming to final rest off of the roadway.

V1 was traveling westbound in the single lane one-way roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling southbound in the single lane one-way roadway approaching the same intersection as V1. Both V1 and V2 entered the intersection at the same time. The right side plane of V1 was impacted by the frontal plane of V2. V1 and V2 came to final rest in the roadway: V1 facing west and V2 facing south.

V1 was traveling south on a two-way, three lane undivided roadway, approaching an intersection controlled by a traffic signal. V2 was traveling west on a two-way, two lane undivided road-way, approaching the same intersection as V1. Both vehicles entered the intersection. The frontal plane of V1 contacted the right side plane of V2. V1 continued forward and came to a final rest in the roadway. V2 continued forward spinning in a clockwise direction into the eastbound lane. V3 had been traveling east on the same two way, two lane undivided roadway approaching the same intersection that V2 was crossing over. V3 was stopped at a traffic signal at this intersection and the left side plane of V2 made contact with the front plane of V3. Both V2 and V3 came to a final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling west, in lane one, on a two lane, two way, non-divided roadway. While negotiating a left curve in the roadway, V1 departed the roadway to the right and contacted a tree with its front plane. V1 came to final rest at the base of the tree, approximately 41 meters after road departure.

V1 was traveling south in lane one on a two lane, two way, non-divided roadway and was negotiating a right curve in the roadway. V2 was traveling north on the same roadway and was negotiating a left curve in the roadway. V1 then departed the roadway on the right side, returned to the roadway, and departed its lane on the left side. V1's front plane then contacted V2's front plane. V1 came to final rest, on the roadway, approximately 11 meters from contact. V2 was pushed rearward and departed the roadway on the right side. The vehicle then traveled down an embankment backwards and came to final rest approximately 17 meters from point of contact.

V1 was traveling east on an undivided two-way traffic, 5 lane road in lane 1 approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north on an undivided two-way traffic, 3 lane road in lane 1. At the intersection, V1 turned right to the south, then immediately turned left to attempt to enter a private drive. The front of V2 then impacted the right side of V1. V1 rotated clockwise and came to rest in the private drive facing south. V2 came to rest partially in the private drive and lane 1 facing northeast.

V1 was traveling westbound a two-lane neighborhood street approaching a four-way intersection. V2 was traveling north a two-lane neighborhood street approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection and the front of V2 struck the left side of V1 (event 1). Subsequently, the left side of V1 struck the right side of V2 (event 2). V1 continued to off the northeast corner of the intersection and its front end struck a fence (event 3) and a came to final rest against a house (event 4). V2 came to final rest in the road facing northwest.

V1 was traveling west on a four lane two way grass median divided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling east on a four lane two way grass median divided roadway approaching the same intersection. In the intersection, V1 attempted a left hand turn and the right side of V1 contacted the front of V2.  Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 and V2 were traveling south in lane 1 of a four lane two way not positively divided roadway approaching an intersection. At the intersection the front of V1 contacted the back of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was northbound on a 5 lane (2 way with middle turn lane) roadway, in Lane 3 and attempting a left turn. V2 was southbound on a 6 lane (2 way with middle turn lane) roadway in the number 2 lane. The front of V1 contacted the front of V2. Both vehicles came to rest within the roadway.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two-way, non-physically divided roadway on the right side shoulder area of the roadway attempting to make a left turn into a private drive. V2 was traveling south on the same two lane, two-way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1 position. The right side of V1 contacted the front of V2. V1 came to rest just after impact facing west on the sidewalk. V2 came to rest just after impact still in lane 1 facing south west.

Vehicle 1 was traveling eastbound on a 7 lane physically divided trafficway in the lane 4 making a left hand turn.  Vehicle 2 was traveling westbound on a 7 lane physically divided trafficway in the lane 1 going straight.  Both vehicles entered the intersection at the same time.  The left plane of Vehicle 1 made contact with the front plane of Vehicle 2.  Vehicle 1 came to final rest at the southern portion of the intersection facing southeast.  Vehicle 2 came to final rest just after impact facing roughly southeast in the southern portion of the intersection.

Vehicle was traveling southeast in lane one on a two lane roadway. The front plane of Vehicle 1 made contact with a deer crossing from the left. Vehicle 1 came to rest on the right side of the road shortly after the deer strike facing southeast.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a two lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1 position. A Deer attempted to cross the roadway. The front left of V1 contacted the deer. V1 departed roadway right side. Entered and traveled over an paved access drive, coming to rest after crossing access drive facing east.

V1 was traveling north on a rural roadway passing through a four leg intersection. The roadway V1 was traveling on had a left jog. V1 went straight through the intersection missing the jog and struck a fence with its frontal plane. V1 came to final rest at in an open field northeast of the intersection.

V1 was traveling north in lane two of a five lane, two-way, not physically divided roadway approaching an intersection with a left and right turn lane. V2 was making a left turn in lane four of a four lane, not physically divided, two-way roadway approaching the same intersection with both a left and right turn lane. Both V1 and V2 entered the intersection simultaneously. V1 front plane contacted V2 right plane. Both Vehicle came to rest in the roadway.

V1 was departing a 2 lane private driveway to the west. V2 was traveling east in lane 2 on a 5 lane roadway, with 2 way left turn lane. V1's front contacted V2's front. Both vehicles came to rest within the roadway.

V1 was traveling south in the #2 lane of a 5 lane undivided roadway. V2 was traveling north in the #3 lane of a 5 lane undivided roadway. V2 turned left to head west. The front of V1 impacted the front of V2. V1 rotated clockwise and came to rest facing west in both the #1 and #2 lanes. V2 rotated counter clockwise and came to rest facing south in the southbound #1 lane.

V1 was traveling eastbound in a single lane roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling northbound in a single lane roadway, approaching the same intersection as V1. Both V1 and V2 entered the intersection at the same time. The frontal plane of V1 impacted the left side plane of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway: V1 facing east and V2 facing west.

V1 was traveling northbound in the number 3 lane of a 6 lane divided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling eastbound in the number 1 lane of a 5 lane divided roadway approaching an intersection. V3 was traveling eastbound in the number 3 lane of a 5 lane divided roadway approaching an intersection. All vehicles entered the intersection. The front of V1 impacted the right side of V2. The force of the collision pushed V2 northerly where the left side of V2 impacted the right side of V3. V1 came to rest facing a southerly direction in the intersection. V2 came to rest facing north in the intersection north of V1. V3 came to rest facing an easterly direction on the east side of the intersection.

V1 and V2 were traveling west on a two lane two way roadway approaching an intersection. In the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the back of V2. V2 proceeded to the north west corner of the intersection, the front of V2 contacted a fence off the roadway and came to final rest. V1 came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 and V2 were traveling east on a two lane two way grass median divided roadway traveling through an intersection. On the east side of the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the back of V2. V1 then rotated counter-clockwise and came to final rest off the road edge. V2 came to final rest on the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north in lane 1 on a 3-lane divided roadway negotiating a right curve. V2 was parked facing north on the shoulder of the same road. V1 departed the roadway to the right and its front plane contacted the back plane of V2. V1 rotated clockwise, departed the road where its front plane contacted a dirt/grass embankment. V1 came to rest against the embankment facing east. V2 rotated clockwise and came to rest off the road facing northeast.

V1 was traveling east in lane 2 on a 3-lane roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north in lane 2 on a 4-lane divided roadway approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection and the right side of V1 was impacted by the front of V2. V1 rotated counter-clockwise. V2 rotated clockwise. The right side of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V1 came to rest facing north at the northeast corner of the intersection. V2 came to rest facing east on the east side of the intersection.

V1 was traveling north in the #4 lane of a 5 lane divided roadway. V1 traveled through an intersection. V1 steered left and traveled off the road to the left. The front of V1 impacted a large bush. V1 continued forward where the front of V1 impacted a wooden post. V1 continued forward where the front of V1 impacted another large bush. V1 continued forward and came to rest in a grass/dirt field facing northwest.

V1 was traveling east on a two-way, not physically divided trafficway, in lane 1, when it departed the roadway on the right, then returned to the roadway.  Control over V1 was lost as V1 skidded laterally in a clockwise rotation and departed the road on the right, where its front end came in contact with an earthen embankment.  V1 then overturned (2 quarter turns, leading left).  During the rollover, V1's top plane came in contact with a wooden utility pole on the roadside, and V1 rolled over one quarter turn back to the right (due to entanglement with the pole, its lines, and their tension).  V1 then came to rest on it left side, facing a southerly direction on the roadside.

V1 was traveling south in lane 2 on a 5-lane roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling west in lane 1 on a 2-lane roadway approaching the same intersection. V2 began to turn left in the intersection and V2 was passing through the intersection when the front of V1 contacted the right side of V2. V1 continued forward and came to rest in the southwest corner of the intersection facing south. V2 rotated counter-clockwise and departed the southwest corner of the intersection where its right front then right rear tire contacted a curb. The front of V2 then contacted a pole and came to rest facing southwest.

Vehicle 1 (V1) and vehicle 2 (V2) were traveling east in lane four of a four-lane divided highway with a concrete center barrier. V2 was ahead of V1. The front plane of V1 contacted the back plane of V2 (event 1). V2 began to yaw counter-clockwise on the wet pavement and departed the road to the left. V2’s front plane contacted the concrete barrier (event 2). V2 continued to rotate, and its right plane contacted the barrier two more times (events 3 and 4). V2 came to rest on the shoulder facing west. V1 fled the scene to the east.
