V1 and V2 were traveling west in lane one on a five lane, two-way roadway with V2 stopped for traffic in front of V1.  V1 glanced off of the right curb edge, was redirected back into its original path then the front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. Both vehicles came to rest just forward of impact.

V1 was traveling southeast on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a slight right hand curve in the roadway. Them front plane of V1 contacted a cow in the roadway. V1 continued forward and its right side contacted the cow. V1 came to rest in its original lane facing southeast.

V1 was traveling east in lane two of a three lane one-way road, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north in lane two of a two-lane service road, approaching the same intersection. Within the intersection, the front of V2 impacted the right side of V1. V1 rotated clockwise and departed the roadway to the north. The left rear wheel of V1 impacted a raised curb. The left side of V1 impacted a light pole. V1 came to rest at the light pole, facing southeast. V2 came to rest north of the intersection in lane 2, facing north.

V1 was traveling north west in the #1 lane of a 2 lane undivided roadway. V1 steered right at an intersection. V1 departed the roadway to the right where the front of V1 impacted a light pole. V1 came to rest facing north with the front end against the light pole and partially still in the roadway.

V1 was traveling south west in the #2 lane of a 2 lane divided roadway. V2 was traveling south in the #2 lane of a 3 lane undivided roadway. V2 entered the intersection turning left. The front of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V2 rotated clockwise where the right side of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V1 came to rest facing south west in the roadway. V2 came to rest facing south west in the roadway.  After coming to rest, V1 experienced a minor post-crash fire.

V1 was turning right out of a parking lot heading east. V2 was eastbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway approaching the same parking lot exit. The left of V1 impacted the front of V2 causing damage. V1 rotated clockwise coming to final rest in the eastbound lane facing east. V2 departed its travel lane to the left then departed the left side of the roadway impacting a curb. V2 came to final rest off the north side of the road facing east.

V3, V2, and V1 were traveling east on a three-lane, two-way road. V3 stopped for a non-contacted vehicle that was traveling in the same direction making a left turn into a business. V2 also slowed down. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2, pushing V2 forward. The front of V2 then impacted the rear of V3. All three vehicles came to rest in their original lanes of travel.

V1 was traveling north on a two-lane, two-way road that curved to the left. V1 departed the road to the right side. The front of V1 struck the median of a two-lane, two-way side road, crossing over both lanes and coming to rest off of the right side of the road.

V1 was southbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway negotiating a left curve. V1 departed the right side of the road impacting a ditch and overturned, left side leading, 4 quarter turns before coming to final rest on its wheels facing west.

V1 was southbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway approaching a temporary stoplight in a construction zone. V2 was stopped at the same stoplight. The front of V1 struck the rear of V2 causing damage. V1 then departed the right side of the roadway, impacting two trees with the frontal plane before coming to rest facing southwest. V2 came to final rest facing south in its initial travel lane.

V1 was traveling in a southern direction of travel, on a two lane, non divided, bidirectional roadway, negotiating a curve to the left. V1 departed the roadway to the right, where its right plane impacted a guardrail. V1 continued south, and returned to the roadway. V1 crossed into the north bound lane of travel, over corrected, and began to rotate clockwise. V1 departed the roadway to the right, where its rear plane impacted an embankment. V1 continued up a hill that ended with an abrupt drainage culvert. V1 entered a drainage culvert impacting its frontal plane.V1 also impacted an unknown object with its rear plane and its left plane. V1 came to final rest in the drainage culvert.

Vehicle #1 was traveling west in a channelized left turn lane.  Vehicle #2 was traveling east in lane one of a two-lane, divided roadway without a positive barrier.  V1 began to turn left at an intersection and the right of V1 contacted the front of V2.  Both vehicles came to rest in the intersection, facing southeast.

V1 was traveling north on a three lane non-physically divided roadway in lane one behind V2. V2 was raveling north on a three lane non-physically divided roadway in lane one behind V3. V3 was traveling north on a three lane non-physically divided roadway in lane one. V3 and V2 both began to decelerate in the road when the front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. The momentum of the impact caused the front of V2 to impact the rear of V3. All three vehicles came to rest facing north in lane one.

V1 was traveling south on a non-physically divided three lane road in lane one. For an unknown reason, V1 drifted off the right road edge, and turned left back onto the roadway where V1 lost control and over turned onto its roof where it skid across the south and northbound lanes. V1 came to rest on its roof within the northbound shoulder facing a northeast direction.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane undivided road approaching a T-intersection. V2 was traveling north on a four lane undivided roadway in lane two approaching the same T-intersection. V1 initiated a left turn at the intersection and the front of V1 impacted the front of V2. The post-crash momentum carried both vehicles to the west road edge where the front of V2 impacted an embankment. Both vehicles came to rest on the west road edge facing west.

V1 was traveling westbound in the number 3 lane of a 3 lane divided roadway, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling eastbound in the number 4 lane of a 5 lane divided roadway, approaching an intersection preparing to turn left. Both vehicles entered the intersection. The front of V1 impacted the front of V2. V2 began rotating counter-clockwise as V1 pushed it westerly. V2 came to rest facing westerly on the west side of the intersection. V1 disengaged from V2 and began rotating clockwise, coming to rest facing northerly on the west side of the roadway.

V1 was traveling southeast in the number 1 lane of a 2 lane divided roadway, approaching an intersection. V1 traveled through the intersection and departed the road to the right, where V1 traveled up a dirt embankment contacting the front bumper before rotating clockwise. V1 then tripped over and began to roll on its left side. V1 continued to roll over and came to rest on its wheels on the west side of the roadway, facing northwest.

V1 was traveling south in the #3 lane of a 5 lane divided roadway. V2 was traveling south in the #2 lane of a 5 lane divided roadway. V2 was slowing down due to traffic. V1 changed lanes into the #2 lane. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2. V1 and V2 came to rest facing south in the roadway.

V1 was traveling northwest on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a left hand curve in the roadway. V1 departed the right hand (east) side of the roadway and then attempted to steer left reentering the roadway. V1 continued forward and after attempting to steer right began to lose control rotating in a clockwise direction. V1 again departed the right hand side of the roadway contacting an embankment with its frontal plane. V1 then rolled one quarter turn with its left side leading where it came to final rest off of the roadway.

V1 was traveling southeast in lane 3 on a three lane divided roadway attempting to turn left at an intersection. V2 was traveling northwest in lane 2 on a two lane divided roadway approaching the same intersection. As both vehicles entered the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V1 rotated counter-clockwise and came to rest in the intersection facing north. V2 continued forward and came to rest on the roadway facing north.

Vehicle 1 was traveling southwest on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 traveled off the left side of the roadway and struck a fence with its frontal plane (event 1). V1 then struck another fence with its frontal plane (event 2). V1 then traveled across a two lane, two way, undivided roadway and struck a pole (event 3), this pole fell across the hood of V1 (event #4). V1 then contacted fence (event 5). V1 came to rest near the last point of impact facing south.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a two lane, divided roadway in lane one negotiating a right curve. V1 then departed the roadway to the right, the front of V1 impacted a light pole. V1 rotated clockwise and came to rest partially in lane one facing southeast.

V1 was traveling north on a 2-lane roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling west in lane 1 on a 4-lane roadway approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection and the right side of V1 was contacted by the front of V2. V1 rotated counter-clockwise as V2 rotated clockwise and the right side of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V1 came to rest off the roadway facing northwest and V2 came to rest on the roadway facing northwest.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane undivided roadway. V2 was legally parked on the right side of the road. The front of V1 contacted the left of V2 (event 1). V1 began to rotate clockwise. V1 tripped over two quarter-turns to the left. V1 came to final rest on its top facing northwest.

V1 was traveling east on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a left hand curve in the roadway. V2 was traveling in front of V1 and on the same roadway as V1. V2 was decelerating in the roadway due to a non-contacted school bus in the westbound lane, and while V2 was decelerating the front plane of V1 contacted the rear plane of V2. V1 and V2 both came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling north in the second of five lanes on a divided, two-way roadway entering a light controlled, four-legged intersection. V2 was traveling west in the fourth of four lanes on a divided, two-way roadway entering the same intersection as V1. Within the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. The vehicles rotated towards each other and the left side of V1 contacted the right side of V2 in a side-slap configuration. V1 then entered a counter-clockwise yaw, where the right rear rim impacted a curb. This caused V1 to roll two-quarter turns coning to rest on its roof off the roadway. V2 came to rest within the intersection.

V1 and V2 were both traveling northwest in lane one on a two lane, divided roadway. V2 stopped for traffic ahead and V1's front plane contacted V2's rear plane. After the initial impact, the vehicles separated and V1's front plane contacted V2's rear plane a second time at a very low speed. Both vehicles then came to final rest on the roadway, in lane one, a short distance from the two impacts.

V1 was traveling west in lane two on a three lane, non positively divided, roadway and was approaching an intersection. V1 began turning left to travel southwest in lane one on a two lane, non-positively divided roadway, when the vehicle began to hydroplane. V1 then rotated in a counter clockwise direction and departed its lane on the left side. V1 then rotated in a clockwise direction in lane two, struck a median curb, departed the roadway on the left side, and began a left leading roll over. During the rollover, V1's left side plane contacted a sign post. V1 continued to roll two quarter turns and came to final rest on its roof. The vehicles final rest position was in lane three of the northeast traffic lanes of the roadway.

V1 was eastbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 departed the right side of the roadway traveling down an embankment and over a gravel driveway. V1 impacted a sign with the left plane before overturning, left side leading, two quarter turns. V1 came to final rest on its roof  facing west.

V1 was northbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was eastbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway approaching the same intersection.  Both vehicles entered the intersection.  The front plane of V1 struck the front plane of V2 causing damage. V1 spun clockwise departing the southeast section of the intersection coming to final rest in the ditch facing south. V2 continued east departing the right side of the roadway coming to final rest in the ditch facing south.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane divided roadway in lane one. For unknown reasons, V1 departed the right road edge and the front of V1 impacted a tree. V1 came to rest against the tree facing a northwesterly direction.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north on a 7 lane, two way, median divided traffic way in lane 4 position approaching an intersection attempting to make a left turn. V2 was traveling south on a 7 lane, two way, median divided traffic way in lane 3 position approaching the same intersection attempting to pass through it and continue south. Both vehicles entered the intersection. V1's right rear side contacted the front of V2. V1 spun in a clockwise rotation and was facing north at final rest in the intersection. V2 came to rest facing south west in the intersection.

Vehicles 1 and 2 were traveling east on a 5 lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1 position. Vehicle 1 was behind Vehicle 2. V2 was behind a non contact vehicle attempting to make a right turn into a parking lot. V2 slowed for the non contact vehicle and the front of V1 contacted the rear of V2. Both vehicles came to rest at impact facing east.

Vehicle 1 was traveling southbound on a two lane non-physically divided roadway approaching an intersection attempting to make a left turn. Vehicle 2 was traveling westbound on the intersecting two lane non-physically divided roadway. Both vehicles entered the intersection at the same time and the front of V2 contacted the left side of V1. Vehicle 1 spun clockwise and was pushed west out of the intersection departing the roadway and coming to rest shortly after impact with barbed fence. Vehicle 2 departed the roadway left side coming to rest shortly after impact with a chain fence. Vehicle was facing north and Vehicle 2 was facing south.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a two-lane, two-way road. V1 departed the right side of the road and its front plane struck a sign post. V1 continued back into its original lane of travel where it came to rest on the right side of the road.

V1 and V2 were traveling south on a two-lane, two-way road. V1 was stopped in lane one. V2 was stopped in the breakdown lane. It is noted that the breakdown lane has parking signs. V2 started to make a right turn. V1 also started to make a right turn at the same time. The front of V1 impacted the left side of V2 two separate times. V2 came to rest on the side of the road and V1 continued into the parking lot off of the right side of the road where it came to rest.

V1 was negotiating a right curve, following a two-way, two lane road, traveling southwest. V1 departed its original travel lane to the left and then the road to the left. Continuing forward, the front of V1 impacted a pole, knocking it in half. The left side of V1 impacted a shrub. The right side impacted the pole again as it snapped before coming to final rest off the roadway facing west..

Vehicle 1 was traveling in the third eastbound lane of a 6 lane median divided roadway. Vehicle 1 contacted its frontal plane with a deer that was in the the travel lane. Vehicle 1 came to rest on the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was travelling eastbound on the three lane undivided roadway, making a left turn at the intersection with a three lane undivided roadway. Vehicle 2 was travelling westbound on the same roadway passing thru the intersection. Vehicle 1 contacted the frontal plane of V2 with the frontal plane of V1.  Both vehicles came to rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a four-lane, two-way roadway in lane two making a left hand turn intending to head south. V2 was traveling on the mentioned roadway in lane one traveling westbound. In the middle of the intersection the front plane of V2 contacted the right side of V1. After impact V1 departed the roadway on the southwest corner where the front plane struck a decorative rock. V1 came to final rest off the roadway against the rock facing south. V2 came to final rest in the roadway facing south.

V1 was traveling south on a painted flush median divided left curved roadway.  V1 departed the right road edge and the front struck a metal utility pole.  V1 came to final rest off the roadway facing south.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a two-lane, two-way roadway. V1 departed the roadway on the right side where the front plane struck a legally parked vehicle. V1 entered a clockwise rotation and rollover over four quarter turns, left side leading. V1 came to final rest in the roadway facing south.

V1 was traveling west on a two way, five lane roadway in the first westbound lane.  V2 was traveling south on a three lane divided intersecting roadway in the second southbound lane.  In the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the left of V2.    Both vehicles continued southwest.  V1 came to final rest partially off the roadway on the southwest corner and V2 came to rest in the first southbound lane along the curb near the southwest corner.

V1 was traveling east in the third of three lanes on a divided, two-way roadway entering a light controlled, four-legged intersection attempting to turn left. V2 was traveling west in the second of four lanes on a divided, two-way roadway entering the same intersection as V1. Within the intersection, the right side of V1 contacted the front of V2. Both vehicles  came to rest in the road..

V1 was traveling south in lane 2 on a 4-lane roadway negotiating a right curve when it departed the left curb edge and its front plane contacted a tree. A portion of the tree broke away and contacted the front left windshield header. V1 continued forward and its right plane contacted a tree in 2 separate areas. V1 continued forward where its front plane contacted another tree. V1 rotated clockwise and came to rest facing south.

V1 was eastbound in lane 2 on a 5 lane roadway approaching a 3 way intersection. V2 was southbound on a 3 lane roadway approaching the same intersection. V3 was westbound on a 4 lane roadway stopped at the same intersection. Within the intersection the front of V1 contacted the right side of V2. V2 was then pushed into V3 where the left side of V2 contacted the front of V3. All vehicles came to rest in the roadway.

V1 was negotiating a left curve in the third of five lanes on an undivided, two-way roadway entering a light controlled, four-legged intersection attempting to turn left. V2 was negotiating a right curve southeast in the second of five lanes entering the same intersection as V1. Within the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V1 came to rest in the road. V2 came to rest partially off the south corner of the intersection.

Vehicle #1 was traveling west.  V1 turned left onto an intersecting two-lane, undivided roadway.  V1 departed the road to the right and the RF tire of V1 contacted the curb.  The front of V1 then contacted a mailbox.  V1 re-entered the roadway.  V1 left the immediate crash scene and came to rest in the next intersection.

V1, V2 and V3 were all traveling northbound in the second lane of a four lane, two-way roadway, approaching a four-legged intersection. V2 was the lead vehicle stopped ahead of V1. V1 was middle vehicle slowing for traffic. The frontal plane of V3 impacted the rear plane of V1. Subsequently, the frontal plane of V1 struck the rear plane of V2. All three vehicles came to final rest facing north in the second lane of the roadway.

V1 was traveling north west in the #1 lane of a 2 lane undivided roadway. V1 departed the road to the right. The front of V1 impacted a plastic reflector. V1 continued forward where the front of V1 impacted a fence. V1 rotated clockwise and came to rest back in the #1 lane facing north.

V1 and V2 were traveling east in the #2 lane of a 3 lane divided roadway. V3 was traveling west in the #2 lane of a 3 lane divided roadway. V4 was traveling west in the #1 lane of a 3 lane divided roadway. V2 came to a stop at an intersection. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2. V2 traveled across the intersection and departed the roadway to the left into the center median. V2 crossed the center median and into the westbound lanes where the front of V2 impacted the front of V3. V3 rotated clockwise where the right side of V3 impacted the left side of V4. V1 after impacting V2 rotated clockwise and came to rest facing south in the middle of the intersection. V2 after impacting V3 rotated counter clockwise and came to rest facing north in the #2 lane of the westbound lanes. V3 came to rest facing north between the #1 and #2 westbound lanes. V4 steered their car to the right shoulder and came to rest facing west on the shoulder of the westbound lanes.

V1 was making a left turn while on a two-lane, two-way road traveling north after making a right hand turn from a side street. V2 was traveling south on the same road. V2 departed its lane over the left lane line and its front plane impacted the front plane of V2. V2 came to rest in the road at the point of impact. V1 continued to travel down the road for several meters before coming to rest on the right side of the road.

Vehicle #1 was traveling east in lane two of a three-lane divided roadway without a positive barrier.  Vehicle #2 was traveling north in lane one of an intersecting three-lane undivided roadway.  Both vehicles entered the intersection and the front of V1 contacted the left of V2.  V2 rotated clockwise and the right of V1 contacted the left of V2.  Both vehicles came to rest near impact.

Vehicle #1 was traveling southwest in lane one of a three-lane divided roadway without a positive barrier.  Vehicle #2 was traveling southeast in lane one of an intersecting divided roadway without a positive barrier.  V2 began to turn left at the intersection and the front of V1 contacted the left of V2. V1 came to rest in the intersection, facing southwest.  V2 came to rest in the intersection, facing northeast.

V1 was traveling east in the #1 lane of a 3 lane undivided roadway. V2 and V3 were stopped in the #1 lane of a 3 lane undivided roadway due to traffic at a crosswalk. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2. V2 was pushed forward and the front of V2 impacted the back of V3. All vehicles came to rest facing east in the #1 lane.

V1 was traveling southbound on a four lane, undivided roadway in lane two approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling northbound on a two lane, undivided roadway in lane one approaching the same intersection. At the intersection V1 attempted to turn left as V2 proceeded straight and the front of V2 impacted the front of V1. V1 rotated counter clockwise and V2 rotated clockwise and the front of V2 contacted the right side of V1. V1 came to rest inside the intersection facing east. V2 rotated clockwise and came to rest inside the intersection facing northeast.

V1 and V2 were traveling on a two lane, divided roadway traveling east. V3 was stopped in the opening between the medians, attempting to turn left with it's trailer partially in lane 2. V2 stopped due to the trailer being in the lane. V1 impacted the back of V2, V2 rotated counter clockwise and the right side of V2 impacted the back of V3's trailer. V2 continued to rotate and came to rest in lane two facing west. V1 came to rest in the private drive south of impact facing southeast. V3 came to rest in the private drive north of impact.

V1 was traveling north in lane one of a two-lane undivided roadway, negotiating a left curve. V1 departed its travel lane to the left, then departed the roadway to the left. The front plane of V1 contacted a ditch. V1 continued traveling off the roadway for a short distance before coming to final rest in the ditch.

V1 was traveling east negotiating a right curve in lane one of a two lane roadway. V1 departed its travel lane to the left then departed the left road edge. V1's undercarriage contacted a ditch/culvert, and continued moving until the front plane contacted a tree were it came to rest.

V1 was traveling southwest in lane one of a two-lane undivided roadway. V1 the departed it's travel lane to the left to avoid a collision with a dog, then departed the roadway to the left. V1 traveled down a ditch embankment where its front left bumper corner contacted a ditch. V1 continued forward contacting a rick with its left front rime and began to traverse the far side of the embankment when it began to trip to the right. Due to the steepness of the embankment, did not roll over, but the right side contacted the embankment in a non-horizontal impact. V1 came to final rest off the roadway on it's right side.

V1 was traveling southwest negotiating a right curve in lane one of a two lane roadway. V2 and V3 were unoccupied and parked off the left road edge in a residence yard. V1 departed its travel lane to the left then departed the left road edge. V1's front plane contacted V2 then V1's right plane contacted V2 again. V1 came to rest off the left road edge. V2 was pushed forward into V3.

Vehicle 1 was traveling northbound on a four lane undivided roadway and entered into the intersection with a four lane undivided roadway. Vehicle 2 was traveling eastbound on the intersecting roadway and also entered the intersection. The frontal plane of vehicle 1 contacted the right side plane of vehicle 2. Vehicle 1 came to rest in the intersection as vehicle 2 crossed over into the westbound travel lanes of its roadway. Vehicle 2 contacted its frontal plane with the frontal plane of vehicle 3, which was stopped in its west bound travel lane. Both of these vehicles came to rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling southbound on a three lane, one-way roadway passing through a four-way intersection. V2 was traveling eastbound on a four lane, two-way roadway. V1's front plane contacted V2's left plane. After initial impact with V1, V2 continued further east and departed the right side of the roadway; where it's front plane contacted a traffic light pole.  The left side of V2 then impacted an unknown type pole and a fire hydrant.  The front of V2 then impacted  two trash bins, and a street sign before returning to the right side roadway, where it came to final rest in the roadway way in between the eastbound lanes.

V1 was traveling SW on a one-lane, one-way road with parallel parking on both sides. V2 and V3 were parked facing SW on the north side of the street. The right plane of V1 contacted the left plane of V2, then the back of V3. All three vehicles came to rest on the road.

Vehicle #1 was traveling NE on a two-lane, one-way interchange ramp in lane one. V1 lost control on the wet pavement, departed its lane to the left, returned to its lane yawing clockwise, then departed the road to the right. The front plane of V1 contacted a guardrail end. The force of impact caused V1's back end to lift off the ground as V1 continued to rotate clockwise. V1 entered a left-leading fall-over as it traversed the rainwater runoff ditch next to the interchange ramp. V1 landed on its left plane at the bottom of the ditch, then continued to roll, completing four quarter turns before coming to rest off road to the south at the bottom of the ditch.

Vehicle 1 was traveling northbound on a 3 lane, two-way, median divided roadway in lane 1 position approaching a round-a-bout. As Vehicle 1 began to negotiate the curve, it began to rotate clockwise. Vehicle 1 continued in a lateral slide through the intersection making contact with curb near the exit of the round-a-bout. Vehicle 1 began a longitudinal roll to the left. Vehicle 1 then made contact with a tree coming to rest on its left side facing southeast.

V1 was traveling north in lane two of a four lane undivided (two-way traffic) roadway, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south in lane two of a three lane divided (no positive barrier) roadway, approaching the same intersection. At the intersection, V1 attempted to turn left. Within the intersection, the front of V2 impacted the right side of V1. V1 rolled onto its left side and moved off the roadway to the southwest corner. V1 came to rest off the roadway, laying on its left side, facing west. V2 came to rest at the edge of the southwest corner, facing southwest.

V1 was westbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 veered right to avoid hitting a deer then departed the right side of the roadway and traveled into a flooded ditch. V1 became submerged in water coming to final rest in the ditch, facing north.

V1 was southbound on a two lane, two way, roadway divided by a raised median. V2 was southbound following V1.  V1 departed the right side of the road before returning to the roadway in an attempt to make a U-turn.  The front of V2 impacted the left side of V1. Upon impact V1 spun counter clockwise, coming to final rest in an intersection facing north. V2 continued southward coming to final rest in the same intersection facing south.

V1 was traveling east on a two-lane, two-way road that curved to the left. A deer entered the roadway from the left side and V1 departed the roadway to the right where its right plane impacted an embankment and front plane impacted downed trees. A downed tree flipped up and struck the greenhouse area. V1 attempted to get unstuck from grass area on the right side of the ultimately failing to do so and came to rest off of the right side of the road.

V1 was traveling south on a two-lane, two-way road, negotiating a curve to the left. V1 departed the right side of the road where its front plane impacted a guardrail end causing it to rotate counterclockwise and it impacted its right side on an embankment. V1 came to rest in a ditch off of the right side of the road.

Vehicle 1 was traveling southwest on a two lane two-way roadway. Vehicle 1 drifted off the left (east) side of the road where its front plane contacted a mailbox. V1 continued forward on the grass roadside when its front plane contacted a culvert.  V1 overturned one quarter turn before coming to final rest off the roadway on is left side, facing southwest.

V1 and V2 were traveling westbound in the first of three lanes on a positively-divided freeway. V1 was following closely behind V2, and when V2 slowed down for traffic, the front of V1 contacted the rear of V2.

V1 was traveling south bound on lane 1 of a 2 lane, two-way, not physically divided roadway. V1 lost control and departed the roadway to the right. V1 front plane contacted a utility pole, rotated clockwise and rolled one quarter turn onto its left side where it came to final rest on the road.

V1, V2 and V3 were all southbound on a 5 lane (with a middle turn lane) divided roadway when the front of V1 contacted the rear of V2, the front of V2 then contacted the rear of V3. All vehicles came to rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling south in the first of five lanes on an undivided, two-way roadway entering a light controlled, four-legged intersection. V2 was traveling west in the second of four lanes on a divided, two-way roadway entering the same intersection as V1. V3 was stopped facing north in the fourth of six lanes on an undivided, two-way roadway at the same intersection. Within the intersection, the right side of V1 contacted the front of V2. V1 began to rotate clockwise and the left side of V1 contacted the left side of V3. All three vehicles came to rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling east on a two way, three lane, undivided roadway with a left turn lane. V1 was making a left turn from the left turn lane, at a three leg intersection. V2 was traveling west on a two lane, two way, roadway passing through the same three leg intersection. The frontal plane of V1 struck the frontal plane of V2. V1 rotated counterclockwise coming to rest heading northwest at the northwest corner of the intersection. V2 rotated clockwise and came to rest heading northeast in the southbound lane.

V1 was heading north, turning left to proceed west, from a private drive onto an undivided roadway with two westbound lanes and one eastbound lane. V2 was traveling west on the same two way, three lane, undivided roadway. The frontal plane of V2 struck the right side plane of the trailer towed by V1. V1 continued traveling and did not come to a final rest position. V2 came to rest facing northwest in lane one of the westbound lanes.

V1 was heading west on a three lane undivided roadway. V2 was traveling north on a four lane undivided roadway. Both vehicles were approaching the same intersection. V1 entered the intersection to make a right turn. V2 entered the intersection to continue on its path of travel. The left of V1 contacted the front of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest near the point of impact.

V1 was traveling in a north western direction on a 3 lane non divided bidirectional roadway, with one lane east bound, one lane west bound and a dedicated left and right turn lane. V2 was traveling in a south eastern direction on the same roadway. V3 was traveling in a north eastern direction on a two lane, non divided bidirectional roadway, that intersected with the roadway. V3 was stopped at a posted stop sign at the intersection. V1 was attempting to make a left turn, in front of V2. V1's right plane impacted V2's frontal plane. V1 rotated counter clockwise, where its frontal plane impacted the frontal plane of V3 and came to final rest in the roadway. V2 rotated clockwise and came to final rest in the intersection, still in contact with V1. V3 came to final rest at its initial impact position, on the roadway.

V1 was traveling in a eastern direction on a two lane, non divided, bidirectional roadway, with a general east and west orientation. A deer entered the roadway from the right. V1s frontal plane impacted the animal. V1 came to final rest on the right side of the roadway.

V1 was traveling east in lane four of a 4-lane divided roadway, approaching an intersection and attempting a left turn. V2 was traveling west in lane two of the same 4-lane divided roadway, passing through the intersection. The front plane of V1 contacted the left plane of V2. V1 came to final rest near impact. V2 continued to travel and departed the roadway to the right and its LF wheel contacted a curb as it departed the roadway. V2 came to final rest off the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. Vehicle 1 crossed the center line, departing the roadway on the left side, re-entered and departed the roadway on the right. The front of Vehicle 1 contacted a brick sign before coming to final rest facing east off of the roadway.

V1 was traveling south on a two-way, two lane undivided roadway, approaching a sign controlled intersection. V2 was traveling east, on a median divided roadway, with four lanes in the same direction, approaching the same intersection as V1. Both vehicles entered the intersection. The frontal plane of V1 contacted the left side plane of V2. V1 continued forward rotating in counter-clockwise direction and came to a final rest on the southwest side of the roadway. V2 continued forward rotating in a counter-clockwise direction and came to a final rest on the shoulder of the southeast side of the roadway.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane, undivided, roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south on a two lane, undivided roadway, approaching the same intersection. In the intersection, the left rear tire of V1 contacted the front of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane, undivided roadway in lane one. V1 departed the roadway to the left, V1 then rolled over left  2-quarter turns onto its into a ditch then rolled back onto its left side and came to rest in the ditch facing north.

V1 was traveling southbound exiting a three lane, two way undivided private drive in lane two approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling eastbound on a four lane, two way undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. In the intersection the front of V2 impacted the right side of V1. V1 rotated clockwise and came to rest in the roadway facing southwest, south of the intersection. V2 rotated clockwise and came to rest in the roadway facing southeast.
V1 was traveling northwest in lane one of a two lane roadway negotiating a left curve. V1 departed the right road edge and its front plane contacted a pole. V1 came to rest off the right road edge.

V1 was traveling in an easterly direction on a designated north/south divided trafficway (median strip with positive barrier) in lane 2 (of two lanes) and was approaching V2, V3 and V4, which were traveling in the same direction, on the same roadway, ahead in lane 2, with V3 behind V4 and V2 behind V3. V5 was parked in the center median facing an easterly direction. In lane 2, the front end of V1 contacted the back end of V2 (Event 1). V2 was pushed forward and its front end contacted the back end of V3 (Event 2). V2 then departed the road on the left where its right side contacted the back end of V5 (Event 3). V2 then rotated counter-clockwise and its undercarriage contacted the guardrail (Event 4) and caught fire (Event 5). V1 continued in an easterly direction, departing its lane on the right, then returning to its lane from the right, where its left side contacted the right side of V4 (Event 6). V1 then departed the road on the left where its front end contacted the guardrail (Event 7). V1 came to rest on

V1 was traveling East on a non-physically divided two-way road in lane one, behind V2. V2 was also traveling East on the same road in front of V1. V3 was traveling West on the same non-physically divided two-way road in lane one, in front of V4. V4 was also traveling West on the same road, behind V3. Due to heavy traffic, the front of V1 impacted the back of V2. V1 then started to roll left  one quarter turn, towards the westbound lane, and the top of V1 impacted the left side of V3. V1 continued to roll an unknown direction in the westbound lane, and the undercarriage of V1 impacted the front of V4. V1 came to rest within the westbound lanes, on its left side facing a westerly direction. V2 came to rest on the right shoulder of the eastbound lanes facing a easterly direction. V3 came to rest in the westbound lanes facing west and V4 came to rest on the westbound shoulder facing northwest.

V1 and V2 were both traveling northwest, in the same lane on a two-lane rural roadway. V2 was ahead of V1. V2 had stopped to make a left turn into a driveway. V1's front plane contacted V2's rear plane (event 1). Subsequently, cargo from V2 landed on V1. V1 came to final rest in its lane. V2 came to final rest off the roadway facing northwest.
V1 and V2 were both traveling east in lane one of a two-lane divided highway. V1 was trailing behind V2. The front of V1 struck the back of V2 and both vehicles came to final rest in their lane.

V1 was traveling north on a straight two-lane undivided (two-way traffic) roadway. V2 was traveling on the same roadway behind V1. The front of V2 impacted the rear of V1. V1 came to rest a short distance north of the point of impact, facing north. V2 started to rotate clockwise and entered the southbound lane of traffic. V2 came to rest in the southbound lane, facing south.

V1 was traveling northeast on a three lane two way roadway approaching a right curve in the roadway. V2 was traveling northwest on a two lane two way roadway approaching the same curve as V1. V1 departed the initial lane of travel to the left and the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling west on a three lane two way roadway approaching a three way intersection to turn left. V2 was traveling east on a three lane two way roadway approaching the same three way intersection to turn right. In the intersection the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 and V2 were traveling north on a three lane interstate. V1 was in lane one and V2 was in lane three. V1 traveled to its left, crossing lane two and entering lane three. The front of V1 contacted the right of V2. V1 then departed the roadway on the left where it came to final rest in the grass median. V2 came to final rest facing north near initial point of impact.

V1 was traveling north on a rural roadway. V1 departed the right side of the roadway striking a concrete driveway edge/culvert with its frontal plane. V1 continued traveling north off the roadway, striking a fence with its frontal plane. V1 came to rest near the second point of impact facing northeast.

V1 traveling northbound in lane one of a two lane, two way, undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 traveling eastbound in lane one of a four lane, two way, not physically divided roadway approaching the same intersection. Both V1 and V2 both enter the intersection at the same time. V1 left plane contacted V2 front plane. As V1 and V2 rotate clockwise V1 left plane contacted by V2 right plane. V1 continued traveling and contacted a guardrail with the front plane of V1.

V1 was traveling south on a two way, four lane road in the left turn travel lane, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north following a five lane, two way divided road in the second lane of travel. At the intersection, V1 attempted to turn left and the front of V1 impacted the front of V2. V1 and V2 began to rotate and the right side of V1 impacted the left side of V2 before coming to final rest on the northeast corner of the intersection, facing northeast. V2 came to final rest close to the second impact, on the roadway facing east.

V1 was traveling east bound on a two lane, non divided bidirectional roadway, negotiating a slight curve to the right. V1 departed the roadway to the left, where its frontal plane impacted a metal post. V1 continued down an embankment, where its frontal plane impacted a pvc fluid transfer manifold pipe and two frac tanks (large capacity steel tanks that can store liquids or solids). V1 rotated counter clockwise, where its right plane impacted a 4" discharge hose connecting the frac tank to the pvc manifold before coming to final rest next to the tanks. There was also a small engine compartment fire as a result of the impacts.

V1 traveling north bound on a two lane, non divided, bidirectional roadway. It was passing through a four way intersection to turn left. V2 was east bound on a two lane non divided bidirectional roadway passing through the same intersection as V1. V1's frontal plane impacted V2's frontal plane. V1 rotated clockwise, where its left plane impacted V2's right plane. V1 and V2 came to final rest in the north leg of the intersection, on the roadway.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane street in lane one, intending to turn left at the intersection.. V2 was traveling north in lane three of an eight lane highway divided by a concrete median approaching the same intersection. V1 entered the intersection and the left side of V1 was impacted by the front of V2. V1 came to rest on the right shoulder of the northbound lanes. V2 came to rest facing southwest in the northbound acceleration lane.

V1 traveled from south to west (made a right turn) through an intersection, from lane 1 (of five lanes), of a two-way, not physically divided trafficway, and entered an Interstate on-ramp. V2 traveled west through the same intersection, from lane 1 (of two lanes), of a one-way trafficway (Interstate off-ramp), and entered the same on-ramp as V1. On the on-ramp (one-way trafficway), in lane 1 (of two lanes), the back end of V1 was contacted by the front end of V2. V1 came to rest on its wheels facing a westerly direction on the right hand shoulder of the on-ramp. V2 came to rest on its wheels facing a westerly direction on the left hand shoulder of the on-ramp.

V1 was traveling south through an intersection from a two-way, not physically divided trafficway, and was in lane 2. V2 was traveling west through the same intersection from a two-way, not physically divided trafficway, and was in lane 1. V1 had stopped at the limit line. V2 was stopped in the northbound lanes of the intersection waiting for traffic in the intersection to clear. V1 resumed traveling south as V2 resumed traveling west. In the intersection, the front end of V1 contacted the right side of V2. V1 came to rest on its wheels facing a southerly direction in the northwest quadrant of the intersection. V2 came to rest on its wheels facing a westerly direction in the northwest quadrant of the intersection.

V1 was traveling northbound in the number 1 lane of a 3 lane divided roadway, negotiating a right-hand curve. V1 departed its lane to the left while rotating counter-clockwise. V1 continued rotating and departed the roadway to the left. The right front tire of V1 impacted a curb. The right rear tire of V1 then impacted the curb. V1 began to rotate clockwise when the right side of V1 impacted a tree. V1 continued to rotate clockwise where the right side of V1 impacted a second tree. V1 rotated clockwise and entered the southbound travel lanes. V1 came to rest facing westerly in the southbound lanes.

V1, V2, V3, and V4 were traveling east in the #1 lane of a 3 lane divided roadway. V2, V3, and V4 came to a stop due to traffic. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2. V2 was pushed forward where the front of V2 impacted the back of V3. V3 was pushed forward where the front of V3 impacted the back of V4. All vehicles came to rest in the number 1 lane facing east.

Vehicle 1 was traveling westbound on a five lane non-physically divided roadway in the the lane 1 position.  Vehicle 2 was traveling southbound on a 3 lane non-physically divided roadway in the the lane 1 position.  Both vehicles entered into the the intersection at the same time.  The front plane of Vehicle 1 made contact with the left plane of Vehicle 2.  Vehicle 2 rotated clockwise in the intersection coming to final rest facing north at the north western edge of the intersection.  Vehicle 1 rotated counter clockwise passing through the intersection departing the roadway at the south western corner of the intersection.  The front plane of Vehicle 1 made contact with a pole then a business property fence coming to rest on the lawn of the business facing southwest.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east bound on a 5 lane, two way roadway negotiating a left curve in lane 1. V1 departed the roadway right side, The front of V1 contacted a road sign. V1 then re-entered the roadway traveling around 800 meters before departing the roadway a second time to the right. V1 then struck a curb with its wheels. As V1 continued on its path the front plane made contact with a tree, ground, post and utility box before coming to rest northeast off the roadway.

V1 was traveling west in lane one, on a two lane roadway divided by a grass median with a cable barrier guardrail. V1 departed the right side of the road striking a guardrail end with its frontal plane.  V1 continued forward on the roadside and its undercarriage contacted the grass covered ground. Two unknown objects scraped the right side of V1. V1 came to final rest off the right side of the road facing west.

The crash occurred on a four lane, two way, trafficway, divided by a grass median with a cable barrier guardrail, in the eastbound lanes. V3 was stopped in lane two headed east. V4 was stopped next to V3, in lane one headed east. V2 was traveling at a slow steady speed behind V3, headed east. V1 was traveling east in lane two. The frontal plane of V1 struck the rear plane of V2. V1 continued east striking the right rear corner of V3 with its frontal plane, and striking the left rear corner of V4 with its frontal plane. V2 departed the left side of the roadway striking the cable barrier guardrail with its rear plane. V2 came to final rest near the point of impact with the cable barrier. V3 and V4 were pushed into forward motion and then came to a controlled stop in lane two. V1 came to rest in lane two.

V1 was west bound on a two lane, non divided bidirectional roadway, negotiating a curve to the right. V1 departed the roadway to the left, rotating clockwise. V1 rolled one quarter turn with its left side leading. V1 impacted a tree with its top plane, interrupting the roll. V1 then slid down a steep embankment, where it impacted a second tree with its top plane, before coming to final rest on its driver's side, at the bottom of the embankment.

Vehicle 1 (V1) was traveling southeast in lane one of a two-lane divided trafficway without a positive barrier.  The front plane of V1 contacted an animal.  The animal rotated clockwise and the left of V1 contacted the animal.  V1 came to rest facing southeast on the right shoulder near impact.

V1 was traveling west on a non-physically divided, three-lane road in lane three and initiated a left turn at a three-leg intersection. V2 was traveling on a non-physically divided, two-lane road in lane one, approaching the same intersection. V3 was stooped in traffic at the west leg of the intersection and facing east, in lane No. 1 of a two-lane roadway. As V1 initiated its left turn sequence the right fender region was impacted by the front of V2 (Event 1). V2 was re-directed towards the west leg of the intersection as its left quarter-panel impacted the back corner of V1 (Event 2). V2 continued forward as its frontal plane impacted the front of V3 (Event 3). V1 came to rest within the southbound lanes facing in a southeasterly direction. V2 came to rest in lane one of the southbound lanes facing south. V3 came to rest on the right shoulder of the southbound lanes.

V1 was driving westbound on a three lane roadway with a two-way left turn lane in lane two. V2 was stopped facing westbound on the same roadway in the center turn lane. V1 then entered the center turn lane proceeding west. V1 then began to exit the center turn lane to its right and the front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. V1 came to rest on the right shoulder facing west. V2 came to rest in the center turn lane facing west.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane non-physically divided roadway. V-2 was parked on the east shoulder of the same roadway facing north. V1 departed the roadway to the right and the front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. After impact V1 began to rotate clockwise and came to rest facing east in the northbound travel lane north of the impact area. V2 came to rest off the east road edge facing northeast.

V1 was traveling westbound in the first lane of a two lane, two-way curved left roadway. As V1 was traveling on the curvature, the vehicle departed the roadway on the right. The frontal plane of V1 impacted the utility pole. V1 was at final rest off the roadway facing west.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a 1-lane, one-way lane roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling northbound on a 1-lane, one-way roadway, approaching the same intersection as V1. Both V1 and V2 entered the intersection at the same time. The right side plane of V1 was impacted by the frontal plane of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway: V1 was facing east and V2 was facing north.

V1 was traveling northwest on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a slight right curve in the roadway. A deer entered the roadway from the southern shoulder and the frontal plane of V1 contacted the animal in the roadway. V1 came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling southwest in lane two of a three lane, non-positively divided roadway and was approaching a 4-way stop intersection. V2 was traveling northwest in lane one of a two lane, two-way, roadway and was also approaching the 4-way stop intersection. At the intersection, V1's front plane contacted V2's right side plane. Both vehicles came to final rest, in the intersection, a short distance from impact.

V1 was traveling EB in lane one of a two lane, two-way, not physically divided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was travelling SB in lane one of a four lane, two-way roadway with a grass median strip roadway approaching the same intersection. As V1 entered the intersection V2 steered left to lane two of the same roadway also entering the intersection. V1 right plane contacted V2 front plane. V1 rotated clockwise contacting a sign with left plane before coming to final rest.

V1 was traveling southbound on an undivided two lane road in lane 1. V1 departed the roadway to the left side and the front of V1 impacted a tree. V1 continued south and returned to the road. V1 then departed the road to the right climbed a steep embankment and rolled over 1 quarter turn left side leading. V1 slid southbound and came to rest partially on the road and the roadside facing south.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a 2 lane undivided private drive approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south on a 2 lane undivided road in lane 1 approaching the same intersection. At the intersection V1 attempted to turn left, during the intersection the front of V2 impacted the front of V1. V1 rotated clockwise and came to rest in the road facing southeast. V2 came to rest on the road facing south.
V1 was traveling south in lane one on a two lane grass median divided roadway. The front of V1 contacted an animal in the roadway. V1 came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling south on a two-way, four lane road in the first lane, approaching a four way intersection controlled by traffic lights. V2 was traveling west on a two-way, three lane road in the second lane, approaching the same four way intersection. As V2 was passing through the intersection, the front of V1 impacted the right side of V2. V2 rotated counterclockwise. The front of V1 impacted the right side of V2 again. Both vehicles came to final rest in the intersection; facing the southeast corner.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north on a two lane, two way undivided roadway approaching an intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling west on a two lane, two way undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. In the intersection the front of Vehicle 1 contacted the left side of Vehicle 2. The right side of Vehicle 1 then contacted the left side of Vehicle 2. Vehicle 2 then departed the roadway to the northwest and the front of Vehicle 2 contacted a utility box. Both vehicles came to final rest off of the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling westbound on a three lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position.  Vehicle 2 was traveling southbound on a six lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 3 position.  Both vehicles entered the intersection at the same time.  The front plane of vehicle 1 made contact with the left plane of Vehicle 2.  Vehicle 1 spun counterclockwise coming to rest facing south in the southwest portion of the intersection.  Vehicle 2 rotated clockwise coming to final rest facing west in the southwest portion of the intersection.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a 2 lane, median divided trafficway, in lane 2 approaching a roundabout. V1 started to negotiate the curve just before the roundabout. V1 departed roadway left side to the center median striking the curb with its Left front and rear wheels. The left side of V1 contacted a crosswalk sign (Event 3). V1 continued traveling on the center median striking the curb with its front right wheel (Event 4 & 5). The front left rim then impacted a curb (Event #6).V1 then made contact with a yield sign (Event 7). V1 made contact with another curb with the right front rim (Event #8). V1 then. entered the roundabout still traveling south. V1 departed roadway left side entering the center median of the roundabout. V1  Contacted a One-way sign with its front bumper (Event #9) before contacting a Large rock with its front bumper (Event #10). V1 Traversed over the large rock coming to rest in the roundabout.

Vehicles 1 and 3 were traveling east on a 3 lane, two way, median divided trafficway in lane 2 position (Left turn lane) approaching an intersection. V3 was behind V1.  V2 was traveling west on a 4 lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 2 position approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection. V1 was attempting to male a "U" turn to head west. V2 was going to pass through to continue west. The right side of V1 contacted the front of V2. Due to impact V1 was pushed over the center median where the front of V1 contacted an unknown pane of V3. V1's final rest was facing south west on the median. V2 came to rest still facing west after impact 1. and V3's final rest was at impact.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a three lane one-way road attempting to make a left hand turn to travel north.  The northbound was a two-lane one-way roadway.  V1 departed its lane to the right and the front plane made contact with a roll off dumpster.  The dumpster was pushed forward and Vehicle 1 came to final rest against the dumpster facing north

V1 was traveling east on a two lane divided roadway crossing over a bridge. V1 began to rotate clockwise and its front plane contacted the bridge railing. V1 continued to rotate clockwise and its left side contacted the bridge railing. V1 came to rest on the road facing west.

V1 was south bound on a two lane, non-divided, bidirectional roadway, when it departed the roadway to the right. V1 traveled down an embankment, before striking a steep embankment with its frontal plane, coming to final rest on the right side of the roadway.

V1 and V2 were north bound on a four lane physically divided roadway, with two lanes north bound and 2 lanes south bound. V1 was in the two lane, and V2 was in the one lane. V1 lost control due to water on roadway, and departed its lane to the right, where it impacted the left plane of V2. V1 impacted V2's left side a second time before both vehicles came to final rest on the right side of the roadway.

V1 was traveling east in lane two of a three lane divided (with positive barrier) highway. V2 was traveling in lane one of the same highway. V1 attempted to change lanes to the right. The right side of V1 impacted the left side of V2 in a sideswipe type impact. V1 came to rest in lane two, facing east. V2 came to rest in lane one, facing east.

V1 was traveling northwest on a one way, one lane interstate on-ramp. The ramp was curved to the right. As V1 was negotiating the curve, it departed the roadway to the left. The front of V1 impacted two trees.  V1 yawed clockwise and started to roll over.  The left side of V1 impacted a tree.  V1 rolled onto its left side before coming to final rest on its side off the roadway, facing north.

V1 and V2 were traveling southeast in lane one of a four lane divided roadway, V2 was ahead of V1. V1's front plane contacted V2's rear plane. V1 departed the left road edge into the median and came to final rest. V2 rotated clockwise, tripped and rolled four quarter turns and departed the right road edge where it came to final rest.

V1 was traveling east in lane one of a two-lane undivided roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right and its front plane contacted a mailbox post. V1 continued to travel, returning to the roadway. V1 then departed the roadway again to the right and its front plane contacted two mailbox posts. V1 then went airborne after ramping the side of driveway and traveled approximately 12m before its undercarriage contacted the ground. V1's front plane then contacted a fire hydrant, breaking off the hydrant, and rotating clockwise. V1's left plane then contacted a pole. V1 then came to final rest in a ditch near impact 7.

V1 was traveling west in the fourth of four lanes on a positively divided, two-way roadway. V2 was traveling west in the third lane of the same roadway. V3 was traveling west in the fourth lane ahead of V1. V1 departed it's lane on the right side and the right side of V1 contacted the left side of V2. The front of V1 then contacted the right side of V3. This caused V1 to roll over to the the right side. All vehicles came to rest in the roadway.

Vehicle #1 was traveling west in lane one of a two-lane, undivided roadway, negotiating a left curve.  V1 departed the road to the right. The front plane of V1 impacted a ditch.  V1 came to rest off the road to the right, facing west.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a 3 lane, one way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 3 approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south on a 3 lane, one-way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 2 approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection at the same time and the front of V1 contacted the right rear side of V2. V1 came to rest facing east in the intersection. V2 came to rest facing south west in the intersection.

V1 was traveling southbound on a four-lane, two-way roadway in lane two approaching a four-way intersection controlled by a traffic light. V2 was traveling westbound on a four-lane, two-way roadway in lane two approaching the intersection. In the middle of the intersection the front plane of V1 contacted the right side of V2. V1 came to final rest facing southwest in the roadway; V2 also came to final rest facing southwest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling northbound on a two-lane, two-way roadway. V1 departed the roadway on the right side where the front plane struck a mailbox and a tree further north. V1 came to final rest facing east in the northbound lanes.

Vehicle #1 was traveling northwest on a four-lane, two-way road in lane 2. Vehicle #2 was traveling southeast on the same road in lane 2. Vehicle #3 was traveling southeast on the same road in lane 1. V1 departed its lane to the left, entering oncoming traffic lanes. V1 crossed over V2's travel path. The front plane of V1 contacted the right plane of V2. V3 steered left, departing its lane. The front plane of V1 contacted the right plane of V2. V2 and V3 came to rest on the road. V1 continued ~700 meters before coming to rest on the road.
V1 was traveling west on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway. A deer entered the roadway from the left (south) shoulder contacting the frontal plane of V1. V1 came to final rest on the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a two lane,  two-way undivided roadway, in lane 1. Vehicle 2 was traveling west on the same roadway, in lane one. V1 began a left turn at the intersection. The front of V2 impacted the right side of V1. Both vehicles came to rest on the north side of the intersection with V1 facing north/northeast and V2 facing northwest.

Vehicle #1 was traveling northeast in lane 4 of a 4-lane divided roadway without a positive barrier.  Vehicle #2 was traveling southwest in lane 1 of the same trafficway.  V1 began to turn left at an intersection and the right of V1 contacted the front of V2.  V1 rotated counter-clockwise and V2 rotated clockwise.  The right of V1 contacted the left of V2. V1 and V2 came to rest still in the intersection with V1 facing southwest and V2 facing west.

V1 was traveling southwest on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway. A deer entered the roadway from the eastern shoulder, and V1 attempted to avoid the deer. V1 began to lose control and exited the right hand (west) side of the roadway. V1 then struck an embankment with its frontal plane and became airborne. V1 then began to rotate in a clockwise direction, rolling one quarter turn onto its left side plane and striking a pole with its top plane. V1 then rolled one quarter towards the right side plane before coming to final rest off of the roadway on its wheels.

V1 was traveling northwest on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a left hand curve. V1 departed the right hand (east) side of the roadway and the frontal plane of V1 contacted a tree. V1 came to final rest off of the roadway near the tree facing west. V1 then caught fire.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane, two-way, undivided roadway. V1 crossed the left lane line and continued off the left edge of the roadway. V1  made contact with a tree with its front plane.  V1 continued forward and yawed clockwise where the left plane made contact with a group of shrubs.  V1 then tripped into a left side leading rollover.  The rollover was interrupted by a tree through the top plane contacting the windshield and right A-pillar  V1 came to final rest  on its left side off the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling southwest on a three-lane trafficway divided by a grass median. The front plane of vehicle 1 struck a wooden object on the road. Vehicle 1 came to final rest on the side of the roadway.

Vehicle 1 and Vehicle 2 were traveling east on a three lane, non-divided roadway, in lane two, approaching an intersection. Just prior to the intersection, the front of Vehicle 1 contacted the rear of Vehicle 2. Both vehicles came to rest just forward of impact, still facing east in lane two.

V1 was traveling northbound in the left lane of a two way roadway with two lanes of travel in each direction. V2 was merging out of shoulder parking area traveling northbound. As V1 was changing lanes, the right side plane of V1 made contact with the left side plane of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling northeast in lane two of a four-lane divided roadway. V1 began to skid on the wet roadway and departed it's travel lane to the right. V1 then began to rotate clockwise and departed the roadway to the right. The front plane of V1 contacted a guardrail face. V1 came to final rest on the should next to the guardrail.

Vehicles 1 and 2 were traveling west on a 5 lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1 position. V1 was behind V2. V2 has stopped for traffic. The front of V1 contacted the rear of V2. Both vehicles came to rest at impact.

V1 and V2 were traveling eastbound in the number 1 lane of a 2 lane divided roadway. V2 was slowing down because a non-collision vehicle was turning right into a private parking lot. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. Both vehicles came to rest facing eastbound in the roadway.

V1 was traveling north in the #3 lane of a 3 lane divided highway. V2 was traveling north in the #2 lane of a 3 lane divided highway. V3 were traveling north in the #1 lane of a 3 lane divided highway. V1 departed its lane to the right. The right side of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V1 continued forward where the right side of V1 impacted the left side of V2 a second time. V1 rotated clockwise where the left side of V1 impacted the back of V3. V1 rotated counter clockwise and departed the road to the right where it came to rest facing west off the roadway. V2 came to rest in the #2 lane facing north. V3 came to rest in the #1 lane facing north.

V1 was traveling in a northeasterly direction on a designated north/south divided trafficway (median strip without positive barrier) in lane 2 (of three lanes) and was approaching V2, which was traveling in the same direction, on the same trafficway, ahead in lane 2. In lane 2, the front end of V1 contacted the back end of V2. V1 came to rest on its wheels, facing a northeasterly direction on the right shoulder. V2 fled the scene.

V1 was traveling eastbound in lane one of a two lane, one-way, physically divided roadway with a left turn lane approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling northbound in lane one of a two lane, two-way, not physically divided roadway approaching the same intersection. V1 and V2 entered the intersection simultaneously. V1 front plane contacted V2 left side.

V1 was traveling westbound in lane two of a four lane, not physically divided, two-way roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling northbound in lane two of a four lane, not physically divided, two-way roadway with a left turn lane approaching the same intersection. V1 and V2 entered the intersection simultaneously. V1 left plane was contacted by V2 front plane. V1 continued forward while rotating clockwise contacting a large rock with the front plane.

Vehicles #1, #2 and #3 were traveling east in lane three of a three-lane divided roadway.  V2 and V3 stopped.  The front of V1 contacted the back of V2.  The front of V2 then contacted the back of V3. All 3 vehicles came to rest near impact, still facing east.

V1 and V2 were traveling north in lane 1 of a two-lane divided roadway without a positive barrier.  The front of V1 contacted the back of V2.  Both vehicles departed the road to the left.  V2 came to rest in the grassy median, facing north.    V1 passed over another roadway (the southbound lanes of this trafficway) and then departed the southbound lanes of the trafficway. V1 came to rest off the roadway to the left, facing northwest.

V1 was traveling west on a two-lane, two-way road passing through an intersection. V2 was traveling north on a two-lane, two-way road passing through the same intersection. The front plane of V1 impacted the right plane of V2 causing both vehicles to rotate clockwise and come to rest in the intersection.

V1 was traveling south on a two-lane, two-way road and taking a left turn onto a side road. V2 was approaching the same side road while traveling north and negotiating a curve to the left. The front of V2 impacted the right side of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in the intersection.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north on a two lane, two-way road. Vehicle 1 traveled off the roadway on the right side where the front plane contacted a mailbox then a guardrail face. Vehicle 1 returned to the roadway, departed the lane on the left side, departed the roadway on the left side and the front plane contacted a guardrail face. Vehicle 1 came to final rest off the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a two lane non physically divided two-way road, approaching a four leg intersection controlled by stop sign. Vehicle 2 was traveling south on a three lane non physically divided two-way road, approaching the same intersection with no traffic controls. Upon entering the intersection the front plane of vehicle 2 contacted the right plane of vehicle 1. Vehicle 1 rotated clockwise and rolled two quarter turns before coming to final rest on its top, in the roadway. Vehicle 2 came to final rest within the intersection, on the roadway.
V1 and V2 were traveling on the same roadway, in lane 2, and headed Southwest. V2 slowed for traffic and the front of V1 contacted the rear of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway negotiating a curve. V2 was traveling north on the same roadway approaching the same curve. V1 crossed the left lane line into the oncoming traffic lane. The frontal plane of V1 contacted the frontal plane of V2. V1 Continued south and V1's frontal plane contacted a guardrail. V1 and V2 came to final rest on the roadway.
V1 was traveling south on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 struck an animal with its frontal plane causing damage. V1 came to rest heading south near the point of impact.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south in lane one on a two lane, two way roadway, approaching a four leg intersection, with no traffic controls. Vehicle 2 was traveling west in lane one on a two lane, two way roadway, approaching the same intersection, controlled by a stop sign. Within the intersection the front plane of vehicle 1 contacted the right plane of vehicle 2. Upon impact vehicle 2 rotated clockwise and departed the roadway to the right and overturned 3 quarter turns before coming to final rest off the roadway on its right side facing north. Vehicle 1 continued forward and came to final rest on the roadway facing west.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west in lane one on a two lane two way roadway. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway to the left. Vehicle 1 then rotated counter-clockwise before overturning three quarter turns. Vehicle 1 came to final rest off the roadway, on its left side, facing south.

V1 and V2 were traveling northeast on a median divided roadway, with two lanes in the same direction. V1 was trailing V2. V2 began to turn left into a private driveway. The frontal plane of V1 made contact with the rear plane of V2. V1 and V2 came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 & V2 were both travelling west in lane two on a two lane, positively divided roadway. As V2 slowed to a stop due to traffic ahead, V1's front plane contacted V2's back plane. Both vehicles came to final rest in lane 2 a short distance from the POI.

V1 was traveling westbound in lane one of a two lane, two-way, not physically divided roadway. V2 was traveling eastbound in lane one of the same two-lane, two way, not physically divided roadway. V1 crossed the center line contacting the front plane of V2 with the front plane of V1.

V1 was eastbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway approaching a four leg intersection. V2 was eastbound on the same roadway stopped in the road waiting to make a left turn. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2 causing damage. V1 and V2 came to final rest on the south side of the road facing east.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on two lane, two-way, non-physically divided roadway, approaching an intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling north on 3 lane, two-way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1, approaching the same intersection.  Both vehicles entered the intersection and the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2.  V2 then rotated counter-clockwise and rolled onto the right side.   V2 came to rest on its right side facing west. V1 came to rest after impact facing north east in the intersection.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane two way roadway. V1 lost traction due to conditions and departed the roadway to the right. Off the roadway, the left side of V1 contacted a utility pole and came to final rest.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane divided highway in lane one. For unknowns reasons, V1 turned into lane two and then departed the left roadway where the left side of V1 impacted a concrete barrier. V1 came to rest on the right shoulder facing north.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane non-physically divided roadway in lane one. For an unknown reason, V1 departed the right road edge and continued down an embankment where the front of V1 impacted a barbed wire fence post. As V1 continued through the barbed wire fence, the left side of V1 was impacted by a fence post. V1 came to rest in a field facing an easterly direction.

V1 was traveling south on a non-physically divided two lane highway in lane two. V1 departed the the left side of the roadway, rotating counterclockwise, entering a dirt, sand, and grass median. V1 rolled right an unknown amount of quarter turns, before coming to rest on its wheels, within the median, facing a northeasterly direction.

V1 was traveling west on a non-physically divided two way road in lane one negotiating a right curve. For an unknown reason, V1 departed the right road edge and traveled on a dirt grass embankment, where the front right and front right tire impacted a metal drain pipe within the embankment. V1 continued traveling along the embankment and the front of V1 impacted a metal utility marker. V1 came to rest on top of the embankment facing a southerly direction.
Vehicle #1 was traveling southeast in lane one of a two-lane, divided trafficway without a positive barrier.  The front of V1 contacted an animal.  V1 came to rest near impact.

Vehicle #1 was traveling northwest in lane one of a two-lane, divided trafficway without a positive barrier. V1 departed the roadway to the right. V1 re-entered the roadway and began to rotate counter-clockwise. V1 departed its lane and then the roadway to the left. V1 tripped over and completed four quarter-turns to the right. V1 came to rest in the median, on its wheels, facing southeast.

V1, V2, V3, and V4 were traveling north east in the #3 lane of a 3 lane divided highway. V4 came to a stop due to traffic. V3 was slowing behind V4. V2 was slowing behind V3. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2. V1 continued forward where the front of V1 impacted the back of V3. V1 continued north partially onto the shoulder where the right of V1 impacted the left of V4. V1 came to rest partially on the left shoulder facing north east. V2 was rotated clockwise and came to rest facing east between the #2 and #3 lanes. V3 was pushed off the roadway onto the shoulder and came to rest facing north east on the shoulder. V4 came to rest in the #3 lane facing north east.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a two-way, two-lane, undivided roadway. Vehicle 2 was traveling east on the same roadway. Vehicle 1 departed the original lane of travel over the left lane line and the front of Vehicle 1 contacted the left plane of Vehicle 2. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway on the left side. The front of Vehicle 1 then contacted a utility pole, and a tree. Vehicle 1 came to final rest off of the roadway against a tree facing northwest. Vehicle 2 rotated counter-clockwise as it departed the roadway on the right side and came to final rest off of the roadway in a ditch facing east.

Vehicle 1 and Vehicle 2 were traveling north on a five lane, one way roadway in lane two. The front of Vehicle 1 contacted the rear of Vehicle 2. Both Vehicles came to final rest on the roadway facing north.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north in lane one on a three lane one way roadway. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway on the left side and the front plane of vehicle 1 contacted a median cable barrier. Vehicle 1 came to final rest off the roadway facing north.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a two lane unprotected roadway, approaching an intersection in lane 1. Vehicle 2 was traveling south on a two lane roadway protected by a stop sign, approaching the same intersection in lane 1. Vehicle 1 and Vehicle 2 entered the intersection going straight. Within the intersection, the front of Vehicle 1 contacted the left side of Vehicle 2. Vehicle 2 drove off the southwest corner of the intersection and the right side contacted a guardrail face.Vehicle 1 came to final rest in the roadway and Vehicle 2 came to final rest facing southeast against the guardrail.

V1 was traveling northeast in the center turn lane (lane 3) of a five lane undivided roadway, attempting a left turn. V2 was traveling southwest in lane one of the same roadway, going straight. A non-contact vehicle was stopped in lane two of V2's direction of travel, causing a view obstruction for both vehicles. The right plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway close to impact.

V1 was traveling southeast in lane one of a two-lane undivided roadway, initially attempting a left turn, but then decided to turn right. V2 was traveling southwest in lane two of a four-lane undivided roadway. The left plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2. V2 came to final rest on the roadway. V1 rotated clockwise after impact, departed the roadway, and its right plane contacted a pole. V1 came to final rest off the roadway in the grass.
V1 was westbound on a freeway off ramp due to a non-collision fire that began on the rear luggage rack. V1 came to a stop on a gravel road.
