V1 was northbound on a 2 lane physically divided roadway, approaching and interchange area.The front of V1 contacted debris in the roadway (tire). V1 then pulled to the east shoulder and came to rest.

V1 was traveling south in the second lane on a three lane, one way roadway, approaching an intersection.  V2 was traveling east in lane two on a four lane, two-way roadway, approaching the same intersection.  Upon entering the intersection, the front plane of V1 made contact with the left plane of V2.  V1 came to rest facing south on the roadway.  V2 came to rest facing north east on the roadway.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a two-lane, two-way roadway approaching an intersection with the north and south lanes controlled by stop signs. V2 was traveling north on a two-lane, two-way roadway attempting a left turn. The front of V1 contacted the left side of V2 in the middle of the intersection. V1 came to final rest in the roadway facing northeast, V2 came to final rest in the roadway facing west.

V1 was driving north in the first of two lanes of a positively divided road. V1 departed the roadway on the right side and the front of V1 contacted a guardrail end. V1 came to rest facing east north of the impact area on the right shoulder.

V1 was stopped eastbound in a parking lot drive waiting to exit left and continue travel northbound. V2 was traveling south in lane 2 on a four lane, two-way roadway approaching the parking lot exit. A non-contact vehicle with an attached camper was traveling south in lane 1 of the same four-lane, two-way roadway and stopped to allow V1 to exit. V1 entered the intersecting roadway attempting to turn left  and the left side plane of V1 was impacted by the front plane of V2. Both V1 and V2 came to final rest in the roadway withV1 facing northeast and V2 facing south.

V1 was traveling west in the first lane of a two lane, two-way roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north in the first lane of a two lane, two-way roadway approaching the same intersection as V1. In the intersection the frontal plane of V1 impacted the right side plane of V2. As V1 rotated slightly clockwise, it's left side plane side slapped the right side plane of V2. Both V1 and V2 came to final rest in the roadway: V1 facing west and V2 facing northwest.

Vehicle 1 was southbound on a two way, two lane roadway.  Vehicle 1 left the roadway to the right and corrected back to the left.  Vehicle 1 left the roadway to the left striking the northbound embankment with its front plane.  Vehicle 1 rolled three quarter turns to the right along the ditch.  Vehicle 1 came to rest facing east in the ditch.

Vehicle 1 was southbound on a two way two lane roadway.  Vehicle 1 left the roadway to the right striking an embankment with its front plane.  Vehicle 1 rolled one quarter turn to the left and returned to the roadway.  Vehicle 1 slid on its left side to a stop coming to rest in the southbound lane facing east.

V1 and V2 were travelling East on a 2 lane 2 way not physically divided roadway. V2 was stopped in the roadway for pedestrian. V1 front plane struck V2 back plane. Both vehicles came to rest facing East.

V1 was traveling west in lane 2 on a four lane, two way, undivided roadway with a two-way center turn lane. V2 was traveling east in lane 1 on the opposing four lane roadway. V1 departed its travel lane to the left crossing over the center turn lane, then over the adjacent lane where the front of V1 contacted the front of V2. V1 and V2 both rotated counter clockwise upon impact. V1 came to final rest in the center turn lane facing west. V2 came to final rest in the eastbound lane facing north.

V1 was traveling in a northwesterly direction, through the left hand curve of the roadway, on a designated north/south divided trafficway (median strip without positive barrier), in lane 2 (of three lanes), and was approaching V2, which was traveling in the same direction, on the same roadway, in lane 1 (of three lanes), at a lower steady speed.  V1 departed its lane on the right, and in lane 1, the front end of V1 came in contact with the back of V2's trailer.  V1 and V2 became entangled, and as V2 was driven to the right hand shoulder and parked, V1 was dragged behind.  Both vehicles came to rest on their wheels, facing a northwesterly direction.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a 3 lane, two-way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1 position. V2 was traveling east on the same 3 lane, two-way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1 position. V1 departed lane of travel left side crossing over to the westbound lane. The front of V1 contacted the front of V2. both vehicles rotated and came to rest on a grassy area facing south.

Vehicle 1 was traveling southbound on a two lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position. Vehicle 2 was traveling eastbound on a four lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position.  Both vehicles entered into the intersection. The right plane of Vehicle 1 made contact with the front plane of Vehicle 2. After the initial impact, V1 rotated counter-clockwise and V2 rotated clockwise and the right side of V1 impacted the left side of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest facing southeast near the southeast corner of the intersection.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway, and was slowing down to turn left at a four leg intersection. V2 was traveling east on the same roadway behind V1. The frontal plane of V2 struck the back plane of V1. The cargo being carried on the trailer of V2 became airborne and landed on top of V2 in the bed. Both vehicles came to rest near the point of impact, in their original travel lane, heading east.

V2 was traveling southeast on a four lane, two way, undivided roadway passing through a four leg intersection. V1 was traveling northwest on a five lane, two way, undivided roadway with a left turn lane, making a left turn at the same four leg intersection. The frontal plane of V2 struck the right side plane of V1. V1 came to rest on the south corner of the intersection heading south. V1 came to rest on the south corner of the intersection heading southeast.

V1 was traveling west on a ramp to enter onto an interstate roadway. V2 was also traveling west on a two lane positively divided roadway on lane one. V1 departed its travel lane to the left. The left of V1 contacted the front of V2 (event 1). V1 began to rotate clockwise. V1 and V2 departed the roadway to the left. The right of V1 contacted the right of V2 (event 2). V1 contacted a guardrail with its right front plan. Both vehicles came to final rest near the second point of impact.

V1 was traveling in a western direction on a two lane, bidirectional roadway, with a general east west orientation. The roadway was bordered on the north by a positive grade embankment, and boarded to the south with a shallow ditch, and a tree line. V1 was negotiating a curve to the right, when it departed the roadway to the left. V1's undercarriage impacted loose stones from the ditch area. It continued in an eastern direction, where its frontal plane impacted a tree. V1 rotated clockwise slightly, and impacted a second tree with its left plane, and impacted an unknown object with its left side before coming to final rest on the left side of the roadway.

V1 was traveling south bound on a three lane, non divided bidirectional roadway, with one lane south bound, one lane north bound and one turn only lane. V1 was in the middle turn lane. V2 was north bound on the same roadway. V1 turned left into a parking lot in front of V2, where V1's right plane impacted V2's frontal plane. V1 rotated counter clockwise and came to final rest on the east side of the roadway. V2 came to final rest on the roadway in the turn lane.

V1 was traveling west on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling east on the same roadway approaching the same intersection. V1 attempted a left hand turn at the intersection and the frontal plane of V2 made contact with the right plane of V1. Both V1 and V2 came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling in a southeasterly direction, on a designated east/west divided trafficway (median strip with positive barrier), in lane 1 (of two lanes), when it departed the road on the right.  V1 continued in a southeasterly direction on the roadside until its front end came in contact with the end of a guardrail.  V1 then overturned (2 quarter turns, leading right) and came to rest on its roof, facing a northerly direction on the roadside.

V1 was traveling east through the right hand curve of the roadway, on a two-way, not physically divided trafficway, in lane 1. V2 was traveling north, through the left hand curve of the same roadway, in lane 1. V1 departed its lane on the left, and its front end contacted the front end of V2. V1 came to rest on its wheels facing east in lane 2. V2 came to rest on its wheels facing a northwesterly direction in lane 1.

V1 was traveling in a southwesterly direction on a designated north/south divided trafficway (median strip with positive barrier) in lane 2 (of three lanes) and was approaching V2, which was traveling in the same direction, on the same roadway, and in the same lane, at a lower steady speed. In lane 2, the front end of V1 contacted the back end of V2.  V1 departed the road on the left, and its front end contacted the concrete traffic barrier in the median strip. V1 came to rest on its wheels, facing an easterly direction in the median strip. V2 was driven to the right hand shoulder and parked.

V1 was traveling north on an unmarked undivided roadway approaching a stop sign. V2 was was traveling west on an unmarked two lane undivided roadway. V1 entered into the intersection to make a right turn. The front of V1 contacted the left of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest near the point of impact.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane, non-divided, bidirectional roadway, negotiating a curve to the left. V1 departed the roadway to the right, then returned to the roadway, crossed over both lanes of travel and departed the roadway to the left, rotating counter-clockwise where it impacted an embankment with its front bumper, V1 then rolled 4 quarter turns right side leading. V1 came to final rest on its wheels on the left side of the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling eastbound on a three lane, non-physically divided roadway, in lane 2 attempting to make a left hand turn into a private drive. Vehicle 2 was traveling westbound on a three lane, non-physically divided roadway, in lane 1 position passing through the same intersection. The front plane of Vehicle 1 made contact with the front plane of Vehicle 2. Vehicle 1 spun approximately 90 degrees counter clockwise coming to final rest facing north just after impact. Vehicle 1 continued through the intersection coming to rest shortly after impact facing west.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane, two-way, non physically divided roadway in lane 1 position negotiating a right hand curve. V1 departed lane of travel then departed roadway left side. The front of V1 contacted a guardrail before rolling 1 quarter turn onto its drivers side coming to rest in the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a two lane, two-way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 2 position. V2 was also traveling east on a two lane, two-way, non-physically divided roadway in lane two position in front of V1. V1's front made contact with the rear of V2. V1 then departed roadway left side coming to rest in a grassy area facing east.. V2 came to rest facing east on the right shoulder area of the roadway.

V1 was traveling north in lane two of a three lane divided (no positive barrier) straight road. V2 was traveling in the same lane ahead of V1. V1 attempted to change lanes and pass V2. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. V1 came to rest in partially in lane three and partially in lane two, facing north. V2 came to rest in lane two facing north.

V1 was eastbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway negotiating a right hand curve. V1 departed the roadway to the right impacting the back of V2 with its frontal plane causing damage. V2 was pushed into V3 causing damage to the rear plane with its frontal plane. All three vehicles came to final rest on the right side of the road facing east.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north on a two lane not physically divided two way road, approaching a four leg intersection with no traffic controls. Vehicle 2 was traveling west on a two lane not physically divided two way road, approaching the same intersection controlled by a stop sign. Within the intersection the front plane of vehicle 2 contacted the right plane of vehicle 1. Upon impact vehicle 1 rotated clockwise departed the roadway on the left side and came to final rest off the roadway in a ditch facing southeast. Vehicle 2 continued forward departed the roadway on the right side and came to final rest off the roadway in a ditch facing northwest.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north in lane one on divided two-lane roadway, approaching a three- leg intersection controlled by a stop sign. Vehicle 2 was traveling east in lane two on a three-lane one way roadway divided by a grass median, approaching the same intersection with no traffic controls. Vehicle 3 was traveling west in lane one of a three-lane, roadway divided by a grass median and concrete raised curb. Within the intersection the front plane of Vehicle 2 impacted the left plane of Vehicle 1. Both vehicles departed the left side of the roadway and entered the center median. Vehicle 2 came to final rest off the roadway, facing northeast. Vehicle 3 was struck by debris from Vehicle 1 and 2 and came to final rest on the shoulder, facing west

V1 was traveling westbound in the first of two lanes on an undivided, two-way road. V2 was traveling eastbound in the first of two lanes on the same roadway. V1 departed its lane on the left side and the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a 5 lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 3 position approaching an intersection to make a left turn. V2 was traveling west on a 5 lane, two way, median divided trafficway in lane 1 position, approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection at the same time. The right side of V1 contacted the front of V2. V1 came to rest facing north at the north side of the intersection. V2 came to rest in the intersection facing south west.

Vehicles 1 and 2 were both traveling east bound on a 4 lane physically divided trafficway in the lane 2 position. An bicyclist was making way through the crosswalk medians. V2 stopped suddenly for the approaching bicyclist. V1 departed roadway onto median left side striking several folding delineator posts. V1 then attempted to return to its lane of travel. The front plane of V1 made contact with the rear plane of V2. V2 was at final rest facing east. V1 rotated slightly clockwise coming to rest just after impact with V2 facing roughly southeast on the median.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two way, undivided road. V1 departed its travel lane to the right. V1 then returned to its travel lane and departed its travel lane to the left, and then departed the left side of the road in a clockwise yaw. V1 then rolled, left side leading, five quarter turns coming to rest on its left side, heading east.

V1 was traveling north on a rural roadway. An area of the roadway was was missing due to being washed out. The frontal plane of V1 struck the roadway with its frontal plane. V1 came to rest at the point of impact.

V1 was heading west on a two lane undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was heading east on the same roadway approaching the same intersection. A non-contact vehicle was heading south approaching the same intersection. The non-contact vehicle entered into the intersection to turn left at the same time as V1 and V2. After V2 steered left to avoid impact with the NCV and departed its lane to the left. The front of V1 connected with the front of V2. The NCV continued on its intended path. V1 and V2 came to final rest near the point of impact.

V1 was traveling west in lane 2 on a 2-lane divided roadway. V2 was traveling west directly in front of V2. As V2 slowed, the front of V1 contacted the back of V2. V1 then departed the left road edge as it rotated clockwise and came to rest in the grass median facing northwest. V2 rotated clockwise as it departed its lane to the right then the road and contacted a guardrail face with its left side. V2 came to rest on the paved shoulder facing northeast.

Vehicle #1 was traveling west in lane two of a two-lane, one-way exit ramp. Vehicle #2 was traveling north in lane one of an intersecting three-lane divided roadway without a positive barrier. Both vehicles entered the intersection and the left of V1 contacted the front of V2. Both vehicles came to rest near the point of impact with V1 facing southeast and V2 facing north.

V1 was traveling south on a divided trafficway (median strip with positive barrier), in lane 3 (of four lanes), and was approaching V2, which was traveling in the same direction, on the same roadway, and in the same lane, at a lower steady speed. In lane 3, the front end of V1 contacted the back end of V2. V1 departed the road on the right, and came to rest on its wheels, facing a northerly direction on the roadside. V2 also departed the road on the right, and came to rest on its wheels, facing a southerly direction on the roadside, south of V1.

V1 was traveling south east in the #1 lane of a 5 lane undivided roadway. V1 departed the road to the right and began traveling down into a ditch. V1 began to rollover through the ditch and came to rest on its roof facing east in a dirt field.

V1 was traveling east in lane 2 on a 3 lane divided highway. V2 was traveling east in lane 1 on the same roadway. V1 changed lanes to the right where the right side of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V1 rotated clockwise and departed the road to the right. V1 started to rollover on its left side. An unknown part of V1 impacted a fence. V1 came to rest facing west on its left side. V2 came to rest facing east on the shoulder of the roadway. The driver of V1 was completely ejected through the driver window during the rollover sequence.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a two-way physically divided roadway in the number 2 lane. Vehicle 2 was traveling south on the same two-way physically divided roadway in the number 5 lane. Vehicle 1's left side and Vehicle 2's right side made contact with each other. After initial contact, vehicle 2's left side made contact with the concrete barrier. Vehicle 1 came to rest in lane number 5 facing south. Vehicle 2 came to rest against the concrete barrier facing south.

V1 was traveling north on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway. V1 departed the left side of the road striking an embankment with its frontal plane (event 1). V1 continued traveling northwest striking a fence with its frontal plane (event 2). V1 continued traveling through the fence, turned north, and struck an embankment with its frontal plane (event 3). V1 then turned northeast striking a fence with its frontal plane (event 4). V1 came to rest heading at the point of impact four heading northeast.

V1 was driving south on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway, when the left rear wheel came off. V1 stopped in the roadway and the driver got out of V1 to retrieve the wheel prior to event 1. V2 was traveling south in the same lane on the same roadway. The frontal plane of V2 struck the rear plane of V1. V1 was pushed off the right side of the road and came to final rest heading northwest. V2 came to rest near the point of impact.

V1 was traveling northbound in the number 1 lane of a 3 lane undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling eastbound in the number 2 lane of a 4 lane undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection and the front of V1 impacted the right side of V2. V1 rotated clockwise and V2 rotated counter clockwise when the left of V1 impacted the right of V2. V2 departed the roadway to the north where the front left tire of V2 impacted a curb. The right front tire of V2 then hit the curb and V2 came to rest facing east on the curb. V1 rotated clockwise after the second impact with V2 and began to roll, left side leading. V1 rolled six quarter turns and came to rest on its roof facing south.

V1 and V2 were traveling northeast in the number 4 lane of a 4 lane divided roadway. V1 was traveling behind V2. V2 began slowing for traffic ahead. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in the number 4 lane facing northeast.

Vehicles #1 and #2 (V1 and V2) were traveling east in lane one of a two-lane, undivided, unmarked roadway.  V2 stopped and began to back up.  V1 also stopped and began to back.  The front of V1 contacted the back of V2.  Both vehicles came to rest near impact, still facing east.

Vehicle #1 (V1) was traveling east in lane one on a two-lane, undivided roadway.  V1 departed the road to the right.  The front of V1 contacted a ditch.  V1 rotated clockwise slightly as it continued forward and its left side contacted a wooden sign post. V1 came to rest in a ditch facing east.

V1 was traveling west in lane one of a four lane divided (no positive barrier) right curved road, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling on the same direction on the same road, in lane three, approaching the intersection. At the intersection V1 crossed both lanes to its left in an attempt to make a left turn at the intersection. The front of V2 impacted the left side of V1. V1 rotated clockwise and V2 rotated counter clockwise and both vehicles impacted in a side slap impact. V1 came to rest within the intersection, facing southwest. After the impacts with V1, V2 kept rotating counter clockwise and departed the road to the south. The right front wheel impacted a raised curb. The front of V2 impacted a wall south of the south curb. V2 came to rest at the wall, facing south.

V1 was traveling west in the first of three lanes on a two-way highway divided by guardrails. V1 departed its lane to the left side, crossed through lanes two and three, and departed the left side of the road. The front of V1 contacted a guardrail end, continued through the grass median and front of V1 then contacted the backside of another guardrail. V1 then began to rotate counterclockwise and rolled over right to top for four quarter turns. V1 came to rest in the median right side up on its wheels.

V1 was northbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway negotiating a left curve. V1 departed the right side of the roadway traveling along a tree line and through underbrush impacting a tree with its frontal plane causing damage. V1 then impacted a tree with its right side causing damage before overturning, left side leading one quarter turn. V1 came to final rest on its left side facing east.

V1 was westbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway following behind another vehicle traveling behind V2. V1 attempted to pass the non collision vehicle and V2. V2 attempted to make a left turn into a driveway. The front of V1 struck the left side of V2 causing damage. V2 began a counter clockwise yaw, impacting the left side of V1 with its left plane. V1 continued off the right side of the roadway and came to rest on the shoulder. V2 continued off the south side of the road and overturned, right side leading, one quarter turn. During the roll V2 impacted a mailbox before coming to final rest on its left side, facing south.

V1 was traveling northeast on a two way, four lane, guardrail divided road. V1 departed the left hand (north) side of the roadway striking a guardrail end with its frontal plane. V1 then proceeded forward striking the guardrail with its undercarriage and right side planes. V1 came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling northwest in the number 1 lane of a 3 lane divided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling southeast in the number 2 lane of a 2 lane divided roadway approaching an intersection. V3 was stopped at an intersection facing eastbound in the number 1 lane of a 2 lane undivided roadway. V3 entered the intersection to turn left. The left side of V3 impacted the front of V2. V3 rotated counter-clockwise and traveled northerly, coming to rest facing north on the northbound side of the road. V2, after the impact with V3, rotated counter-clockwise and traveled east where the front of V2 impacted the left side of V1. V2 rotated counter-clockwise and came to rest facing northerly on the east side of the roadway. V1 continued forward and to the right, coming to rest facing northerly on the east shoulder.

V1 was traveling south on a physically divided two lane highway in lane one. For an unknown reason, V1 made an unsafe turn and ran off the left road edge. V1's front impacted a cable barrier post, then the cables wrapped around V1, where it came to rest in the dirt/grass median facing a southerly direction.

V1 was traveling west, in lane 3, of a 5 lane roadway with 2 way left turn lane. V2 was traveling east,in lane 1, of the same roadway. V1 turned left. V1's front contacted V2's left side. Both vehicles came to rest within the roadway.

V1 was traveling east on a two way, five lane roadway in the third lane of travel approaching a four way intersection. At the mentioned intersection, V1 attempted to turn left. V1 departed the roadway to the right impacting a curb with its front. V1 came to final rest off the roadway facing north.

V1 was traveling north on a non-physically divided three lane road in lane two, approaching a stop sign at an intersection. V2 was traveling east on a non-physically divided three lane road, in lane two, approaching an intersection. V1 entered the intersection attempting a left turn and the front of V1 impacted the right side of V2. Both vehicles came to rest on the eastbound lane facing an easterly direction.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane roadway in lane one. V2 was traveling west on a two lane roadway in front of V1. The front of V1 contacted the rear of V2. V1 then traveled northwest and impacted north curb of the westbound lane. V1 then separated from the curb and rotated slightly counterclockwise, contacting the right rear wheel to the curb. V1 separated from the curb again and impacted the curb a third time with the front. V1 came to rest on the shoulder facing west. V2 came to rest in lane one facing west.

V1 and V2 were traveling north in the #1 lane of a 2 lane roadway. The front of V1 contacted the back of V2. V2 traveled off the road to the left where the front of V2 contacted a tree. V1 traveled to the right shoulder and came to rest facing north. V2 came to rest facing North West against the tree.

V1 was traveling southeast in the number 3 lane of a 3 lane divided roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the left where the left front tire of V1 impacted a curb. V1 continued off the roadway in the median where the front of V1 impacted a bush and then a tree. V1 rotated counter-clockwise and came to rest in the median facing east.

V1 was traveling north on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a left curve. V1 departed the right side of the roadway, traveled forward along the roadside and began to rotate in a counter clockwise direction before overturning two quarter turns. V1 then contacted a tree with its left side plane. V1 came to final rest on its roof off of the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a two-way physically divided traffic way in lane number 3. Vehicle 1 attempted  to change lanes to the left and began to yaw. Vehicle 1 rotated counter clockwise and came to final rest in lane number 6 facing west.
V1 was traveling south on a two-lane undivided road negotiating a slight right curve. V1 departed the right side of the road and its front struck a sign (event 1) and a tree (event 2).

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a two-way physically divided roadway in lane number 1. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway to the right and vehicle 1's front, and left side, made contact with a bridge support.  Vehicle 1 came to final rest, against the concrete bridge support off of the roadway.

V1 was south on a two lane undivided roadway. V2 was heading north on the same roadway. V1 departed its initial travel lane to the left. The front of V1 connected with the front of V2. V1 was redirected to the right where it came to final rest near the initial point of impact facing northeast. V2 was redirected to its right where it came to final rest near the initial point of impact facing northwest.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway approaching a right curve. V1 was negotiating the curve and departed the left lane line then departed the left road edge. V1 contacted the embankment with its frontal plane and came to rest off the roadway.

Vehicle #1 was traveling north in lane one of a two-lane undivided roadway, negotiating a left curve.  Vehicle #2 was parked facing west in a driveway, east of the roadway. V1 departed the road to the right.  The front of V1 contacted a mailbox.  V1 continued north and the front of V1 contacted the left of V2.  V1 than contacted another mailbox.  V1 re-entered the roadway and come to rest on the roadway facing north.  V2 came to rest in the grass near impact, facing northwest.

V1 was traveling in a northeasterly direction, through the right hand curve of the roadway, on a designated north/south divided trafficway (median strip without positive barrier), in lane 2 (of two lanes), when it departed the roadway on the left and was then returned to the roadway from the left.  Control over V1 was lost.  V1 skidded laterally in a clockwise rotation and departed the road on the right, where it overturned (8 quarter turns, leading left) as it ascended an earthen embankment running parallel to the road.  V1 came to rest on its wheels, facing a southwesterly direction on the roadside.

V1 was traveling north through an intersection from a two-way, not physically divided trafficway, and was in lane 2 (of five lanes).  V2 was traveling east through the same intersection from a two-way, not physically divided trafficway, and was in lane 2 (of five lanes).  V3 was stopped at the entrance to the same intersection, facing west, on a two-way, not physically divided trafficway, and was in lane 2 (of five lanes).  In the intersection, the frontal plane of V1 came in contact with the right plane of V2.  V2 immediately overturned (two-quarter turns, leading left).  V2 (unknown plane) then came in contact with V3 (unknown plane).  V1 came to rest on its wheels, facing a northeasterly direction in the southeast quadrant of the intersection.  V2 came to rest on its roof, facing an easterly direction in the northeast quadrant of the intersection.  V3 came to rest on its wheels, facing west in its original travel lane.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north on a 5 lane physically divided roadway in lane number 4. Vehicles 2,3 and 4 were stopped on the same roadway in the same lane. Vehicle 1's front made contact with vehicle 2's rear end. Vehicle 2 was than pushed into vehicle 3's rear end. Vehicle 3's front was pushed into vehicle 4's rear end. All vehicle's came to rest in the original travel lanes.

V1 was traveling south in lane 4 on a 5-lane divided roadway. V2 was traveling south in lane 3 on the same roadway. V3 was traveling south in lane 2 on the same roadway. V1 began to change lanes to its left and the left side of V1 contacted the right side of V2. V2 then departed its lane to the left and the left side of V2 contacted the right side of V3. V1 rotated counter-clockwise as it continued forward and its front plane contacted the front plane of V2. V3 departed the left road edge and its front plane contacted a concrete barrier. V3 came to rest on the paved shoulder facing south. V1 came to rest on an on-ramp lane facing southeast. V2 came to rest in lane 5 facing southwest.

V1 was traveling west on a two way, two lane residential roadway approaching an intersection.  V2 was traveling north on a two way, two lane roadway approaching the same intersection.  Both vehicles entered the intersection and the front of V1 contacted the right side of V2. V1 rotated clockwise as V2 rotated counter-clockwise and the left side of V1 contacted the right side of V2. V1 then departed the northwest corner of the intersection and its front plane contacted 3 separate trees and came to rest facing northwest. V2 came to rest in the northwest corner of the intersection facing northwest.

V1 was traveling north east in the #3 lane of a 3 lane divided roadway preparing to turn left at an intersection. V2 was traveling south west in the #2 lane of a 3 lane divided roadway approaching the same intersection. V1 entered the intersection turning left. The front of V1 impacted the front of V2. V1 rotated counter-clockwise and V2 rotated clockwise as it continued forward and the right side of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V1 departed the southwest corner of the intersection and came to rest facing northwest. V2 continued to rotate clockwise, depard the westbound road edge and came to rest facing east.

V1 was traveling westbound in the number 1 lane of a 2 lane divided roadway. V2 was traveling eastbound in the number 1 lane of a 2 lane divided roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the left where the front of V1 impacted a curb. V1 continued to travel over the curb where the front of V1 impacted the front of V2. V1 rotated counter-clockwise while still moving westerly and came to rest on the eastbound lanes facing northerly. V2 rotated counter-clockwise after the impact with V1 and was pushed southerly, coming to rest facing northerly on the south shoulder.

V1 was heading north east in the #1 lane of a 3 lane divided roadway. V2 was stopped in the #1 lane of a 3 lane divided roadway due to traffic. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2. Both V1 and V2 both came to rest in the #1 lane facing north east.

V1 was traveling west through the right hand curve of the roadway, on a divided trafficway (median strip without positive barrier), and was in lane 2 (of two lanes) when it departed the road on the left, and was then returned to the roadway from the left.  Control over V1 was lost.  V1 skidded laterally in a clockwise rotation and departed the road on the right, where it then overturned (6 quarter turns, leading left).  V1 came to rest on its roof, facing an easterly direction on the roadside.

V1 was traveling west on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a left hand curve in the roadway. V1 began to lose control and skid in a counter clockwise direction departing the left hand lane line and then the left (south) side of the roadway. V1 departed the roadway and contacted an embankment with its frontal plane. V1 then overturned with its right side leading two quarter turns before coming to final rest off of the roadway on its roof.

V1 was traveling west on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a left hand curve in the roadway. V2 was traveling east on the same roadway negotiating a right hand curve in the roadway. V3 was also traveling east on the same roadway behind V2. V1 departed the right hand side (north) of the roadway and contacted a guardrail end with its frontal plane. V1 then reentered its initial travel lane and then departed the left hand lane line. The frontal plane of V1 contacted an the frontal plane of V2. V2 began to rotate in a counter clockwise direction and began to overturn right side leading. V2 completed two quarter turns where it came to final rest on its top in a ditch. V1 began to rotate in a counter clockwise direction and began to overturn right side leading. V1 completed one quarter turn on the roadway while rotating 180 degrees. While on its passenger side facing east the rear plane of V1 contacted the frontal plane of V3. V1 and V3 both came to final rest off of the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a one way roadway in lane number 2. Vehicle 1 drove off the road on the left side and vehicle 1's front made contact with the guardrail. After initial contact, vehicle 1 rolled over 3 quarter turns and came to final rest on the guardrail, facing southeast on the left side.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a 4 lane median divided intersection in lane number 4, intending to turn left. Vehicle 2 was traveling north on a three lane, two way, median divided trafficway approaching the same intersection. In the intersection the front of vehicle 1 contacted the front of vehicle 2. After initial contact the right side of vehicle 2 contacted a concrete barrier on the north east side of the intersection. Vehicle 1 left the scene. Vehicle 2 came to final rest facing northwest in lane number 1.

Vehicle 1 was traveling eastbound on 5 lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position. Vehicle 2 was traveling northbound on a 3 lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 2 position. Both Vehicles 1 and 2 entered the intersection at the same time. The front plane of Vehicle 1 made contact with the left plane of Vehicle 2. Vehicle 1 came to final rest facing east near the south east corner of the intersection. Vehicle 2 came to final rest facing northeast along the east edge of the intersection.

V1 was traveling southeast on a two way, five lane roadway in the third lane of travel, approaching a four way intersection. V2 was stopped at the intersection, in front of V1.  The front of V1 impacted the back of V2.  Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway facing southeast.

V1 was heading south on a four lane undivided roadway. V2 was north on the same roadway. V1 departed is initial travel lane to the left. The front of V1 contacted the left of V2. V2 came to final rest near the point of impact. V1 continued on its path. It departed the roadway to the left. The front of V1 contacted a guy wire and then a utility pole. V1 rolled over to the right two quarter turns and came to final rest on the top plane on a concrete sewer cover

V1 was heading south out of a private drive to make a left turn. V2 was heading east on a two lane unmarked roadway. The right of V1 contacted the front of V2.  Both vehicles came to final rest near the point of impact.

V1 was traveling north in lane three of a three lane left curved divided (no positive barrier) trafficway, negotiating a curve. V2 was traveling in the same lane behind V2. V1 decelerated in its lane. The front of V2 impacted the rear of V1. Both vehicles came to rest in lane three facing north.

V1 was traveling northeast in the number 2 lane of a 3 lane divided roadway. V2 was traveling northeast in the number 3 lane of a 3 lane divided roadway. V1 changed lanes to the left in front of V2. V1 departed the roadway to the left where the front of V1 impacted a guardrail face. V1 rotated clockwise where the front of V1 impacted a concrete wall. Debris from V1 flew into the air and the front of V2 impacted the debris. V1 continued to rotate clockwise to the east, crossing all lanes of traffic where the left side of V1 impacted a second concrete wall. V1 rotated clockwise and came to rest facing northwest in the number 1 and number 2 lanes. V2 came to rest facing northeast in the number 3 lane.
