V2 was driven to the right hand shoulder and parked.

V1 was traveling northwest on a two lane, non physically divided trafficway, making a left turn.  V2 was traveling south through the same intersection from a two-way, not physically divided trafficway.  In the intersection, the right side of V1 contacted the front end of V2. Occupant 2 was fully ejected from V1.  V1 was directed in a southerly direction, and its left side contacted a dirt embankment along the west road edge, south of the intersection, where it came to rest on its wheels facing a westerly direction. V2 came to rest on its wheels facing an easterly direction in its original travel lane, south of V1.

V1 was traveling southbound in the first lane of a two lane, one way roadway ahead of V2. V2 was traveling southbound in the first lane of a two lane, one way roadway behind of V1. Both V1 and V2 were approaching a split in the roadway.  V1 had attempted to take a right towards the split while V2 had attempted to take a left towards the split. The right side plane of V1 was sideswiped by the frontal plane of V2 as both vehicles approached the split in the roadway. V1 continued forward and then departed the roadway on the left side into the median. V2 departed the roadway on the right to stop in the breakdown lane. V1 rotated counterclockwise entering into the first lane heading south and then departed that lane into the second lane before departing off the roadway on the left.  The front of V1 impacted the ground.  V2 came to final rest off the roadway in the breakdown lane facing south. V1 came to final rest off the roadway facing east.

V1 was traveling west on a six lane, two way positively divided roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the left and the front of V1 contacted a concrete barrier. The left side of V1 then contacted the same concrete barrier.  V1 came to final rest in the roadway on the shoulder against the concrete barrier, facing west.

V1 was traveling west in the first lane of a seven lane, two way median divided roadway.  V1 departed the roadway to the right and the front of V1 struck a curb.  V1 continued off the roadway and the front of V1 contacted a signpost.  V1 continued traveling off the roadway and the front of V1 contacted a pole.  V1 came to final rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling west on a four-lane, two-way trafficway divided by a grass median. V1 departed the right side of the roadway striking an embankment with its frontal plane. V1 continued up the embankment striking two trees with its frontal plane. V1 came to final rest off the roadway heading west.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 departed the right side of the roadway striking a sign with its frontal plane. V1 then struck a concrete culvert barrier with its frontal plane, then a fence with its frontal plane, and then a tree with its frontal plane. V1 came to rest near the last point of impact with the tree, heading north.

V1 was west bound on a two lane, non-divided, bidirectional roadway, traveling on snow covered roads. V1 departed its lane of travel to the left, and departed the roadway where it entered a ditch. V1's left plane impacted a utility pole, and its frontal plane impacted the end of the ditch. V1 came to final rest in the ditch on the left side of the roadway.

Vehicle 1 and vehicle 2  was traveling east on a 2 lane,  two-way physically divided roadway in lane number 1. Vehicle 1's front end made contact with vehicle 2's rear-end. Vehicle 1 continued forward and rotated clock wise and came to final rest in the embankment on southside of the roadway. Vehicle 2 came to final rest in lane number 2.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a 6 lane, two-way undivided roadway, in lane number 1. Vehicle 2 was exiting a private drive attempting to turn left onto the same roadway as vehicle 1. The front of vehicle 1 contacted the back of vehicle 2. Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling south on a two-lane divided highway in lane two. V2 was involved in a prior crash and was left unoccupied facing northeast in lane two on the same highway. The front of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V1 came to rest facing a north easterly direction obstructing both the number one and two lanes. V2 came to rest facing a southerly direction in the number two lane.

V1 was traveling south on a non-physically divided five lane road in lane two, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north on a non-physically divided five lane road in lane three, stopped at the light to turn left. As V2 attempted to turn left the front right of V2 was impacted by the front of V1, that attempted to pass through the intersection. V1 came to rest within the intersection facing a southwesterly direction. V2 came to rest within the intersection facing a northwest direction.

V1 was traveling northbound on a non-physically divided five lane roadway in lane two. V2 was traveling south on a non-physically divided five lane roadway in lane two. V1 lost control and began to spin counter-clockwise into the southbound lanes where the front of V1 impacted the left side of V2. After the impact, the front of V2 impacted a curb west of lane one. V1 came to rest in lane one of the southbound lanes facing south. V2 came to rest straddling lane one and the curb facing a southwesterly direction.

V1 was heading south on a two lane undivided roadway negotiating a right curve. V1 swerved to the left in an attempt to avoid an animal. The front of V1 contacted a wall. V1 came to final rest near the point of impact.

V1 was traveling westbound in the number 2 lane of an divided 2 lane road, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling southbound in the number 2 lane of a 3 lane undivided road, approaching an intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection. The front of V1 impacted the left of V2. Both vehicles rotated and the right side of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V2 continued rotating clockwise and came to rest in the intersection facing west. V1 rotated counter-clockwise, coming to rest facing south near the south shoulder of the intersection.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane undivided roadway in lane one approaching a stop sign. V2 was traveling south on a three lane divided highway in lane two approaching an intersection. V1 entered the highway attempting to make a left turn into the north bound lanes when the left side of V1 was contacted by the front of V2. V1 spun counter-clockwise and came to rest in the center median facing south. V1 came to rest in the middle of the intersection facing east.

V1 was traveling east on a physically divided six lane street in lane two, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north on a three lane off ramp in lane two, attempting to make a right turn into the east bound lanes. As V2 turned right, the left side was impacted by the front of V1. After the initial impact, V2 rotated clockwise and the the left side of V2 contacted the right side of V1. V1 came to rest in lane three facing east. V2 came to rest in lane one facing east.

V1 was traveling southwest in lane one of a two-lane undivided road, negotiating a right curve. V1 was traveling at a high rate of speed and lost control, departing its travel lane to the left. V1 then returned to its original travel lane before departing the roadway on the right. V1 began to rotate clockwise and its left side contacted a culvert causing it to trip left and become airborne. At the same time it contacted a trash can. V1 continued airborne and contacted a guy wire. The vehicle continued to roll before contacting the limbs of a tree. After completing 7 quarter turns, V1 came to final rest off the roadway on the grass on its right side.

V1 was traveling southwest in lane one of a two lane undivided roadway. V1 departed the right road edge and the front undercarriage contacted a ditch. The right plane contacted an unknown object and V1 came to rest off the right road edge.

V1 was traveling northwest in lane four of a seven lane divided roadway approaching an intersection attempting a left turn. V2 was traveling southeast in lane one approaching the same intersection. V1's front plane contacted V2's front plane. Both vehicles came to rest in the intersection near impact.

Vehicle 1 was southbound on a two way, three lane roadway.  Vehicle 2 was northbound on a two way, three lane roadway.  Vehicle 1 was making a left turn through the intersection.  Vehicle 2 was traversing the same intersection.  Vehicle 2 front plane struck the right plane of vehicle 1.  Vehicle 1 left the scene.  Vehicle 2 came rest facing north in the intersection.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a two way roadway with a single lane of travel in each direction. V1 departed the roadway on the right side and the frontal plane of V1 made contact with a pole. V1 came to final rest partially on the roadway.

V1 was merging to the left onto a divided seven-lane roadway with two lanes traveling westbound, attempting to travel westbound in lane one. V2 was traveling westbound on the mentioned roadway in lane one, just after making a left at an intersection. The front of V1 contacted the right side of V2. After initial contact V2 started to rotate clockwise when the front plane of V1 struck the right side of V2 again. V2 then departed the roadway where the left side struck a curb and continued off the roadway where the left side struck a sign post. V2 came to final rest off the roadway facing south, V1 came to final rest on the roadway facing west.

V1 was traveling northeast in lane two of a four lane divided roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the left, returned to the roadway but overcorrected and departed the roadway again to the left. V1 traveled a distance off the roadway in the median before its front plane contacted a bridge support. V1 then rotated clockwise and the left plane contacted an unknown object (possibly the bridge support), before coming to final rest off in the median facing southwest.

V1 was traveling west in lane one of a two-lane undivided roadway. V2 was parked facing east at the westbound curb side. The front plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2. Due to the height difference of the vehicle and geography of the road, V1 overrode V2 and tripped left. The driver of V1 was partially ejected out of the open left front glazing but was pulled back into the vehicle as it rotated. V1 completed four quarter turns and came to final rest on its wheels on the roadway facing north. During the rollover, an unknown component of V1 contacted the top plane of V2. V2 was pushed over the curb and contacted a shrub before coming to final rest off the roadway facing east. Both of the right side doors of V2 were open prior to impact and the driver of V2 was partially ejected out of the vehicle, but at impact the driver of V2 was ejected completely out of the vehicle and struck by V2. A pedestrian was also struck by V2 following the impact with V1.

V1 was traveling west on a two-lane, two-way road while negotiating a curve to the right. V2 was traveling east on the same road negotiating a left curve. V1 steered left when a dog entered the road. The front of V1 impacted the front of V2. Both vehicles rotated counter-clockwise. V1 came to rest on the roadway facing southwest. V2 came to rest on the roadway facing northeast.
V1 was traveling west on a three lane two way grass median divided roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right and the undercarriage contacted the ground. V1 came to final rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling south on a 6 lane median divided intersection in lane number 3. Vehicle 2 was traveling north  on a 6 lane median divided intersection in lane number 2  intending to turn left to go west. Vehicle 1's left side and vehicle 2's front side made contact with each while in the intersection. Vehicle 1 came to final  rest facing SW in the number 1 lane. Vehicle 2 came to final rest facing NW in lane number 1.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south on six lane, two- way, non-divided roadway, in lane two. The driver of V1 initiated a "wide" left turn input and and never completed the turn sequence, allowing V1 to ultimately  depart the right side of the roadway. The  RF tire impacted the curb (Event 1) as V1 continued in a forward trajectory, off road. The frontal plane of V1  impacted a tree (Event 2) and rotated slightly in counterclockwise fashion, before coming to rest facing east.

V1 and V2 were traveling west on a four lane, two way, median divided trafficway. V1 was traveling in lane two of the westbound road and V2 was traveling in lane one of the westbound road. The right side plane of V1 struck the left side plane of V2. Both vehicles departed the right side of the trafficway, proceeded downhill and then uphill through a field. Both vehicles then crossed over a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 struck a group of trees and came to final rest near the point of impact with the trees heading west. V2 struck two trees, coming to final rest near the point of impact with the second tree heading west.

V1 was traveling east in lane two of the eastbound lanes, on a two way, four lane, physically divided trafficway. V1 departed the left side of the roadway and the front of V1 struck and embankment. The front of V1 then contacted a cable barrier guardrail. V1 then crossed back over the road to the right. V1 came to rest off the right side of the road facing southeast.

V1 was traveling south east in the #2 lane of a 6 lane highway. V2 was traveling south east in the #3 lane of a 6 lane highway. V1 steered left to avoid impacting a stopped vehicle and traveled into the #3 lane. The right side of V1 impacted the back of V2. V1 came to rest partially in the #3 lane and the #4 lane facing east. V2 came to rest in the #3 lane facing south east.

V1 was traveling southbound in the number 3 lane of a 4 lane undivided, one-way road, traveling in the wrong direction. V2 was traveling northbound in the number 3 lane of a 4 lane undivided roadway. V3 was traveling northbound in the number 1 lane of a 4 lane undivided roadway. V1 entered the intersection and began to make a u-turn. The right of V1 impacted the front of V2. V1 began to rotate clockwise and to the east where the front of V1 impacted the left side of V3. V2 came to rest facing a northerly direction north of the intersection. V1 rotated counter-clockwise after the impact with V3 and came to rest facing northeast. V3 came to rest facing northeast, north of V1.

V1 was traveling southbound in the first lane of a two lane, two-way roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling eastbound in the first lane of a two lane, two-way roadway approaching the same intersection. The right side plane of V1 was impacted by the frontal plane of V2 as both vehicles entered the intersection at the same time. V1 rotated slightly counterclockwise as V2 rotated slightly clockwise from impact.  The right side plane of V1 was impacted by the left side plane of V2 as both vehicles were moving in a forward direction. Both V1 and V2 departed the roadway: V1 departed the roadway to the the left and V2 departed the roadway to the right.  V1 came to final rest on the sidewalk, off the roadway, facing east. V2 continued forward impacting three shrubs with its' frontal plane. V2 then impacted the staircase of a residential home with its' frontal plane before coming to final rest. V2 was facing east, off of the roadway, at final rest.

Vehicles 1, 2, and 3 were traveling southbound on a six lane positively divided roadway.  Vehicle 1 was in the first travel lane, vehicle 3 was in the second travel lane and vehicle 2 was in the third travel lane.  Vehicle 3 departed the second travel lane and contacted vehicle 1 in the first travel lane.  After contact vehicle 1 crossed all three lanes of travel and contacted the back plane of vehicle 2 with the front plane.  Vehicle 1 came to rest in the roadway.  Vehicle 2 sideswiped a concrete traffic barrier on the left side and continued traveling.  Vehicle 2 was then contacted on the right side plane with an unknown plane of vehicle 3.   Vehicle 2 came to rest in the roadway. Vehicle 3 continued traveling and left the scene.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a two lane, two-way roadway. The driver of V1 fell asleep and V1 departed the roadway on the right side. V1 then continued on to strike a utility pole with it's front plane, before coming to final rest off roadway facing eastbound.

Vehicle 1 was traveling eastbound on a 5 lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position approaching an intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling westbound on a 5 lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 3 position approaching the same intersection to make a left turn to head southbound. Vehicle 3 was traveling northbound on a 4 lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 2 position stopped at the intersection. Vehicles 1 and 2 entered the intersection at the same time. The left plane of Vehicle 1 made contact with the front plane of Vehicle 2. Vehicle 2 rotated counter clockwise coming to final rest in the intersection facing south. Vehicle 1 rotated clockwise the left rear plane of V1 made contact with the front plane of V2. Vehicle 1 continued traveling south/east. V1's front made contact with V3's front left corner. Vehicle 1 came to final rest facing southeast upon contact with Vehicle 3 at southern part of the intersection. Vehicle 3's final rest was at impact.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a three lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1 position approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north on a 3 lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1 position approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection. The front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V1 came to rest on the east side on the intersection facing north east. V2 came to rest on the north side of the intersection facing north.

V1 was travelling South on a 3 lane 2 way not physically divided roadway. V1 swerved to avoid object in roadway, Departed roadway to the left, down embankment, across pedestrian path, and struck shrubbery, then railroad track rail and came to rest on the tracks facing East.

V1 was traveling in a northeasterly direction on a designated north/south divided trafficway (median strip with positive barrier), in lane 2 (of two lanes) and was approaching V2, which was traveling in the same direction, on the same roadway, and in the same lane, at a lower steady speed.  V1 departed its travel lane to the left, and was then returned partially to its original travel lane.  While returning to its travel lane, V1's front came in contact with V2's left side. V1 contacted V2 again in the left side with its front. V1 then overturned (8 quarter turns, leading left) and came to rest on its wheels, facing a southerly direction in lanes 1 and 2.  During the rollover, Occupant 1 was partially ejected from V1, and Occupant 2 was totally ejected from V1.  V2 was driven approximately one-half mile beyond the crash scene, and then parked on the right hand shoulder.

V1 was traveling southwest in lane three of a three lane left curved road, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling northeast in lane two of a four lane right curved roadway, approaching the same intersection. V3 was stopped at the intersection in lane one of an undivided (two-way traffic) northbound roadway, facing northwest. At the intersection V1 attempted to turn left. Within the intersection, the front of V2 impacted the right side of V1. V1 rotated counter clockwise and moved to the southeast corner of the intersection. The right side of V1 impacted the front of V3. After the impact with V1, V2 rotated clockwise and moved towards the southeast corner of the intersection. The front of V2 impacted the left side of V3. V1 came to rest within the intersection facing east. V2 came to rest at the second impact, facing southeast. V3 came to rest in its original lane of traffic, facing northwest.

V1 and V2 were traveling south on a two way, three lane, undivided roadway. V1 was following V2. V2 slowed and the front of V1 contacted the rear of V2. V1 and V2 came to final rest on the roadway south of the impact point.

V1 was traveling north west on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway. V1 traveled to its left and departed the left road edge. V1 contacted two mailboxes, one mailbox with its frontal plane and the other with an unknown plane. V1 continued and contacted a culvert with its frontal plane. V1 then rolled primarily to the left two quarter turns and came to final rest off the west roadway on its roof facing northwest.

V1 was traveling north on a two-lane, two-way road that curved to the left. V1 turned right onto a side road and departed the right side of the road. The right side of V1 impacted a curb and came to rest on the right side of the road.

V1 was approaching an intersection while traveling north in lane two on a cobblestone median divided road with two lanes going north and one lane going south. V2 was approaching the same intersection while traveling west in lane two of a divided road with two lanes going west and one lane going east, making a left turn to continue south. The front of V1 impacted the left side of V2 in the intersection. V1 rotated counter-clockwise and came to rest in the intersection facing northwest. V2 rotated clockwise and cam to rest in the intersection facing northwest.

V1 was traveling east in lane 5 on a 5-lane divided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling in lane 2 on a 5-lane divided roadway approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection and as V1 turned left and V2 proceeded straight, the front plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2. V1 rotated counter-clockwise as V2 rotated clockwise and the right side of V1 contacted the left side of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in the intersection facing north.

Vehicle 1 and Vehicle 2 were southbound on a three lane roadway with a median divided by a positive barrier. Vehicle 1 in lane three and Vehicle 2 in lane 2. Vehicle 1 lost control, the front of Vehicle 1 contacted the left side of Vehicle 2. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway on the left side and came to final rest facing south, Vehicle 2 came to final rest on the roadway facing south.

V1 was traveling west in the first lane of a two lane grass median divided two way trafficway approaching an intersection. A non-collision vehicle traveling on the same roadway in the second lane changed their initial lane of travel to the right. V1 turned to the right of the roadway, and departed the roadway. Off the roadway, the undercarriage of V1 contacted an embankment. V1 proceeded across the intersecting roadway and came to final rest off the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling in the southbound center turn lane of a five lane non divided roadway, turning left. Vehicle 2 was traveling in the second northbound lane of the roadway. The frontal plane on Vehicle 1 contacted the frontal plane of Vehicle 2, both vehicles came to rest on the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was southbound on a two way, two lane roadway approaching an intersection.  Vehicle 2 was eastbound on a two way, two lane roadway approaching the same intersection.  As both vehicles proceeded straight Vehicle 2's front plane contacted Vehicle 1's right plane.  Vehicle 1 rotated clockwise rolling one quarter turn to the left.  Vehicle 1 came to rest in the roadway on its left side facing southwest.  Vehicle 2 came to rest facing southeast in the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was southbound on a two way, two lane roadway. Vehicle 2 was parked in a private driveway facing west.  Vehicle 1 turned right, into a private driveway and contacted a tree with Vehicle 1's front plane.  Vehicle 1 continued forward, in the driveway, striking the left plane of vehicle 2 with the front plane of vehicle 1.  Vehicle 1 came to rest facing northeast in the driveway.  Vehicle 2 came to rest facing southwest in the driveway against a house with its right side.

V1, V2, and V4 were traveling north west in the #2 lane of a 4 lane divided highway. V3 was traveling north west in the #3 lane of a 4 lane divided highway. V3 and V4 were accelerating from a stop due to traffic. V2 was decelerating due to traffic. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2. V2 was pushed forward and to the left into the #3 lane where the left side of V2 impacted the right side of V3. V2 continued forward between the #2 and #3 lanes where the right side of V2 impacted the left side of V4. V1 after impacting V2 came to rest facing north west between the #1 and #2 lanes. V2 after the impact with V4 traveled off the road to the left and came to rest facing west in the center median. V3 came to rest facing north west in the #3 lane. V4 came to rest facing north west in the #2 lane.

V1 was traveling north west in the #2 lane of a 2 lane divided highway. V1 departed the road to the right. The front of V1 impacted a barbed wire fence. V1 continued forward and down into a dried creek bed where the front of V1 impacted an embankment. V1 came to rest facing north west against the embankment.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north on a 3 lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1 position approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling east on a 3 lane, two way, non-physically divided road way in lane 1 position approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection. The left side of V1 contacted the front of V2. V1 came to rest at the north east corner of the intersection facing north east. V2 came to rest also facing north east in the intersection.

V1 was traveling south in lane two of a six lane one-way traffic roadway. V1 departed the roadway to its right. The front of V1 impacted a wooden utility pole. V1 came to rest at the pole, facing southwest.

V1 was traveling in a northerly direction, through the right hand curve of the roadway, on a divided trafficway (median strip with positive barrier), in lane 4 (of five lanes), when it departed its lane on the left and then the road on the left.  V1 entered the median strip between an opening in the guardrail and descended into a ditch, where it overturned (6 quarter turns, leading left).  V1 came to rest on its roof, facing a southwesterly direction in the ditch.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a four-lane roadway approaching a three-leg intersection with no traffic controls. The west leg is undeveloped. V1 traveled through the intersection into the undeveloped area where the front of Vehicle 1 contacted a three plank vinyl barricades at the dead end of the roadway and ramped a small pile of asphalt at the edge of the roadway. The front of Vehicle 1 then contacted a tree and came to final rest off the roadway in the tree line.
V1 was traveling west on a two lane, two-way roadway.  V1 departed the roadway on the right side where the front plane made contact with a tree.  V1 came to final rest off the roadway facing east.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane, two-way roadway, approaching an intersection.  V2 was traveling north on a two lane, two-way roadway, approaching the same intersection as V1.  As V1 entered the intersection, the front plane of V1 made contact with the right plane of V2. Both vehicle came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling northbound on a two-lane, one-way roadway approaching a T-shaped intersection with lanes to travel west. V2 was traveling southbound on the mentioned roadway attempting to turn left into a private driveway. V3 was legally parked north of the driveway on the east side of the roadway. The front on V1 contacted the right side of V2 as it was turning. After initial impact the front of V2 contacted the back plane of V3. V1 came to final rest in the roadway facing north, V2 facing north at point of impact with V3, and V3 at point of impact.

V1 was traveling eastbound, on a median divided roadway, with three lanes in the same direction, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling northbound on a two way, three lane undivided roadway, and was stopped at the intersection waiting to turn left. V1 departed its lane to its right and the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. Both V1 and V2 came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling northeast in lane two of a three lane roadway. V2 was stopped in lane two of the same roadway at a red light, also traveling northeast. The front plane of V1 contacted the back plane of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest close to impact on the roadway.

V1 was traveling east following a two way, four lane, divided trafficway, in the second lane, approaching a four way intersection. V2 was traveling west on a two way, four lane trafficway, in the third lane, approaching the same intersection. V2 was attempting to turn left at the intersection. Both V1 and V2 entered the intersection at the same time. The front of V1 impacted the front of V2. After impact, V1 began to spin clockwise causing it's left side to impact the front of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest in the intersection, both facing south.

V1 was traveling north following a two-way, two lane road. V1 departed the roadway to the right impacting a utility pole with its front. V1 rotated clockwise coming to final rest on the roadway facing northeast.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a two lane, one way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1 position. An Unknown small wild animal entered the roadway. V1 contacted the animal. V1 was able to pull over to the side of the road after impact.

V1 was traveling north following a two way, two lane road in the right lane. V2 was traveling north, decelerating on the same two way, two lane road, in front of V1. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2. Continuing forward, the right side of V1 impacted the back of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway facing north.

V1 was traveling south west on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 departed the right road edge. The frontal plane of V1 contacted a utility pole. V1 rotated counter-clockwise and its front contacted a tree and came to rest facing south. Tree branches contacted the windshield and the right side plane during the crash sequence.

V1 was traveling south east on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway.V1 crossed the left lane line and departed the left roads edge. V1 contacted the frontal plane of V1 and came to final rest off the roadway.

V1 was heading east on a seven lane undivided roadway approaching the intersection to make a left turn. V2 was heading west on the same roadway approaching the same intersection. V3 was stopped at the traffic light facing south on a six lane undivided roadway. The right of V1 connected with the front of V2 (event 1). V1 was redirected backward and to the left. The rear of V1 contacted the front of V3 (event 2). V1 came to final rest at the second point of impact. V2 came to final rest facing west near the point of impact. V3 came to final rest at point of impact.

V1 was traveling north in lane 2 on a 4-lane roadway. V2 was traveling south in lane 2 on the same roadway. V1 departed its lane to the left and the front of V1 contacted the front of V2. V1 rotated counter-clockwise and came to rest in the north bound lanes facing east. V2 rotated counter-clockwise then rolled one-quarter turn coming to rest on its right side in the southbound lanes facing east.

V1 was traveling west in lane three of a three lane divided (no positive barrier) straight roadway. V1 departed the roadway to its left and drove onto the raised median. The front of V1 impacted a light pole on the median. V1 came to rest on the median, facing west.

V1 was traveling west in lane two of a two lane left curved divided (no positive barrier) roadway, negotiating a left curve. V1 changed its direction of travel and started to negotiate a right curve. V1 entered the driveway of a business and departed the roadway to its left. The left front wheel of V1 impacted a raised curb. V1 drove onto a grassy median and impacted the concrete base of a light pole with its left side in a sideswipe type impact. V1 continued to move and drove off the median and into another business parking lot. V1 impacted the front of a store with its front and a cement block of the end of a marked (painted) parking spot with its left rear wheel at the same time, damaging the store front and moving the non-fixed cement block forward. V1 came to rest partially inside the store, facing north.

V1 was traveling northbound in lane one of a four lane roadway with a left turn lane approaching an intersection.  V2 was traveling westbound in lane two of a three lane, one way roadway approaching the same intersection.  Both vehicles entered the intersection simultaneously and the front plane of V1 contacted the left plane of V2.  Both vehicles came to final rest in the intersection.

V1 was traveling east on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a right hand curve in the roadway. V1 lost control and entered the westbound travel lane. V1 continued forward in the westbound lane and departed the left hand side of the roadway (north). V1 exited the roadway and contacted an embankment with its front. V1 came to final rest off of the roadway on the north road edge facing east.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 began a clockwise yaw as it passed a non-involved vehicle. V1 departed the right side of the roadway striking a utility box with its back plane (event 1). V1 then struck a stop sign with its left side plane (event 2). V1 continued in a rearward motion striking a utility pole with its back plane (event 3), a sign post with its back plane (event 4), and a sign post with its right side plane (event 5). V1 came to final rest off the right side of the roadway heading west.

V1 was traveling west in lane one of a three lane undivided service road, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north in lane one of a four lane divided (no positive barrier) road, approaching the same intersection. V3 was traveling west in lane one of a four lane undivided (two-way traffic) way, approaching the an intersection north of the first intersection. At the south intersection, V1 attempted to turn right into the northbound lanes. Within the intersection, the front of V2 impacted the left side of V1. V1 rotated clockwise and came to rest in the northbound lanes, facing north. After the impact with V1, V2 continued to move north and passing through the northern intersection. The front of V3 impacted the right side of V2. V2 came to rest facing north. V3 came to rest facing west.

V1 traveling in a western direction on a two lane, non divided, bidirectional roadway, negotiating a slight curve to the left. V1 departed the roadway to the right, where its frontal plane impacted a cement culvert. V1 continued west, where its frontal plane impacted an embankment. V1 traveled up an embankment, and then returned to the roadway, coming to final rest on the right side of the roadway facing west.

V1 was traveling south in the second of three lanes on an undivided, two-way roadway entering a three-legged intersection attempting to turn left. V2 was traveling west in the first of two lanes on a two-way, divided roadway entering the same intersection as V1. Within the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the right side of V2. After the initial impact, Vehicle 1 rotated counterclockwise and came to rest west of the intersection facing west. Vehicle 2 rotated came to rest west of the intersection facing west.

V1 was traveling east in the only lane of a highway on ramp. V1 departed the left side of the road and contacted the north curb with all four tires/wheels. V1 began to rotate counter and the undercarriage of V1 contacted the ground. V1 came to off the road to the north.

V1 was traveling north in the #2 lane of a 3 lane one way road. V2 was traveling east in the #2 lane of a 3 lane one way road. V1 and V2 entered into an intersection. The front of V1 impacted the right side of V2. V1 rotated clockwise and came to rest facing north east in the intersection. V2 rotated counter clockwise and came to rest in the intersection facing north east.

V1 was traveling north in the two way left turn lane of a 4 lane undivided roadway. V2 was traveling west exiting a parking lot. V2 traveled between non-collision vehicles stopped in traffic to turn left and head south. The front of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V2 rotated clockwise and came to rest facing south west in the two way left turn lane. V1 rotated counter clockwise and came to rest facing north in the two way left turn lane.

V1 was traveling east, on a median divided roadway, with four lanes in the same direction, approaching a traffic signal controlled intersection. V2 was traveling north on a two-way, two lane undivided roadway, negotiating a slight left hand curve and approaching the same intersection as V1. Both vehicles entered the intersection. The frontal plane of V2 contacted the right side plane of V1. V1 continue forward and came to a final rest on the southeast shoulder of the roadway. V2 rotated in a clockwise direction and came to a final rest on the southeast side of the median divided roadway facing east.

Vehicle 1 was traveling eastbound on a two lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position and changed to lane 2.  Vehicle 2 was traveling southbound on a two lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position.  Both vehicles entered the intersection at the same time.  The front plane of Vehicle 1 made contact with the right plane of Vehicle 2.  Vehicle 2 departed the roadway at the southeast corner of the intersection coming to final rest facing east.  Vehicle 1 came to final rest shortly after impact facing southeast.

Vehicle 1 was traveling eastbound on a seven lane, physically divided trafficway in the lane 1 position approaching an intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling west on a 7 lane, two-way, physically divided trafficway approaching the same intersection attempting to make a left turn south. The front plane of Vehicle 1 made contact with the right plane of Vehicle 2. Vehicle 2 rotated clockwise coming to final rest facing north at the southern most edge of the intersection. Vehicle 1 came to final rest in middle of the intersection shortly after impact.

V1 was traveling south on a non-physically divided two-way road in lane one, waiting to turn left. V2 was traveling north on the same non-physically divided two lane road in lane one, negotiating a curve left. V1 attempted to make the left turn and the front of V1 impacted the front of V2. After the initial impact, V2 continued off the right road edge where the tires impacted a curb and V2 rolled left 2 quarter turns, coming to rest on its roof facing a southerly direction. V1 came to rest within the intersection facing northeasterly direction.
V1 and V2 were both traveling west in lane two of a two-lane divided highway. V2 was ahead of V1. The front of V1 struck the back of V2. Both vehicles came to rest on the road facing west.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane undivided roadway negotiating a curve left. V2 was traveling south on a the same roadway negotiating a curve right. V1 crossed into the southbound lane and the front of V1 impacted the front of V2. V1 came to rest in the southbound lane facing north. V2 came to rest in the southbound lane facing south.
Vehicles #1 and #2 were traveling north on a one-lane divided roadway. V2 slowed for traffic. The front plane of V1 contacted the back plane of V2.

V1 was traveling in a northeasterly direction on a designated north/south divided trafficway (median strip with positive barrier) in lane 1 (of two lanes), when it departed the road on the right.  On the roadside, V1's front end came in contact with a corrugated metal drain pipe lying perpendicular to its path.  V1 then descended into a ditch, where its front end came in contact with the ditch bottom.  Occupant 1 became partially ejected through the windshield.  V1 then overturned (4 quarter turns, leading left) while ascending and then descending the side of the ditch.  V1 came to rest on its wheels, facing a northwesterly direction in the ditch bottom.

V1 was traveling north in lane 4 on a 4 lane divided roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right where the front of V1 impacted a pole. V1 rotated clockwise and came to rest facing east on the roadway blocking lanes 1 and 2.

V1 was traveling in a southwesterly direction on a designated north/south divided trafficway (median strip with positive barrier) in lane 3 (of three lanes). V2 was disabled, on its roof, on the same roadway in the same lane ahead of V1. In lane 3, the front end of V1 contacted the front end of V2. V1 came to rest on its wheels, facing a southerly direction in lane 3. V2 came to rest on its roof, facing a southerly direction in lane 3.

V1 was traveling east on four lane, two way, physically divided trafficway, in lane one of the eastbound lanes. V1 departed its travel lane to the left, then departed the road to the left. The frontal plane of V1 struck the cable barrier guardrail causing damage. V1 came to final rest in the median heading east.

V1 was traveling westbound in the number 1 lane of a 4 lane divided roadway. V2 was traveling westbound in the number 3 lane of a 4 lane divided roadway. V1 departed its lane to the left and traveled across all lanes of traffic where the front of V1 impacted a concrete traffic divider. V1 rotated counter-clockwise and re-entered the roadway going backwards, where the left side of V1 impacted the front of V2. V1 came to rest facing southerly blocking the number 1 and 2 lanes. V2 came to rest facing westerly blocking the number 3 and 4 lanes.

V1 was traveling north on a two-way, two lane, undivided gravel roadway. V1 lost control and departed the right hand (east) side of the roadway contacting a signpost with its frontal plane. V1 continue forward making contact with a guardrail end also with its frontal plane. V1 rotated in a counter clockwise direction and then rolled two-quarter turns down an embankment on its right side plane. V1 came to final rest off the roadway on its top plane.

V1 was traveling northwest on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway. V2 was traveling southeast on the same roadway as V1. V1 attempting to avoid a deer that entered the roadway steered left. The front plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2. V1 continued forward rotating in a counter clockwise direction. V1 departed the left side of the roadway and hit an embankment with its front plane. V1 came to a final rest off of the roadway. V2 continued forward rotating in a counter clockwise direction and departed the right side of the roadway. V2 reentered the roadway still rotating in a counter clockwise direction. V2 began to rollover right side leading in the roadway crossing the left lane line and then departing the left side of the roadway after completing 4 quarter turns. V2 came to a final rest off of the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling southwest on the right shoulder of a three lane, physically divided roadway by a cable barrier. Vehicle 2 was traveling in the same direction in lane two. Vehicle 1 entered the roadway from the shoulder, attempted to cross all three lanes and the left side of Vehicle 1 contacted the front of Vehicle 2. Vehicle 1 and Vehicle 2 traveled off the left side of the roadway into the median. Vehicle 1 came to final rest facing south. Vehicle 2 came to final rest facing southwest.

V1 was traveling northbound on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a left hand curve in the roadway. While negotiating the left hand curve in the roadway, V1 departed the right hand (east) side of the roadway. V1 struck a culvert with its undercarriage and crossed over a private driveway. V1 continued forward off the roadway rotating in a counter clockwise direction. V1 then overturned with its right side leading two quarter turns before coming to final rest off of the roadway on its roof.

V1 was traveling eastbound, on a median divided trafficway, with two lanes in the same direction. In an attempt to avoid the two deer standing in the roadway, V1 departed lane 1 and then the left (north) side of the roadway. V1 struck a Guardrail end with its frontal plane and rotated in a clockwise direction striking an unknown object with its rear bumper. V1 came to final rest off of the roadway.
V1 was traveling northbound on a two way undivided roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right impacting a ditch with its front. V1 then rolled 8 quarter turns and came to rest on it's wheels.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane, undivided, roadway approaching a sign controlled 3-legged intersection. V2 was traveling south on a two lane, undivided, roadway, approaching the same intersection. In the intersection, the right side of V1 contacted the front of V2. Then the left side of V1 contacted the right side of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling northbound in the first lane of a two lane, two-way roadway. V2 was a legally parked, not in transport vehicle, facing north. V1 departed the roadway on the right, impacting the back plane of V2 with it's frontal plane. V1 re-entered the roadway on the left but began to overturn onto its left side plane. V1 made one quarter turn and was at final rest on it's left side plane facing north. After impact, V2 was pushed off of the roadway to the right. V2 was at final rest off the roadway, facing north.

V1 was traveling east on a four lane roadway in lane two approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling east in lane one beside V1. V1 attempted a right turn from the number two lane and the right side of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V2 continued through the intersection and departed the southeast apex. The front of V1 then contacted a curb and a sign post. V2 continued forward traveling southeast off the roadway and the front of V2 impacted a tree. V1 came to rest in the intersection in lane one of the westbound lanes facing west. V2 came to rest off the roadway against the tree facing east.

V1 was traveling north following a two way, two lane road in the right lane. V2 was following the same two way, two lane road, in front of V1. V2 slowed in traffic. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest at impact, in the road, facing north.

V1 was traveling north in the first of four lanes on an undivided, two-way roadway entering a light controlled, four-legged intersection. V2 was traveling west in the second of three lanes on a two-way, positively divided roadway entering the same intersection as V1. Within the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. After the initial impact, Vehicle 1 rotated counterclockwise and came to rest within the intersection. V2 rotated counterclockwise and departed the northwest corner. The back of V2 contacted a pole. V2 came to rest partially off the roadway.

V1 was traveling northbound on a two way, two lane undivided roadway, approaching an intersection with a stop sign. V2 was traveling eastbound, on a two way, two lane undivided roadway, negotiating a slight left hand curve and approaching the same intersection as V1 with a stop sign. Both vehicles entered the intersection. The front of V1 contacted the right side of V2. Both vehicles came to a final rest on the roadway.
